    'https://us02web.zoom.us/j/82807622497?pwd=1oWxQKkVvrj4tRTln1UgER5pencHWv.1',
    '{"id":"01KEHVX2YQSJ1AZTVV60D64P0Q","title":"Ponce Bank // MiD: HubSpot Sync","summary":{"notes":"## **Data Integration and System Alignment**\n\nThe team confirmed that the **data mapping between Mulesoft, HubSpot, and Salesforce** is aligned to proceed with integration testing (08:56).\n\n- **Colin Costigan** highlighted that the systems will sync by object type, allowing Salesforce to remain the system of record for lead versus customer status, which will then update lifecycle stages in HubSpot (12:08).\n    - This setup enables marketing to differentiate leads and customers based on Salesforce data without HubSpot managing that distinction.\n    - The integration supports both personal and business lead types, ensuring a broad use case coverage.\n    - Testing will begin using sample contacts to validate the sync setup before full rollout.\n    - This approach avoids duplicative data entry and ensures marketing and sales alignment.\n\n- The team agreed that **HubSpot will host the new web-to-lead forms**, replacing the current Webflow forms, and these leads will be pushed to Salesforce after initial qualification (13:07).\n    - Gabe Bencosme explained that Mulesoft can trigger lead creation in Salesforce once a lead is warmed up in HubSpot, preserving the lead’s identity through the email address as the unique key.\n    - Colin confirmed email as the primary record key in HubSpot, which ties marketing and sales data together.\n    - This process improves lead segmentation and qualification before sales engagement.\n    - It maintains data integrity by avoiding multiple records for the same contact.\n\n- A **project plan with detailed subtasks and phases** was established to track deliverables, due dates, and joint efforts across teams (09:58).\n    - The plan breaks down complex data integration tasks into manageable pieces for clarity and accountability.\n    - It allows the team to identify higher-lift tasks and coordinate collaboration efficiently.\n    - This structure supports on-time delivery and transparent progress tracking.\n\n## **Lead and Customer Data Processes**\n\nThe team discussed the **handling of leads versus customers in Salesforce and HubSpot** to ensure data consistency and proper tracking (10:55).\n\n- It was clarified that Salesforce distinguishes between leads and customers using separate queues and naming conventions, whereas HubSpot uses a unified field with tracking codes to mark customer status (11:34).\n    - Betty Campiz noted that the lead conversion process exists but is underused by sales teams and requires cultural reinforcement.\n    - Christina Zanca emphasized the need to reactivate lead conversion to connect marketing efforts to sales outcomes.\n    - A working session was proposed to realign lead processes and review necessary field updates, ensuring no gaps before next project steps (23:19).\n\n- Marketing campaigns in Salesforce will continue to be operated via the **Campaigns object**, but Ashley Taska clarified that a **custom object** will be used instead of the standard campaigns object for certain data, due to field limitations (20:42).\n    - This prevents manual work by aligning campaign tracking with system capabilities.\n    - Betty and Christina will coordinate to sync marketing campaigns in Salesforce with sales activities.\n    - The integration will enable attribution of closed deals to active marketing campaigns through lead source tracking.\n\n- The team agreed on the necessity to track **lead source and campaign attribution** to measure marketing impact on sales conversions effectively (24:38).\n    - HubSpot will handle lead source with detailed drill-downs to identify performance by channel.\n    - This will address previous concerns about brand campaign ROI and justify marketing spend.\n    - Sales reps will have the ability to capture “how did you hear about us” data to enrich lead profiles.\n    - Victor Garcia and Christina flagged the need to add one or two fields related to leads into the project plan for completeness.\n\n## **Data Privacy and Masking Strategy**\n\nThe group reviewed **PII data masking requirements** to protect sensitive customer information while maintaining operational usability (29:14).\n\n- Christina Zanca explained that **account numbers and social security numbers will be masked except for the last four digits**, balancing security with the need for operational communications referencing account data (29:14).\n    - Email addresses will not be masked since they serve as primary contact keys.\n    - Gabe Bencosme offered to handle masking on the Mulesoft side by dropping sensitive fields from the payload before sending to HubSpot.\n    - This approach ensures no sensitive data persists unnecessarily in transit or storage.\n    - The masking list is in final review, with few fields flagged for removal due to privacy or compliance concerns.\n\n- Ashley Taska pointed out that fields like **annual income and mother’s maiden name are marked for masking** and will not be brought into HubSpot (33:05).\n    - Christina confirmed that some fields, such as balances, should remain unmasked to enable campaign qualification triggers.\n    - The team will review and finalize the masking list by midweek following the holiday to avoid delays.\n    - This finalization is critical to move into phase eight testing and batch data imports.\n\n## **Integration Testing and Sync Strategy**\n\nThe team agreed on a **hybrid sync approach** combining real-time trigger-based updates and scheduled nightly syncs to optimize performance and data freshness (27:20).\n\n- Gabe clarified that Mulesoft will send full payloads only for new records and update only changed fields thereafter, reducing load and avoiding unnecessary overwrites (27:35).\n    - This ensures efficient data transfer without stressing systems.\n    - Colin emphasized the importance of real-time updates for key marketing triggers like new accounts and transactions.\n    - These triggers will enable customer journeys such as immediate surveys post-branch visits, improving customer experience.\n    - Scheduled nightly syncs will handle maintenance updates and less time-sensitive data.\n\n- The team confirmed developer access for key members, with Gabe already able to view all needed tools, clearing a key dependency for testing (26:23).\n    - This access enables faster issue resolution and direct coordination during testing.\n    - The team expressed confidence in moving into testing given alignment on fields, masking, and sync protocols.\n    - Testing will validate the system interactions and identify any adjustments before full deployment.\n\n## **Website and Content Development Timeline**\n\nThe team outlined the plan to complete **website content and design by next week** to support the new HubSpot-based web-to-lead forms (40:00).\n\n- Colin shared that website design is modular by page category (homepage, location pages, product pages) to avoid long timelines.\n    - This method speeds up delivery and allows parallel content creation.\n    - Victor Garcia confirmed content readiness is the next major step after integration tasks.\n    - The team is prepared to quickly build emails and landing pages as content is provided.\n    - This enables simultaneous progress on marketing campaigns and CRM integration.\n\n- Future phase two discussions will focus on adding new fields, channels, and campaigns after the April launch (41:04).\n    - Victor and Colin agreed on ongoing iteration post-launch to expand capabilities.\n    - The team is aligned on priorities to avoid overloading phase one.\n    - Marketing will continue to create campaigns while sales focuses on deal closure.\n    - Continued coordination will ensure smooth handoffs and tracking across systems.\n\n## **Overall Alignment and Next Steps**\n\nThe team reached strong consensus on current progress, with only the **masking list finalization** remaining as a slight timeline adjustment (35:47).\n\n- Christina committed to reviewing the masking list promptly and escalating decisions to leadership if needed (36:32).\n    - The timeline was adjusted to allow completion by midweek after the holiday.\n    - Once finalized, the team will proceed to phase eight testing and batch imports.\n    - Betty, Ashley, Gabe, and Colin confirmed readiness to move forward.\n    - Victor asked for visibility into content and dependencies to keep other departments aligned.\n\n- The team emphasized the importance of **tracking lead source and marketing attribution** to measure campaign ROI and sales impact (42:27).\n    - HubSpot and Salesforce fields are in place or can be created to support detailed tracking.\n    - Custom coding has been done previously to support granular lead source data.\n    - This capability will validate marketing efforts and guide future budget decisions.\n    - The team expressed confidence that this integration will improve cross-department collaboration and data-driven decisions.\n\n- The meeting ended with mutual appreciation and a commitment to maintain momentum through the holiday weekend and into next week’s testing phase (38:52).","outline":null,"keywords":["HubSpot","Salesforce","Mulesoft","Data Integration","Lead Conversion","Data Masking"],"overview":"- **Data Mapping Confirmed:** Mulesoft, HubSpot, and Salesforce data mapping is ready for integration testing, enhancing lead-customer tracking.  \n- **Web-to-Lead Forms Transition:** HubSpot will replace Webflow forms, ensuring leads are qualified before transferring to Salesforce.  \n- **Project Plan Established:** A project plan with clear tasks and timelines will improve accountability and ensure timely delivery.  \n- **PII Data Masking Strategy:** Sensitive data will be masked during transfers, ensuring security while maintaining operational usability.  \n- **Hybrid Sync Approach:** Combining real-time updates with scheduled syncs will optimize performance and maintain data accuracy.  \n- **Content Development Timeline:** Website content and design will be completed next week to support new integrations and marketing campaigns.","action_items":"\n**Christina Zanca**\nReview and adjust masking list fields; coordinate with Betty, Louie, and Liz for approval if needed (35:00)\nLook into calendar invite issue and resolve missing Zoom link (06:23)\nCoordinate micro leads working session focusing on lead processes (39:02)\n\n**Gabriel Bencosme**\nHandle masking at payload level to drop PII fields before sending to HubSpot (30:00)\nContinue coordinating data sync and field mapping validation (27:00)\nConfirm developer access tools with Colin (26:45)\n\n**Victor Garcia**\nSchedule and set up micro leads meeting with Christina and Ashley (39:02)\nReview lead fields for campaign tracking; ensure lead source field is set up and usable in Salesforce (43:00)\nCommunicate upcoming content needs and lead conversion tracking details to all relevant departments (39:47)\n\n**Ashley Taska**\nConfirm developer access to tools for integration (26:41)\nAssist in updating Salesforce with custom objects for campaigns as requested by other departments (20:42)\nSupport review of masking field list and confirm fields that must not be brought into HubSpot (33:05)\n\n**Colin Costigan**\nPresent and maintain detailed project plan, including subtasks and deadlines (07:34)\nAdd fields related to leads and campaign tracking to project plan (19:24)\nFacilitate phase eight testing preparation after masking decision (35:50)\nSupport data sync strategy implementation (real-time and nightly batch sync) (27:30)\nCoordinate with developers on testing and troubleshooting (26:30)\nEnsure alignment on lead and customer data flows between HubSpot and Salesforce (00:00)\n\n**Betty Campiz**\nPrepare sales teams for adherence to lead conversion process; provide training during upcoming GPS training sessions (17:57)\nCoordinate with Maria for campaign alignment and system communication improvements (19:24)\nReview masking and field mapping recommendations as needed (35:00)\n\n**Luis Gonzalez**\nAssist Christina with calendar invite troubleshooting (07:17)\n\n**Guille Santana**\nAssist Colin with project plan updates and coordination (00:00)\n"},"duration":44,"speakers":[{"id":0,"name":"christinazanca"},{"id":1,"name":"victor garcia"},{"id":2,"name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"id":3,"name":"luisgonzalez"},{"id":4,"name":"Colin Costigan"},{"id":5,"name":"christinazanca"},{"id":6,"name":"bettycampiz"},{"id":7,"name":"christinazanca"},{"id":8,"name":"Ashlie Taska"}],"sentences":[{"text":"Sa.","index":0,"end_time":128.13,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":127.89,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Sam.","index":1,"end_time":178.72,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":153.42,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"What''s going on?","index":2,"end_time":194.23,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":193.75,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Gabe, good morning.","index":3,"end_time":194.949,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":194.23,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Hey, good morning.","index":4,"end_time":200.11,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":199.03,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"How are you, brother?","index":5,"end_time":200.87,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":200.11,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Good, man.","index":6,"end_time":201.67,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":201.03,"speaker_name":"luisgonzalez"},{"text":"How''s everything with you?","index":7,"end_time":202.71,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":201.67,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Oh, man, I''m feeling like being sick for the last three days.","index":8,"end_time":209.83,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":203.75,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Everybody got that?","index":9,"end_time":212.95,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":212.07,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Everybody got that.","index":10,"end_time":213.91,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":213.11,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"That.","index":11,"end_time":214.11,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":213.91,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That.","index":12,"end_time":214.39,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":214.11,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Somebody exposed me to it and I.","index":13,"end_time":217.59,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":215.67,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Damn.","index":14,"end_time":218.63,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":218.07,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Colin did over the.","index":15,"end_time":220.789,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":219.59,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Over the.","index":16,"end_time":221.35,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":220.789,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Over the last zoom meeting.","index":17,"end_time":222.39,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":221.35,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"I''m sure he did.","index":18,"end_time":223.19,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":222.39,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Oh, man.","index":19,"end_time":224.07,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":223.35,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"It''s bad.","index":20,"end_time":225.19,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":224.55,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Not feeling great, Gabe.","index":21,"end_time":227.99,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":226.71,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I''m sorry to hear that.","index":22,"end_time":230.39,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":229.35,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, something''s definitely been going around.","index":23,"end_time":232.39,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":230.47,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Is it giving, like, flu vibes or is it just.","index":24,"end_time":235.41,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":232.89,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"It''s like flu plus.","index":25,"end_time":236.61,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":235.41,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I mean, I don''t know what Gabe''s.","index":26,"end_time":237.73,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":236.61,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Dealing with, but my head is kind of congested and, like, it just feels like a big headache because it''s congested.","index":27,"end_time":245.13,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":237.73,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"My body feels good.","index":28,"end_time":246.33,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":245.37,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Is.","index":29,"end_time":246.65,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":246.33,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"I can''t really focus because my head is just, like, exploding.","index":30,"end_time":250.33,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":247.05,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":31,"end_time":251.05,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":250.57,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I would say when I have that, it''s like my head feels like it''s in a bubble.","index":32,"end_time":254.33,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":251.13,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Right.","index":33,"end_time":255.21,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":254.81,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":34,"end_time":255.93,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":255.45,"speaker_name":"luisgonzalez"},{"text":"How about your throat?","index":35,"end_time":257.37,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":256.33,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That was.","index":36,"end_time":257.81,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":257.37,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That was like a big thing started.","index":37,"end_time":259.01,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":257.81,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But I''ve been taking a lot of tea and, like.","index":38,"end_time":261.21,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":259.01,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"So it kind of helps the.","index":39,"end_time":263.02,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":261.77,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"There a little bit.","index":40,"end_time":263.81,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":263.09,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":41,"end_time":265.05,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":264.69,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That''s the weird thing about whatever this flu is.","index":42,"end_time":266.93,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":265.05,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Like, there''s a throat pain aspect to it.","index":43,"end_time":269.25,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":266.93,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Sore throat.","index":44,"end_time":269.97,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":269.25,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Well, good morning, everybody.","index":45,"end_time":274.29,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":272.85,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Morning.","index":46,"end_time":275.17,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":274.77,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Morning.","index":47,"end_time":275.89,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":275.49,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Good morning, everyone.","index":48,"end_time":279.409,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":277.73,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Do we still have Ashley and Luis and Christina and Betty joining?","index":49,"end_time":291.73,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":287.17,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"They should.","index":50,"end_time":295.19,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":294.55,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"I don''t see why not.","index":51,"end_time":296.47,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":295.35,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"I''m thinking Ashley right now.","index":52,"end_time":298.55,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":297.03,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"There''s Lewis right there.","index":53,"end_time":300.79,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":299.67,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"I''m sure Christina''s gonna join us in a second.","index":54,"end_time":304.87,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":302.79,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"I''ll just.","index":55,"end_time":305.83,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":305.35,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"I''ll pick her just in.","index":56,"end_time":306.87,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":305.83,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Good morning.","index":57,"end_time":319.21,"speaker_id":6,"start_time":318.65,"speaker_name":"bettycampiz"},{"text":"Good morning, buddy.","index":58,"end_time":320.81,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":319.85,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"How are you?","index":59,"end_time":322.65,"speaker_id":6,"start_time":321.93,"speaker_name":"bettycampiz"},{"text":"Doing well.","index":60,"end_time":323.61,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":323.05,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"How about yourself?","index":61,"end_time":324.33,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":323.61,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I''m doing well, thank you for asking.","index":62,"end_time":326.97,"speaker_id":6,"start_time":324.81,"speaker_name":"bettycampiz"},{"text":"Lewis, it''s great to meet you.","index":63,"end_time":330.33,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":329.05,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Good to meet you.","index":64,"end_time":331.93,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":331.05,"speaker_name":"luisgonzalez"},{"text":"How you doing?","index":65,"end_time":332.57,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":331.93,"speaker_name":"luisgonzalez"},{"text":"Doing all right.","index":66,"end_time":333.569,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":332.73,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"How about yourself?","index":67,"end_time":334.25,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":333.569,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I''m good.","index":68,"end_time":335.41,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":334.81,"speaker_name":"luisgonzalez"},{"text":"It''s good for Friday.","index":69,"end_time":336.57,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":335.41,"speaker_name":"luisgonzalez"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":70,"end_time":337.25,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":336.81,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Kick the day off Friday with a holiday on Monday.","index":71,"end_time":341.21,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":337.25,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":72,"end_time":343.17,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":342.81,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"No, Betty was trying to give me a meeting on Monday and apparently that''s not allowed.","index":73,"end_time":346.41,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":343.17,"speaker_name":"luisgonzalez"},{"text":"Listen, I did that to so many people.","index":74,"end_time":349.86,"speaker_id":6,"start_time":348.02,"speaker_name":"bettycampiz"},{"text":"I kept trying to book meetings on Monday and everyone kept turning them down.","index":75,"end_time":353.78,"speaker_id":6,"start_time":350.02,"speaker_name":"bettycampiz"},{"text":"I''m like, what''s going on?","index":76,"end_time":354.94,"speaker_id":6,"start_time":353.78,"speaker_name":"bettycampiz"},{"text":"Everyone''s just declining.","index":77,"end_time":356.42,"speaker_id":6,"start_time":354.94,"speaker_name":"bettycampiz"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":78,"end_time":357.46,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":356.98,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"As they should.","index":79,"end_time":358.42,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":357.54,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Listen, I don''t blame them.","index":80,"end_time":361.3,"speaker_id":6,"start_time":359.78,"speaker_name":"bettycampiz"},{"text":"But as it was happening and I wasn''t thinking of the holiday, I''m like, okay, what''s going on?","index":81,"end_time":366.1,"speaker_id":6,"start_time":361.3,"speaker_name":"bettycampiz"},{"text":"Yeah, everyone''s schedule seemed clear when I looked at it.","index":82,"end_time":369.38,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":366.18,"speaker_name":"luisgonzalez"},{"text":"Exactly.","index":83,"end_time":370.74,"speaker_id":6,"start_time":370.02,"speaker_name":"bettycampiz"},{"text":"Thank you, Louie.","index":84,"end_time":372.34,"speaker_id":6,"start_time":371.3,"speaker_name":"bettycampiz"},{"text":"Someone needs to back me up.","index":85,"end_time":373.86,"speaker_id":6,"start_time":372.34,"speaker_name":"bettycampiz"},{"text":"No, no, no.","index":86,"end_time":375.31,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":374.27,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Enjoy a day off.","index":87,"end_time":376.59,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":375.47,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Reset.","index":88,"end_time":377.63,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":376.91,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":89,"end_time":378.59,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":378.27,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I had no idea until my wife Looked at the calendar.","index":90,"end_time":380.75,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":378.59,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Good morning.","index":91,"end_time":382.35,"speaker_id":6,"start_time":381.55,"speaker_name":"bettycampiz"},{"text":"Good morning, Christina.","index":92,"end_time":384.19,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":383.07,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Hi.","index":93,"end_time":385.11,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":384.67,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Can.","index":94,"end_time":385.47,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":385.11,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Gia.","index":95,"end_time":386.07,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":385.63,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Can you check the invite for me?","index":96,"end_time":387.87,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":386.07,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Because I just have.","index":97,"end_time":389.43,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":387.87,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"It says MiD weekly sync, but there''s no information or zoom link or anything in my calendar invite.","index":98,"end_time":397.67,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":389.43,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"It''s like the Odyssey.","index":99,"end_time":398.83,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":397.67,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Oh, yeah, I''ll check it.","index":100,"end_time":400.51,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":399.23,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Yeah, I''m gonna.","index":101,"end_time":403.65,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":402.85,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"I want to just show you what I see because I want to make sure that it gets rectified.","index":102,"end_time":409.81,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":404.21,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Hold on.","index":103,"end_time":411.33,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":410.77,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So I''m gonna share my screen for just 30 seconds.","index":104,"end_time":415.33,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":413.17,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Sorry, guys.","index":105,"end_time":415.85,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":415.33,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"I just want to make sure that it''s like, if it''s my computer, then I''ll figure that out.","index":106,"end_time":419.81,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":415.85,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"But.","index":107,"end_time":420.13,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":419.81,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Like, I. I just see this.","index":108,"end_time":423.73,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":422.21,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"I don''t know.","index":109,"end_time":427.26,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":426.7,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"That''s just odd.","index":110,"end_time":429.58,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":428.46,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So, yeah, I don''t know if you''re gonna need to just resend it to me or just fix the entire thing, but I just wanted to fly that.","index":111,"end_time":436.78,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":429.58,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Christina, we''ll look at it.","index":112,"end_time":439.14,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":437.9,"speaker_name":"luisgonzalez"},{"text":"Because I see it on mine.","index":113,"end_time":440.54,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":439.14,"speaker_name":"luisgonzalez"},{"text":"Mine looks a little different, so I think maybe there''s a disconnect on it.","index":114,"end_time":444.94,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":441.66,"speaker_name":"luisgonzalez"},{"text":"Yeah, maybe.","index":115,"end_time":445.98,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":445.1,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"All right, well, we could.","index":116,"end_time":447.38,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":446.62,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"We could figure that offline.","index":117,"end_time":448.3,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":447.38,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"But anyways, thank you all, you know, for.","index":118,"end_time":451.66,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":448.3,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"For joining.","index":119,"end_time":452.26,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":451.66,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"I think know the purpose of this call is to just bring us all together to just, you know, stay aligned with the data kind of integration component of the.","index":120,"end_time":462.17,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":452.26,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Of the project.","index":121,"end_time":462.73,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":462.17,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Because there''s a lot of moving pieces.","index":122,"end_time":464.29,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":462.73,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Just Louis, for your background, just to bring you up to speed.","index":123,"end_time":468.85,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":465.49,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So we''ve had a couple of conversations with Ashley, Gabe and team to just kind of identify what fields we''re.","index":124,"end_time":477.25,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":468.85,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"We''re going to be bringing into HubSpot from Mulesoft.","index":125,"end_time":481.89,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":477.81,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And we kind of matched up both the.","index":126,"end_time":484.95,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":482.37,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"How HubSpot kind of will lay out those fields by naming convention and matching.","index":127,"end_time":492.99,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":484.95,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"It up to, you know, what''s already existing in.","index":128,"end_time":496.03,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":492.99,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"In Salesforce and then.","index":129,"end_time":497.39,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":496.19,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And Mulesoft.","index":130,"end_time":499.31,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":497.47,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So we''re at this stage of kind of just beginning the.","index":131,"end_time":503.55,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":500.03,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"The mapping.","index":132,"end_time":504.59,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":503.79,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And so what I''ve asked MiD.","index":133,"end_time":507.95,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":505.55,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And that''s kind of the acronym for the agency, so Colin, Tristan, and Guille to do is just set these calls up.","index":134,"end_time":514.95,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":508.43,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So have that alignment on deliverables.","index":135,"end_time":517.849,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":514.95,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"There''s a project plan that we have for the overall project, but we''ve broken out just to make it easier for this team, just the tasks that are assigned specifically for this phase.","index":136,"end_time":528.489,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":518.249,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So Colin, if you can bring.","index":137,"end_time":531.208,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":529.689,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Bring that up and really it''ll just be a discussion of where we.","index":138,"end_time":536.649,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":531.208,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"We stand.","index":139,"end_time":537.289,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":536.649,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"There is one question that we.","index":140,"end_time":541.049,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":538.729,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"We wanted to just go over that came up when Victor and I were looking at the mapping document and looking at kind of the masking and all that.","index":141,"end_time":550.83,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":541.449,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So I guess Colin, can you bring up the project plan and then we''ll jump into that.","index":142,"end_time":557.07,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":551.55,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Unless Lou, you have any questions or Ashley, you have anything you want to raise before we go that route.","index":143,"end_time":562.91,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":557.07,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So I''m good right now.","index":144,"end_time":566.43,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":565.31,"speaker_name":"luisgonzalez"},{"text":"Ashley had to jump off because she didn''t have audio, but she is trying to get back in.","index":145,"end_time":569.78,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":566.43,"speaker_name":"luisgonzalez"},{"text":"Oh.","index":146,"end_time":570.45,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":570.25,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Oh, okay.","index":147,"end_time":571.13,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":570.45,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":148,"end_time":571.69,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":571.13,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":149,"end_time":574.77,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":574.41,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Kia, can you share that face plan that Christina''s talking about?","index":150,"end_time":578.25,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":574.77,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":151,"end_time":579.89,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":579.53,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"While she''s pulling that up.","index":152,"end_time":580.69,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":579.89,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We had some great async communication this week.","index":153,"end_time":582.81,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":580.69,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So yeah, Victor and Christina, we have the answer to your question and we sent that a few days ago so we can align on that.","index":154,"end_time":588.81,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":583.45,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then Gabe, from everything that you checked, just giving us more confidence that we''re all aligned here and we can move into the phase a testing that we''ve outlined in that other sheet as well.","index":155,"end_time":598.09,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":588.97,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":156,"end_time":599.22,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":598.82,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And so just for everybody''s alignment, what I asked MIT to do was from the original project plan where we kind of had the high level overview of the main task associated with every component to get the data into the system.","index":157,"end_time":615.14,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":600.1,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"We asked them to break it up in phases and also just break it up into subtasks to make sure that we were tracking against due dates and then also could see which tasks had a bigger lift.","index":158,"end_time":626.42,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":615.38,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So some of those subtasks also required like a joint effort between all three of us.","index":159,"end_time":632.11,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":627.3,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So we wanted to just make that clear.","index":160,"end_time":633.71,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":632.11,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So I think this project plan is going to be super helpful to just keep us all aligned.","index":161,"end_time":638.67,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":633.95,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"The thing that we wanted to just call out and we could talk about it at the tail end, but I just wanted to flag.","index":162,"end_time":647.31,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":641.47,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So when we originally discussed the mapping fields, it looks like they''re very specific to.","index":163,"end_time":655.87,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":647.39,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And Victor, correct me if I''m wrong on the naming convention, but the customer there''s in HubSpot going to be real.","index":164,"end_time":665.53,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":656.49,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"No different path for a lead or a prospect other than a, I guess a tracking code that would say hey customer, yes or no and Colin, correct me if I''m wrong in that understanding.","index":165,"end_time":678.89,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":665.61,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"When it comes to Salesforce, the way that process is, I believe there is two queues.","index":166,"end_time":687.25,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":680.33,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So there''s one kind of mapping convention for a customer and one mapping convention for lead.","index":167,"end_time":693.65,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":687.25,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So I guess the question is when we kind of make the system speak together and hopefully Ashley, okay, you''re here.","index":168,"end_time":701.73,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":694.53,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Can we send information for a customer and a lead to essentially the same field in HubSpot or do we have to kind of go a different route and if that doesn''t make sense, I can explain it in a different way.","index":169,"end_time":728.64,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":702.93,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Or maybe you''re all good.","index":170,"end_time":730.56,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":728.72,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So where we are with what Gabe had shared from the ability for the system to sync is by object.","index":171,"end_time":738.64,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":731.28,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we are actually in a really good spot with supporting both personal and business and the lead side of things with, with that structure.","index":172,"end_time":747.1,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":739.2,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So what we''re recommending for this alignment is that Salesforce is the, the system of record for lead versus customer.","index":173,"end_time":753.82,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":747.1,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So that field, I think it was like is existing customer field would be influencing whether we''re a lead first customer because of the activity happening on the Salesforce side that would then update the lifecycle stage and few other properties inside of HubSpot.","index":174,"end_time":768.62,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":753.82,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we know whether we''re marketing to a lead or an existing customer.","index":175,"end_time":771.34,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":768.62,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"HubSpot''s not going to manage that.","index":176,"end_time":773.4,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":771.92,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It''s going to read that value from Salesforce and mulesoft through that sync and then yeah, that''ll, that''ll update all of those.","index":177,"end_time":781.76,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":773.4,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So I think that really moves us into a stage where we are good to start testing with the sample contacts that we have.","index":178,"end_time":787.36,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":781.84,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, now let me just ask a follow up question just so I understand.","index":179,"end_time":790.96,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":787.84,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So HubSpot is going to be the place where the website is built.","index":180,"end_time":799.56,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":791.36,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"The new, what we''re going to call for just consistency purposes, the web to lead form.","index":181,"end_time":805.52,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":799.56,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"That''s going to kind of capture leads and then there''s going to be a bunch of other ways that we could get leads.","index":182,"end_time":814.72,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":805.52,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So purchase prospect lists and things of that nature.","index":183,"end_time":817.44,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":814.72,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So my goal is to have those uploaded into into HubSpot.","index":184,"end_time":822.4,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":817.52,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Now is that going to change any thing in Salesforce?","index":185,"end_time":829.44,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":824,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Ashley, Just because right now we''re only.","index":186,"end_time":831.88,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":829.44,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Really sending leads to Salesforce via the Web2Lead form.","index":187,"end_time":835.28,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":831.88,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"If not, then I think this process works.","index":188,"end_time":838.96,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":836.72,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"I just wanted to make sure that you know, there wasn''t any issues with Salesforce being able to accept that process.","index":189,"end_time":847.2,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":839.04,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So now allow me to kind of elaborate a little bit on that.","index":190,"end_time":852.76,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":848.72,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"I just want to make sure that is the web2lead form that''s being collected now in this website, is that going to stop coming over to Salesforce or is it going to just go to HubSpot?","index":191,"end_time":863.36,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":852.76,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Well, so it''s going to stop in, in in terms of coming over from it being built out of webflow.","index":192,"end_time":869.76,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":863.44,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So the coding and the way the form is set up will be different.","index":193,"end_time":873.12,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":869.76,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"But essentially we''re going to replicate that in HubSpot and then just send it over kind of the same way the, the form will change a little bit because we''ll be expanding on the the fields.","index":194,"end_time":886.13,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":873.76,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So.","index":195,"end_time":886.26,"speaker_id":7,"start_time":886.13,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So for example, like I think the form is very basic now.","index":196,"end_time":889.77,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":886.81,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"We''re going to be making the form a little bit more intuitive.","index":197,"end_time":893.37,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":890.57,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So then what we can do is kind of segment is the lead, a marketing lead.","index":198,"end_time":897.45,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":893.45,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Right.","index":199,"end_time":897.85,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":897.53,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"If they''re not necessarily ready for the sales team to act and if it''s a little bit more warm based off of kind of questions that would indicate that then it''s going to go the normal process it would have.","index":200,"end_time":909.93,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":897.85,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"From Web2 leads, you know, to Salesforce.","index":201,"end_time":913.06,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":910.17,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":202,"end_time":913.94,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":913.46,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"At that point, since the lead is already in Hotspot, I think that mealsoft should be able to.","index":203,"end_time":918.74,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":914.34,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"We can create some type of trigger that should be able to send it to Salesforce.","index":204,"end_time":922.06,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":918.98,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"So there shouldn''t be any impact on that end.","index":205,"end_time":923.94,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":922.06,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Okay.","index":206,"end_time":924.38,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":924.02,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah.","index":207,"end_time":925.02,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":924.38,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So from the HubSpot perspective, Gabe, it''ll just be a form that we have a workflow set up for in the integration itself.","index":208,"end_time":930.5,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":925.02,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So it''ll say they''ll.","index":209,"end_time":932.18,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":931.14,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That''s.","index":210,"end_time":932.66,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":932.18,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That''s one of the sides where contacts are created in HubSpot before they''re created in Salesforce.","index":211,"end_time":937.62,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":932.66,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Most other activities, contacts are created in Salesforce and then pass the HubSpot.","index":212,"end_time":941.78,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":937.78,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So for the marketing perspective, someone fills out a form or we get, you know, Google Ads lead, whatever kind of, you know, lead generation we''re running, we''re getting form fills.","index":213,"end_time":950.48,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":942.26,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Lead created in HubSpot is a contact with that lead life cycle stage that is then synced back through mulesoft and Salesforce.","index":214,"end_time":956.64,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":950.8,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So I guess the idea for this column is if we send that lead over to Salesforce.","index":215,"end_time":963.56,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":958.08,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Right.","index":216,"end_time":963.92,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":963.56,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"As a warm lead, for example, then I guess the idea is to keep the same most likely email and that''s going to tie it back once let''s for example, once that lead becomes maybe a contact itself like on our system.","index":217,"end_time":978.13,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":964.08,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Because a contact on our system would mean that they already booked an account so that then would actually.","index":218,"end_time":982.33,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":978.13,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"We would need that email to actually tie it back to the HubSpot or can we use a different ID?","index":219,"end_time":988.57,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":983.77,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"So email is the record in HubSpot.","index":220,"end_time":991.89,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":989.37,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That''s like the source of truth for everything.","index":221,"end_time":993.21,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":991.89,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":222,"end_time":994.33,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":993.85,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So let me just add to that because Gabe, that''s a good call out.","index":223,"end_time":997.25,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":994.65,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So Victor has been testing something with Wanda because we uploaded prospect lists for 207 and essentially as part of the lead conversion process in Salesforce, which I''m not necessarily sure all branches are using or all sales teams are using right now.","index":224,"end_time":1014.93,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":997.25,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So it''s part of.","index":225,"end_time":1015.77,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1014.93,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Betty, this is flagging for you.","index":226,"end_time":1017.77,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1016.17,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Part of just like a minor update that we''ll have to give to the, to the Branches to improve kind of the flow of things that when a customer or potential customer comes in to open up an account when they''re looking for them in the system, they don''t necessarily check to see if they''re a lead first because we''ve never really had a bunch of leads.","index":227,"end_time":1039.67,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1018.01,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So they start by entering in the customer information as a new record.","index":228,"end_time":1043.91,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1039.91,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"What would probably need to happen is that they have to check that area and if they''re in there, use the lead conversion button, which would then basically tie everything that marketing is doing to.","index":229,"end_time":1056.07,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1044.23,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And we had that process before Christina.","index":230,"end_time":1059.96,"speaker_id":6,"start_time":1057.92,"speaker_name":"bettycampiz"},{"text":"We steered away from that because the sales culture wasn''t there.","index":231,"end_time":1063.36,"speaker_id":6,"start_time":1059.96,"speaker_name":"bettycampiz"},{"text":"But that infrastructure exists and we even have guides that speak to that, how that needs to happen.","index":232,"end_time":1070.08,"speaker_id":6,"start_time":1063.84,"speaker_name":"bettycampiz"},{"text":"So we''re just going to need to clean up.","index":233,"end_time":1072.48,"speaker_id":6,"start_time":1070.16,"speaker_name":"bettycampiz"},{"text":"And since I have GPS training coming up, I''ll take the opportunity to bring it up then.","index":234,"end_time":1076.88,"speaker_id":6,"start_time":1072.48,"speaker_name":"bettycampiz"},{"text":"Okay.","index":235,"end_time":1077.68,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1077.12,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"All right, so that''s perfect because then that would keep the consistency and then also help us track.","index":236,"end_time":1082.32,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1077.68,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And then just so everybody''s aware what marketing then will be doing is then also in Salesforce operating true marketing campaigns.","index":237,"end_time":1092.81,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1082.4,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So when you think about Salesforce, there''s the section of that''s called campaigns.","index":238,"end_time":1096.65,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1092.81,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"It''s essentially building the connection between a marketing campaign and a sales campaign.","index":239,"end_time":1102.73,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1097.21,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So that''s where Betty, I''m going to be working with Maria to kind of sync things together and just make the system speak better.","index":240,"end_time":1110.89,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1102.81,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Victor, one second, because I know you''re going to jump in with a good point.","index":241,"end_time":1114.61,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1111.37,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"I just want to finish this thought.","index":242,"end_time":1115.53,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1114.61,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So I''ll help.","index":243,"end_time":1117.45,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1116.65,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"I''ll help work with her to identify kind of that process to connect anything that she''s doing with the branches for their.","index":244,"end_time":1125.01,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1118.33,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"For their campaigns.","index":245,"end_time":1126.09,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1125.01,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"But the real reason why I wanted to call this out is because I just wanted to make sure that when looking at the original data sets in.","index":246,"end_time":1135.53,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1126.81,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"In Salesforce that we didn''t miss anything.","index":247,"end_time":1138.17,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1136.17,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"There''s a.","index":248,"end_time":1138.73,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1138.17,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"There''s a secondary tab that is just for leads.","index":249,"end_time":1142.95,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1138.81,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So what might have to happen, Colin, is we might have to just add one or two fields because I think the way Salesforce is currently set up is that there''s different naming conventions.","index":250,"end_time":1157.58,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1144.06,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And I think when we originally had the side by side comparison, we focused it on the customer records.","index":251,"end_time":1163.82,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1158.14,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So if we could just add that into the project plan is just a quick takeaway.","index":252,"end_time":1169.58,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1164.38,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"I think it''s like one or two.","index":253,"end_time":1171.1,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1169.82,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Victor, right when we were looking at it yesterday that you flagged it could be fields that we would want to look at.","index":254,"end_time":1177.56,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1171.56,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Yeah, there was.","index":255,"end_time":1179.56,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1178.04,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"And.","index":256,"end_time":1179.92,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1179.64,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"And it''s funny enough I saw them as the.","index":257,"end_time":1182.2,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1179.92,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"I want to make sure I say this correctly.","index":258,"end_time":1185.36,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1183.88,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"I saw this as the lead, not the relationship.","index":259,"end_time":1190.6,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1185.36,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":260,"end_time":1191.24,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1190.68,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So, yeah, there were just a few things that I felt like we could utilize, but a little bit more in depth with the whole campaigns thing.","index":261,"end_time":1199.32,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1192.04,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Lorena actually reached out to me just to make sure if we were going to be using the campaigns tab.","index":262,"end_time":1205.09,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1199.64,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"So just Colin and Gay.","index":263,"end_time":1207.37,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1205.33,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Interesting.","index":264,"end_time":1207.93,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1207.37,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"So that, you know, Lorena is a member of our team that works in the GPS team.","index":265,"end_time":1212.45,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1207.93,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"She just works on the background stuff, the infrastructure of it.","index":266,"end_time":1215.97,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1212.61,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"She asked if we were going to use the campaigns.","index":267,"end_time":1219.33,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1216.29,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"But I want to make sure that how they''re going to utilize or rather get another set of training for how they''re going to utilize the campaigns and bring that information back to us so that everything can sync properly and it fills out anything so that we don''t have to do any kind of manual work.","index":268,"end_time":1236.48,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1219.33,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Right.","index":269,"end_time":1237.04,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1236.64,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Yeah, I do.","index":270,"end_time":1238.64,"speaker_id":6,"start_time":1237.76,"speaker_name":"bettycampiz"},{"text":"I have another.","index":271,"end_time":1239.6,"speaker_id":6,"start_time":1238.88,"speaker_name":"bettycampiz"},{"text":"Oh, sorry, go ahead, Ashley.","index":272,"end_time":1241.84,"speaker_id":6,"start_time":1240.48,"speaker_name":"bettycampiz"},{"text":"No, about that.","index":273,"end_time":1243.6,"speaker_id":8,"start_time":1242.16,"speaker_name":"Ashlie Taska"},{"text":"We''re not training on campaigns, Victor.","index":274,"end_time":1245.88,"speaker_id":8,"start_time":1243.68,"speaker_name":"Ashlie Taska"},{"text":"That was solely handled by marketing.","index":275,"end_time":1247.92,"speaker_id":8,"start_time":1245.88,"speaker_name":"Ashlie Taska"},{"text":"It was just that another department was looking for a way to incorporate their work.","index":276,"end_time":1252.92,"speaker_id":8,"start_time":1248.32,"speaker_name":"Ashlie Taska"},{"text":"But we''re not going to use the campaigns object.","index":277,"end_time":1255.36,"speaker_id":8,"start_time":1252.92,"speaker_name":"Ashlie Taska"},{"text":"We''re actually going to going to create a custom object because that''s a standard object.","index":278,"end_time":1259.64,"speaker_id":8,"start_time":1255.36,"speaker_name":"Ashlie Taska"},{"text":"So we don''t have the ability to add the fields that they''re looking for there.","index":279,"end_time":1262.76,"speaker_id":8,"start_time":1259.64,"speaker_name":"Ashlie Taska"},{"text":"So they won''t be touching that at all.","index":280,"end_time":1265.16,"speaker_id":8,"start_time":1263.08,"speaker_name":"Ashlie Taska"},{"text":"Okay.","index":281,"end_time":1265.76,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1265.4,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Okay.","index":282,"end_time":1266.12,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1265.76,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"All right, well that makes sense then.","index":283,"end_time":1267.72,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1266.36,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So.","index":284,"end_time":1268.6,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1268.28,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So then Ashley, just let me know, you know, if anything that they need or anything that you''re building is going.","index":285,"end_time":1273.4,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1268.6,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"To impact it because, you know, we.","index":286,"end_time":1274.44,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1273.4,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Could then make sure that we''re aligned.","index":287,"end_time":1276.04,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1274.44,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"But marketing will still continue to, you know, support the campaign development within Salesforce.","index":288,"end_time":1283.3,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1276.04,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And you know, when I talk to Maria, maybe eventually it''ll be something that she would want to, you know, help support and manage.","index":289,"end_time":1289.7,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1283.3,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"But essentially the systems do need to speak to each other just to ensure that we support the process.","index":290,"end_time":1297.94,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1290.9,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Marketing will create the campaigns and then sales will close the deals.","index":291,"end_time":1302.78,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1299.62,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"But yeah, that''s basically all I wanted to say.","index":292,"end_time":1305.14,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1302.78,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"One quick call out and I was pinging Ashley on the side about this.","index":293,"end_time":1308.91,"speaker_id":6,"start_time":1305.63,"speaker_name":"bettycampiz"},{"text":"Based on how this was built out in the past, obviously agnostic to anything that''s going on now.","index":294,"end_time":1318.71,"speaker_id":6,"start_time":1311.39,"speaker_name":"bettycampiz"},{"text":"With HubSpot, we had lead in referrals that would convert to opportunities and the opportunities that needed to be tied back to a booked account via the viscode.","index":295,"end_time":1330.75,"speaker_id":6,"start_time":1318.71,"speaker_name":"bettycampiz"},{"text":"That''s in summary, how that plays out.","index":296,"end_time":1333,"speaker_id":6,"start_time":1331.16,"speaker_name":"bettycampiz"},{"text":"I heard Colin mentioning the conversion of the lead or you, Christina and I want to make sure.","index":297,"end_time":1340,"speaker_id":6,"start_time":1333.24,"speaker_name":"bettycampiz"},{"text":"That as you''re thinking through that process that that''s accounted for because right now it''s not like the lead is converting to the booked account but rather there was kind of that flow already in place.","index":298,"end_time":1353.8,"speaker_id":6,"start_time":1340,"speaker_name":"bettycampiz"},{"text":"Again, it''s not one that they''re following now because we automated opportunity closing with Encino Dao.","index":299,"end_time":1361.62,"speaker_id":6,"start_time":1354.2,"speaker_name":"bettycampiz"},{"text":"So right now that happens in the background.","index":300,"end_time":1363.94,"speaker_id":6,"start_time":1362.34,"speaker_name":"bettycampiz"},{"text":"They''re not interacting with that process.","index":301,"end_time":1365.94,"speaker_id":6,"start_time":1363.94,"speaker_name":"bettycampiz"},{"text":"But in order to revert back to it, there needs to be an understanding of how that flow impacts what you''re expecting or may need to be modified to get the results.","index":302,"end_time":1376.5,"speaker_id":6,"start_time":1366.74,"speaker_name":"bettycampiz"},{"text":"Maybe there''s nothing to do just calling it out for review.","index":303,"end_time":1380.42,"speaker_id":6,"start_time":1377.06,"speaker_name":"bettycampiz"},{"text":"And some teams just jump straight into opportunities like cash management.","index":304,"end_time":1384.9,"speaker_id":8,"start_time":1381.3,"speaker_name":"Ashlie Taska"},{"text":"They don''t have leads, it''s just opportunity.","index":305,"end_time":1387.38,"speaker_id":8,"start_time":1384.98,"speaker_name":"Ashlie Taska"},{"text":"And opportunity is also a big piece when it comes to the lending side of the house because the opportunity is then converted into the loan versus into the application.","index":306,"end_time":1398.94,"speaker_id":8,"start_time":1388.22,"speaker_name":"Ashlie Taska"},{"text":"So we might have to go through a slight change in that process because.","index":307,"end_time":1403.1,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1399.26,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"There will be leads for all areas.","index":308,"end_time":1405.1,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1403.1,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Like even when I was just talking.","index":309,"end_time":1406.62,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1405.26,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"To Maria about cash management, there is going to be leads for cash management.","index":310,"end_time":1413.5,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1406.62,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Cannabis, all of that because we''re going to start to either purchase lists or be able to better track kind of interest bonds product and then send it to, you know, the sales teams depending on, you know, if they meet the criteria.","index":311,"end_time":1425.76,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1413.5,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So maybe what we could do actually offline is just have a quick working.","index":312,"end_time":1429.68,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1425.76,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Session just to talk about leads so.","index":313,"end_time":1432.72,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1429.68,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"It doesn''t kind of derail the the next steps in the project plan.","index":314,"end_time":1435.599,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1432.72,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"But Colin, just add that into the project plan so we could track it.","index":315,"end_time":1440.72,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1435.599,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"That we just want to realign and.","index":316,"end_time":1443.48,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1440.72,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Make sure that we''re not missing anything for the lead process.","index":317,"end_time":1445.56,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1443.48,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And we''ll look at all the fields and at the same time.","index":318,"end_time":1449.87,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1447.87,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So yeah, one thing I want to saw, Gabe just sent a message of opportunities in Salesforce or deals in HubSpot.","index":319,"end_time":1455.83,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1449.95,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"The original plan wasn''t to track sales activities in HubSpot.","index":320,"end_time":1459.11,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1455.83,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It was just for marketing perspective.","index":321,"end_time":1460.55,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1459.11,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So I don''t know that we need to track deals.","index":322,"end_time":1462.389,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1460.55,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I think the biggest thing is just understanding through the this key or through that is existing customer field whether they are a lead which could be lead opportunity or a current customer which would basically that that''s the biggest indicator of what we send to them from a marketing perspective.","index":323,"end_time":1477.85,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1462.389,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":324,"end_time":1478.97,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1478.49,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"As long as we can track or attribute a closed deal, whether it be any product to an active marketing campaign.","index":325,"end_time":1488.17,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1479.05,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":326,"end_time":1489.41,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1489.05,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And that''ll be through lead source.","index":327,"end_time":1490.73,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1489.41,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":328,"end_time":1491.21,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1490.81,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"We also want to do tracking non marketing campaign from organic kind of just Channel perspective.","index":329,"end_time":1500.13,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1491.21,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Because if, if it we''re just doing brand campaigns or not even brand campaigns, but if it''s just a brand awareness, digital channel, better kind of organic search activity, like if we''re getting traffic to those pages and it''s funneling and it gets a deal, like that''s a good indication of the performance of our brand campaigns.","index":330,"end_time":1518.08,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1500.13,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And that''s one of the things that was always a qualm like we''re doing too much branding.","index":331,"end_time":1521.88,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1518.08,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Is it doing anything right?","index":332,"end_time":1523.8,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1522.28,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So as long as track it, we''re good.","index":333,"end_time":1526.68,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1523.88,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":334,"end_time":1527.09,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1526.93,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And that''s all handled through HubSpot.","index":335,"end_time":1528.25,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1527.09,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So lead source and then there''s several drill downs from the lead source as well to get more fine detail.","index":336,"end_time":1532.13,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1528.25,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":337,"end_time":1533.09,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1532.53,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And then the last question on the that and we can maybe actually we could talk about it on the leads my little working session.","index":338,"end_time":1540.25,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1533.41,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"But if there''s any account section that the rep can say like how did you hear about us?","index":339,"end_time":1549.05,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1540.25,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And it could have the different channels in there, that would be another field that we would want to just look at from a leads perspective.","index":340,"end_time":1555.51,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1549.05,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"But again I think that was on the tab that we didn''t necessarily focus on because it was more leads based and we were, we were you know, focusing more on the customer records.","index":341,"end_time":1569.19,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1555.51,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So we could talk about that.","index":342,"end_time":1570.75,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1569.67,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Just Victor, make a note so we don''t forget that in the discussion.","index":343,"end_time":1574.15,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1570.75,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Okay, so more to come there.","index":344,"end_time":1577.79,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1576.23,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"But I think, you know, Colin the project plan geek, bring that back up.","index":345,"end_time":1581.55,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1577.79,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"I think we''re in a good spot.","index":346,"end_time":1583.27,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1581.55,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So yeah, we can close a few of those today.","index":347,"end_time":1586.05,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1583.43,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So one thing I wanted to confirm Gabe and Ashley is that so you guys have a core seat with developer access to tools.","index":348,"end_time":1592.09,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1586.05,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So you should be able to see everything that you were looking to see.","index":349,"end_time":1595.09,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1592.09,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So want to confirm that we can cross that as off alpha is complete?","index":350,"end_time":1598.45,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1595.09,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I haven''t been able to confirm that.","index":351,"end_time":1603.01,"speaker_id":8,"start_time":1601.25,"speaker_name":"Ashlie Taska"},{"text":"Okay, I''m actually logged in right now.","index":352,"end_time":1605.45,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1603.65,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Colin.","index":353,"end_time":1605.77,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1605.45,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"I''m able to see all the tabs.","index":354,"end_time":1607.09,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1605.77,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Okay, perfect.","index":355,"end_time":1609.17,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1608.29,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Sounds good.","index":356,"end_time":1611.94,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1611.46,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Thank you.","index":357,"end_time":1612.42,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1611.94,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"All right.","index":358,"end_time":1612.82,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1612.42,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then so Gabe, thanks for sending the email.","index":359,"end_time":1615.5,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1612.82,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So you went through the, the list of fields that we had compiled.","index":360,"end_time":1618.82,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1615.5,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Seems like we''re, we''re very aligned on the, the capabilities of Mulesoft and Salesforce with this integration to HubSpot.","index":361,"end_time":1627.14,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1620.02,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So that gives us confidence to, to move into this phase a testing period.","index":362,"end_time":1630.58,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1627.14,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I do want to talk about the syncing so we can start to make some decisions there.","index":363,"end_time":1634.66,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1631.14,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"What I''m thinking is having trigger based real time syncs where appropriate so we can split it up based on object and then having that sch Scheduled nightly sync for like maintenance updates.","index":364,"end_time":1643.84,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1635.38,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I think new records would, we would need to send like a full payload.","index":365,"end_time":1647.68,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1644.64,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But for like anything that''s just like specific fields being updated, I think we can just update those specific fields, not a full payload.","index":366,"end_time":1654.32,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1648.08,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, that sounds good.","index":367,"end_time":1656.64,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1655.68,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"I haven''t really had the chance to.","index":368,"end_time":1658.64,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1656.72,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Typically the way we do it right now we always deal with kind of like a full payload on that sense.","index":369,"end_time":1663.2,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1658.64,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"But I think when something I can do in mulesof is if, if it''s something that doesn''t haven''t changed, then don''t update it.","index":370,"end_time":1669.74,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1663.36,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"So even though it carries that full payload, if it hasn''t changed anyone updated only.","index":371,"end_time":1674.34,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1669.74,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Only the fields that have different values.","index":372,"end_time":1676.42,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1674.5,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"So yeah, me also will perform that check before actually updates anything.","index":373,"end_time":1680.14,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1676.42,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"So yeah, that''s perfect because the biggest things.","index":374,"end_time":1682.26,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1680.14,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Because it''s.","index":375,"end_time":1683.14,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1682.66,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Because basically once we assign something to the payload, I don''t want to go back and start removing stuff.","index":376,"end_time":1688.02,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1683.14,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"It''s fine if it goes over as long as it doesn''t, you know, replace on as it.","index":377,"end_time":1692.82,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1688.34,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Unless it needs to replace.","index":378,"end_time":1694.1,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1692.82,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah.","index":379,"end_time":1695,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1694.52,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And that makes total sense because the biggest things that we need to understand are like customer or lead and what products that they are interested in or are signed up with.","index":380,"end_time":1702.04,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1695,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":381,"end_time":1703.28,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1702.92,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And remember our goal there is, you know, obviously we want to inundate the system.","index":382,"end_time":1706.44,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1703.28,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"We don''t want to stress anything out and make things break.","index":383,"end_time":1708.68,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1706.44,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"But you know, the things that are real time from a marketing perspective that are important to us is like Colin said, the new accounts, any kind of, you know, maybe transaction.","index":384,"end_time":1717.2,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1708.68,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Because when we want to build journeys and kind of provide the customer with a more real time communications experience, surveys, you know, welcome, you know, letters and things like that.","index":385,"end_time":1730.01,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1717.2,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Like those are the components that would help us trigger those and make the customer like if they walk out of the branch, like you know, they''re getting a survey like I don''t know, five minutes later.","index":386,"end_time":1737.81,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1730.01,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Like that''s kind of the experience we want to build.","index":387,"end_time":1740.01,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1737.81,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"But we can figure out if that, you know, there''s any issues when we get to the testing.","index":388,"end_time":1745.37,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1740.65,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"I don''t know the project plan.","index":389,"end_time":1748.81,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1747.61,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Can you bring that back up?","index":390,"end_time":1750.05,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1749.05,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Because I think I, I just wanted.","index":391,"end_time":1751.21,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1750.05,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"To make sure that I touched on the masking because that was a task.","index":392,"end_time":1754.05,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1751.21,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Yeah, that was the next thing.","index":393,"end_time":1754.89,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1754.05,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yep.","index":394,"end_time":1755.99,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1755.59,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So backtrack just a quick, quick second.","index":395,"end_time":1759.83,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1756.79,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So you understand kind of the, the whole masking thing.","index":396,"end_time":1762.15,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1759.83,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So when we re rated the agency and the, the SOC and all that.","index":397,"end_time":1768.23,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1762.15,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Kind of stuff, it was comfortable with.","index":398,"end_time":1770.75,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1768.23,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"The RE rating under the parameters that, you know, the PII that super super sensitive, right?","index":399,"end_time":1778.47,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1770.75,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Like social account number, those are going to be masked and so where going to still have PII that''s not masked right?","index":400,"end_time":1788.04,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1778.47,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Because email is pii, right.","index":401,"end_time":1789.52,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1788.04,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"It''s personal to the person.","index":402,"end_time":1790.6,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1789.52,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"But we can''t mask that just because.","index":403,"end_time":1792.6,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1791,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"It''S a field that we need full visibility.","index":404,"end_time":1795.72,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1792.68,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So at this point.","index":405,"end_time":1797.16,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1796.28,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Account number will mask except for the last four and.","index":406,"end_time":1803.52,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1799.24,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Then also social will mask except for.","index":407,"end_time":1806.16,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1803.52,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"The, the last four.","index":408,"end_time":1807.4,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1806.16,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"I don''t believe that there''s any other sensitive, sensitive PII that would need to be masked.","index":409,"end_time":1814.55,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1808.36,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"But like you know, if, if we come across those we can, you know, we can make a decision as we''re going.","index":410,"end_time":1823.15,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1814.55,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"But I looking at the list I think that those are the two that would be of most concern.","index":411,"end_time":1827.39,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1823.39,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"The other ones check a little bit.","index":412,"end_time":1830.51,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1827.55,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Just to save you guys time we can go ahead and define what needs to be masked or not.","index":413,"end_time":1836.03,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1830.75,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"I think a But Ashley and I are pretty self aware of the things that we need to have to be masked.","index":414,"end_time":1841.82,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1836.19,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"But instead of masking is something that I could do it on my end that way that I know if it''s a PII field I could just simply drop that from the payload.","index":415,"end_time":1850.26,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1841.82,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"I mean it doesn''t have to go into HubSpot, you don''t have to collect it, you don''t have to create a field on your side.","index":416,"end_time":1854.86,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1850.26,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"It''s something that we completely ignore and you know, take whatever other fields you need instead of taking that specific field that you need masking.","index":417,"end_time":1862.02,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1854.94,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Again Miosoft doesn''t save any data.","index":418,"end_time":1863.9,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1862.02,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"As soon as transaction completes then that, that payload is completely erased from the, from the, from the API level.","index":419,"end_time":1870.03,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1864.27,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"So that''s something that necessarily you have to spend time in defining what needs to be masked unless actually you want to bring something up.","index":420,"end_time":1877.47,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1870.11,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"So Gabe, just hold on because I want to make sure I understand.","index":421,"end_time":1879.87,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1877.47,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So, so we, we are going to be sending things that would be considered PII into HubSpot mask to that.","index":422,"end_time":1888.15,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1880.11,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"That was the kind of the consensus that Liz was comfortable with because at as part of kind of like the longer term goal we''re exploring like operational communication.","index":423,"end_time":1902.06,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1888.15,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So for example, like let''s just say that you know, online banking was down or there was a transaction that didn''t go through or something impacted a certain subset of customers and we have that list by impacted account numbers or impacted socials.","index":424,"end_time":1917.02,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1902.06,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Like what we''re going to be doing is build those communications out and like in the communication referencing like you know, regarding account ending in yadda yadda yadda.","index":425,"end_time":1926.86,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1917.02,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Right.","index":426,"end_time":1927.14,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1926.86,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And so there will be a need to have that information in I''m not 100% sure if there''s ever going to be a need for Social Security numbers.","index":427,"end_time":1933.62,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1927.3,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So I think at that point we could just say like we''re not going to accept social as I think that that''s the biggest, you know, possible security risk there.","index":428,"end_time":1942.34,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1933.62,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"But definitely account number there.","index":429,"end_time":1947.23,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1943.14,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"The hard part about just saying hey, like let''s automatically just not accept PII is the problem is, is that there''s a lot of PII with varying different differences of risk level.","index":430,"end_time":1960.11,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1947.55,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Email for example, like I said, is pii.","index":431,"end_time":1962.47,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1960.59,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So if we were to just go and said hey and said hey Gabe, don''t send anything that''s pii, email would be part of that list.","index":432,"end_time":1968.51,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1962.47,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So that''s why I didn''t kind of just go ahead and make that blanket statement and wanted to try to look at it at each record level.","index":433,"end_time":1975.54,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1968.83,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And the ones that I had flagged that would have been kind of concerned were account number and you know, obviously social.","index":434,"end_time":1982.98,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1976.5,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So.","index":435,"end_time":1983.7,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1983.3,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So Christina, on the Excel there are fields that in the column are that just straight out say mask.","index":436,"end_time":1992.5,"speaker_id":8,"start_time":1985.3,"speaker_name":"Ashlie Taska"},{"text":"So are those fields that you''re okay with us not bringing in?","index":437,"end_time":1997.86,"speaker_id":8,"start_time":1992.82,"speaker_name":"Ashlie Taska"},{"text":"You have an example other than the two that I just mentioned?","index":438,"end_time":2003.39,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2000.75,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Yeah, there was.","index":439,"end_time":2004.83,"speaker_id":8,"start_time":2003.95,"speaker_name":"Ashlie Taska"},{"text":"I need to find this Excel.","index":440,"end_time":2007.39,"speaker_id":8,"start_time":2005.47,"speaker_name":"Ashlie Taska"},{"text":"While she looks there, while she looks for the Excel document.","index":441,"end_time":2017.03,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2013.07,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"I just want a clarifying thought.","index":442,"end_time":2019.15,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2017.03,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"The progress that the customer makes on either the customer side and, or the, or the lead side and that''s getting updated into Salesforce.","index":443,"end_time":2030.51,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2019.55,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"But will we get that update in HubSpot as well just so that we can see how.","index":444,"end_time":2035.19,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2030.51,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Yeah, it''s a bi directional sync.","index":445,"end_time":2036.63,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2035.19,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":446,"end_time":2036.99,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2036.63,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So, so any, any fields that are updated will, will sync together.","index":447,"end_time":2040.23,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2036.99,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Cool, thank you.","index":448,"end_time":2041.229,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2040.47,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Okay.","index":449,"end_time":2041.75,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2041.229,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"All right.","index":450,"end_time":2042.39,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2041.99,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And just be mindful like I think we''re, we''re at time.","index":451,"end_time":2044.71,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2042.39,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So.","index":452,"end_time":2045.11,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2044.71,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So for example, annual income, the masking needed is set to true or mother''s maiden name set to true.","index":453,"end_time":2054.759,"speaker_id":8,"start_time":2047.27,"speaker_name":"Ashlie Taska"},{"text":"So it''s not like you''re bringing anything partial in for those fields.","index":454,"end_time":2057.839,"speaker_id":8,"start_time":2054.759,"speaker_name":"Ashlie Taska"},{"text":"Okay, I see what you''re saying.","index":455,"end_time":2062.239,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2060.959,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"I just had to kind of visualize it.","index":456,"end_time":2064.039,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2062.559,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Yeah, like, like things like that I don''t, I don''t think are on our, on our list.","index":457,"end_time":2069.839,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2064.039,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Mothers made a name that''s more of like an operational thing that, that is needed.","index":458,"end_time":2076.159,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2071.039,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"We wouldn''t ever need to touch.","index":459,"end_time":2077.919,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2076.399,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"To touch that balances I would want to unmask because I think at the, at some point, especially in the lending side will want to kind of research based off of like, let''s just say if somebody has a zero balance on a, on a Mortgage or a line or they''re ending a certain period.","index":460,"end_time":2097,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2077.919,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Like that''ll be a trigger for us to be able to qualify them for a campaign.","index":461,"end_time":2100.68,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2097,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So I would, I would like to have that one.","index":462,"end_time":2104.04,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2101.96,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"If you have a small list of anything that falls into that category, Ashley or Gabe, and you can send it to me, I''ll take a quick look and just, just, you know, let you know if you need to change any of those parameters.","index":463,"end_time":2115.13,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2105.32,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"But yeah, we don''t.","index":464,"end_time":2116.45,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2115.13,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"I don''t think we have made a name.","index":465,"end_time":2118.41,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2116.45,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"I think we took off other, other ones.","index":466,"end_time":2121.21,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2118.57,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Like, I think it was like pronouns we took off, like anything that.","index":467,"end_time":2127.61,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2121.21,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And Betty had flagged us that could kind of like come up as like a diversity or true, you know, fair lending or anything of that nature, we had taken off.","index":468,"end_time":2138.09,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2127.69,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So I can look at that as part of my takeaways.","index":469,"end_time":2144.22,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":2140.78,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Okay, awesome.","index":470,"end_time":2147.5,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2145.26,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"But overall, I think we''re in a good place.","index":471,"end_time":2150.98,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":2147.66,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"I think, Colin, correct me if I''m wrong, we kind of are good on the timeline.","index":472,"end_time":2154.42,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":2150.98,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"I don''t think there''s any major outstanding tasks, right?","index":473,"end_time":2157.18,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":2154.42,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"No.","index":474,"end_time":2157.78,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2157.42,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So it sounds like the only thing that we''ll have to push from the timeline that was like today to lock up was the masking.","index":475,"end_time":2163.46,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2157.78,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we''ll give you a few more days on that.","index":476,"end_time":2165.18,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2163.46,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We''ll just update that in the timeline.","index":477,"end_time":2166.46,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2165.18,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But everything else that was set for today we''re all good on.","index":478,"end_time":2168.86,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2166.46,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And so as soon as we''re good on that masking, we know, like, this is the exact list of fields that we''re pulling over and how we''re pulling them over.","index":479,"end_time":2175.04,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2169.76,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Then we''re in phase eight testing.","index":480,"end_time":2176.72,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2175.2,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So Gabe and Ashley and Christina and Vic.","index":481,"end_time":2180.28,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2176.8,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So everyone, when do you think is a good day that you can, like, look at that masking and be like, this is the list of true versus false.","index":482,"end_time":2187.76,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2180.28,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I mean, as soon as I get that list, I could look at it and have the, you know, a same day answer.","index":483,"end_time":2196.84,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":2192.88,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"I mean, if there''s any decision, obviously that I have to take to Betty, Louie, or even, you know, Liz for that that matter, I''ll do that.","index":484,"end_time":2203.26,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":2196.84,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So that might need an extra day, but I don''t think it should take too long.","index":485,"end_time":2207.34,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":2203.66,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Okay, cool.","index":486,"end_time":2208.22,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2207.42,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Gia, can you just send that spreadsheet over again?","index":487,"end_time":2210.7,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2208.3,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Just what I would say is flagging that month is a holiday, so probably just, you know, you might want to give a lease until Wednesday, Thursday.","index":488,"end_time":2218.14,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":2211.98,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":489,"end_time":2218.54,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2218.14,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":490,"end_time":2218.94,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2218.54,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right, that sounds good.","index":491,"end_time":2221.5,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2220.46,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":492,"end_time":2222.74,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2222.22,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right, well, feeling like we''re very aligned in every space, so really excited for this, guys, and excited to get into testing because that''s where we figure out.","index":493,"end_time":2230.97,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2222.74,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, you know, this didn''t go maybe exactly to plan or everything did go to plan and whatever tweaks are needed, but we''re in a really good spot.","index":494,"end_time":2237.45,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2230.97,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So Ashley and Gabe, are you guys feeling good?","index":495,"end_time":2241.85,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":2237.45,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Lou, do you have anything Betty, any before we, you know, drop.","index":496,"end_time":2244.69,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":2241.85,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"I just want to make sure that everybody''s kind of all feeling good at the same time.","index":497,"end_time":2248.01,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":2244.69,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"I think Betty tried to eat some.","index":498,"end_time":2250.21,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2249.05,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Breakfast so make sure that we were with anything, you know, pending.","index":499,"end_time":2258.21,"speaker_id":8,"start_time":2250.21,"speaker_name":"Ashlie Taska"},{"text":"I know once that mask list is confirmed then from our side we''ll be able to query and send that doc the.","index":500,"end_time":2267.85,"speaker_id":8,"start_time":2259.09,"speaker_name":"Ashlie Taska"},{"text":"The file over for a one time import.","index":501,"end_time":2269.89,"speaker_id":8,"start_time":2267.85,"speaker_name":"Ashlie Taska"},{"text":"It''s just a matter of just knowing which fields will need to be masked.","index":502,"end_time":2276.53,"speaker_id":8,"start_time":2270.21,"speaker_name":"Ashlie Taska"},{"text":"One hundred and again I''m just looking at the Excel that was shared with.","index":503,"end_time":2281.25,"speaker_id":8,"start_time":2276.53,"speaker_name":"Ashlie Taska"},{"text":"Us and I, I do see just.","index":504,"end_time":2282.61,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2281.25,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"A few fields there, but if those can be reviewed.","index":505,"end_time":2286.97,"speaker_id":8,"start_time":2282.61,"speaker_name":"Ashlie Taska"},{"text":"Yeah, I''ll look, I''ll look at, I''ll look at them.","index":506,"end_time":2290.65,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":2288.65,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Okay.","index":507,"end_time":2291.69,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2291.13,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"I don''t think there''s anything on the encompass side that.","index":508,"end_time":2294.97,"speaker_id":8,"start_time":2291.85,"speaker_name":"Ashlie Taska"},{"text":"Well, I don''t actually see a column for that.","index":509,"end_time":2298.01,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2296.01,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So I''m just referencing contact object right now when I, when I speak about that.","index":510,"end_time":2301.93,"speaker_id":8,"start_time":2298.01,"speaker_name":"Ashlie Taska"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":511,"end_time":2302.73,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":2302.33,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Okay.","index":512,"end_time":2303.29,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":2302.73,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Good.","index":513,"end_time":2305.54,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2305.38,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Okay, so then I think that that''s, that''s a quick thing that we can move forward.","index":514,"end_time":2309.06,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":2305.54,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Betty, Louie, good.","index":515,"end_time":2311.1,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":2310.1,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Are we good?","index":516,"end_time":2311.7,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":2311.1,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Anything to add or, or any concerns?","index":517,"end_time":2314.34,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":2312.02,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Not at the moment.","index":518,"end_time":2316.82,"speaker_id":6,"start_time":2315.78,"speaker_name":"bettycampiz"},{"text":"All right, great.","index":519,"end_time":2319.46,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":2318.1,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Really quick.","index":520,"end_time":2320.58,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2320.1,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"I just have one, one question.","index":521,"end_time":2322.18,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2320.58,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Ashley, everybody else can honestly like you guys are good in my opinion.","index":522,"end_time":2326.22,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2322.26,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"If, unless Colin Guille have any other things to add on.","index":523,"end_time":2329.7,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2326.22,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"No.","index":524,"end_time":2330.42,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2330.02,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":525,"end_time":2331.55,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2331.15,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"All right, well, thank you.","index":526,"end_time":2332.99,"speaker_id":6,"start_time":2331.63,"speaker_name":"bettycampiz"},{"text":"Thanks everybody.","index":527,"end_time":2333.79,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2332.99,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Thank you for the extra five minutes.","index":528,"end_time":2335.15,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2333.87,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Have a great weekend.","index":529,"end_time":2335.95,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2335.15,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Victor, I''m gonna, I''m gonna draw for the next one, but that''s fine.","index":530,"end_time":2339.99,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":2336.99,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"I''m just figuring out next steps for myself.","index":531,"end_time":2342.83,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2339.99,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Okay, fine.","index":532,"end_time":2343.95,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":2342.99,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Just make sure you send us get it.","index":533,"end_time":2345.35,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":2343.95,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Set up the meeting with Ashley and us for the little micro leads meeting.","index":534,"end_time":2348.27,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2345.35,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Yeah, okay, thanks guys.","index":535,"end_time":2350.47,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2348.51,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Bye.","index":536,"end_time":2350.83,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2350.47,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Thank you.","index":537,"end_time":2351.39,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2350.83,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"First off, appreciate you guys.","index":538,"end_time":2355.11,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2353.63,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Thank you very, very much.","index":539,"end_time":2356.11,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2355.11,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Yeah, I just wanted to say like glad that we had.","index":540,"end_time":2360.98,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2358.58,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I feel like Monday''s meeting was so good for us to like break through the ice, you know.","index":541,"end_time":2364.94,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2360.98,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And Ashley like your emails like just breaking through any confusion.","index":542,"end_time":2367.74,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2364.94,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I think we''re in a really good spot so I hope you guys are feeling that too.","index":543,"end_time":2370.1,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2367.74,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah, definitely.","index":544,"end_time":2372.9,"speaker_id":8,"start_time":2371.54,"speaker_name":"Ashlie Taska"},{"text":"So just next steps for us, Ashley and Gabe, you guys are good to go.","index":545,"end_time":2376.66,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2373.7,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Oh, for us.","index":546,"end_time":2377.7,"speaker_id":8,"start_time":2376.98,"speaker_name":"Ashlie Taska"},{"text":"Okay.","index":547,"end_time":2378.18,"speaker_id":8,"start_time":2377.7,"speaker_name":"Ashlie Taska"},{"text":"Bye.","index":548,"end_time":2381.18,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2380.74,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Have a great weekend for the meeting.","index":549,"end_time":2382.9,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2381.18,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Enjoy your long weekend.","index":550,"end_time":2384.49,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2383.37,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Thanks, you too.","index":551,"end_time":2385.49,"speaker_id":8,"start_time":2384.65,"speaker_name":"Ashlie Taska"},{"text":"Bye.","index":552,"end_time":2385.77,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2385.49,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Bye everyone.","index":553,"end_time":2386.17,"speaker_id":8,"start_time":2385.77,"speaker_name":"Ashlie Taska"},{"text":"So what other things do you Guys need from me to make sure that we meet all these timelines and deadlines from ahead of time as well, whether it''s content from other departments, stuff like that, so that I can stay on top of everybody else so that we.","index":554,"end_time":2400.21,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2387.69,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Can meet this on the, on the CRM, like integration side.","index":555,"end_time":2404.33,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2400.21,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Once we have that masking list, like finalized and confirmed, we''re just going to go into testing with the few contacts that you guys gave, make sure that those flow through the systems correctly.","index":556,"end_time":2413.87,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2404.33,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then it''s like, cool.","index":557,"end_time":2415.55,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2413.87,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Now we can do the big batch upload on the website side.","index":558,"end_time":2419.47,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2415.55,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Gia, you''re gonna have more insight into that than me.","index":559,"end_time":2421.87,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2419.47,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"If we need any feedback on copy or anything like that.","index":560,"end_time":2425.31,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2421.87,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I think Christina was reviewing it.","index":561,"end_time":2429.51,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2427.39,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"She hasn''t, like, added any comments on markup, but here she said next week.","index":562,"end_time":2436.51,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2429.51,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Okay, perfect.","index":563,"end_time":2438.84,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2437.32,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So then, yeah, I mean, we''re looking good because once we get feedback on that, we''re like designing the pages.","index":564,"end_time":2443.56,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2439,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So it''s not like we''re not making every page a new, brand new custom design that would make this website process like a year long.","index":565,"end_time":2450.2,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2443.56,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We''re going to have them by category.","index":566,"end_time":2452.439,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2450.84,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So, like every, like, parent tab you see.","index":567,"end_time":2454.32,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2452.439,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So like, the homepage is going to have a design, the location pages will have a design, the products pages will have a design, things like that.","index":568,"end_time":2461.08,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2454.32,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So, I mean, yeah, we''re feeling pretty good about that.","index":569,"end_time":2463.95,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2462.12,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, cool.","index":570,"end_time":2465.14,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2464.42,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"So as we look at it from a phase two perspective, let''s say after we launch in April, what do we see as next steps?","index":571,"end_time":2474.22,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2465.22,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"I have a thought process, but I also want to get your input on that just really quickly.","index":572,"end_time":2478.5,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2474.22,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Yeah, I mean, next steps would be, do we need to add any new fields that we didn''t include in this kind of like phase one?","index":573,"end_time":2484.82,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2478.66,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Are there any new channels or marketing campaigns that we need to launch and make sure everything''s communicating direct together?","index":574,"end_time":2491.1,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2485.38,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Any landing pages, it''s really just going to be like net new or things that we across the board agreed on, not prioritizing before launch.","index":575,"end_time":2498.48,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2491.1,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That''s perfect.","index":576,"end_time":2499.84,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2499.28,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"So, yeah, we''re.","index":577,"end_time":2500.72,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2499.84,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"We''re aligned thought process wise.","index":578,"end_time":2502.24,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2500.72,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Because, yeah, Christina was saying that we needed to have, you know, content ready for that for you guys so that we can create these things.","index":579,"end_time":2508.56,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2502.24,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"I''m like, yeah, but let''s, let''s get this part done first.","index":580,"end_time":2511.28,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2508.56,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Let''s.","index":581,"end_time":2511.68,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2511.28,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":582,"end_time":2511.96,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2511.68,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Well, what I will say, Victor, is like, we can, we can build like, so, you know, if you, if you guys want to send us over like an email or something that you want us to build, I mean, we have all the designs and everything.","index":583,"end_time":2520.36,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2511.96,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Like it''s not going to take any different time for us to just put one email.","index":584,"end_time":2524.01,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2520.36,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It''s not going to affect the CRM push, you know, things like that.","index":585,"end_time":2526.61,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2524.01,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":586,"end_time":2527.05,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2526.61,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"All right, cool.","index":587,"end_time":2528.01,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2527.21,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"So masking list campaign thoughts for phase two?","index":588,"end_time":2530.97,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2528.01,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Yeah, we''re good to go guys.","index":589,"end_time":2532.53,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2531.21,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"No, I think we, I think we''re all aligned.","index":590,"end_time":2534.41,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2532.53,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"After we got the confusion of making sure that Ashley knew that we weren''t expecting them to like build everything and we just were like controlling strings.","index":591,"end_time":2542.73,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2534.57,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You know, we''re doing our work in HubSpot, you guys are doing the other systems because we don''t have access to those.","index":592,"end_time":2546.51,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2542.73,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Right.","index":593,"end_time":2547.3,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2547.06,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":594,"end_time":2547.78,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2547.3,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"My biggest concern was also that what we spoke about earlier, making sure that the we''re able to differentiate that we actually converted a lead off of the marketing efforts that we''re doing between HubSpot and Salesforce because yeah, that''ll be through.","index":595,"end_time":2562.459,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2547.86,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Lead source and drill down fields.","index":596,"end_time":2564.58,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2562.459,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":597,"end_time":2566.02,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2565.46,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"So it''ll be on, on your guys side if you need to create any extra field for that inside of Salesforce is already exist in HubSpot.","index":598,"end_time":2572.22,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2566.02,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So that''s just something to figure out on your side.","index":599,"end_time":2573.74,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2572.22,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"If you don''t have like a lead source, which I, I, I''m pretty sure you do, that''s the only thing you would have to create.","index":600,"end_time":2579.17,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2573.74,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And we could pass back through from HubSpot.","index":601,"end_time":2581.33,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2579.17,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, Hubs Salesforce has a lead source.","index":602,"end_time":2585.57,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2582.45,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"But there I had to, whenever we were creating the web to lead forms, I had to custom code it so that it could, it can be, you know, 2025, January 6th or 2026, January 16th, you know, community event or something like that.","index":603,"end_time":2599.97,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2585.57,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":604,"end_time":2600.37,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2599.97,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So everything was wrote, done separately as obviously it should be.","index":605,"end_time":2605.09,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2600.37,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Got you.","index":606,"end_time":2605.45,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2605.09,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":607,"end_time":2605.65,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2605.45,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So that''s an open text field.","index":608,"end_time":2606.81,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2605.65,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I mean we can pass anything through to it.","index":609,"end_time":2608.37,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2606.81,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Perfect.","index":610,"end_time":2608.89,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2608.45,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Okay, so we''re, we''re good then.","index":611,"end_time":2610.37,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2608.89,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Thank you so much guys for the extra 10 minutes.","index":612,"end_time":2612.17,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2610.37,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Yeah, of course.","index":613,"end_time":2612.69,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2612.17,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right, thank you.","index":614,"end_time":2613.41,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2612.69,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Enjoy your weekend.","index":615,"end_time":2614.57,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2613.65,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"You too.","index":616,"end_time":2615.09,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2614.57,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Bye, guys.","index":617,"end_time":2616.13,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2615.49,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"}],"dateString":"2026-01-16T15:00:00.000Z","host_email":"guille.santana@marketersindemand.com","meeting_link":"https://us02web.zoom.us/j/82807622497?pwd=1oWxQKkVvrj4tRTln1UgER5pencHWv.1","participants":["guille.santana@marketersindemand.com,colin.costigan@marketersindemand.com,victor.garcia@poncebank.net,tristan.pelligrino@marketersindemand.com,gabriel.bencosme@poncebank.net,christina.zanca@poncebank.net,ashlie.taska@poncebank.net,betty.campiz@poncebank.net","colin.costigan@marketersindemand.com","victor.garcia@poncebank.net","tristan.pelligrino@marketersindemand.com","gabriel.bencosme@poncebank.net","christina.zanca@poncebank.net","ashlie.taska@poncebank.net","betty.campiz@poncebank.net"],"transcript_url":"https://app.fireflies.ai/view/01KEHVX2YQSJ1AZTVV60D64P0Q","organizer_email":"guille.santana@marketersindemand.com"}'::jsonb,
    '{"label":"positive","confidence":0.92,"bullets":["Confirmed project is on timeline; masking list is the last task before testing phase.","Agreed Salesforce will remain system of record; lifecycle stage sync flows from Salesforce to HubSpot.","Gabe confirmed MuleSoft prevents unnecessary updates, optimizing syncs without data overwriting.","Team aligned on tracking lead attribution through HubSpot lead source for marketing ROI.","Marketing to manage campaigns in Salesforce; training planned to ensure sales follows conversion flow."],"highlights":[{"quote":"We''re in a really good spot so I hope you guys are feeling that too.","speaker":"Colin Costigan"},{"quote":"Overall, I think we''re in a good place.","speaker":"christinazanca"},{"quote":"Yeah, that sounds good... MuleSoft will perform that check before actually updates anything.","speaker":"gabrielbencosme"}],"topics":["integration","marketing","testing","CRM","leads"],"model":"openai/gpt-4-1106-preview","version":1,"generated_at":"2026-01-16T00:00:00Z"}'::jsonb,
    '{"fireflies_summary":{"notes":"## **Data Integration and System Alignment**\n\nThe team confirmed that the **data mapping between Mulesoft, HubSpot, and Salesforce** is aligned to proceed with integration testing (08:56).\n\n- **Colin Costigan** highlighted that the systems will sync by object type, allowing Salesforce to remain the system of record for lead versus customer status, which will then update lifecycle stages in HubSpot (12:08).\n    - This setup enables marketing to differentiate leads and customers based on Salesforce data without HubSpot managing that distinction.\n    - The integration supports both personal and business lead types, ensuring a broad use case coverage.\n    - Testing will begin using sample contacts to validate the sync setup before full rollout.\n    - This approach avoids duplicative data entry and ensures marketing and sales alignment.\n\n- The team agreed that **HubSpot will host the new web-to-lead forms**, replacing the current Webflow forms, and these leads will be pushed to Salesforce after initial qualification (13:07).\n    - Gabe Bencosme explained that Mulesoft can trigger lead creation in Salesforce once a lead is warmed up in HubSpot, preserving the lead’s identity through the email address as the unique key.\n    - Colin confirmed email as the primary record key in HubSpot, which ties marketing and sales data together.\n    - This process improves lead segmentation and qualification before sales engagement.\n    - It maintains data integrity by avoiding multiple records for the same contact.\n\n- A **project plan with detailed subtasks and phases** was established to track deliverables, due dates, and joint efforts across teams (09:58).\n    - The plan breaks down complex data integration tasks into manageable pieces for clarity and accountability.\n    - It allows the team to identify higher-lift tasks and coordinate collaboration efficiently.\n    - This structure supports on-time delivery and transparent progress tracking.\n\n## **Lead and Customer Data Processes**\n\nThe team discussed the **handling of leads versus customers in Salesforce and HubSpot** to ensure data consistency and proper tracking (10:55).\n\n- It was clarified that Salesforce distinguishes between leads and customers using separate queues and naming conventions, whereas HubSpot uses a unified field with tracking codes to mark customer status (11:34).\n    - Betty Campiz noted that the lead conversion process exists but is underused by sales teams and requires cultural reinforcement.\n    - Christina Zanca emphasized the need to reactivate lead conversion to connect marketing efforts to sales outcomes.\n    - A working session was proposed to realign lead processes and review necessary field updates, ensuring no gaps before next project steps (23:19).\n\n- Marketing campaigns in Salesforce will continue to be operated via the **Campaigns object**, but Ashley Taska clarified that a **custom object** will be used instead of the standard campaigns object for certain data, due to field limitations (20:42).\n    - This prevents manual work by aligning campaign tracking with system capabilities.\n    - Betty and Christina will coordinate to sync marketing campaigns in Salesforce with sales activities.\n    - The integration will enable attribution of closed deals to active marketing campaigns through lead source tracking.\n\n- The team agreed on the necessity to track **lead source and campaign attribution** to measure marketing impact on sales conversions effectively (24:38).\n    - HubSpot will handle lead source with detailed drill-downs to identify performance by channel.\n    - This will address previous concerns about brand campaign ROI and justify marketing spend.\n    - Sales reps will have the ability to capture “how did you hear about us” data to enrich lead profiles.\n    - Victor Garcia and Christina flagged the need to add one or two fields related to leads into the project plan for completeness.\n\n## **Data Privacy and Masking Strategy**\n\nThe group reviewed **PII data masking requirements** to protect sensitive customer information while maintaining operational usability (29:14).\n\n- Christina Zanca explained that **account numbers and social security numbers will be masked except for the last four digits**, balancing security with the need for operational communications referencing account data (29:14).\n    - Email addresses will not be masked since they serve as primary contact keys.\n    - Gabe Bencosme offered to handle masking on the Mulesoft side by dropping sensitive fields from the payload before sending to HubSpot.\n    - This approach ensures no sensitive data persists unnecessarily in transit or storage.\n    - The masking list is in final review, with few fields flagged for removal due to privacy or compliance concerns.\n\n- Ashley Taska pointed out that fields like **annual income and mother’s maiden name are marked for masking** and will not be brought into HubSpot (33:05).\n    - Christina confirmed that some fields, such as balances, should remain unmasked to enable campaign qualification triggers.\n    - The team will review and finalize the masking list by midweek following the holiday to avoid delays.\n    - This finalization is critical to move into phase eight testing and batch data imports.\n\n## **Integration Testing and Sync Strategy**\n\nThe team agreed on a **hybrid sync approach** combining real-time trigger-based updates and scheduled nightly syncs to optimize performance and data freshness (27:20).\n\n- Gabe clarified that Mulesoft will send full payloads only for new records and update only changed fields thereafter, reducing load and avoiding unnecessary overwrites (27:35).\n    - This ensures efficient data transfer without stressing systems.\n    - Colin emphasized the importance of real-time updates for key marketing triggers like new accounts and transactions.\n    - These triggers will enable customer journeys such as immediate surveys post-branch visits, improving customer experience.\n    - Scheduled nightly syncs will handle maintenance updates and less time-sensitive data.\n\n- The team confirmed developer access for key members, with Gabe already able to view all needed tools, clearing a key dependency for testing (26:23).\n    - This access enables faster issue resolution and direct coordination during testing.\n    - The team expressed confidence in moving into testing given alignment on fields, masking, and sync protocols.\n    - Testing will validate the system interactions and identify any adjustments before full deployment.\n\n## **Website and Content Development Timeline**\n\nThe team outlined the plan to complete **website content and design by next week** to support the new HubSpot-based web-to-lead forms (40:00).\n\n- Colin shared that website design is modular by page category (homepage, location pages, product pages) to avoid long timelines.\n    - This method speeds up delivery and allows parallel content creation.\n    - Victor Garcia confirmed content readiness is the next major step after integration tasks.\n    - The team is prepared to quickly build emails and landing pages as content is provided.\n    - This enables simultaneous progress on marketing campaigns and CRM integration.\n\n- Future phase two discussions will focus on adding new fields, channels, and campaigns after the April launch (41:04).\n    - Victor and Colin agreed on ongoing iteration post-launch to expand capabilities.\n    - The team is aligned on priorities to avoid overloading phase one.\n    - Marketing will continue to create campaigns while sales focuses on deal closure.\n    - Continued coordination will ensure smooth handoffs and tracking across systems.\n\n## **Overall Alignment and Next Steps**\n\nThe team reached strong consensus on current progress, with only the **masking list finalization** remaining as a slight timeline adjustment (35:47).\n\n- Christina committed to reviewing the masking list promptly and escalating decisions to leadership if needed (36:32).\n    - The timeline was adjusted to allow completion by midweek after the holiday.\n    - Once finalized, the team will proceed to phase eight testing and batch imports.\n    - Betty, Ashley, Gabe, and Colin confirmed readiness to move forward.\n    - Victor asked for visibility into content and dependencies to keep other departments aligned.\n\n- The team emphasized the importance of **tracking lead source and marketing attribution** to measure campaign ROI and sales impact (42:27).\n    - HubSpot and Salesforce fields are in place or can be created to support detailed tracking.\n    - Custom coding has been done previously to support granular lead source data.\n    - This capability will validate marketing efforts and guide future budget decisions.\n    - The team expressed confidence that this integration will improve cross-department collaboration and data-driven decisions.\n\n- The meeting ended with mutual appreciation and a commitment to maintain momentum through the holiday weekend and into next week’s testing phase (38:52).","outline":null,"keywords":["HubSpot","Salesforce","Mulesoft","Data Integration","Lead Conversion","Data Masking"],"overview":"- **Data Mapping Confirmed:** Mulesoft, HubSpot, and Salesforce data mapping is ready for integration testing, enhancing lead-customer tracking.  \n- **Web-to-Lead Forms Transition:** HubSpot will replace Webflow forms, ensuring leads are qualified before transferring to Salesforce.  \n- **Project Plan Established:** A project plan with clear tasks and timelines will improve accountability and ensure timely delivery.  \n- **PII Data Masking Strategy:** Sensitive data will be masked during transfers, ensuring security while maintaining operational usability.  \n- **Hybrid Sync Approach:** Combining real-time updates with scheduled syncs will optimize performance and maintain data accuracy.  \n- **Content Development Timeline:** Website content and design will be completed next week to support new integrations and marketing campaigns.","action_items":"\n**Christina Zanca**\nReview and adjust masking list fields; coordinate with Betty, Louie, and Liz for approval if needed (35:00)\nLook into calendar invite issue and resolve missing Zoom link (06:23)\nCoordinate micro leads working session focusing on lead processes (39:02)\n\n**Gabriel Bencosme**\nHandle masking at payload level to drop PII fields before sending to HubSpot (30:00)\nContinue coordinating data sync and field mapping validation (27:00)\nConfirm developer access tools with Colin (26:45)\n\n**Victor Garcia**\nSchedule and set up micro leads meeting with Christina and Ashley (39:02)\nReview lead fields for campaign tracking; ensure lead source field is set up and usable in Salesforce (43:00)\nCommunicate upcoming content needs and lead conversion tracking details to all relevant departments (39:47)\n\n**Ashley Taska**\nConfirm developer access to tools for integration (26:41)\nAssist in updating Salesforce with custom objects for campaigns as requested by other departments (20:42)\nSupport review of masking field list and confirm fields that must not be brought into HubSpot (33:05)\n\n**Colin Costigan**\nPresent and maintain detailed project plan, including subtasks and deadlines (07:34)\nAdd fields related to leads and campaign tracking to project plan (19:24)\nFacilitate phase eight testing preparation after masking decision (35:50)\nSupport data sync strategy implementation (real-time and nightly batch sync) (27:30)\nCoordinate with developers on testing and troubleshooting (26:30)\nEnsure alignment on lead and customer data flows between HubSpot and Salesforce (00:00)\n\n**Betty Campiz**\nPrepare sales teams for adherence to lead conversion process; provide training during upcoming GPS training sessions (17:57)\nCoordinate with Maria for campaign alignment and system communication improvements (19:24)\nReview masking and field mapping recommendations as needed (35:00)\n\n**Luis Gonzalez**\nAssist Christina with calendar invite troubleshooting (07:17)\n\n**Guille Santana**\nAssist Colin with project plan updates and coordination (00:00)\n"},"migrated_from":"contract_meetings","original_id":"8f121923-597a-45b8-bce8-5deb8c6d2c34","master_marketer":{"status":"migrated"}}'::jsonb,
