  'Meeting Notes: EASE // MiD - Weekly Meeting',
  '## **Content Production and Podcast Strategy**

The team is advancing content projects with a focus on delivering final assets and tracking audience engagement.

- **The 2025 recap blog post is nearly complete, with copy set to be shared for review tomorrow with Cindy and Josh** to finalize the title and text (01:20)  
    - This content aims to wrap up the year’s highlights, helping boost site traffic and brand authority.  
    - Paula plans to gather feedback quickly to keep the timeline tight.  
    - The blog’s completion supports broader content marketing goals for early 2025.  
    - Timely publication is critical to capture interest while the year-end is still fresh.

- **The podcast team is integrating animations into episodes, targeting inclusion in the upcoming MiD Weekly show** after the advice section (03:33)  
    - This multimedia enhancement is intended to increase listener engagement and differentiate the podcast.  
    - Josh emphasized the importance of tracking growth in listeners across Buzzsprout, YouTube, and Spotify.  
    - Paula will coordinate with Bailey to identify the best way to monitor new reviews and listener feedback across platforms.  
    - Having a clear review tracking process will help guide future content improvements and marketing efforts.

## **Outreach Campaign Performance**

The outreach campaign launched and is showing early engagement signals that require monitoring for impact assessment.

- **The email outreach campaign launched this morning and has already achieved between 10% to 30% email sends** through Smart Lead software (01:45)  
    - Paula is actively monitoring incoming responses to measure campaign effectiveness and adjust tactics if needed.  
    - Early send rates indicate the campaign is functioning as planned, supporting lead generation goals.  
    - Continuous monitoring will provide insights to optimize messaging and targeting to improve conversion rates.  
    - The campaign’s timely launch aligns with Q1 sales and marketing priorities to build momentum.

## **Video Production and Delivery Timelines**

Video development is progressing with a clear deadline pressure to deliver training content by the end of January.

- **The OTG training video’s first rough cut is expected early next week, with animations progressing well** (02:10)  
    - Josh highlighted significant internal demand to complete all videos by January 31 for wider organizational use.  
    - Paula committed to prioritizing animation work and adjusting team focus to meet the tight deadline.  
    - Minimal post-production edits are hoped for, based on thorough preparatory work, to avoid delays.  
    - Delivering on time will support training schedules and reduce pressure from stakeholders awaiting the content.

## **Metrics Tracking and Review Process Improvements**

The team is setting up better ways to track podcast audience growth and reviews to inform content strategy.

- **Josh requested regular tracking of podcast listener growth and new reviews across key platforms like Buzzsprout, YouTube, and Apple Podcasts** to measure engagement trends (03:58)  
    - Paula plans to pull listener stats weekly for joint review, enabling data-driven decisions on content adjustments.  
    - She will collaborate with Bailey to find an efficient way to aggregate and respond to reviews, avoiding platform fragmentation.  
    - Streamlined review tracking will improve responsiveness to audience feedback and help spot trends early.  
    - This effort is part of a broader push toward more measurable content marketing outcomes.',
