WITH new_meeting AS (
  INSERT INTO compass_meetings (contract_id, meeting_date, source, external_id, title, participants, duration_seconds, recording_url, transcript, sentiment, raw_metadata, created_at, updated_at)
  VALUES (
    'e50afe94-037e-49d6-8f2e-8c05ac7e3294',
    '2026-01-16 13:30:00+00',
    'fireflies',
    '01KEHVX2WZ3N0YKHWZR2X33686',
    'Data Assessment // MiD: Weekly Marketing Meeting',
    '{"Axel Völker","Colin Costigan","Colin Costigan","MaximilianRabeler"}'::text[],
    1444,
    'https://us02web.zoom.us/j/86344108572?pwd=qdakcUFJbrjywReJlBZ3DxNLrBYqXb.1',
    '{"id":"01KEHVX2WZ3N0YKHWZR2X33686","title":"Data Assessment // MiD: Weekly Marketing Meeting","summary":{"notes":"## **Campaign Strategy and Messaging**\n\nThe team agreed to focus campaign messaging more tightly on consulting and bench management to boost relevance and engagement.\n\n- **Colin Costigan confirmed the ABM contact list now includes around 514 qualified leads, updated per Max Rabeler’s feedback** (05:15)  \n    - This curated list aims to target resource managers and operations personnel specifically.  \n    - Axel Völker noted the importance of tailoring salutations carefully using machine learning to avoid incorrect gender assumptions.  \n    - An intern will support adding salutation data to the contact list for improved personalization.  \n    - Proper personalization is expected to increase email engagement by making messages feel less automated.\n\n- **The ad copy was refined to emphasize managing consulting skills and project staffing over generic terms like “staffing” or “resume,” which risk confusing LinkedIn users** (08:11)  \n    - Axel suggested including terms like “ICT consulting” or “project staffing” to clarify the offering and avoid misinterpretation.  \n    - Colin committed to creating multiple ad headline versions, including a bench-focused ad such as “clearing your bench” to test performance.  \n    - Max and Axel agreed that concise, pain-point-driven headlines targeting the right audience would improve click rates.  \n    - Avoiding terms like “CV” on LinkedIn prevents attracting job seekers instead of managers.\n\n- **The animated video preview featuring the DESI Dolo logo and CTA was approved to move forward with a rough cut to align with existing newsletter branding** (10:55)  \n    - Max confirmed the style aligns with the newsletter’s look, helping brand consistency.  \n    - This video will be embedded on the landing page to increase conversions.\n\n## **Landing Page and Lead Generation**\n\nThe landing page design is underway to highlight multiple core features and improve conversion through layered calls to action.\n\n- **Colin shared that the landing page copy covers six core DESI Dolo offerings such as bench management, RFP handling, and utilization management** (11:11)  \n    - This page will integrate the explainer video to enrich user understanding.  \n    - Axel emphasized that bench management should be clearly featured to align with the campaign’s messaging focus.  \n    - The design is expected to be shared with the team the same day for prompt feedback and iteration.  \n    - The page aims to convert visitors by showcasing the platform’s practical value for consulting firms.\n\n- **Colin proposed lead magnet campaigns featuring interactive forms collecting firm size, utilization, bench size, and skill tracking methods to generate qualified leads** (18:53)  \n    - These forms would redirect to customized landing pages offering IT consulting best practices and benchmark data.  \n    - Axel noted generating an industry benchmark report using internal data combined with AI projections would add credibility and value.  \n    - The approach allows personalized email follow-ups comparing prospects’ current methods with DESI Dolo capabilities.  \n    - Lead gen forms would be promoted via LinkedIn ads targeting relevant personas.\n\n- **Interactive demo tools like Novatic or Storylane were discussed as ways to let users explore the product at their own pace, complementing the explainer video** (20:26)  \n    - Colin highlighted that interactive demos have shown higher success in engagement compared to passive videos.  \n    - Axel prefers explainer videos but agreed a rotation of options could serve different user preferences.  \n    - These demos will showcase key workflows, such as staffing a 20-person project in three weeks, to illustrate use cases.  \n    - Incorporating these tools supports educating prospects and shortening the sales cycle.\n\n## **Personalization and Data Enrichment**\n\nImproving data quality and personalization was prioritized to enhance campaign effectiveness and reduce the appearance of automation.\n\n- **Axel shared that a machine learning model capable of inferring gender from first and last names with high accuracy will be used to enrich salutations** (06:10)  \n    - The model also flags uncertain cases to avoid wrong assumptions.  \n    - Colin agreed to explore combining this ML approach with other language models to improve coverage and accuracy.  \n    - An intern will assist with integrating this data into the contact list.  \n    - Proper salutation personalization is seen as critical for maintaining a professional tone in enterprise outreach.\n\n- **The team acknowledged challenges with incomplete LinkedIn data, such as missing last names, requiring fallback logic using first names only** (07:18)  \n    - Axel pointed out cultural trends in Germany favor using first names in emails, but enterprise contexts still favor full names for formality.  \n    - This balancing act impacts how automated emails are perceived, affecting open and response rates.  \n    - The enrichment effort aims to reduce generic or impersonal greetings that could lower engagement.  \n    - Combining multiple data sources will help mitigate inaccuracies and fill gaps.\n\n## **Ad Design and Creative Direction**\n\nVisual and copy elements of the campaign were carefully reviewed to ensure clarity, relevance, and brand alignment.\n\n- **Colin confirmed the ad designs have been updated based on feedback, especially to avoid generic or misleading imagery and copy** (08:11)  \n    - The “spreadsheet” ad was improved to specifically address managing consulting skills, increasing its direct appeal.  \n    - Axel recommended focusing one ad at least on bench management to differentiate and test messaging effectiveness.  \n    - Max noted that the animation style used in ads is consistent with the newsletter, supporting cohesive branding.  \n    - The team will continue iterating ad copy and visuals to optimize click-through rates and conversions.\n\n- **Concerns were raised about certain terms like “CV” being misinterpreted on LinkedIn, leading to ad copy adjustments** (15:42)  \n    - Axel shared past US campaign learnings where “resume” attracted job seekers rather than managers, informing current choices.  \n    - Colin plans to draft several headline alternatives with clearer, non-technical language to avoid confusion.  \n    - The focus remains on clarity around consulting staffing and project management to attract the right audience.  \n    - This fine-tuning process aims to increase qualified traffic while minimizing wasted impressions.\n\n## **Next Steps and Follow-ups**\n\nThe team aligned on priorities to complete core assets and explore additional campaign ideas post-launch.\n\n- **Colin committed to delivering updated ad copy versions, completing the landing page design, and sharing these materials promptly via SharePoint** (23:02)  \n    - He will also assess salutation enrichment options and coordinate with Axel’s team for data integration.  \n    - The priority is to finalize the current campaign assets before pursuing new lead magnet ideas.  \n    - This staged approach ensures focus on quality before expanding outreach channels.\n\n- **Further ideation on interactive demos and lead magnet campaigns will continue after the initial launch to enhance prospect engagement** (20:12)  \n    - Colin will refine the form questions and landing page content to support personalized nurture sequences.  \n    - Axel stressed the importance of starting with core materials before layering additional complexity.  \n    - This phased rollout balances speed to market with continuous improvement.  \n    - The team agreed to regroup after reviewing initial campaign performance data.","outline":null,"keywords":["Account-Based Marketing","Salutation Personalization","Ad Copy Refinement","Bench Management","Lead Generation Campaign","Explainer Video"],"overview":"- **Campaign Focus:** Emphasize consulting and bench management to boost engagement with resource managers and operations personnel.  \n- **Lead List Update:** ABM contact list now has 514 qualified leads tailored for targeted outreach and personalization.  \n- **Refined Ad Copy:** Focused on project staffing terms, avoiding confusion by replacing generic language like \"CV\" on LinkedIn.  \n- **Landing Page Progress:** Design features six core offerings, integrated explainer video, aimed at increasing visitor conversions.  \n- **Lead Generation Strategy:** Interactive forms to capture firm data, generating qualified leads with personalized follow-up emails.  \n- **Next Steps:** Finalize campaign assets before exploring additional innovations like interactive demos and lead magnets.","action_items":"\n**Colin Costigan**\nDouble-verify and incorporate all edits and comments on the contact list spreadsheet (05:43)\nDevelop and test salutation enrichment combining LLM models to improve gender/format detection and automate adding this info to contact list (07:01)\nUpdate ad copy with revised messaging focusing on bench, consultancy staffing, and avoiding “CV” terminology; send variations to team for review (15:05)\nMove forward with producing the rough cut of the explainer video animation following approved styles (10:18)\nShare landing page design once finished; ensure copy aligns with bench-related messaging (11:11)\nFlesh out and share lead magnet campaign ideas including potential industry benchmark survey questions and nurture flow (18:53)\nUpload all campaign materials, updated contact lists, ad copy, and ideation documents to SharePoint for team access (22:59)\n\n**Axel Völker**\nAssign intern to help automate adding gender-based salutations to the contact list (07:01)\nReview upcoming updated ad copy and landing page designs for bench-specific content (11:59)\nProvide internal data or input towards creating projected benchmark reports for lead magnet campaign (18:53)\n\n**Maximilian Rabeler**\nProvide feedback on ad copy relevance and clarity, focusing on clear, pain-point-driven messaging (13:20)\nCollaborate on ensuring bench-related wording in ads effectively targets correct audience (14:47)\n"},"duration":24.06999969482422,"speakers":[{"id":0,"name":"Axel Völker"},{"id":1,"name":"Colin Costigan"},{"id":2,"name":"Colin Costigan"},{"id":3,"name":"MaximilianRabeler"}],"sentences":[{"text":"It.","index":0,"end_time":230.17,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":229.93,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Hi.","index":1,"end_time":269.86,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":269.46,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Okay.","index":2,"end_time":274.5,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":273.78,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"I hope that everyone noticed the meeting was rescheduled.","index":3,"end_time":285.95,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":281.15,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Okay.","index":4,"end_time":291.95,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":291.31,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Like Hendrick''s joining.","index":5,"end_time":294.75,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":293.39,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Max should join.","index":6,"end_time":296.91,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":295.63,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Okay.","index":7,"end_time":297.55,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":296.99,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Hi.","index":8,"end_time":298.03,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":297.55,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right, and let''s start.","index":9,"end_time":302.27,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":300.75,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"I''m not sure who else is joining.","index":10,"end_time":305.71,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":302.27,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Hope you''re feeling better.","index":11,"end_time":309.64,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":308.76,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, I''m okay, thanks.","index":12,"end_time":312.92,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":310.84,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Right.","index":13,"end_time":316.36,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":315.96,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So just want to go over the feedback and then update on the explainer video the landing page.","index":14,"end_time":324.96,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":319.96,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then I just put together some.","index":15,"end_time":326.08,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":324.96,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"New campaign recommendations as well.","index":16,"end_time":327.96,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":326.08,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So for the ABM plan, it sounds like we''re all good.","index":17,"end_time":331.84,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":329.88,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We updated the contact list based on Max''s feedback and the table that he shared last week.","index":18,"end_time":337.32,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":331.84,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So that is all set to go.","index":19,"end_time":340.26,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":338.98,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It''s.","index":20,"end_time":340.54,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":340.26,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It''s around 514 people.","index":21,"end_time":342.9,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":340.54,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I also made some.","index":22,"end_time":344.5,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":343.38,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"I added some notes.","index":23,"end_time":345.58,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":344.5,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"I hope you saw them.","index":24,"end_time":346.54,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":345.58,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"I basically just added them as comments in your.","index":25,"end_time":349.62,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":346.54,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"In your Google sheet.","index":26,"end_time":352.66,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":349.86,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Okay.","index":27,"end_time":353.62,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":353.14,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, I''ll double verify.","index":28,"end_time":355.06,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":353.62,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That''s.","index":29,"end_time":355.54,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":355.06,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That''s all taken care of.","index":30,"end_time":356.82,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":355.54,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":31,"end_time":360.02,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":359.38,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"And then we have your copy.","index":32,"end_time":364.1,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":361.78,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So I was looking through that document.","index":33,"end_time":365.84,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":364.6,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We''ve updated our.","index":34,"end_time":366.84,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":365.84,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":35,"end_time":367.4,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":366.92,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Have you checked that?","index":36,"end_time":368.08,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":367.4,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"How is it?","index":37,"end_time":368.68,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":368.08,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Yeah, I think.","index":38,"end_time":370.76,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":370.2,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I think this is good.","index":39,"end_time":371.64,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":370.76,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"The one thing that I want to talk about is the salutation.","index":40,"end_time":375.24,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":371.72,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It''s pretty.","index":41,"end_time":377.8,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":377.08,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It''s not really possible to enrich for gender and if we made like an assumption based on names, then we might run into a tricky scenario.","index":42,"end_time":385.88,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":377.88,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, I checked it with.","index":43,"end_time":387.64,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":386.44,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Actually, I checked it was Google Notebook ML or something.","index":44,"end_time":391.79,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":387.64,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"It works pretty well.","index":45,"end_time":392.75,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":391.79,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"And it will actually tell you when it''s not sure.","index":46,"end_time":395.63,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":393.23,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"And it''s actually even taking the last name to say, oh, this is an Italian last name.","index":47,"end_time":400.99,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":395.95,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"So Andrea is probably male and not female like it would be in German.","index":48,"end_time":405.07,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":401.07,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"And it''s pretty smart actually.","index":49,"end_time":407.23,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":405.23,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"But I haven''t really figured out how to add that to.","index":50,"end_time":410.91,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":407.71,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"To a specific column.","index":51,"end_time":413.23,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":410.99,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"But we have a intern starting here next week and my idea is to give that to him to add that to A.","index":52,"end_time":419.43,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":413.23,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Okay, well, we can.","index":53,"end_time":422.15,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":421.19,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We can combine the LLMs then and see what we can put together for salutation.","index":54,"end_time":426.11,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":422.15,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I just wanted to check with you guys before building an enrichment that just.","index":55,"end_time":429.11,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":426.11,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Kind of makes an assumption.","index":56,"end_time":429.87,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":429.11,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"No, I think, I think it should.","index":57,"end_time":430.95,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":429.87,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"It should work most of any way.","index":58,"end_time":433.19,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":431.19,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"We have some missing last name.","index":59,"end_time":435.75,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":433.19,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Sometimes it just says A or S or whatever.","index":60,"end_time":438.07,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":435.83,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Yeah, and that was their LinkedIn profile.","index":61,"end_time":440.15,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":438.47,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That''s all it says.","index":62,"end_time":441.03,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":440.15,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So then we have to take the first name.","index":63,"end_time":443.43,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":441.43,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"But it is.","index":64,"end_time":444.07,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":443.43,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"So it is a bit.","index":65,"end_time":445.76,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":444.6,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"I don''t know, it''s.","index":66,"end_time":446.68,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":445.76,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"There''s.","index":67,"end_time":447.16,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":446.68,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"You see more and more people just using the first name in German, which is not.","index":68,"end_time":454.92,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":447.96,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Which like a few years ago you would not have Done that.","index":69,"end_time":459.64,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":455.8,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Now it''s becoming more and more common.","index":70,"end_time":461.56,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":459.72,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"And I guess one of the reasons is that those mail automation tools, they cannot really handle it.","index":71,"end_time":467.48,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":461.56,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"But in a enterprise context, you''re more on the safe side.","index":72,"end_time":474.09,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":468.92,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"If you use the.","index":73,"end_time":475.57,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":474.33,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Not the last name, I would say.","index":74,"end_time":477.25,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":475.57,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Okay, all right, I got you.","index":75,"end_time":478.81,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":477.25,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That is what I would think otherwise.","index":76,"end_time":482.57,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":478.81,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Also, one, one for me, if I get a mail with a first name, it always very much looks like email automation and less.","index":77,"end_time":491.53,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":482.57,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Less personal.","index":78,"end_time":492.25,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":491.61,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, understood.","index":79,"end_time":495.37,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":493.85,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then we also updated the ad designs based on your feedback.","index":80,"end_time":499.14,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":496.5,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So the one that was about spreadsheets, so we changed the copy to still managing consultant skills and spreadsheets.","index":81,"end_time":507.06,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":499.22,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"There''s a better way to scale.","index":82,"end_time":508.18,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":507.06,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So it''s.","index":83,"end_time":509.18,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":508.66,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":84,"end_time":509.62,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":509.18,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Generic.","index":85,"end_time":510.74,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":510.18,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"That could have been anything.","index":86,"end_time":511.819,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":510.74,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"It''s.","index":87,"end_time":512.26,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":511.819,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":88,"end_time":513.02,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":512.66,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Al Crew spreadsheets.","index":89,"end_time":513.94,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":513.02,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, I agree.","index":90,"end_time":514.74,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":513.94,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we updated that, but it seemed like everything.","index":91,"end_time":517.66,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":515.14,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That was your only comment on the ad.","index":92,"end_time":518.82,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":517.66,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So it seemed like.","index":93,"end_time":519.3,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":518.82,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I haven''t checked the other ones because they are different texts.","index":94,"end_time":522.74,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":519.3,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"I think I have checked because.","index":95,"end_time":525.77,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":522.74,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"That''s also pretty generic because staffing could.","index":96,"end_time":534.05,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":531.77,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Could also be.","index":97,"end_time":534.97,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":534.05,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"I think we should somehow put ICT consulting or something in there so that people know what it''s about.","index":98,"end_time":545.13,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":538.65,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Okay.","index":99,"end_time":546.29,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":545.77,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Or do we want to change it to be more bench focused?","index":100,"end_time":549.29,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":546.29,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"How many different ads do you want to run?","index":101,"end_time":552.9,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":551.3,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"I would basically kind of have one focus on bench at least and then see which ones perform the best.","index":102,"end_time":559.7,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":553.06,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":103,"end_time":560.7,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":560.26,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we have three different types of ads.","index":104,"end_time":562.26,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":560.7,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So one of them is stop reformatting CVS.","index":105,"end_time":564.42,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":562.26,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Let AI handle the formatting that on LinkedIn.","index":106,"end_time":568.26,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":564.42,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"People will think that''s.","index":107,"end_time":569.94,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":568.66,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"That''s my personal CV.","index":108,"end_time":572.5,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":569.94,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Okay.","index":109,"end_time":573.46,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":572.9,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We had the same problem with resume in the US I would probably not use CV on LinkedIn.","index":110,"end_time":578.18,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":573.62,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Okay, gotcha.","index":111,"end_time":579.68,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":578.64,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Then we just make a bench one here.","index":112,"end_time":582.24,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":580.48,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":113,"end_time":583.12,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":582.64,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right, I''ll get those updated and sent over.","index":114,"end_time":586.08,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":584,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then seemed like we were all good on the initial designs.","index":115,"end_time":598.48,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":594.32,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Hendrik, I''m not sure if you saw.","index":116,"end_time":600.64,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":599.36,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"These that we shared.","index":117,"end_time":602,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":600.64,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Just a preview to see if we''re good in the design direction.","index":118,"end_time":607.25,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":604.09,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So this is showing an animation of.","index":119,"end_time":608.65,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":607.25,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"The logo bringing up CTA.","index":120,"end_time":611.01,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":608.65,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We''re going to change this to desidollo.com.","index":121,"end_time":612.77,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":611.01,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Instead of the subdomain.","index":122,"end_time":614.01,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":612.77,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then this would be the animation style.","index":123,"end_time":616.65,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":614.49,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I''m not sure.","index":124,"end_time":619.05,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":618.41,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Max.","index":125,"end_time":619.41,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":619.05,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Heinrich, have you looked at this?","index":126,"end_time":620.97,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":619.41,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"I did.","index":127,"end_time":622.49,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":621.93,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"I didn''t have a lot of time to look at it.","index":128,"end_time":625.21,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":623.29,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":129,"end_time":626.53,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":626.17,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"I mean, it''s just six pictures, right?","index":130,"end_time":628.49,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":626.53,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"I mean, the style is somehow commonly used, as far as I know from what we.","index":131,"end_time":637.89,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":630.05,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"I mean, for example, our newsletter also uses a design which is looking like.","index":132,"end_time":642.41,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":637.97,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"That It Looks similar.","index":133,"end_time":643.89,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":642.41,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":134,"end_time":644.61,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":644.05,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":135,"end_time":645.09,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":644.61,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"So might make sense to use it again, but I don''t have a clue how this affects people.","index":136,"end_time":653.09,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":645.65,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":137,"end_time":655.7,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":655.5,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So it sounds like it''s tied closely to something you guys are already doing from an animation perspective on the newsletter.","index":138,"end_time":660.54,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":655.7,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So I think that''s good.","index":139,"end_time":661.98,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":660.54,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So cool.","index":140,"end_time":663.78,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":663.26,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We''ll move forward with producing the rough cut of this video then.","index":141,"end_time":666.22,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":663.78,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":142,"end_time":670.06,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":669.5,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"We''ve also written out the landing page.","index":143,"end_time":675.1,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":671.18,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"This is being designed today, so I''ll be able to share that with you.","index":144,"end_time":677.62,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":675.1,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Guys as soon as it''s designed.","index":145,"end_time":679.1,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":677.62,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But this goes through a few different.","index":146,"end_time":681.34,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":679.5,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Of the six core offerings, you know, that are on the homepage of the DESI Dialo website.","index":147,"end_time":685.98,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":682.06,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So it talks.","index":148,"end_time":686.7,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":685.98,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"The bench, it talks through RFPs and just utilization management.","index":149,"end_time":693.48,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":687.8,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So wanted to have a few different pieces of the DESI dollar tool throughout.","index":150,"end_time":697.44,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":693.72,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"This page and then just play around.","index":151,"end_time":698.92,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":697.44,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"With how the calls to action are.","index":152,"end_time":700.24,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":698.92,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Layered throughout the page, see if we can get more conversions.","index":153,"end_time":702.68,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":700.24,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So where is that?","index":154,"end_time":705.08,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":704.2,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"That''s the landing page or what?","index":155,"end_time":706.92,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":705.56,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah.","index":156,"end_time":707.56,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":706.92,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So this is being designed today.","index":157,"end_time":708.64,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":707.56,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"This is the copy that we wrote for it.","index":158,"end_time":710.2,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":708.64,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":159,"end_time":711.92,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":711.56,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"So the mail and the ads are now pretty much focus on the bench stuff.","index":160,"end_time":717.8,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":711.92,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"So we should have that there.","index":161,"end_time":719.08,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":717.8,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Yep, somewhere.","index":162,"end_time":720.76,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":719.56,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":163,"end_time":722.72,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":722.36,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we have the.","index":164,"end_time":723.32,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":722.72,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then we also have a placeholder.","index":165,"end_time":724.92,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":723.32,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"For adding in the explainer video when that''s done.","index":166,"end_time":726.84,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":724.92,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":167,"end_time":728.12,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":727.48,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"So I don''t know, have you reviewed the.","index":168,"end_time":738.84,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":733.64,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"The ads for LinkedIn?","index":169,"end_time":740.74,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":739.78,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Because I only looked at the first one and then not the other ones.","index":170,"end_time":745.06,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":740.74,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"But are you going to make new suggestions for them, Colin, or.","index":171,"end_time":749.82,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":745.94,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Yeah, I was going to update the ad copy just based on your feedback.","index":172,"end_time":752.34,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":749.82,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I mean, are there more ads than the few we have seen like a minute ago?","index":173,"end_time":757.38,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":753.22,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"Yeah, these are the ads that he''s referring to.","index":174,"end_time":760.26,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":758.02,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, I mean, I know those, but.","index":175,"end_time":763.02,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":760.5,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"Yeah, but what is yours?","index":176,"end_time":764.18,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":763.02,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"What is your thought on that?","index":177,"end_time":766.41,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":765.53,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Because I find them somewhat too generic.","index":178,"end_time":768.33,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":766.41,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Yeah, but I mean, the other way around.","index":179,"end_time":771.85,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":769.29,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"I don''t know what I would.","index":180,"end_time":773.85,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":771.85,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"I mean, I''m not in the.","index":181,"end_time":775.53,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":774.17,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"I''m very far from the person we want to address.","index":182,"end_time":778.97,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":776.01,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"So I don''t really know what sort of ad people would click at.","index":183,"end_time":788.89,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":781.45,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"But I mean, I think for example, there''s still managing consultant skills and spreadsheets is somehow.","index":184,"end_time":796.58,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":791.3,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"Yeah, that is better now because if.","index":185,"end_time":800.46,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":798.58,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"You manage in spreadsheets, you might click on this.","index":186,"end_time":803.7,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":800.46,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"If you do not mention spreadsheets, but you have some sort of software which might not be good.","index":187,"end_time":809.94,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":804.34,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"It''s already a thing.","index":188,"end_time":814.42,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":811.06,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"Do you want to change whatever you.","index":189,"end_time":816.38,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":814.5,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"Wherever you manage your skills or not?","index":190,"end_time":818.9,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":816.38,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"But I think that might be efficient for people which have some sort of pain there because it''s a clear thing.","index":191,"end_time":827.22,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":819.94,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"Where do you manage your skills?","index":192,"end_time":828.9,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":827.22,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"Well, yeah, that one is better now.","index":193,"end_time":832.34,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":830.18,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"But that''s already updated.","index":194,"end_time":833.54,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":832.34,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Yeah, that''s not updated.","index":195,"end_time":834.98,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":833.62,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Well, I mean.","index":196,"end_time":837.42,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":836.26,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"Yeah, you already said that.","index":197,"end_time":838.86,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":837.42,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"Staffing is really.","index":198,"end_time":839.86,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":838.86,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"It should be.","index":199,"end_time":841.7,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":840.82,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"I mean, we have those, those.","index":200,"end_time":843.46,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":841.78,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"Like generic people who we want to address.","index":201,"end_time":849.74,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":847.5,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"And I would just.","index":202,"end_time":850.86,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":849.82,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"Can you go back to the ads?","index":203,"end_time":852.98,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":851.58,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"I would just tackle one specific thing they do and give a brief summary in few words that we can make it better.","index":204,"end_time":863.34,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":852.98,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"Can you, can you go back to the staffing one?","index":205,"end_time":865.82,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":863.66,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Maybe we can just call it.","index":206,"end_time":871.75,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":870.39,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"We can just call it project staffing.","index":207,"end_time":874.07,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":872.15,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"That would be a bit more clear.","index":208,"end_time":875.27,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":874.07,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"And it''s more.","index":209,"end_time":876.15,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":875.27,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"There''s not like recruiting or something.","index":210,"end_time":878.79,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":876.71,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Now we explicitly take it as finding the right people at the right time or something.","index":211,"end_time":887.03,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":881.51,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"Yeah, that''s also AI.","index":212,"end_time":890.15,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":887.75,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Like AI finds the right.","index":213,"end_time":895.83,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":892.87,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"Yeah, I don''t know.","index":214,"end_time":898.84,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":897.16,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"It has to be short.","index":215,"end_time":900.12,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":899.16,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"I''ll think through a few different versions.","index":216,"end_time":905.8,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":904.2,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, of course, stuffing is better than just staffing because it''s a bit more clear.","index":217,"end_time":909.16,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":905.96,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"We''re not especially like with this robo arm.","index":218,"end_time":913.24,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":909.24,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"It looks like production somehow to me.","index":219,"end_time":915.8,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":913.72,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Looks like some robot in some assembly line or something.","index":220,"end_time":919.32,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":916.2,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Yeah, we automated.","index":221,"end_time":920.92,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":919.72,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"We''re doing a lot of these types of shapes that are very tied in with AI with the DESI dollar logo.","index":222,"end_time":926.12,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":921.4,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But I didn''t want to just keep doing that design.","index":223,"end_time":927.8,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":926.12,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But I mean, can you, can you go back to the left?","index":224,"end_time":933.15,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":930.91,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"That''s for example, something.","index":225,"end_time":934.59,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":933.39,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"I mean.","index":226,"end_time":934.95,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":934.59,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"Okay, actually you just said CVS is not something which is good for LinkedIn people.","index":227,"end_time":941.63,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":934.95,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"But no, see this one you want to change because I think if you put CV on LinkedIn they would.","index":228,"end_time":947.31,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":942.43,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"People will just assume it''s my CV for job applications or something.","index":229,"end_time":951.71,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":947.31,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":230,"end_time":952.15,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":951.79,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"Okay, so a part of that.","index":231,"end_time":953.71,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":952.15,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"I really like this because it''s.","index":232,"end_time":955.6,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":954.12,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"It has a clear.","index":233,"end_time":956.44,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":955.6,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"It has a clear target here.","index":234,"end_time":958.28,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":956.84,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"Okay, I''m reformatting CVS for my consultants.","index":235,"end_time":961.64,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":958.28,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"Okay, this is not clear in this case.","index":236,"end_time":963.48,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":961.64,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"Fine, but then you already feel like, okay, I have to do this next week again, I don''t want to do this.","index":237,"end_time":969.72,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":963.48,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"Is there an easier way?","index":238,"end_time":970.92,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":969.72,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"We can try it because maybe in German it''s more clear.","index":239,"end_time":976.04,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":971.8,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"But we, we noticed when we did this in the US we call the resume it.","index":240,"end_time":983.05,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":976.04,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Is it attracted completely wrong people, just job seekers that.","index":241,"end_time":988.69,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":983.05,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"So they get some kind of tool to generate nice resumes for them or something.","index":242,"end_time":995.25,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":988.69,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Are there more generic words like for CVS and staffing as well?","index":243,"end_time":1000.97,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":996.37,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So these are all some decidalo type words, I would say.","index":244,"end_time":1004.97,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1000.97,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So maybe we should have something more generic that is clear for everyone.","index":245,"end_time":1010.84,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1004.97,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Because also staffing is maybe only clear for stuffing manager.","index":246,"end_time":1017.32,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1011,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, but you''re targeting the ads, right?","index":247,"end_time":1020.12,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1018.12,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"So they''re not.","index":248,"end_time":1020.68,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1020.12,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Yeah, so it''s mainly resource managers and operations personnel.","index":249,"end_time":1024.04,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1020.68,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Stuffing.","index":250,"end_time":1027.32,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1026.6,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"I mean we could even have like stop bulk reformatting CVS so that it.","index":251,"end_time":1034.32,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1029.16,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I think you should at least have consultancy these or something because otherwise people would just think it''s your.","index":252,"end_time":1041.36,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1034.8,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"I think for these I''ll.","index":253,"end_time":1053.76,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1052.64,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I''ll come up with a few different.","index":254,"end_time":1055.12,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1053.92,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Headlines and send them over to you guys.","index":255,"end_time":1057.2,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1055.12,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And we should have one with.","index":256,"end_time":1059.76,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1058.24,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"For the bench.","index":257,"end_time":1060.88,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1060.08,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Yeah, stuff like, I don''t know, having consultants on the bench or something.","index":258,"end_time":1066.42,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1061.12,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"We''ll get them off.","index":259,"end_time":1068.82,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1067.78,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Something like that.","index":260,"end_time":1069.62,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1068.82,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Yeah, something about clearing your bench or utilizing your bench.","index":261,"end_time":1072.26,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1069.78,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":262,"end_time":1072.9,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1072.5,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":263,"end_time":1073.38,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1072.9,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"All right.","index":264,"end_time":1075.7,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1075.14,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Okay, good.","index":265,"end_time":1076.82,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1075.78,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":266,"end_time":1078.019,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1077.54,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then I was just thinking through a few other like lead magnet style campaigns that we can run where, you know, we get them to entice, maybe download a playbook or a white paper or something like that, and then they can enroll into automated nurture sequence for education.","index":267,"end_time":1090.41,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1078.019,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So one was kind of around like an industry benchmark and I was thinking this is something like a form that we could collect the company''s firm size, their utilization estimate, bench size estimate, how long it takes them to staff projects and what method they''re using for tracking skills, whether that''s spreadsheets or something else.","index":268,"end_time":1110.89,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1091.61,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then it would just redirect them to a landing page with IT consulting and IT services, best practices, practices and metrics for these types of things and.","index":269,"end_time":1119.32,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1111.13,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"How Desi Doll is able to, you know, enhance those.","index":270,"end_time":1122.6,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1119.32,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Any thoughts there?","index":271,"end_time":1127.8,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1126.84,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, we would have to.","index":272,"end_time":1135.56,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1133.4,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"So we would need to do a benchmark or something or.","index":273,"end_time":1139.4,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1135.64,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Yeah, and I don''t know if you''d be able to do this with, you know, in house data or if we''d have to combine some research to it.","index":274,"end_time":1146.54,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1140.92,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It''s kind of like taking all the case studies.","index":275,"end_time":1149.98,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1147.98,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":276,"end_time":1151.5,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1151.02,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Well, on an industry benchmark we can try to get something from our data, but we see if we get there.","index":277,"end_time":1168.94,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1157.5,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"I mean, this is only used.","index":278,"end_time":1172.86,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1171.42,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"In which case is it used?","index":279,"end_time":1175.74,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1173.9,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"Is it needed that the data are completely true or can we just make an output?","index":280,"end_time":1183.66,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1175.74,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"You can just ask ChatGPT to write you a report and add our data or something.","index":281,"end_time":1190.62,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1184.38,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"I mean, this is.","index":282,"end_time":1192.9,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1192.14,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Data is not.","index":283,"end_time":1193.74,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1192.9,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"No one can really validate that.","index":284,"end_time":1195.34,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1193.82,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"That''s.","index":285,"end_time":1195.74,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1195.54,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"I think that''s the point.","index":286,"end_time":1196.66,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1195.74,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Yeah, we could say on the landing page that it''s a projection.","index":287,"end_time":1200.02,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1197.14,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You know, we can use our data.","index":288,"end_time":1202.34,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1200.1,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"This data will make a projection from it or something.","index":289,"end_time":1204.74,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1202.42,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":290,"end_time":1205.62,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1205.06,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That could probably work.","index":291,"end_time":1208.1,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1206.82,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"We have to see how cool can do that.","index":292,"end_time":1211.38,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1209.62,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Okay, so I''ll flush that idea a little bit more and then send you guys some things that we would need from your end.","index":293,"end_time":1219.22,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1212.58,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, but let''s first get the current stuff already, like the landing page and the mail and all that.","index":294,"end_time":1226.12,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1219.62,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Oh, absolutely.","index":295,"end_time":1227.24,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1226.36,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":296,"end_time":1227.48,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1227.24,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"This is, this is a separate, separate ideation.","index":297,"end_time":1229.48,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1227.48,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then we talk through.","index":298,"end_time":1231.48,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1230.36,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You know, obviously people can sign up directly for the platform, but there are tools like Novatic or storylane which we can control a demo experience where they can just click around.","index":299,"end_time":1241.16,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1231.64,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So I really think that having something.","index":300,"end_time":1243.08,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1241.72,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Like that would be beneficial, I think.","index":301,"end_time":1245.84,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1243.08,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, maybe even just the few videos like Screencast or something where you see how it looks.","index":302,"end_time":1252.51,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1245.84,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Yeah, the cool thing about storylane or Nevadic is the, the user gets to.","index":303,"end_time":1257.43,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1252.99,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Control the pace that they''re moving at.","index":304,"end_time":1259.31,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1257.43,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And we get to control like what the screen says or what the highlight.","index":305,"end_time":1262.75,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1259.31,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Of the button says.","index":306,"end_time":1263.71,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1262.75,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":307,"end_time":1264.99,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1264.35,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"And we can get a video.","index":308,"end_time":1267.15,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1265.87,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I''m personally not using that.","index":309,"end_time":1269.59,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1268.11,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"I prefer a video where someone explains what, what I see.","index":310,"end_time":1274.59,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1269.59,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"I''m not sure if maybe other people like other stuff better, but yeah, we''ve.","index":311,"end_time":1279.86,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1274.59,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Seen higher success with the interactive demos.","index":312,"end_time":1282.1,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1279.86,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":313,"end_time":1283.7,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1283.06,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"But I think, you know, we''re making an explainer video as well and, and we have the, the screen recording so we can have, you know, a rotation.","index":314,"end_time":1291.22,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1284.82,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Of what people can choose to look at.","index":315,"end_time":1292.98,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1291.22,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":316,"end_time":1294.18,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1293.62,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"And then a few other things.","index":317,"end_time":1298.26,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1297.14,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Kind of just giving someone a scenario for, for how they would handle these sorts of projects.","index":318,"end_time":1304.62,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1298.9,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So hey, you just want an RFP, it''s a 20 person staffing project.","index":319,"end_time":1307.58,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1304.62,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It starts in three weeks.","index":320,"end_time":1308.58,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1307.58,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Are you staff it and kind of just asking this question of how people.","index":321,"end_time":1312.8,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1308.58,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Are handling these types of scenarios and then obviously pushing Desi dollo as a solution to, to enhance their, their skill process and then same thing on the skill side on the right here and.","index":322,"end_time":1326.52,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1312.8,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Really just getting an understanding of what.","index":323,"end_time":1328.12,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1326.52,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Method they''re currently using to track skills.","index":324,"end_time":1331.44,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1328.12,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Is it just a spreadsheet?","index":325,"end_time":1332.8,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1331.44,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Is it something in SharePoint?","index":326,"end_time":1333.96,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1332.8,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Do they have some sort of PSA software already in use so that we can get an understanding?","index":327,"end_time":1338.4,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1333.96,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then from there, based on this data, we could send them more personalized.","index":328,"end_time":1342.57,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1338.73,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Emails with a comparison to what they''re already using.","index":329,"end_time":1344.97,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1342.57,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And sorry, how do we use that?","index":330,"end_time":1347.93,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1345.93,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Is that like ads or what is that?","index":331,"end_time":1349.69,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1347.93,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Or.","index":332,"end_time":1349.97,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1349.69,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Yeah, so we would entice someone to go to fill this out as an ad.","index":333,"end_time":1353.17,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1349.97,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So on a LinkedIn lead gen form we can ask them a custom question and they could indicate in the dropdown what they''re using and then we could send them a more personalized email that''s like a comparison between Desi Dalo and.","index":334,"end_time":1363.29,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1353.17,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"What they''re currently using.","index":335,"end_time":1364.17,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1363.29,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So it''s an ad.","index":336,"end_time":1365.44,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1364.76,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"They first have to click on an ad or something?","index":337,"end_time":1367.4,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1365.44,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Yes.","index":338,"end_time":1368.12,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1367.64,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":339,"end_time":1369.16,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1368.6,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"So these were just a few.","index":340,"end_time":1375.44,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1374.52,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Different ideas that I had written down.","index":341,"end_time":1377.56,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1375.44,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"For different things that we can run.","index":342,"end_time":1379.08,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1377.72,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Can you share that?","index":343,"end_time":1380.2,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1379.32,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Just put it on the SharePoint?","index":344,"end_time":1382.52,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1380.52,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Yeah, we''ll do.","index":345,"end_time":1383.64,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1382.68,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right, so I''ll get the ad copy, I''ll write a few variations and send those over to you.","index":346,"end_time":1390.92,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1385.4,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I''ll make sure that the list has all of your edits in it, and I''ll see what enrichment we can do for the salutations.","index":347,"end_time":1396.5,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1390.92,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then I''ll share the landing page.","index":348,"end_time":1398.98,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1397.06,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Design when that is finished today, and I''ll share these ideas.","index":349,"end_time":1402.1,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1398.98,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, sounds good.","index":350,"end_time":1406.18,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1404.26,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"From your end, was there anything else.","index":351,"end_time":1407.7,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1406.5,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That you guys wanted to chat through?","index":352,"end_time":1408.9,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1407.7,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Max?","index":353,"end_time":1410.98,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1410.58,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Henrik?","index":354,"end_time":1411.62,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1410.98,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Not for me at the moment, no.","index":355,"end_time":1414.42,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1411.78,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"All right.","index":356,"end_time":1417.78,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1417.22,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Okay.","index":357,"end_time":1418.9,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1418.34,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Thanks, Dan.","index":358,"end_time":1419.86,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1419.06,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Thank you.","index":359,"end_time":1421.22,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1420.66,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"All right, you as well.","index":360,"end_time":1422.1,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1421.22,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Bye.","index":361,"end_time":1422.82,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1422.34,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Thanks.","index":362,"end_time":1423.38,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1422.9,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"}],"dateString":"2026-01-16T13:30:00.000Z","host_email":"colin.costigan@marketersindemand.com","meeting_link":"https://us02web.zoom.us/j/86344108572?pwd=qdakcUFJbrjywReJlBZ3DxNLrBYqXb.1","participants":["tristan.pelligrino@marketersindemand.com,colin.costigan@marketersindemand.com,joachim.giesen@uni-jena.de,guille.santana@marketersindemand.com,nathalie.mintjens@marketersindemand.com,voelker@data-assessment.com,bebinger@decidalo.com,osbaldeston@data-assessment.com,pollex@data-assessment.com,rabeler@data-assessment.com","tristan.pelligrino@marketersindemand.com","joachim.giesen@uni-jena.de","guille.santana@marketersindemand.com","nathalie.mintjens@marketersindemand.com","voelker@data-assessment.com","bebinger@decidalo.com","osbaldeston@data-assessment.com","pollex@data-assessment.com","rabeler@data-assessment.com"],"transcript_url":"https://app.fireflies.ai/view/01KEHVX2WZ3N0YKHWZR2X33686","organizer_email":"colin.costigan@marketersindemand.com"}'::jsonb,
    '{"label":"positive","confidence":0.91,"bullets":["Finalized ABM contact list with 514 entries after incorporating Max''s feedback and shared table.","Updated explainer video animation aligns with newsletter design and will use main domain branding.","Refined LinkedIn ad messaging for clarity; Colin to deliver updated ad copy based on team input.","Landing page copy completed and under design; tied to DESI core offerings and explainer integration.","Lead magnet and enrichment ideas discussed; benchmark projections may leverage internal data estimates."],"highlights":[{"quote":"I''ll get the ad copy, I''ll write a few variations and send those over to you.","speaker":"Colin Costigan"},{"quote":"So the mail and the ads are now pretty much focus on the bench stuff.","speaker":"Axel Völker"},{"quote":"We''ll move forward with producing the rough cut of this video then.","speaker":"Colin Costigan"}],"topics":["ads","copy","landing","enrichment","campaign","video"],"model":"openai/gpt-4-0613","version":1,"generated_at":"2026-01-16T15:01:00Z"}'::jsonb,
    '{"fireflies_summary":{"notes":"## **Campaign Strategy and Messaging**\n\nThe team agreed to focus campaign messaging more tightly on consulting and bench management to boost relevance and engagement.\n\n- **Colin Costigan confirmed the ABM contact list now includes around 514 qualified leads, updated per Max Rabeler’s feedback** (05:15)  \n    - This curated list aims to target resource managers and operations personnel specifically.  \n    - Axel Völker noted the importance of tailoring salutations carefully using machine learning to avoid incorrect gender assumptions.  \n    - An intern will support adding salutation data to the contact list for improved personalization.  \n    - Proper personalization is expected to increase email engagement by making messages feel less automated.\n\n- **The ad copy was refined to emphasize managing consulting skills and project staffing over generic terms like “staffing” or “resume,” which risk confusing LinkedIn users** (08:11)  \n    - Axel suggested including terms like “ICT consulting” or “project staffing” to clarify the offering and avoid misinterpretation.  \n    - Colin committed to creating multiple ad headline versions, including a bench-focused ad such as “clearing your bench” to test performance.  \n    - Max and Axel agreed that concise, pain-point-driven headlines targeting the right audience would improve click rates.  \n    - Avoiding terms like “CV” on LinkedIn prevents attracting job seekers instead of managers.\n\n- **The animated video preview featuring the DESI Dolo logo and CTA was approved to move forward with a rough cut to align with existing newsletter branding** (10:55)  \n    - Max confirmed the style aligns with the newsletter’s look, helping brand consistency.  \n    - This video will be embedded on the landing page to increase conversions.\n\n## **Landing Page and Lead Generation**\n\nThe landing page design is underway to highlight multiple core features and improve conversion through layered calls to action.\n\n- **Colin shared that the landing page copy covers six core DESI Dolo offerings such as bench management, RFP handling, and utilization management** (11:11)  \n    - This page will integrate the explainer video to enrich user understanding.  \n    - Axel emphasized that bench management should be clearly featured to align with the campaign’s messaging focus.  \n    - The design is expected to be shared with the team the same day for prompt feedback and iteration.  \n    - The page aims to convert visitors by showcasing the platform’s practical value for consulting firms.\n\n- **Colin proposed lead magnet campaigns featuring interactive forms collecting firm size, utilization, bench size, and skill tracking methods to generate qualified leads** (18:53)  \n    - These forms would redirect to customized landing pages offering IT consulting best practices and benchmark data.  \n    - Axel noted generating an industry benchmark report using internal data combined with AI projections would add credibility and value.  \n    - The approach allows personalized email follow-ups comparing prospects’ current methods with DESI Dolo capabilities.  \n    - Lead gen forms would be promoted via LinkedIn ads targeting relevant personas.\n\n- **Interactive demo tools like Novatic or Storylane were discussed as ways to let users explore the product at their own pace, complementing the explainer video** (20:26)  \n    - Colin highlighted that interactive demos have shown higher success in engagement compared to passive videos.  \n    - Axel prefers explainer videos but agreed a rotation of options could serve different user preferences.  \n    - These demos will showcase key workflows, such as staffing a 20-person project in three weeks, to illustrate use cases.  \n    - Incorporating these tools supports educating prospects and shortening the sales cycle.\n\n## **Personalization and Data Enrichment**\n\nImproving data quality and personalization was prioritized to enhance campaign effectiveness and reduce the appearance of automation.\n\n- **Axel shared that a machine learning model capable of inferring gender from first and last names with high accuracy will be used to enrich salutations** (06:10)  \n    - The model also flags uncertain cases to avoid wrong assumptions.  \n    - Colin agreed to explore combining this ML approach with other language models to improve coverage and accuracy.  \n    - An intern will assist with integrating this data into the contact list.  \n    - Proper salutation personalization is seen as critical for maintaining a professional tone in enterprise outreach.\n\n- **The team acknowledged challenges with incomplete LinkedIn data, such as missing last names, requiring fallback logic using first names only** (07:18)  \n    - Axel pointed out cultural trends in Germany favor using first names in emails, but enterprise contexts still favor full names for formality.  \n    - This balancing act impacts how automated emails are perceived, affecting open and response rates.  \n    - The enrichment effort aims to reduce generic or impersonal greetings that could lower engagement.  \n    - Combining multiple data sources will help mitigate inaccuracies and fill gaps.\n\n## **Ad Design and Creative Direction**\n\nVisual and copy elements of the campaign were carefully reviewed to ensure clarity, relevance, and brand alignment.\n\n- **Colin confirmed the ad designs have been updated based on feedback, especially to avoid generic or misleading imagery and copy** (08:11)  \n    - The “spreadsheet” ad was improved to specifically address managing consulting skills, increasing its direct appeal.  \n    - Axel recommended focusing one ad at least on bench management to differentiate and test messaging effectiveness.  \n    - Max noted that the animation style used in ads is consistent with the newsletter, supporting cohesive branding.  \n    - The team will continue iterating ad copy and visuals to optimize click-through rates and conversions.\n\n- **Concerns were raised about certain terms like “CV” being misinterpreted on LinkedIn, leading to ad copy adjustments** (15:42)  \n    - Axel shared past US campaign learnings where “resume” attracted job seekers rather than managers, informing current choices.  \n    - Colin plans to draft several headline alternatives with clearer, non-technical language to avoid confusion.  \n    - The focus remains on clarity around consulting staffing and project management to attract the right audience.  \n    - This fine-tuning process aims to increase qualified traffic while minimizing wasted impressions.\n\n## **Next Steps and Follow-ups**\n\nThe team aligned on priorities to complete core assets and explore additional campaign ideas post-launch.\n\n- **Colin committed to delivering updated ad copy versions, completing the landing page design, and sharing these materials promptly via SharePoint** (23:02)  \n    - He will also assess salutation enrichment options and coordinate with Axel’s team for data integration.  \n    - The priority is to finalize the current campaign assets before pursuing new lead magnet ideas.  \n    - This staged approach ensures focus on quality before expanding outreach channels.\n\n- **Further ideation on interactive demos and lead magnet campaigns will continue after the initial launch to enhance prospect engagement** (20:12)  \n    - Colin will refine the form questions and landing page content to support personalized nurture sequences.  \n    - Axel stressed the importance of starting with core materials before layering additional complexity.  \n    - This phased rollout balances speed to market with continuous improvement.  \n    - The team agreed to regroup after reviewing initial campaign performance data.","outline":null,"keywords":["Account-Based Marketing","Salutation Personalization","Ad Copy Refinement","Bench Management","Lead Generation Campaign","Explainer Video"],"overview":"- **Campaign Focus:** Emphasize consulting and bench management to boost engagement with resource managers and operations personnel.  \n- **Lead List Update:** ABM contact list now has 514 qualified leads tailored for targeted outreach and personalization.  \n- **Refined Ad Copy:** Focused on project staffing terms, avoiding confusion by replacing generic language like \"CV\" on LinkedIn.  \n- **Landing Page Progress:** Design features six core offerings, integrated explainer video, aimed at increasing visitor conversions.  \n- **Lead Generation Strategy:** Interactive forms to capture firm data, generating qualified leads with personalized follow-up emails.  \n- **Next Steps:** Finalize campaign assets before exploring additional innovations like interactive demos and lead magnets.","action_items":"\n**Colin Costigan**\nDouble-verify and incorporate all edits and comments on the contact list spreadsheet (05:43)\nDevelop and test salutation enrichment combining LLM models to improve gender/format detection and automate adding this info to contact list (07:01)\nUpdate ad copy with revised messaging focusing on bench, consultancy staffing, and avoiding “CV” terminology; send variations to team for review (15:05)\nMove forward with producing the rough cut of the explainer video animation following approved styles (10:18)\nShare landing page design once finished; ensure copy aligns with bench-related messaging (11:11)\nFlesh out and share lead magnet campaign ideas including potential industry benchmark survey questions and nurture flow (18:53)\nUpload all campaign materials, updated contact lists, ad copy, and ideation documents to SharePoint for team access (22:59)\n\n**Axel Völker**\nAssign intern to help automate adding gender-based salutations to the contact list (07:01)\nReview upcoming updated ad copy and landing page designs for bench-specific content (11:59)\nProvide internal data or input towards creating projected benchmark reports for lead magnet campaign (18:53)\n\n**Maximilian Rabeler**\nProvide feedback on ad copy relevance and clarity, focusing on clear, pain-point-driven messaging (13:20)\nCollaborate on ensuring bench-related wording in ads effectively targets correct audience (14:47)\n"},"migrated_from":"contract_meetings","original_id":"875f1da7-4813-4710-b1f8-85af754b5ae5","master_marketer":{"status":"migrated"}}'::jsonb,
