INSERT INTO compass_notes (contract_id, meeting_id, note_type, title, content_raw, note_date, status, action_items, is_auto_generated)
SELECT
  new_meeting.contract_id,
  new_meeting.meeting_id,
  'meeting',
  'Meeting Notes: Data Assessment // MiD: Weekly Marketing Meeting',
  '## **Campaign Strategy and Messaging**

The team agreed to focus campaign messaging more tightly on consulting and bench management to boost relevance and engagement.

- **Colin Costigan confirmed the ABM contact list now includes around 514 qualified leads, updated per Max Rabeler’s feedback** (05:15)  
    - This curated list aims to target resource managers and operations personnel specifically.  
    - Axel Völker noted the importance of tailoring salutations carefully using machine learning to avoid incorrect gender assumptions.  
    - An intern will support adding salutation data to the contact list for improved personalization.  
    - Proper personalization is expected to increase email engagement by making messages feel less automated.

- **The ad copy was refined to emphasize managing consulting skills and project staffing over generic terms like “staffing” or “resume,” which risk confusing LinkedIn users** (08:11)  
    - Axel suggested including terms like “ICT consulting” or “project staffing” to clarify the offering and avoid misinterpretation.  
    - Colin committed to creating multiple ad headline versions, including a bench-focused ad such as “clearing your bench” to test performance.  
    - Max and Axel agreed that concise, pain-point-driven headlines targeting the right audience would improve click rates.  
    - Avoiding terms like “CV” on LinkedIn prevents attracting job seekers instead of managers.

- **The animated video preview featuring the DESI Dolo logo and CTA was approved to move forward with a rough cut to align with existing newsletter branding** (10:55)  
    - Max confirmed the style aligns with the newsletter’s look, helping brand consistency.  
    - This video will be embedded on the landing page to increase conversions.

## **Landing Page and Lead Generation**

The landing page design is underway to highlight multiple core features and improve conversion through layered calls to action.

- **Colin shared that the landing page copy covers six core DESI Dolo offerings such as bench management, RFP handling, and utilization management** (11:11)  
    - This page will integrate the explainer video to enrich user understanding.  
    - Axel emphasized that bench management should be clearly featured to align with the campaign’s messaging focus.  
    - The design is expected to be shared with the team the same day for prompt feedback and iteration.  
    - The page aims to convert visitors by showcasing the platform’s practical value for consulting firms.

- **Colin proposed lead magnet campaigns featuring interactive forms collecting firm size, utilization, bench size, and skill tracking methods to generate qualified leads** (18:53)  
    - These forms would redirect to customized landing pages offering IT consulting best practices and benchmark data.  
    - Axel noted generating an industry benchmark report using internal data combined with AI projections would add credibility and value.  
    - The approach allows personalized email follow-ups comparing prospects’ current methods with DESI Dolo capabilities.  
    - Lead gen forms would be promoted via LinkedIn ads targeting relevant personas.

- **Interactive demo tools like Novatic or Storylane were discussed as ways to let users explore the product at their own pace, complementing the explainer video** (20:26)  
    - Colin highlighted that interactive demos have shown higher success in engagement compared to passive videos.  
    - Axel prefers explainer videos but agreed a rotation of options could serve different user preferences.  
    - These demos will showcase key workflows, such as staffing a 20-person project in three weeks, to illustrate use cases.  
    - Incorporating these tools supports educating prospects and shortening the sales cycle.

## **Personalization and Data Enrichment**

Improving data quality and personalization was prioritized to enhance campaign effectiveness and reduce the appearance of automation.

- **Axel shared that a machine learning model capable of inferring gender from first and last names with high accuracy will be used to enrich salutations** (06:10)  
    - The model also flags uncertain cases to avoid wrong assumptions.  
    - Colin agreed to explore combining this ML approach with other language models to improve coverage and accuracy.  
    - An intern will assist with integrating this data into the contact list.  
    - Proper salutation personalization is seen as critical for maintaining a professional tone in enterprise outreach.

- **The team acknowledged challenges with incomplete LinkedIn data, such as missing last names, requiring fallback logic using first names only** (07:18)  
    - Axel pointed out cultural trends in Germany favor using first names in emails, but enterprise contexts still favor full names for formality.  
    - This balancing act impacts how automated emails are perceived, affecting open and response rates.  
    - The enrichment effort aims to reduce generic or impersonal greetings that could lower engagement.  
    - Combining multiple data sources will help mitigate inaccuracies and fill gaps.

## **Ad Design and Creative Direction**

Visual and copy elements of the campaign were carefully reviewed to ensure clarity, relevance, and brand alignment.

- **Colin confirmed the ad designs have been updated based on feedback, especially to avoid generic or misleading imagery and copy** (08:11)  
    - The “spreadsheet” ad was improved to specifically address managing consulting skills, increasing its direct appeal.  
    - Axel recommended focusing one ad at least on bench management to differentiate and test messaging effectiveness.  
    - Max noted that the animation style used in ads is consistent with the newsletter, supporting cohesive branding.  
    - The team will continue iterating ad copy and visuals to optimize click-through rates and conversions.

- **Concerns were raised about certain terms like “CV” being misinterpreted on LinkedIn, leading to ad copy adjustments** (15:42)  
    - Axel shared past US campaign learnings where “resume” attracted job seekers rather than managers, informing current choices.  
    - Colin plans to draft several headline alternatives with clearer, non-technical language to avoid confusion.  
    - The focus remains on clarity around consulting staffing and project management to attract the right audience.  
    - This fine-tuning process aims to increase qualified traffic while minimizing wasted impressions.

## **Next Steps and Follow-ups**

The team aligned on priorities to complete core assets and explore additional campaign ideas post-launch.

- **Colin committed to delivering updated ad copy versions, completing the landing page design, and sharing these materials promptly via SharePoint** (23:02)  
    - He will also assess salutation enrichment options and coordinate with Axel’s team for data integration.  
    - The priority is to finalize the current campaign assets before pursuing new lead magnet ideas.  
    - This staged approach ensures focus on quality before expanding outreach channels.

- **Further ideation on interactive demos and lead magnet campaigns will continue after the initial launch to enhance prospect engagement** (20:12)  
    - Colin will refine the form questions and landing page content to support personalized nurture sequences.  
    - Axel stressed the importance of starting with core materials before layering additional complexity.  
    - This phased rollout balances speed to market with continuous improvement.  
    - The team agreed to regroup after reviewing initial campaign performance data.',
  '2026-01-16 13:30:00+00',
  'published',
  '[{"text":"Double-verify and incorporate all edits and comments on the contact list spreadsheet (05:43)","completed":false},{"text":"Develop and test salutation enrichment combining LLM models to improve gender/format detection and automate adding this info to contact list (07:01)","completed":false},{"text":"Update ad copy with revised messaging focusing on bench, consultancy staffing, and avoiding “CV” terminology; send variations to team for review (15:05)","completed":false},{"text":"Move forward with producing the rough cut of the explainer video animation following approved styles (10:18)","completed":false},{"text":"Share landing page design once finished; ensure copy aligns with bench-related messaging (11:11)","completed":false},{"text":"Flesh out and share lead magnet campaign ideas including potential industry benchmark survey questions and nurture flow (18:53)","completed":false},{"text":"Upload all campaign materials, updated contact lists, ad copy, and ideation documents to SharePoint for team access (22:59)","completed":false},{"text":"Assign intern to help automate adding gender-based salutations to the contact list (07:01)","completed":false},{"text":"Review upcoming updated ad copy and landing page designs for bench-specific content (11:59)","completed":false},{"text":"Provide internal data or input towards creating projected benchmark reports for lead magnet campaign (18:53)","completed":false},{"text":"Provide feedback on ad copy relevance and clarity, focusing on clear, pain-point-driven messaging (13:20)","completed":false},{"text":"Collaborate on ensuring bench-related wording in ads effectively targets correct audience (14:47)","completed":false}]'::jsonb,
