-- Meeting: PTO Exchange // New North Weekly Meeting (2026-01-15 18:30:00+00)
WITH new_meeting AS (
  INSERT INTO compass_meetings (contract_id, meeting_date, source, external_id, title, participants, duration_seconds, recording_url, transcript, sentiment, raw_metadata, created_at, updated_at)
  VALUES (
    '3f032f15-833e-4d7d-9347-381febf6d953',
    '2026-01-15 18:30:00+00',
    'fireflies',
    '01KEFG96F9CJHGDFRR2J176E85',
    'PTO Exchange // New North Weekly Meeting',
    '{"Nina Belina","Colin Costigan","Josh Reinhard","Colin Costigan"}'::text[],
    2041,
    'https://us02web.zoom.us/j/87477024015?pwd=gVpnKPDuNsoZ0giaFoA7gicVcI6afV.1',
    '{"id":"01KEFG96F9CJHGDFRR2J176E85","title":"PTO Exchange // New North Weekly Meeting","summary":{"notes":"## **Campaign Strategy and Messaging**\n\nThe team agreed to rapidly launch at least two new campaign ideas focused on clear, measurable business impacts.\n\n- **Colin Costigan and Josh Reinhard decided to prioritize a campaign highlighting accrued paid time off (PTO) as a financial liability potentially worth millions, aiming to convert interest into first meetings rather than complex online tools** (14:53)  \n    - The campaign will feature a high-level PTO liability calculator requiring just **three data points**: employee headcount, average accrual rate, and average pay rate, providing a rough estimate of liabilities.  \n    - Josh emphasized the tool must be simple to avoid gating prospects and to build credibility through a meeting, enabling deeper insight gathering later.  \n    - The messaging will include a call to action encouraging prospects to book a meeting for customized analysis based on anonymized data and projections.  \n    - This approach targets organizations unaware of their PTO liability, acknowledging that many finance teams already track this metric.  \n\n- **A multi-generational workforce campaign will address PTO offerings tailored to diverse employee needs, using industry playbooks and LinkedIn ads to drive lead form fills and nurture sequences** (21:29)  \n    - Josh and Colin plan to leverage existing survey data showing different PTO preferences by age group to substantiate campaign messaging.  \n    - This campaign aims to close benefit gaps and expand PTO flexibility, appealing broadly across industries.  \n    - The team will incorporate charts and raw survey data from the “Time to Rethink PTO” report to back messaging and target specific age groups effectively.  \n    - LinkedIn ads will serve as the primary lead generation channel, funneling prospects into nurture sequences designed to push first meetings.  \n\n- **A healthcare industry campaign will focus on preventing burnout by promoting flexible PTO policies as a key benefit, tailored to healthcare workers’ financial and personal needs** (26:32)  \n    - The campaign will highlight burnout issues among nurses, doctors, and surgeons, emphasizing PTO flexibility to improve employee retention and engagement.  \n    - Colin confirmed content creation will be supported by curated external articles and internal research fed into AI tools for efficient campaign development.  \n    - Josh will add Colin to the internal Slack curated content channel to ensure timely access to relevant articles, supporting rapid content updates during the first two quarters.  \n    - This campaign is positioned to preempt union negotiations and improve employee relations as a competitive differentiator in healthcare staffing.  \n\n- **The team aims to build a 2026 employee benchmark report focused on PTO policy choices using internal data and research rather than costly external surveys** (28:54)  \n    - Colin proposed starting with a content framework and mockup webpage similar to past benchmark reports to generate ideas and structure.  \n    - Josh confirmed this approach is more feasible than previous attempts that relied on external partnerships and surveys.  \n    - The report will serve as an industry-agnostic “State of Employee” insight tool to drive awareness and position the company as a thought leader.  \n    - This benchmark will support long-term engagement and content strategy aligned with evolving employee benefit trends.  \n\n## **Sales Workflow and Lead Management**\n\nThe team refined lead routing, status tracking, and sales sequence strategies to improve efficiency and conversion clarity.\n\n- **Colin created a comprehensive workflow cheat sheet detailing current lead sources, next steps, and routing by industry to streamline sales activities** (08:57)  \n    - The document includes an overview of territories, tools, and a table of contents for quick lookup of actions by lead source (demo requests, benchmark reports, LinkedIn, ads).  \n    - Colin recommended a follow-up cadence of **two to four touches over two weeks** before moving leads to nurture sequences based on lead status changes.  \n    - Sales reps will classify leads by industry to assign them to corresponding nurture sequences, simplifying sales team workload.  \n    - The cheat sheet will remain a living document, updated as new campaigns and sequences roll out.  \n\n- **Lead status and lifecycle stage distinctions were clarified to improve qualification and nurturing** (11:42)  \n    - Josh sought clarity on when to update lifecycle stages versus lead status; Colin explained leads enter as “Lead,” move to “Marketing Qualified Lead” (MQL), then “Sales Qualified Lead” (SQL).  \n    - Lead status (e.g., cold, nurture) signals engagement level within a lifecycle stage and triggers enrollment into industry-specific nurture sequences.  \n    - Colin agreed to include lifecycle stage update instructions in the cheat sheet to reduce confusion and ensure consistent lead handling.  \n    - The sales team will continue to manually update lifecycle stages and lead statuses until the HubSpot audit recommends automation.  \n\n- **Current inbound lead handling will continue as usual until new sequences launch, targeted for early February** (32:43)  \n    - Colin estimated that new email sequences and industry-specific nurture flows will go live at the **start of February**, allowing a transition period of several weeks.  \n    - The cheat sheet will be updated continuously to reflect new workflows and sequence assignments during this interim.  \n    - Josh confirmed no changes to team expansion or contract status, with new team members fully onboarded to support upcoming initiatives.  \n\n## **HubSpot Audit and System Improvements**\n\nThe team committed to a thorough HubSpot audit to clean up workflows and improve campaign execution.\n\n- **A full HubSpot audit is underway, with a target to complete and review recommendations by next week** (30:53)  \n    - The audit will identify obsolete sequences and workflows, enabling the team to discard ineffective processes per feedback from Steph and Dan.  \n    - Post-audit, the team will clean up HubSpot records and implement updated routing and nurture sequences aligned with new campaign strategies.  \n    - Colin will share pages requiring review and incorporate feedback into the audit deliverables for transparency and collaboration.  \n    - The audit is critical to support scalability as new campaigns and sequences launch in early 2024.  \n\n- **Workflow improvements include routing leads into industry-specific sequences based on lead status and enabling sales teams to track engagement via updated fields** (10:53)  \n    - The team plans to add a “cold” lead status option and use lead status to trigger nurture enrollment automatically.  \n    - Colin emphasized the importance of making processes easy for sales reps to minimize manual errors and improve follow-up consistency.  \n    - The updated cheat sheet will clearly explain these workflow changes, lifecycle stage updates, and lead status usage to ensure smooth adoption.  \n    - These system improvements support better measurement of lead engagement and campaign effectiveness.  \n\n## **Team Coordination and Scheduling**\n\nThe team synchronized calendars and communication channels to maintain momentum on deliverables.\n\n- **Colin rescheduled the next meeting to Tuesday at 2:00pm Eastern to accommodate an upcoming day out of office** (31:35)  \n    - Josh confirmed the new meeting time works well for his schedule.  \n    - The team will maintain the usual Thursday meeting as a backup or follow-up session.  \n\n- **Josh confirmed the team expansion contract was fully executed during the call, ensuring resource availability** (33:00)  \n    - This update confirms readiness for increased workload from new campaign launches and HubSpot cleanup.  \n\n- **Colin and Josh agreed to use Slack for sharing curated content to support timely campaign content creation** (27:20)  \n    - Josh will grant Colin access to the internal curated content Slack channel for relevant articles and research.  \n    - This will help Colin feed fresh insights into AI-assisted content generation and maintain responsiveness to market trends.  \n\n## **Content Creation and Research Integration**\n\nThe team leveraged internal and external data sources to inform campaign messaging and content accuracy.\n\n- **Colin uses a dedicated ChatGPT project folder to consolidate PTO Exchange research and content for campaign writing** (27:00)  \n    - This approach blends AI support with curated research articles to speed content development without sacrificing quality.  \n    - Josh emphasized feeding relevant Slack channel content directly to Colin to keep campaigns timely and relevant.  \n\n- **Existing survey data from the “Time to Rethink PTO” report will provide detailed employee age group preferences to tailor messaging** (22:00)  \n    - Josh highlighted that employees near retirement are four times more likely than younger groups to prefer certain PTO uses, supporting targeted communication.  \n    - Raw data access allows the team to create nuanced campaign segments that reflect real employee benefit interests.  \n\n- **Industry-specific playbooks will be developed using research data and external articles to support campaign claims and value propositions** (21:51)  \n    - These playbooks will guide LinkedIn ad targeting and nurture sequences with credible, data-backed messaging.  \n    - The healthcare burnout campaign will specifically use data on financial pressures and burnout to frame PTO flexibility as a retention tool.  \n    - Ongoing content updates will incorporate market news such as union strikes to maintain relevance and urgency in messaging.  ","outline":null,"keywords":["PTO liability","HubSpot workflow","campaign strategy","multigenerational workforce","healthcare burnout","benchmark report"],"overview":"- **Campaign Launch:** Two campaigns will focus on PTO financial liability and multi-generational workforce needs to drive leads.  \n- **Healthcare Focus:** Campaign to highlight flexible PTO as a retention tool for healthcare workers facing burnout issues.  \n- **Employee Benchmark Report:** The team will create a 2026 PTO policy report using internal data for industry insights and engagement.  \n- **Lead Management Refined:** New workflows and lead status tracking to enhance sales efficiency, launching updated sequences in early February.  \n- **HubSpot Audit:** Comprehensive audit to clean obsolete workflows and improve campaign execution, with findings to guide upcoming changes.  \n- **Content Strategy:** Utilize research data to tailor campaign messaging and ensure timely content creation for audience relevance.","action_items":"\n**Colin Costigan**\nUpdate workflow cheat sheet with lead status and life cycle stage instructions for sales team (11:50)\nDraft new email nurture sequences aligned to four initial industry campaigns (13:40)\nBuild and finalize PTO financial liability calculator content and integration for campaign #1 (16:00)\nIncorporate ''Time to Rethink PTO'' report data into campaign messaging for multigenerational workforce playbook (22:00)\nContinue collecting and integrating curated content into Slack for campaign development (27:30)\nDevelop content framework for 2026 benchmark report using internal data and research (30:15)\nPrepare HubSpot audit report for next week’s review (30:00)\nSchedule next weekly meeting for Tuesday 2:00 pm Eastern (31:35)\nRefine and maintain the workflow cheat sheet as a living document for sales and marketing teams (32:00)\n\n**Josh Reinhard**\nProvide additional curated content articles and reports into Slack channel for campaign support (27:00)\nShare raw data behind PTO employee preference surveys to aid in targeted messaging (24:56)\nContinue normal sales follow-up on inbound leads until new sequences launch (32:28)\nConfirm and update team DocuSign signatures for expansion executed during the meeting (33:00)\n"},"duration":34.02000045776367,"speakers":[{"id":0,"name":"Nina Belina"},{"id":1,"name":"Colin Costigan"},{"id":2,"name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"id":3,"name":"Colin Costigan"}],"sentences":[{"text":"Hi, Colin.","index":0,"end_time":276.02,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":275.22,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"How''s it going?","index":1,"end_time":277.7,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":276.98,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Sorry, I didn''t even notice you guys were there.","index":2,"end_time":279.78,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":278.02,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We just went from one meeting to the next, and then another one.","index":3,"end_time":285.15,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":281.31,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"Rules.","index":4,"end_time":288.19,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":287.55,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I almost fell asleep, Ric.","index":5,"end_time":296.35,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":292.27,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"Hey, what''s up, Collins?","index":6,"end_time":309.12,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":307.88,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"How''s it going, Josh?","index":7,"end_time":310.12,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":309.12,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Good.","index":8,"end_time":310.68,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":310.36,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"How you doing?","index":9,"end_time":311.24,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":310.68,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Doing all right.","index":10,"end_time":312.52,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":311.64,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"How about yourself, Cameron?","index":11,"end_time":314.76,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":313.24,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Good.","index":12,"end_time":315.56,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":315.16,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":13,"end_time":317.64,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":317,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I guess you''re on today''s call.","index":14,"end_time":321.72,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":319.32,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"What''s that?","index":15,"end_time":322.88,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":322.279,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I said we got a new face on today''s call.","index":16,"end_time":324.84,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":322.88,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":17,"end_time":325.24,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":324.92,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Have you not met Natalie yet?","index":18,"end_time":326.76,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":325.24,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I don''t know if we''ve met.","index":19,"end_time":327.56,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":326.76,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Maybe we have.","index":20,"end_time":328.24,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":327.56,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"I don''t think so.","index":21,"end_time":329.08,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":328.24,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Well, then we should definitely start with an introduction.","index":22,"end_time":330.88,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":329.16,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":23,"end_time":331.12,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":330.88,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Natalie is another strategist here on our team.","index":24,"end_time":333.48,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":331.12,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I wanted to bring her on for.","index":25,"end_time":334.84,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":333.48,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Extra support as we''re.","index":26,"end_time":336.68,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":335.16,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We''re going to talk through some standing.","index":27,"end_time":338.18,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":337.06,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Up, some more campaigns and everything today.","index":28,"end_time":339.58,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":338.18,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But, Natalie, I''ll let you introduce yourself.","index":29,"end_time":341.78,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":339.58,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, like Colin said, I''m another strategist.","index":30,"end_time":345.54,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":342.66,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"I''ve been reviewing your account, and I''m excited to work together.","index":31,"end_time":348.26,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":345.54,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":32,"end_time":349.38,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":348.74,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Me too.","index":33,"end_time":350.3,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":349.78,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"And Natalie''s in.","index":34,"end_time":352.1,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":350.3,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Hi.","index":35,"end_time":352.98,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":352.5,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"Natalie''s based in Chicago.","index":36,"end_time":355.46,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":353.94,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But, Natalie, you''re going back to Hong Kong to work from there at the end of the month.","index":37,"end_time":359.9,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":355.46,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You said correct?","index":38,"end_time":361.22,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":359.9,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":39,"end_time":361.82,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":361.46,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Oh, nice.","index":40,"end_time":362.42,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":361.82,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Have you lived there before?","index":41,"end_time":363.63,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":362.75,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Have I?","index":42,"end_time":365.79,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":365.23,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"Yeah, I grew up there and then came to the States for college.","index":43,"end_time":369.55,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":365.79,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"But since I''m remote, I try to go back as much as possible and work from there.","index":44,"end_time":374.27,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":369.55,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"Nice.","index":45,"end_time":375.15,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":374.67,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, one of my very good friends moved there, what was supposed to be temporarily, and now he''s been there for, like, 15 years, and I don''t think he''s ever leaving.","index":46,"end_time":384.59,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":375.39,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Yeah, it''s a great city.","index":47,"end_time":385.95,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":384.83,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"All right.","index":48,"end_time":389.08,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":388.84,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Well, I know we got a lot.","index":49,"end_time":389.96,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":389.08,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Also a Commander''s fan, Colin, this guy.","index":50,"end_time":392.24,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":389.96,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Oh, I don''t know how many Commanders fans there are.","index":51,"end_time":394.36,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":392.24,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"They must be a great guy.","index":52,"end_time":395.4,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":394.36,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, great guy also.","index":53,"end_time":396.8,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":395.56,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Red hair, too, and he''s like your doppelganger.","index":54,"end_time":400.04,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":396.8,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":55,"end_time":400.32,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":400.04,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It''s a match made in heaven, Josh.","index":56,"end_time":401.52,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":400.32,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":57,"end_time":401.76,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":401.52,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"You got good friends.","index":58,"end_time":402.52,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":401.76,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That''s right.","index":59,"end_time":403.4,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":402.68,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":60,"end_time":404.68,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":404.119,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Well, yeah, I know.","index":61,"end_time":405.48,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":404.68,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I was gonna say, probably meekly looking at the NFL schedule this weekend of like.","index":62,"end_time":409.96,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":405.48,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right, I guess I can watch that game.","index":63,"end_time":411.4,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":409.96,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, Yeah, I can watch any game.","index":64,"end_time":415.64,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":412.6,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Get enough money on it.","index":65,"end_time":416.56,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":415.64,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"You can watch any game.","index":66,"end_time":417.32,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":416.56,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Right, Exactly.","index":67,"end_time":418.36,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":417.32,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That''s what makes it interesting now when.","index":68,"end_time":419.88,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":418.52,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Your team''s not in it.","index":69,"end_time":420.92,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":419.88,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Exactly.","index":70,"end_time":422.72,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":422.12,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Well, I still got.","index":71,"end_time":423.4,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":422.72,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"My wife''s a huge Seahawks fan, so now I''m like, you know, jumping on the bandwagon.","index":72,"end_time":427.76,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":423.4,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"You know, people undervalue Sam Darnold.","index":73,"end_time":429.68,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":427.76,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I''ve always, you know, I think he.","index":74,"end_time":432.08,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":429.68,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"He has talent.","index":75,"end_time":432.84,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":432.08,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I just, he''s won 26 games in the last two regular seasons.","index":76,"end_time":436.6,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":432.84,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"No one here believes in him, which is really funny because they''re the number one seed.","index":77,"end_time":440.76,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":437.4,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Just crazy.","index":78,"end_time":441.89,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":441.01,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right, well, we got a lot to go through today, so I''ll hop right into it.","index":79,"end_time":447.73,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":443.09,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We did.","index":80,"end_time":448.77,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":448.21,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"For the links that we sent over.","index":81,"end_time":451.37,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":450.21,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We did update the Slack message, so all those links should point to the correct pages now.","index":82,"end_time":456.21,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":451.37,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You updated the old Slack message?","index":83,"end_time":459.09,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":457.33,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Yeah, the one that Nina had sent.","index":84,"end_time":460.61,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":459.09,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, perfect.","index":85,"end_time":461.57,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":460.77,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Okay, awesome.","index":86,"end_time":465.33,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":464.37,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"We''ll get on that.","index":87,"end_time":466.77,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":465.57,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Perfect.","index":88,"end_time":467.57,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":467.17,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then I just wanted to touch base.","index":89,"end_time":469.09,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":467.81,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We sent over, like, the slide deck.","index":90,"end_time":470.25,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":469.09,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"A few weeks ago, and I never.","index":91,"end_time":471.45,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":470.25,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Heard any feedback on it, so I.","index":92,"end_time":472.45,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":471.45,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Just wanted to touch base on that.","index":93,"end_time":473.65,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":472.45,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, I.","index":94,"end_time":475.41,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":474.37,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"We.","index":95,"end_time":476.69,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":476.29,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Dave and I looked at it.","index":96,"end_time":478.17,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":477.09,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"We.","index":97,"end_time":478.45,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":478.17,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"We have a lot of feedback on it, so I don''t.","index":98,"end_time":480.93,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":478.53,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"So we just kind of put that on the back burner for now.","index":99,"end_time":483.89,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":481.01,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"I think, you know, part of it is like, it''s so drastically different from what we were doing currently that it was like a little bit of, you know, shock.","index":100,"end_time":492.21,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":483.89,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"So I, I think for now we''re going to keep that on the back burner because we got so much other stuff that we want to work on.","index":101,"end_time":500.08,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":494.24,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"But I think some of the parts of it were, were really good.","index":102,"end_time":503.88,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":500.08,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"I think some of it kind of missed the mark and it was just like, again, just like not the priority for us now.","index":103,"end_time":510.08,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":503.88,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Yeah, I don''t know what.","index":104,"end_time":511.28,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":510.16,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"I don''t know what we were expecting or if we even have expectations, but like, we''re just want to focus on some of the other stuff and then.","index":105,"end_time":518.24,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":511.52,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Yeah, take that as it comes.","index":106,"end_time":519.97,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":518.24,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"If you don''t.","index":107,"end_time":520.53,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":519.97,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Okay, yeah, no problem at all.","index":108,"end_time":521.85,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":520.53,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Totally hear you.","index":109,"end_time":522.57,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":521.85,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Cool.","index":110,"end_time":523.85,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":523.45,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then a couple other things that I have updates on is I''ve created.","index":111,"end_time":526.57,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":523.85,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"The cheat sheet for workflows as they currently exist for activities that we are doing.","index":112,"end_time":531.13,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":526.57,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So I''ll walk through that just real quickly here.","index":113,"end_time":533.93,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":531.77,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Starts out with an overview how territories.","index":114,"end_time":536.41,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":534.17,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Work and then the tools that are at play.","index":115,"end_time":537.97,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":536.41,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Then I just have a table of contents in here for, like, easy access.","index":116,"end_time":541.29,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":537.97,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Anyone can go like, oh, I see this person requested a demo.","index":117,"end_time":544.57,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":541.37,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Like, how did that come in?","index":118,"end_time":545.61,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":544.57,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"What should I do?","index":119,"end_time":546.37,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":545.61,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Or they submitted the benchmark report, or it was through LinkedIn or an ad.","index":120,"end_time":550.64,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":546.37,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So all of that''s broken down in.","index":121,"end_time":552.39,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":551.19,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Here as to, you know, what steps they should take, how the source is coming in, everything like that.","index":122,"end_time":559.03,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":552.39,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then does it have a link?","index":123,"end_time":564.31,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":562.79,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Like, is there a sequence that we''re pointing them to?","index":124,"end_time":568.71,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":564.47,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"So that''s, that''s the, the additional part that I''m Working on, because we talked on Monday about kind of throwing out.","index":125,"end_time":574.59,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":569.35,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All of the existing sequences was the feedback that Steph and Dan gave.","index":126,"end_time":577.99,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":574.59,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So that leads to us writing new sequences.","index":127,"end_time":581.97,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":578.85,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Now we have a new 11 new industry pages that we''ve created.","index":128,"end_time":585.33,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":582.45,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But on Monday, you alluded to four main industry sequences that you wanted to start with.","index":129,"end_time":591.21,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":585.33,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Is that like, is that finance and healthcare manufacturing?","index":130,"end_time":596.21,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":591.21,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"The four that we typically say are healthcare, finance, nonprofit and professional services.","index":131,"end_time":605.72,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":598.45,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Okay.","index":132,"end_time":606.6,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":606.04,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But I like that we also have a manufacturing and a higher.","index":133,"end_time":612.12,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":608.44,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Higher ed one because we''re starting to see more success, especially at higher ed.","index":134,"end_time":617.96,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":612.2,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"So I think we want to position ourselves like that''s going to be the fifth one.","index":135,"end_time":622,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":618.12,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"And I would say manufacturing would then be the sixth one.","index":136,"end_time":624.52,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":622,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"But trying to think if we have like enough social proof, we probably have enough social proof to be able to do anything.","index":137,"end_time":635.1,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":626.68,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Extend those out also and then having like an other.","index":138,"end_time":638.34,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":635.1,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Like more generic.","index":139,"end_time":641.06,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":640.1,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":140,"end_time":641.54,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":641.06,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So, so what if we start with those four as the primary, like test guinea pigs and then we just add on as we go.","index":141,"end_time":648.74,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":642.58,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And the way that I look at this document is it''s not like a set in stone.","index":142,"end_time":652.1,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":649.38,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"This is a living document that we will update as we have those campaigns built out.","index":143,"end_time":656.9,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":652.1,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, great.","index":144,"end_time":659.72,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":658.92,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But we do have like, so in here.","index":145,"end_time":661.24,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":659.72,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You know, based on our conversation, I''ve made a recommendation for Dan and Steph to follow up like two to four times over the course of two weeks to see if they can get a.","index":146,"end_time":669.2,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":661.24,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Response and then utilize the lead status.","index":147,"end_time":672.04,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":669.2,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Property to say like, hey, this has.","index":148,"end_time":673.84,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":672.04,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Gone cold, or this person''s not responding to me.","index":149,"end_time":675.84,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":673.84,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And that would be our trigger to.","index":150,"end_time":677.12,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":675.84,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Enroll them into their industry specific nurture sequence.","index":151,"end_time":680.04,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":677.12,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"This is for like, for basically any sequence that we''re putting them in.","index":152,"end_time":685.32,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":681.96,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":153,"end_time":686.07,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":685.79,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":154,"end_time":686.59,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":686.07,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":155,"end_time":687.47,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":686.83,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we would set up the routing to like, based on their industry.","index":156,"end_time":690.03,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":687.55,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"They would go into X sequence.","index":157,"end_time":692.35,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":690.11,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So try to make it as easy on the sales team as possible.","index":158,"end_time":695.11,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":692.75,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That all they would have to do.","index":159,"end_time":696.03,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":695.11,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Is change lead status to.","index":160,"end_time":697.39,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":696.03,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And we can just add a field for cold.","index":161,"end_time":699.39,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":697.47,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":162,"end_time":700.27,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":699.79,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"And then are they changing the lead status?","index":163,"end_time":703.39,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":700.27,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"One of the things that I was always a little bit unclear of and what, what Sam was saying, but like, if someone comes in to the.","index":164,"end_time":712.43,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":705.47,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"You.","index":165,"end_time":714.67,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":714.59,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Know, accepts our LinkedIn requests and now we''re putting them.","index":166,"end_time":717.07,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":714.67,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"And I don''t know where that fits.","index":167,"end_time":718.51,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":717.07,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"I guess number three.","index":168,"end_time":719.79,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":718.67,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Yep.","index":169,"end_time":720.43,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":719.87,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Are we changing their lead status immediately from whatever it is to like marketing qualified lead or sales qualified lead?","index":170,"end_time":730.109,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":721.39,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"So that''s actually life cycle stage or life cycle stage.","index":171,"end_time":733.55,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":730.75,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":172,"end_time":733.91,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":733.55,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":173,"end_time":734.35,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":733.91,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So on life cycle stage, they come.","index":174,"end_time":736.15,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":734.43,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"In as a Lead.","index":175,"end_time":736.83,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":736.15,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":176,"end_time":737.79,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":737.23,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"And then yeah, it would be on.","index":177,"end_time":739.71,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":738.27,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"The sales team to change them to a sales qualified lead.","index":178,"end_time":742.38,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":739.71,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We can have them come in as.","index":179,"end_time":743.26,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":742.38,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Marketing qualified lead right away, we can change that.","index":180,"end_time":746.06,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":743.26,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But from there the lead status would be the biggest indicator because lifecycle stage, you don''t typically move backwards.","index":181,"end_time":753.66,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":747.5,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Like you wouldn''t say they''re a sales.","index":182,"end_time":755.22,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":753.9,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Qualified lead and now they''re just a lead.","index":183,"end_time":756.94,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":755.22,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But if you have a sales qualified.","index":184,"end_time":759.3,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":757.82,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Lead and their lead status is like cold or nurture, then we know like.","index":185,"end_time":764.06,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":759.3,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, they weren''t responding to the sales team.","index":186,"end_time":765.82,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":764.06,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Let''s enroll them in some educational content that''s going to drip out over the course of, you know, know, weeks.","index":187,"end_time":770.15,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":765.82,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":188,"end_time":771.27,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":770.71,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Now I know ultimately we''re going to be doing like a full, you guys are looking like a whole HubSpot audit here.","index":189,"end_time":777.27,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":772.23,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"But if there is something like that that they should do is change the life cycle stage from lead to either marketing qualified lead or sales qualified lead.","index":190,"end_time":785.19,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":777.27,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"If you can have that in these instructions also.","index":191,"end_time":787.71,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":785.589,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"So just like, yep, here''s everything that you do.","index":192,"end_time":790.15,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":787.71,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Yeah, that, that would be great.","index":193,"end_time":792.07,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":790.39,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Yep, no problem.","index":194,"end_time":792.95,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":792.07,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Cool.","index":195,"end_time":794.75,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":794.31,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And if, honestly if, like, if you don''t think we''re going to use that field anymore, then we''re gonna, we''re gonna use it.","index":196,"end_time":803.37,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":794.75,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Yeah, they''re very, very mission critical to HubSpot.","index":197,"end_time":806.57,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":803.37,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, awesome.","index":198,"end_time":808.65,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":806.57,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then a few other things that we''re working on.","index":199,"end_time":811.49,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":808.81,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we''ll draft the, the email sequences there.","index":200,"end_time":813.53,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":811.49,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And I''ve kind of laid out what that strategy is going to look like of sending them an email roughly every.","index":201,"end_time":818.65,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":814.49,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Eight to 10 days so that it''s.","index":202,"end_time":821.37,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":818.97,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Enough to stay like in front of.","index":203,"end_time":823.04,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":821.37,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Them but not overwhelm them to the point that they''re unsubscribing on the drip.","index":204,"end_time":826.56,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":823.04,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Side, the nurture side.","index":205,"end_time":827.6,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":826.56,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, but I know, but on the initial campaign it''s like four touches in.","index":206,"end_time":833.08,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":828,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Like a two week span from the sales team.","index":207,"end_time":835.6,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":833.08,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":208,"end_time":836,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":835.6,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"And then some LinkedIn mixed in.","index":209,"end_time":838,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":836,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah.","index":210,"end_time":839.12,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":838.4,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So I made a recommendation that, that the sales team in the document, I recommend that the sales team should reach.","index":211,"end_time":843.56,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":839.36,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Out via LinkedIn and email.","index":212,"end_time":844.88,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":843.56,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, perfect.","index":213,"end_time":846.56,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":845.36,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I mean that''s typically how our sequences are set.","index":214,"end_time":848.96,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":846.72,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Where it''s like you initially send an email, I think you do a LinkedIn connection, you send another email.","index":215,"end_time":855.69,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":848.96,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"If they connected with you, you''re doing something on LinkedIn and there''s two more emails.","index":216,"end_time":860.53,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":856.49,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"But as long as we know like what the steps are, then.","index":217,"end_time":862.57,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":860.53,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Okay, cool.","index":218,"end_time":864.33,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":863.53,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then the big thing that I want to take the bulk of our time to talk through is we laid out some new campaign Ideas and I.","index":219,"end_time":871.21,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":864.73,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Want to honestly get at least two or three of these in motion very quickly.","index":220,"end_time":875.45,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":871.21,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So one of these, I don''t want to say it''s like a fear angle, but really harping on the like the financial liability.","index":221,"end_time":883.03,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":876.01,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I mean we''ve talked about the PTO.","index":222,"end_time":885.11,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":883.03,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Time bomb before, but I think really hammering in with a message of, you know, your accrued paid time off isn''t just time off, it''s actually millions in.","index":223,"end_time":893.71,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":885.11,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Unsecured debt that''s sitting in your books.","index":224,"end_time":895.75,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":893.71,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Really trying to, especially in this time period when people are looking at their.","index":225,"end_time":900.95,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":896.47,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Benefit solutions and where their financial liability may sit with these types of things.","index":226,"end_time":905.19,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":900.95,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Having some sort of like exposure assessment.","index":227,"end_time":908.55,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":905.91,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That we can tie on to this.","index":228,"end_time":910.07,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":908.87,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And I know that you guys have your spreadsheet calculator where you''re kind of, you know, going through that or someone.","index":229,"end_time":914.79,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":910.15,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Provides you with some anonymized data.","index":230,"end_time":917.67,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":914.79,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"What we really want to push here.","index":231,"end_time":919.39,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":918.07,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Is that first meeting.","index":232,"end_time":920.19,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":919.39,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So heard Rob clearly heard you clearly really push for that first meeting.","index":233,"end_time":923.83,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":920.19,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So I''m not.","index":234,"end_time":924.79,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":924.15,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I don''t think that we need a.","index":235,"end_time":927.23,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":924.87,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Really in depth like method for someone.","index":236,"end_time":929.19,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":927.23,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"To do anything on the website.","index":237,"end_time":930.39,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":929.19,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I think we can have like maybe a high level calculator but really push them towards booking that first meeting to get the in depth insights.","index":238,"end_time":937.77,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":930.39,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":239,"end_time":939.17,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":938.73,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yep.","index":240,"end_time":939.61,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":939.17,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"We, we toyed around with the idea of like could we do something where they''re inputting information.","index":241,"end_time":945.53,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":940.01,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"It''s just to have it be something that''s meaningful.","index":242,"end_time":949.37,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":945.61,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"It''s so much information that they would need to put in that it''s like a gate that just would never happen.","index":243,"end_time":954.09,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":949.37,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":244,"end_time":954.77,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":954.33,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we''re trying to think of like.","index":245,"end_time":955.85,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":954.77,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Them to get us to meet with us and then we can get some credibility, we can get some trust from them and then they''ll send us the information so we put together.","index":246,"end_time":963.93,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":956.09,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Right.","index":247,"end_time":964.5,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":964.3,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So what do you think are like the two, three, four things that they would have like on hand and just.","index":248,"end_time":969.82,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":964.5,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Like, yeah, I can toss this into a calculator or some type of tool.","index":249,"end_time":973.74,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":969.82,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That would also benefit you guys for the, the first meeting where you can.","index":250,"end_time":977.38,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":974.38,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Come in with some more insight.","index":251,"end_time":978.62,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":977.38,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Could even be like employee headcount and range of tenure of employees.","index":252,"end_time":993.23,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":987.34,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It would need to be head employee headcount.","index":253,"end_time":997.47,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":994.35,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"It would need to be like.","index":254,"end_time":999.39,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":998.03,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Trying.","index":255,"end_time":1002.71,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1002.43,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"To think if they gave employ headcount average like average accrual rate and average pay rate.","index":256,"end_time":1012.91,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1002.71,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"We could then say okay, their total like based on our book of business, we could probably say like their average.","index":257,"end_time":1028.87,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1014.03,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"The average employee accrues 200 hours.","index":258,"end_time":1033.35,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1031.19,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"I think we could probably look at our Data and say that probably means that the average employee balance today is like 110 hours.","index":259,"end_time":1041.67,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1034.07,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"And if it was 240 hours that they accrue, their average employee probably has about 130 hours now or like whatever.","index":260,"end_time":1049.19,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1042.07,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"I would have to look at our data warehouse and see what it is.","index":261,"end_time":1051.91,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1049.59,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"But I think if they plug those three things in, we could say our projection is that you''re sitting on this much liability.","index":262,"end_time":1058.47,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1051.91,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Right.","index":263,"end_time":1059.11,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1058.71,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I think that would be fairly like close enough that if someone''s only putting three data points in.","index":264,"end_time":1067.99,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1060.47,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Yeah, it''s a projection.","index":265,"end_time":1069.22,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1068.3,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Right?","index":266,"end_time":1069.5,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1069.22,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":267,"end_time":1070.1,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1069.74,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"They can''t expect that to be like, you know, truth.","index":268,"end_time":1072.94,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1070.1,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Right.","index":269,"end_time":1073.18,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1072.94,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Or like the, the, the gospel there.","index":270,"end_time":1075.18,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1073.18,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But I think that''s enticing.","index":271,"end_time":1077.42,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1075.9,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"The only, the only problem with that is that if we''re way off, a lot of like good organizations know absolutely what their PTO liability is because it''s a number that there''s finance folks are talking to them a lot about.","index":272,"end_time":1094.14,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1077.74,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"So this would more be for people that, that don''t really know that.","index":273,"end_time":1097.98,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1094.86,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Well, it could give an option.","index":274,"end_time":1100.38,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1099.34,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You know, it could be a tree branch of like, do you know your PTO liability?","index":275,"end_time":1103.5,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1100.38,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Plug it in here.","index":276,"end_time":1104.46,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1103.58,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"If they hit, they don''t know it.","index":277,"end_time":1105.78,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1104.54,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Then it just pops up with those three fields.","index":278,"end_time":1107.42,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1105.78,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But then like say they know it.","index":279,"end_time":1114.78,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1113.1,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"What''s.","index":280,"end_time":1115.26,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1114.78,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"What.","index":281,"end_time":1115.66,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1115.26,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Because in my mind the thing that we''re doing is we''re showing them what their potential liability could be if they didn''t know it.","index":282,"end_time":1122.3,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1116.38,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Right.","index":283,"end_time":1122.61,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1122.45,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So if they do know it, what are they getting by plugging it into the thing?","index":284,"end_time":1126.45,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1122.61,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"So I think from there, and it would, it would be dependent on like the data that you''re able to pull.","index":285,"end_time":1131.61,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1126.93,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But if we''re able.","index":286,"end_time":1132.49,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1131.61,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So you remember like the benchmark report.","index":287,"end_time":1134.09,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1132.49,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We have like the three like just kind of boilerplate suggestions that feel like.","index":288,"end_time":1138.05,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1134.09,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"They apply to everyone.","index":289,"end_time":1138.93,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1138.05,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I feel like we could have something like that where it''s like if it''s in this range, say this.","index":290,"end_time":1143.89,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1139.89,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"If it''s in that range, say this.","index":291,"end_time":1145.81,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1144.29,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then again keep continuing to push them towards that booking that first meeting.","index":292,"end_time":1150.25,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1146.29,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"To get more valuable insights.","index":293,"end_time":1151.89,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1150.25,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":294,"end_time":1153.49,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1153.21,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"I really, I like this angle.","index":295,"end_time":1154.97,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1153.49,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"I just want to figure out what the, what the get is for the person that''s filling it out.","index":296,"end_time":1162.01,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1155.13,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Yeah, but I like where we''re going with this.","index":297,"end_time":1165.17,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1162.01,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":298,"end_time":1165.49,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1165.17,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I mean, I think if they know their PTO liability, it''s, it''s insight into like.","index":299,"end_time":1168.97,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1165.49,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Or just like, I mean it is very high level insight into like what.","index":300,"end_time":1174.49,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1168.97,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That means in relation to their business.","index":301,"end_time":1176.41,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1174.49,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So maybe they have to put PTA liability and like Overall revenue or something like that, and we''re able to give some sort of insight.","index":302,"end_time":1184.3,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1176.57,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And if they don''t know their PTO.","index":303,"end_time":1185.5,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1184.3,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Liability, then they fill out those three fields that we outlined and we can give them a rough estimate.","index":304,"end_time":1189.62,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1185.5,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, okay.","index":305,"end_time":1192.26,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1190.82,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Because the other thing we could do too is again, all, all of this like, is theoretical and spreadsheet math.","index":306,"end_time":1200.38,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1192.42,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"But like, would you be interested in reducing whatever 20% of their P. Of what their PTO liability is at a cost of, you know, 80 cents on the dollar?","index":307,"end_time":1218.75,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1200.38,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"If that''s something that you''re interested in, we should set up time to talk about it, blah, blah, blah, blah.","index":308,"end_time":1223.27,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1219.15,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"And like actually like plug in the numbers based on what they put in that.","index":309,"end_time":1226.43,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1223.27,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"That''s something I think that we could do.","index":310,"end_time":1229.79,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1226.43,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"And again, it''s like, it''s all spreadsheet math.","index":311,"end_time":1232.24,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1229.79,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"It''s all very, you know.","index":312,"end_time":1235.04,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1232.24,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah.","index":313,"end_time":1236.28,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1235.44,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And it''s, that''s what these things are when you, when you fill out stuff online.","index":314,"end_time":1239.48,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1236.28,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Like, that''s exactly, it''s just a calculation.","index":315,"end_time":1241.6,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1239.48,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, cool.","index":316,"end_time":1242.84,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1242.24,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Okay, I like that.","index":317,"end_time":1243.84,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1242.84,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"All right.","index":318,"end_time":1244.72,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1244.32,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So then another angle was going towards the multi generational workforce.","index":319,"end_time":1248.16,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1244.72,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So this was really positioned of like, hey, you know, you got, you got these people coming in in their first few years.","index":320,"end_time":1254.6,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1248.16,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"They''re looking to get as much vacation time or you know, whatever kind of benefit they''re looking for versus the older generation is going to be looking more of like, does my retirement look, what can I do with donating to nonprofits and getting, you know, something back from that?","index":321,"end_time":1268.98,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1254.6,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Really more flexibility in what they''re able to do with it.","index":322,"end_time":1271.5,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1268.98,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So coming in with.","index":323,"end_time":1273.42,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1272.38,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And we probably soften up the language.","index":324,"end_time":1275.14,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1273.42,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"A little bit of like instead of your boomers want this and your Gen Cs want this.","index":325,"end_time":1278.46,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1275.14,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But I feel like that was a good way for us to articulate it here of fixing that gap between what they are able to offer and basically expanding their, their PTO offerings so that.","index":326,"end_time":1290.43,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1279.18,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It''S basically agnostic to who''s on the receiving end of them.","index":327,"end_time":1294.23,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1290.43,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yes.","index":328,"end_time":1296.07,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1295.59,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"I love this.","index":329,"end_time":1297.11,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1296.31,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"So what we would build there is an industry playbook and that would be.","index":330,"end_time":1302.43,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1297.99,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Run through LinkedIn ads to drive legion form fills again going into sequences then to push towards that first meeting.","index":331,"end_time":1308.95,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1302.43,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Great.","index":332,"end_time":1310.47,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1310.07,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Do you have.","index":333,"end_time":1312.31,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1311.51,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Sorry, I''m trying to pull it up while we''re talking here.","index":334,"end_time":1316.99,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1314.47,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Do we ever send you the time to rethink PTO ebook that we have?","index":335,"end_time":1323.59,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1317.15,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"I, I''ve read it off the website.","index":336,"end_time":1325.23,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1323.59,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":337,"end_time":1326.43,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1325.87,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Because I think, I think like specifically for this, I think there''s a bunch of charts that''s like different different ages of employees, what they''re most interested in.","index":338,"end_time":1341.63,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1327.15,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Let me.","index":339,"end_time":1343.13,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1342.73,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"They do have.","index":340,"end_time":1368.18,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1367.46,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"They do have the.","index":341,"end_time":1371.18,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1370.34,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"They did this survey and they do have the ages of the employees.","index":342,"end_time":1375.46,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1371.18,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Feel like somewhere we should have what was most interesting to each of the different age groups.","index":343,"end_time":1385.86,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1377.54,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"But I''d have to go back, but that''s something that, like, I mean, kind of specific to what you''re talking about.","index":344,"end_time":1395.54,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1390.74,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Like, I think we have real data that shows exactly that.","index":345,"end_time":1400.5,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1395.54,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Yeah, I have to find the PDF in here, but I know exactly what you''re talking about.","index":346,"end_time":1405.3,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1402.34,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, we''ll have to go back and look at it, but yes, I''m.","index":347,"end_time":1414.14,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1411.46,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"I love this.","index":348,"end_time":1415.86,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1414.14,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"I have the full report here.","index":349,"end_time":1420.87,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1419.47,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"I could dump it.","index":350,"end_time":1421.59,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1420.87,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"I mean, you''re in the right place.","index":351,"end_time":1423.31,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1421.59,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Okay, perfect.","index":352,"end_time":1424.99,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1424.03,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"There''s a bunch of documents in this folder.","index":353,"end_time":1429.71,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1427.79,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":354,"end_time":1430.43,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1429.95,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Lhra, go up a little bit.","index":355,"end_time":1433.07,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1430.99,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Oh, no, that''s the other one they did for us.","index":356,"end_time":1437.47,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1435.23,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"It should just.","index":357,"end_time":1442.43,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1441.71,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"It should be called, like, time to rethink pto.","index":358,"end_time":1445.23,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1442.43,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Yeah, that''s.","index":359,"end_time":1453.52,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1452.88,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"That''s the one.","index":360,"end_time":1454.24,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1453.52,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"But if you go to, like, the very end of it.","index":361,"end_time":1462.64,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1460.72,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Yeah, I see a bunch of chart as I''m scrolling through.","index":362,"end_time":1469.44,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1467.52,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, keep going here.","index":363,"end_time":1473.77,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1469.6,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"It.","index":364,"end_time":1474.41,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1474.01,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"It shows that we know the gender and the respondent age of the people that submitted this.","index":365,"end_time":1479.29,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1474.65,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"And I think there was questions of, like, if you could use your pto, how would you want to use it?","index":366,"end_time":1484.13,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1479.53,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Because I think we pulled out stuff that was like, in the executive summary of it.","index":367,"end_time":1489.93,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1484.13,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"That was like four out of five employees that are this age wanted to do this or whatever it was.","index":368,"end_time":1496.25,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1490.09,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Right.","index":369,"end_time":1497.06,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1496.82,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":370,"end_time":1500.9,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1500.42,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":371,"end_time":1501.74,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1501.38,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So I also think also we just have, like, the raw data for this, so if it''s not in the actual chart, we do have the raw data somewhere.","index":372,"end_time":1507.1,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1501.74,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"We should have access to it.","index":373,"end_time":1507.98,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1507.1,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"I mean, this was a report we paid for, so we can use that to substantiate whatever kind of thing you''re.","index":374,"end_time":1513.94,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1507.98,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"You''re thinking of for this second campaign.","index":375,"end_time":1516.18,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1513.94,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Yeah, and all of this stuff''s great, too.","index":376,"end_time":1518.34,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1516.58,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, there''s a ton of good stuff in here.","index":377,"end_time":1520.74,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1519.06,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Yeah, perfect.","index":378,"end_time":1522.42,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1520.82,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"There it is.","index":379,"end_time":1524.12,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1523.76,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Like, that''s exactly what it is.","index":380,"end_time":1525.28,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1524.12,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Where it was like, they''re people near retirement age are like four times as likely, you know, than who are 54 and older than people that are 18 to 24.","index":381,"end_time":1537,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1526,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"So we have this data somewhere.","index":382,"end_time":1538.56,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1537,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah, yeah.","index":383,"end_time":1539.92,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1538.56,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"This is great.","index":384,"end_time":1540.48,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1539.92,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right, perfect.","index":385,"end_time":1542.64,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1541.68,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":386,"end_time":1545.6,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1545.2,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So that was the multi generational.","index":387,"end_time":1546.72,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1545.6,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Then the next one was a focus on the healthcare industry and preventing burnout.","index":388,"end_time":1552.56,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1546.96,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So, you know, just through research, we see a lot of burnout with people.","index":389,"end_time":1556.84,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1553.84,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"In the healthcare industry, you know, nurses Doctors, surgeons, all sorts of stuff.","index":390,"end_time":1560.96,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1556.84,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Very high burnout industry there.","index":391,"end_time":1564.24,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1561.52,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And we wanted to create another playbook for this industry that really talks about how having more options in your PTO.","index":392,"end_time":1573.12,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1564.24,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Policies can help to eliminate burnout.","index":393,"end_time":1577.6,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1573.12,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Especially because, you know, in the healthcare.","index":394,"end_time":1579.68,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1577.6,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Industry, they''re coming in with a lot.","index":395,"end_time":1581,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1579.68,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Of educational payments, you know, school loans that they need to pay off, they need emergency cash.","index":396,"end_time":1586.46,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1581,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You know, they''re just dealing with.","index":397,"end_time":1588.78,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1587.26,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"With an array of issues across the board.","index":398,"end_time":1590.78,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1588.78,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So again, another playbook geared towards how you can best serve your staff, you know, in this industry.","index":399,"end_time":1597.18,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1591.5,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":400,"end_time":1599.66,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1599.1,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Do.","index":401,"end_time":1602.38,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1601.98,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"When you.","index":402,"end_time":1603.94,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1603.42,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"When we send you content to look at, are you like, feeding that into some kind of like, AI tool or something that.","index":403,"end_time":1613.48,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1603.94,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"That kind of sorts it and tracks it, or is it more just like you''re reading these articles and then you''re thinking of what you''re writing for the content?","index":404,"end_time":1622.6,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1613.72,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"It''s a little bit of both.","index":405,"end_time":1623.72,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1622.76,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I have like a chat GPT project folder for PTO exchange that I like.","index":406,"end_time":1627.359,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1623.72,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I dump everything into.","index":407,"end_time":1628.6,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1627.359,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So if we''re.","index":408,"end_time":1631.8,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1630.44,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Because we have a Slack channel internally that''s just called, like, curated content.","index":409,"end_time":1636.52,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1631.96,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"And it''s mostly Dave Sherman, who has all these different, like, Google alerts that he finds he sees an interesting article, he just posts the article into that Slack channel.","index":410,"end_time":1645.3,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1636.52,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"I mean, I would think some of this stuff we could feed to you because.","index":411,"end_time":1650.98,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1648.02,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":412,"end_time":1651.54,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1650.98,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then.","index":413,"end_time":1652.62,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1652.1,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"And then take whatever, you know, tidbits from each of the things.","index":414,"end_time":1655.7,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1652.62,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"There was just a really interesting article earlier this week in the New York Times about.","index":415,"end_time":1660.42,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1655.7,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Because there''s all these nurses that are on strike in New York City right now.","index":416,"end_time":1664.06,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1660.66,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"It''s like all the major hospitals.","index":417,"end_time":1665.62,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1664.06,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"And part of the messaging on something like this is basically like if you want to get out in front of union negotiations and offer employees something that''s an easy benefit to offer, that''s going to improve employee relations and engagement.","index":418,"end_time":1681,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1666.76,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Like here, you know, get out in front of it before they go on strike kind of a thing.","index":419,"end_time":1686,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1681.88,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"But like, yeah, we''re always coming across articles like that that I think would help, you know, educate whatever tool you''re using to create this kind of content and these kind of email campaigns.","index":420,"end_time":1697.97,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1686,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"So if there''s an easy way for.","index":421,"end_time":1699.61,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1698.21,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"For me to feed that to you.","index":422,"end_time":1700.89,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1699.61,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"So you can just feed it into the.","index":423,"end_time":1702.37,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1700.89,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Yeah, just our Slack channel.","index":424,"end_time":1703.97,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1702.61,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Totally.","index":425,"end_time":1704.33,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1703.97,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Just, Just.","index":426,"end_time":1704.73,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1704.33,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Just put it in, like the link to the.","index":427,"end_time":1706.29,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1704.73,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Yep.","index":428,"end_time":1706.73,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1706.29,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Thing.","index":429,"end_time":1707.09,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1706.73,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Okay.","index":430,"end_time":1707.89,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1707.25,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"What.","index":431,"end_time":1708.89,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1708.53,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Actually if I just.","index":432,"end_time":1709.81,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1708.89,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Or if you want to add me to the.","index":433,"end_time":1712.61,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1711.33,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I was gonna say, I. I don''t have any issue with.","index":434,"end_time":1714.93,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1712.61,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Let me just make sure that Rob doesn''t.","index":435,"end_time":1717.33,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1715.33,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"But I don''t think we would have any issue of just adding you into the curated content.","index":436,"end_time":1720.41,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1717.33,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"That way if I don''t send it to you, you don''t miss it.","index":437,"end_time":1723.95,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1720.41,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah, yeah.","index":438,"end_time":1724.67,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1723.95,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But, but it''s like, you know, once every couple days there''s an interesting article that''s.","index":439,"end_time":1728.79,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1724.67,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":440,"end_time":1729.23,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1728.79,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That we need to be timely with.","index":441,"end_time":1730.63,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1729.39,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"These, especially in this first two quarters.","index":442,"end_time":1732.43,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1730.63,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":443,"end_time":1732.91,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1732.43,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Okay.","index":444,"end_time":1734.43,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1733.87,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"And then the last one was more of something that we would have to definitely work with you guys on of building a 2026 state of employee benchmark report.","index":445,"end_time":1743.63,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1734.83,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You guys have done something similar to.","index":446,"end_time":1745.43,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1743.71,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"This in the past.","index":447,"end_time":1746.11,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1745.43,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Um, but really having a focus around.","index":448,"end_time":1749.96,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1746.76,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Giving employees the benefit of choice of how they use their PTO policy.","index":449,"end_time":1754.2,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1749.96,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And we find that these sort of like industry agnostic, like this is the status of.","index":450,"end_time":1763.08,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1755.56,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"This is the State of the Union report.","index":451,"end_time":1764.68,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1763.08,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Really drive a lot of interest and awareness for.","index":452,"end_time":1768.08,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1765.96,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"For companies.","index":453,"end_time":1768.68,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1768.08,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, we, I mean, we want to do this so bad.","index":454,"end_time":1773.48,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1770.2,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"We have gone down this path of like, how can we put together a benchmark report?","index":455,"end_time":1780.47,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1773.48,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"It''s just so costly to do.","index":456,"end_time":1782.87,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1780.71,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Like the survey we were trying to piggyback off of Locked Ins.","index":457,"end_time":1789.75,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1784.63,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"They weren''t really like interested in having us do it.","index":458,"end_time":1791.83,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1789.75,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"We were talking about doing a joint thing with.","index":459,"end_time":1793.99,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1791.83,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"With.","index":460,"end_time":1796.71,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1796.31,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Who?","index":461,"end_time":1799.39,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1799.11,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Was it someone else, Hub maybe or something like that, and then it just kind of fizzled out.","index":462,"end_time":1804.24,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1799.39,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"But we definitely want to do something like this.","index":463,"end_time":1807.52,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1804.56,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"I just don''t know.","index":464,"end_time":1809.76,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1808.72,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"So maybe we take it even like, you know, if you remember how we started the benchmark report, that was kind of me like putting together like a web page and a mock up of how exactly we picture all of it coming together.","index":465,"end_time":1819.04,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1810.88,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So what if we took a first.","index":466,"end_time":1820.24,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1819.12,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Stab at like the content framework?","index":467,"end_time":1822.16,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1820.24,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Maybe that generates some ideas of how we can put something like this together.","index":468,"end_time":1825.36,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1822.4,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":469,"end_time":1826.75,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1826.55,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"I mean, are you thinking of this like, like it''s a survey people are taking or is this just our own?","index":470,"end_time":1833.43,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1826.75,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"I think this is using your own data.","index":471,"end_time":1835.99,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1833.91,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Data and research.","index":472,"end_time":1837.03,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1836.23,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":473,"end_time":1837.91,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1837.43,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, then that''s different.","index":474,"end_time":1839.67,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1838.23,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"I think it''s much more feasible.","index":475,"end_time":1841.989,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1840.23,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, it''s much more feasible to do that.","index":476,"end_time":1843.99,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1842.15,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":477,"end_time":1844.79,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1844.23,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":478,"end_time":1845.75,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1845.11,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right, cool.","index":479,"end_time":1847.43,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1845.75,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So those were the four ideas that.","index":480,"end_time":1849.23,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1847.59,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We wanted to pitch.","index":481,"end_time":1849.91,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1849.23,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So sounds like we got some good stuff here.","index":482,"end_time":1851.75,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1849.91,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, great stuff here.","index":483,"end_time":1853.06,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1851.86,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":484,"end_time":1853.94,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1853.3,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right, I know we got three minutes left.","index":485,"end_time":1857.14,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1854.9,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We are going to work on the HubSpot audit.","index":486,"end_time":1860.34,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1857.94,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We talked about that yesterday.","index":487,"end_time":1861.34,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1860.34,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we''ll put that together and have that ready for next week to go through.","index":488,"end_time":1864.38,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1861.34,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then if you guys are good.","index":489,"end_time":1865.26,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1864.38,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"With our recommendations and plan, then we''ll just get right into cleaning everything up.","index":490,"end_time":1869.1,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1865.26,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"In HubSpot, we''ve sent over the pages that need review.","index":491,"end_time":1872.9,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1869.1,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"One thing I do want to ask.","index":492,"end_time":1875.18,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1874.02,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I completely forgot that I''m out of.","index":493,"end_time":1877.94,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1875.18,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"The office on Monday.","index":494,"end_time":1878.82,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1877.94,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Do you want to move our meeting to.","index":495,"end_time":1881.88,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1880.2,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Tuesday?","index":496,"end_time":1884.84,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1884.44,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We still have our Thursday.","index":497,"end_time":1886.6,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1885.56,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I have some time on Tuesday or Wednesday.","index":498,"end_time":1891.72,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1889.96,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"When?","index":499,"end_time":1893.76,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1893.48,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Say.","index":500,"end_time":1894.04,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1893.76,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Either do it Tuesday or just wait till Thursday.","index":501,"end_time":1897.96,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1895.88,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"But what do you have available on Tuesday?","index":502,"end_time":1900.44,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1897.96,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"I have 2:00pm Eastern, so it''s at 11 your time.","index":503,"end_time":1904.36,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1900.84,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, that actually works for me.","index":504,"end_time":1906.45,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1905.25,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"All right, I''m going to update that then.","index":505,"end_time":1908.21,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1906.61,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, my wife is looking at the.","index":506,"end_time":1912.37,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1911.17,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Calendar, and she was like, I think you''re off.","index":507,"end_time":1914.45,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1912.37,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And I was like, yep, I totally forgot about that.","index":508,"end_time":1916.65,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1914.45,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, we''re not.","index":509,"end_time":1917.33,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1916.65,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Well, we lost that holiday at one point.","index":510,"end_time":1920.729,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1918.85,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"I think now we have Juneteenth instead of MLK Day.","index":511,"end_time":1925.01,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1920.729,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":512,"end_time":1925.73,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1925.25,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":513,"end_time":1927.69,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1927.25,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Perfect.","index":514,"end_time":1928.13,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1927.69,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":515,"end_time":1930.13,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1929.57,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right, so we''ll make the tweaks to the workflow cheat sheet, and then we''ll start getting these plans into sort.","index":516,"end_time":1939.04,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1930.72,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Of like a campaign structure so we can continue talking through those.","index":517,"end_time":1942.64,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1939.04,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And we''ll work on the nurture sequences and the HubSpot audit.","index":518,"end_time":1945.64,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1942.64,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we got a lot of homework on our side.","index":519,"end_time":1947.92,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1945.64,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So for the time being, until we can create those additional sequences, just like business as usual for them on these inbound leads.","index":520,"end_time":1958.4,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1948.4,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":521,"end_time":1958.95,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1958.71,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Do you have a general idea of when you think that that new stuff will be ready?","index":522,"end_time":1962.87,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1958.95,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"I mean, I''m probably looking at getting.","index":523,"end_time":1965.31,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1963.03,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Them live, like, right at the beginning of February.","index":524,"end_time":1967.67,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1965.31,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":525,"end_time":1969.07,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1968.63,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"So we''re going to have a few weeks where we still need to figure out exactly when these types of leads come in, how they''re handling them.","index":526,"end_time":1974.23,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1969.07,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":527,"end_time":1974.589,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1974.23,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And I''ll be updating, like I said, the.","index":528,"end_time":1976.07,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1974.589,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"The chief, the cheat sheet, so that.","index":529,"end_time":1978.15,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1976.07,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That''s, like, our living document of truth.","index":530,"end_time":1979.75,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1978.15,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, cool.","index":531,"end_time":1981.99,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1980.07,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"And.","index":532,"end_time":1982.27,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1981.99,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"And we''re all good on the doc, like, the expansion of the team.","index":533,"end_time":1986.27,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1982.27,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"I. Justin sent me the DocuSign today.","index":534,"end_time":1988.45,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1986.27,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"I signed it, sent it back while we were on the call.","index":535,"end_time":1990.65,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1988.61,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"He fully executed one, so we''re all good there.","index":536,"end_time":1993.09,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1990.65,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":537,"end_time":1993.73,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1993.17,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right, well, thank you for that update.","index":538,"end_time":1995.25,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1993.73,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right.","index":539,"end_time":1996.05,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1995.41,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Thank you.","index":540,"end_time":1996.77,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1996.21,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Looking forward to kicking ass this year.","index":541,"end_time":1998.69,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1996.77,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Thank you, everyone.","index":542,"end_time":1999.33,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1998.69,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":543,"end_time":1999.73,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1999.33,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Thanks, guys.","index":544,"end_time":2001.37,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2000.45,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"See you.","index":545,"end_time":2001.89,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2001.37,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"}],"dateString":"2026-01-15T18:30:00.000Z","host_email":"colin.costigan@marketersindemand.com","meeting_link":"https:/