  '## **Campaign Strategy and Messaging**

The team agreed to rapidly launch at least two new campaign ideas focused on clear, measurable business impacts.

- **Colin Costigan and Josh Reinhard decided to prioritize a campaign highlighting accrued paid time off (PTO) as a financial liability potentially worth millions, aiming to convert interest into first meetings rather than complex online tools** (14:53)  
    - The campaign will feature a high-level PTO liability calculator requiring just **three data points**: employee headcount, average accrual rate, and average pay rate, providing a rough estimate of liabilities.  
    - Josh emphasized the tool must be simple to avoid gating prospects and to build credibility through a meeting, enabling deeper insight gathering later.  
    - The messaging will include a call to action encouraging prospects to book a meeting for customized analysis based on anonymized data and projections.  
    - This approach targets organizations unaware of their PTO liability, acknowledging that many finance teams already track this metric.  

- **A multi-generational workforce campaign will address PTO offerings tailored to diverse employee needs, using industry playbooks and LinkedIn ads to drive lead form fills and nurture sequences** (21:29)  
    - Josh and Colin plan to leverage existing survey data showing different PTO preferences by age group to substantiate campaign messaging.  
    - This campaign aims to close benefit gaps and expand PTO flexibility, appealing broadly across industries.  
    - The team will incorporate charts and raw survey data from the “Time to Rethink PTO” report to back messaging and target specific age groups effectively.  
    - LinkedIn ads will serve as the primary lead generation channel, funneling prospects into nurture sequences designed to push first meetings.  

- **A healthcare industry campaign will focus on preventing burnout by promoting flexible PTO policies as a key benefit, tailored to healthcare workers’ financial and personal needs** (26:32)  
    - The campaign will highlight burnout issues among nurses, doctors, and surgeons, emphasizing PTO flexibility to improve employee retention and engagement.  
    - Colin confirmed content creation will be supported by curated external articles and internal research fed into AI tools for efficient campaign development.  
    - Josh will add Colin to the internal Slack curated content channel to ensure timely access to relevant articles, supporting rapid content updates during the first two quarters.  
    - This campaign is positioned to preempt union negotiations and improve employee relations as a competitive differentiator in healthcare staffing.  

- **The team aims to build a 2026 employee benchmark report focused on PTO policy choices using internal data and research rather than costly external surveys** (28:54)  
    - Colin proposed starting with a content framework and mockup webpage similar to past benchmark reports to generate ideas and structure.  
    - Josh confirmed this approach is more feasible than previous attempts that relied on external partnerships and surveys.  
    - The report will serve as an industry-agnostic “State of Employee” insight tool to drive awareness and position the company as a thought leader.  
    - This benchmark will support long-term engagement and content strategy aligned with evolving employee benefit trends.  

## **Sales Workflow and Lead Management**

The team refined lead routing, status tracking, and sales sequence strategies to improve efficiency and conversion clarity.

- **Colin created a comprehensive workflow cheat sheet detailing current lead sources, next steps, and routing by industry to streamline sales activities** (08:57)  
    - The document includes an overview of territories, tools, and a table of contents for quick lookup of actions by lead source (demo requests, benchmark reports, LinkedIn, ads).  
    - Colin recommended a follow-up cadence of **two to four touches over two weeks** before moving leads to nurture sequences based on lead status changes.  
    - Sales reps will classify leads by industry to assign them to corresponding nurture sequences, simplifying sales team workload.  
    - The cheat sheet will remain a living document, updated as new campaigns and sequences roll out.  

- **Lead status and lifecycle stage distinctions were clarified to improve qualification and nurturing** (11:42)  
    - Josh sought clarity on when to update lifecycle stages versus lead status; Colin explained leads enter as “Lead,” move to “Marketing Qualified Lead” (MQL), then “Sales Qualified Lead” (SQL).  
    - Lead status (e.g., cold, nurture) signals engagement level within a lifecycle stage and triggers enrollment into industry-specific nurture sequences.  
    - Colin agreed to include lifecycle stage update instructions in the cheat sheet to reduce confusion and ensure consistent lead handling.  
    - The sales team will continue to manually update lifecycle stages and lead statuses until the HubSpot audit recommends automation.  

- **Current inbound lead handling will continue as usual until new sequences launch, targeted for early February** (32:43)  
    - Colin estimated that new email sequences and industry-specific nurture flows will go live at the **start of February**, allowing a transition period of several weeks.  
    - The cheat sheet will be updated continuously to reflect new workflows and sequence assignments during this interim.  
    - Josh confirmed no changes to team expansion or contract status, with new team members fully onboarded to support upcoming initiatives.  

## **HubSpot Audit and System Improvements**

The team committed to a thorough HubSpot audit to clean up workflows and improve campaign execution.

- **A full HubSpot audit is underway, with a target to complete and review recommendations by next week** (30:53)  
    - The audit will identify obsolete sequences and workflows, enabling the team to discard ineffective processes per feedback from Steph and Dan.  
    - Post-audit, the team will clean up HubSpot records and implement updated routing and nurture sequences aligned with new campaign strategies.  
    - Colin will share pages requiring review and incorporate feedback into the audit deliverables for transparency and collaboration.  
    - The audit is critical to support scalability as new campaigns and sequences launch in early 2024.  

- **Workflow improvements include routing leads into industry-specific sequences based on lead status and enabling sales teams to track engagement via updated fields** (10:53)  
    - The team plans to add a “cold” lead status option and use lead status to trigger nurture enrollment automatically.  
    - Colin emphasized the importance of making processes easy for sales reps to minimize manual errors and improve follow-up consistency.  
    - The updated cheat sheet will clearly explain these workflow changes, lifecycle stage updates, and lead status usage to ensure smooth adoption.  
    - These system improvements support better measurement of lead engagement and campaign effectiveness.  

## **Team Coordination and Scheduling**

The team synchronized calendars and communication channels to maintain momentum on deliverables.

- **Colin rescheduled the next meeting to Tuesday at 2:00pm Eastern to accommodate an upcoming day out of office** (31:35)  
    - Josh confirmed the new meeting time works well for his schedule.  
    - The team will maintain the usual Thursday meeting as a backup or follow-up session.  

- **Josh confirmed the team expansion contract was fully executed during the call, ensuring resource availability** (33:00)  
    - This update confirms readiness for increased workload from new campaign launches and HubSpot cleanup.  

- **Colin and Josh agreed to use Slack for sharing curated content to support timely campaign content creation** (27:20)  
    - Josh will grant Colin access to the internal curated content Slack channel for relevant articles and research.  
    - This will help Colin feed fresh insights into AI-assisted content generation and maintain responsiveness to market trends.  

## **Content Creation and Research Integration**

The team leveraged internal and external data sources to inform campaign messaging and content accuracy.

- **Colin uses a dedicated ChatGPT project folder to consolidate PTO Exchange research and content for campaign writing** (27:00)  
    - This approach blends AI support with curated research articles to speed content development without sacrificing quality.  
    - Josh emphasized feeding relevant Slack channel content directly to Colin to keep campaigns timely and relevant.  

- **Existing survey data from the “Time to Rethink PTO” report will provide detailed employee age group preferences to tailor messaging** (22:00)  
    - Josh highlighted that employees near retirement are four times more likely than younger groups to prefer certain PTO uses, supporting targeted communication.  
    - Raw data access allows the team to create nuanced campaign segments that reflect real employee benefit interests.  

- **Industry-specific playbooks will be developed using research data and external articles to support campaign claims and value propositions** (21:51)  
    - These playbooks will guide LinkedIn ad targeting and nurture sequences with credible, data-backed messaging.  
    - The healthcare burnout campaign will specifically use data on financial pressures and burnout to frame PTO flexibility as a retention tool.  
    - Ongoing content updates will incorporate market news such as union strikes to maintain relevance and urgency in messaging.  ',
