    '{"id":"01KET2R1APCG3CJMH8AZQNA7HD","title":"Colin Costigan and Josh Reinhard","summary":{"notes":"## **HubSpot System Audit and Optimization**\n\nThe team agreed to conduct a thorough **HubSpot audit** to clean up properties, workflows, and campaigns for clearer sales-marketing alignment and cost savings (04:14).\n\n- **Colin Costigan** outlined that the audit will focus on reducing duplicative custom properties, simplifying workflows, and optimizing automated nurture campaigns to reduce confusion and improve lead handoff (16:49).\n- The audit is expected to take **two days (16 hours)**, with results delivered early next week and implementation starting the following week once signed (18:27).\n- The cleanup aims to streamline sales processes, ensuring leads pass smoothly from marketing to sales with clear roles and automated follow-ups (18:58).\n- This effort will also identify data cleanup opportunities that could reduce storage costs and improve system efficiency, aligning with **Rob Whalen’s** priority to maximize HubSpot ROI (06:41).\n\n## **Marketing and Sales Meeting Cadence Integration**\n\nThey decided to integrate the marketing and sales meeting rhythms to improve communication and ownership of marketing deliverables (09:42).\n\n- **Josh Reinhard** described the current weekly structure: a Monday one-on-one, a Monday marketing meeting, and a Wednesday joint sales-marketing call focusing primarily on sales but including marketing and channel updates (09:42).\n- **Colin Costigan** emphasized starting with heavier meeting involvement, then shifting toward asynchronous updates as trust and dashboard transparency grow over 1-3 months (11:02).\n- The team agreed that **Colin’s group would take over Sam’s marketing tasks**, including campaign updates, collateral like one-pagers, and HubSpot maintenance, improving efficiency and accountability (13:15).\n- They plan to share living documents via OneNote and use Figma for campaign design, ensuring smooth handoffs and centralized feedback (15:34).\n\n## **Contract Amendment and Partnership Expectations**\n\nThe group committed to moving forward with a contract amendment starting in **February**, with the audit work to begin immediately upon approval (21:02).\n\n- **Rob Whalen** stressed the importance of measuring success by the number of **first meetings generated**, defining this as the key metric for ongoing evaluation of the partnership (21:26).\n- **Colin Costigan** will confirm contract exit terms with Justin to understand the flexibility if the company hires internally later (20:37).\n- The amendment will reflect a service upgrade from **80 points ($8,000) to 130 points ($10,000)** monthly, increasing service scope by **$5,000** while raising cost by $2,000, improving value (05:33).\n- Rob emphasized urgency to ramp up marketing efforts in **Q1 (January to April)** because that is when clients plan new benefit launches for the second half of the year (23:13).\n\n## **First Meeting Pipeline and Lead Management**\n\nThey identified issues with lifecycle stage mismanagement and inconsistent lead tagging, causing confusion and inefficiencies in deal tracking (01:00).\n\n- **Josh Reinhard** noted the need to correct reps’ misunderstanding of lifecycle stages, clarifying that first meetings should not move contacts directly to opportunity without a deal created in HubSpot (02:19).\n- There is currently no evidence of deals tagged to the **New North** lead source despite ongoing activity, indicating a need for workflow cleanup and accurate source tracking (03:04).\n- The team acknowledged that improving lead qualification and pipeline hygiene will directly support the goal of increasing first meetings, the primary revenue driver (01:09).\n- Rob highlighted the importance of the sales team focusing on first meetings and demos as the primary revenue lever, reinforcing that all marketing and sales efforts must align with this objective (08:44).\n\n## **Product and Campaign Development Timeline**\n\nThe team plans to launch new **industry pages and landing pages** with conversion optimization within the next **one to two weeks** to support upcoming campaigns (27:02).\n\n- Colin requested feedback on the draft pages via comments directly on the live pages, aiming for quick iteration and deployment ahead of a campaign pitch scheduled the following day (27:55).\n- They will fix navigation and URL issues promptly to avoid confusion during review (28:21).\n- Josh confirmed that past marketing assets like one-pagers (e.g., for instant cash) will be transitioned from Sam to Colin’s team, ensuring continuity and easier future updates (15:06).\n- The team uses Figma for design work and plans to replicate successful past assets to accelerate development of new campaign materials (15:41).\n\n## **Leadership Visibility and Collaboration**\n\nThere is a plan for **Colin Costigan** to virtually join an all-hands meeting on **February 10th** to increase visibility and alignment across the company (24:58).\n\n- Rob emphasized the need for open communication and data sharing to support the marketing team’s work, committing to provide all necessary info to achieve first meeting goals (25:31).\n- Colin confirmed that joining regular sales and marketing calls will help uncover insights and enable more targeted marketing efforts, improving responsiveness to sales needs (26:06).\n- The collaboration aims to create a feedback loop where marketing ideas directly respond to sales team challenges, driving improved deal flow and conversion (11:02).","outline":null,"keywords":["HubSpot audit","first meetings","marketing optimization","point system pricing","workflow cleanup","sales and marketing integration"],"overview":"- **HubSpot Audit:** The team will audit HubSpot to streamline processes, reduce confusion, and enhance cost efficiency.  \n- **Timeline:** Audit expected to last 16 hours, with results early next week and implementation available soon after approval.  \n- **Meeting Integration:** Marketing and sales meetings will align for better communication, starting with increased involvement and later asynchronous updates.  \n- **Contract Changes:** Contract amendment will begin in February, raising service scope and cost while prioritizing first meetings as a success metric.  \n- **Lead Management Issues:** Lifecycle mismanagement and inconsistent lead tagging need correction to improve first meeting generation and deal tracking.  \n- **Campaign Development:** New industry pages aimed for launch in one to two weeks, using Figma for design and feedback for quick iteration.","action_items":"\n**Colin Costigan**\nDraft and send amendment confirming contract terms and start date; clarify out clause regarding internal hire scenario (20:37)\nBegin HubSpot audit immediately upon contract finalization, targeting completion early next week (18:12)\nConduct detailed cleanup of HubSpot custom properties, workflows, and nurture campaigns post-audit, pending client approval (17:59)\nJoin sales and marketing meetings regularly to stay informed and foster collaboration (26:06)\nPrepare to participate virtually in the all-hands meeting on February 10th (24:58)\nCoordinate with Nina to fix URL errors on industry pages and share updated links for review (27:47)\nLaunch new industry landing pages with conversion optimization within 1-2 weeks to support upcoming campaigns (23:48)\n\n**Josh Reinhard**\nShare past meeting documentation and OneNote notes with Colin to facilitate transition (13:32)\nProvide content and feedback for the new industry pages once updated links are shared (28:45)\nTransfer marketing task requests, such as the instant cash one-pager, to Colin and his team going forward (15:34)\nAssist in coordinating internal stakeholder communications and feedback loops during audit and implementation phases (15:34)\n\n**Rob Whalen**\nApprove amendment and push to get agreement finalized to enable audit and work to start immediately (21:02)\nEnsure open communication of data, information, and resources needed by Colin’s team to meet first meeting and marketing goals (25:31)\nFacilitate scheduling for Instacash engineering meetings and inclusion of appropriate team members (24:05)\nSupport coordination of all-hands meeting participation and company alignment (24:58)\n"},"duration":29.360000610351562,"speakers":[{"id":0,"name":"Colin Costigan"},{"id":1,"name":"Rob Whalen"},{"id":2,"name":"Josh Reinhard"}],"sentences":[{"text":"Hey, Rob.","index":0,"end_time":16.96,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":16.4,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Hey, Colin.","index":1,"end_time":17.68,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":17.04,"speaker_name":"Rob Whalen"},{"text":"How''s it going?","index":2,"end_time":18.16,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":17.68,"speaker_name":"Rob Whalen"},{"text":"Good.","index":3,"end_time":18.64,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":18.32,"speaker_name":"Rob Whalen"},{"text":"How are you?","index":4,"end_time":19.2,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":18.64,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Good.","index":5,"end_time":19.84,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":19.44,"speaker_name":"Rob Whalen"},{"text":"New Year.","index":6,"end_time":22.28,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":21.84,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Off to a good start.","index":7,"end_time":23.12,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":22.28,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, I think it is.","index":8,"end_time":26.64,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":24.96,"speaker_name":"Rob Whalen"},{"text":"It is off to a pretty good start.","index":9,"end_time":28.8,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":26.96,"speaker_name":"Rob Whalen"},{"text":"So we''re closing some deals.","index":10,"end_time":31.52,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":29.36,"speaker_name":"Rob Whalen"},{"text":"Business seems to be in the right track.","index":11,"end_time":34.64,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":32.88,"speaker_name":"Rob Whalen"},{"text":"We need to solve some issues, but I think we''re headed in the right direction.","index":12,"end_time":38.4,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":34.64,"speaker_name":"Rob Whalen"},{"text":"It''s awesome.","index":13,"end_time":39.36,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":38.56,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Josh, how''s it going?","index":14,"end_time":40.64,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":39.68,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"What''s up, Colin?","index":15,"end_time":41.84,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":40.88,"speaker_name":"Rob Whalen"},{"text":"Not much.","index":16,"end_time":42.96,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":42.32,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"How''s your day been so far?","index":17,"end_time":49.92,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":48.64,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"This has been crazy.","index":18,"end_time":52.89,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":51.69,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"We are busy, like Rob was just saying.","index":19,"end_time":56.73,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":54.73,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"I mean, it''s great.","index":20,"end_time":57.53,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":56.73,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":21,"end_time":58.05,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":57.69,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Busy is good.","index":22,"end_time":58.73,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":58.05,"speaker_name":"Rob Whalen"},{"text":"Busy is definitely good.","index":23,"end_time":60.09,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":58.89,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"But I. I might have.","index":24,"end_time":61.85,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":60.25,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Maybe the field wasn''t updated correctly, but I saw that Dan had moved some people to Opportunity.","index":25,"end_time":66.49,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":61.85,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Out of some LinkedIn leads, possibly.","index":26,"end_time":73.13,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":69.37,"speaker_name":"Rob Whalen"},{"text":"I was actually just looking at our dashboard because I had some things I needed to update for Steph, but I didn''t see anything in there.","index":27,"end_time":83.64,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":73.93,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Which ones are you seeing?","index":28,"end_time":91.4,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":90.04,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Let me pull it up.","index":29,"end_time":93.24,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":92.28,"speaker_name":"Rob Whalen"},{"text":"Memorial herman.","index":30,"end_time":100.12,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":99,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"John Kelly was moved to life or to opportunity, And he has a task to follow back up with him from LinkedIn.","index":31,"end_time":117.09,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":105.01,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Oh, okay.","index":32,"end_time":120.25,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":119.17,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"So he.","index":33,"end_time":120.969,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":120.25,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"So what are you seeing on your side?","index":34,"end_time":123.01,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":120.969,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"That it got changed, that it got updated to.","index":35,"end_time":125.49,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":123.01,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Yeah, it says his life cycle stages at Opportunity.","index":36,"end_time":128.45,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":126.05,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I think that''s just.","index":37,"end_time":140.059,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":139.099,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"I think that''s a.","index":38,"end_time":143.819,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":142.779,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"That is a example of, like, the reps not knowing what they''re supposed to be doing.","index":39,"end_time":148.859,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":144.059,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Gotcha.","index":40,"end_time":149.779,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":149.179,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":41,"end_time":150.379,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":149.779,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Because that really probably should be a sales qualified lead, I would think.","index":42,"end_time":155.659,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":151.979,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Mm.","index":43,"end_time":156.6,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":156.2,"speaker_name":"Rob Whalen"},{"text":"And that''s when we get a first meeting with someone.","index":44,"end_time":165.16,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":159.72,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"We''re.","index":45,"end_time":165.64,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":165.24,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"We''re never changing the life cycle stage of the contact to opportunity or to first meeting.","index":46,"end_time":173,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":165.64,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"So I don''t know what Sam was doing when he was creating that.","index":47,"end_time":176.6,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":173.32,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"We just create deals in HubSpot.","index":48,"end_time":183.01,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":177.08,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":49,"end_time":183.65,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":183.17,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":50,"end_time":184.13,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":183.73,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I got you an opportunity.","index":51,"end_time":185.81,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":184.13,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"But one of the lead sources for the deals is New north, and one of them is 11x and one of them is demanding.","index":52,"end_time":193.17,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":185.81,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"One of them is channel.","index":53,"end_time":194.37,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":193.17,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"So when I''m looking at the first meetings that have been run so far this year, I don''t see anything tagged to New north yet, but I don''t know if that''s.","index":54,"end_time":205.89,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":194.61,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Yeah, like a workflow cleanup.","index":55,"end_time":208.01,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":206.61,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Probably.","index":56,"end_time":208.37,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":208.01,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Could be.","index":57,"end_time":211.08,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":210.6,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"I mean, usually the deal stuff is pretty cut and dry because we run a first meeting, we put it in HubSpot.","index":58,"end_time":218.6,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":211.24,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Like, there''s so many other things that we need to do.","index":59,"end_time":221,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":218.6,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"As a part of that deal that if there wasn''t a first meeting that occurred.","index":60,"end_time":228.44,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":225,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"I mean, unless it was like, it happened today, and I haven''t put it in yet.","index":61,"end_time":231.32,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":228.44,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Normally those things are pretty.","index":62,"end_time":233.04,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":231.56,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Pretty dialed In Gotcha.","index":63,"end_time":234.81,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":233.04,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Okay.","index":64,"end_time":235.33,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":234.81,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"All right, good to know.","index":65,"end_time":237.73,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":236.69,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So what.","index":66,"end_time":244.29,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":243.73,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"So we''re just kind of going over today, like, what expansion would look like.","index":67,"end_time":248.93,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":244.69,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"I think, Rob, you had some questions around, like, the point system.","index":68,"end_time":253.41,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":250.129,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Yeah, I just want to understand the point system.","index":69,"end_time":256.21,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":254.45,"speaker_name":"Rob Whalen"},{"text":"You know, I don''t understand the.","index":70,"end_time":258.77,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":256.29,"speaker_name":"Rob Whalen"},{"text":"Frankly, I don''t understand the bid.","index":71,"end_time":262.52,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":259.33,"speaker_name":"Rob Whalen"},{"text":"Yeah, I gotcha.","index":72,"end_time":265.16,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":262.76,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So if you could just educate me.","index":73,"end_time":267.08,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":265.32,"speaker_name":"Rob Whalen"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":74,"end_time":267.8,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":267.32,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So at its simplest, one point equals $100.","index":75,"end_time":271.16,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":268.04,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"The reason that we price our services at points is actually to benefit you guys.","index":76,"end_time":276.84,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":272.12,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So, you know, say, for example, we''re developing a webpage, and that''s 12 points.","index":77,"end_time":281.2,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":276.84,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"If we ran into, like, four, five, six hours of issues, you''re not just getting billed more for the time that we spent on it.","index":78,"end_time":287.88,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":281.2,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we don''t do the hourly model so that we can actually save our clients on that cost.","index":79,"end_time":292.72,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":289.04,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Gotcha.","index":80,"end_time":295.28,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":294.56,"speaker_name":"Rob Whalen"},{"text":"And then on the same end, if you get it done sooner, you win on that.","index":81,"end_time":301,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":296.56,"speaker_name":"Rob Whalen"},{"text":"On that game.","index":82,"end_time":301.76,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":301,"speaker_name":"Rob Whalen"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah.","index":83,"end_time":302.48,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":301.84,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"For being more efficient.","index":84,"end_time":303.44,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":302.48,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"For being more efficient.","index":85,"end_time":304.88,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":303.68,"speaker_name":"Rob Whalen"},{"text":"Okay, so.","index":86,"end_time":307.76,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":306.16,"speaker_name":"Rob Whalen"},{"text":"So, like, when we say, like, walk me through it.","index":87,"end_time":313.08,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":307.84,"speaker_name":"Rob Whalen"},{"text":"Like, walk me through.","index":88,"end_time":313.8,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":313.08,"speaker_name":"Rob Whalen"},{"text":"So there was.","index":89,"end_time":314.56,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":313.8,"speaker_name":"Rob Whalen"},{"text":"I can''t remember where it''s at.","index":90,"end_time":316.7,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":314.94,"speaker_name":"Rob Whalen"},{"text":"You can bring it up.","index":91,"end_time":317.9,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":316.78,"speaker_name":"Rob Whalen"},{"text":"What The.","index":92,"end_time":319.42,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":318.86,"speaker_name":"Rob Whalen"},{"text":"Oh, what?","index":93,"end_time":323.78,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":323.02,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Just.","index":94,"end_time":324.06,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":323.78,"speaker_name":"Rob Whalen"},{"text":"Yeah, the stuff that you gave to Josh.","index":95,"end_time":326.86,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":324.94,"speaker_name":"Rob Whalen"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":96,"end_time":327.58,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":327.1,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I''m sure he forwarded it to me some point in time.","index":97,"end_time":332.46,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":327.66,"speaker_name":"Rob Whalen"},{"text":"Yep.","index":98,"end_time":333.82,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":333.26,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":99,"end_time":334.66,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":334.22,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So what Justin had positioned was going from 80 points, so 80 points for $8,000 to actually getting 130 points for $10,000, meaning that you''re paying 2,000 more a month, but you get $5,000 more a month in services.","index":100,"end_time":355.36,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":334.66,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":101,"end_time":360.08,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":359.52,"speaker_name":"Rob Whalen"},{"text":"Okay.","index":102,"end_time":364.24,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":363.68,"speaker_name":"Rob Whalen"},{"text":"And then, you know, if I kind of look at what Sam did, obviously you''re going to probably be more efficient than I''m assuming, Sam, on some of the HubSpot stuff.","index":103,"end_time":374.68,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":364.24,"speaker_name":"Rob Whalen"},{"text":"I also did like the idea of kind of doing an evaluation on HubSpot and kind of looking at if there is better ways to.","index":104,"end_time":385.8,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":375.8,"speaker_name":"Rob Whalen"},{"text":"To do what Sam was doing.","index":105,"end_time":388.52,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":386.12,"speaker_name":"Rob Whalen"},{"text":"Yep.","index":106,"end_time":389.8,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":389.24,"speaker_name":"Rob Whalen"},{"text":"And so I think that would be great because we.","index":107,"end_time":393.16,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":390.36,"speaker_name":"Rob Whalen"},{"text":"We.","index":108,"end_time":393.84,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":393.68,"speaker_name":"Rob Whalen"},{"text":"We invest so much money in this goddamn thing.","index":109,"end_time":395.84,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":393.84,"speaker_name":"Rob Whalen"},{"text":"It''s like, yeah.","index":110,"end_time":396.64,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":395.84,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We need to get every penny out of it.","index":111,"end_time":401.2,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":398.56,"speaker_name":"Rob Whalen"},{"text":"Totally hear you.","index":112,"end_time":402.2,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":401.52,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And one thing I mentioned to Josh was we''re also HubSpot partners.","index":113,"end_time":405.28,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":402.2,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So, I mean, we do.","index":114,"end_time":407.64,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":406.8,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We do this work all the time, and we have reps over there.","index":115,"end_time":410.64,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":407.64,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So, you know, not only making sure that you''re getting the most out of HubSpot for what you''re putting in, but, you know, seeing if there''s opportunity for, you know, if there''s a lot of data cleanup that we can get out of the system that''s just costing you guys right now, taking up storage.","index":116,"end_time":422.86,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":410.64,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You know, what opportunities do we have to save you guys on cost there?","index":117,"end_time":426.06,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":423.18,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, and, and, and I know.","index":118,"end_time":428.3,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":426.62,"speaker_name":"Rob Whalen"},{"text":"I think our deal comes up in April with HubSpot.","index":119,"end_time":430.86,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":428.3,"speaker_name":"Rob Whalen"},{"text":"I think that''s our.","index":120,"end_time":431.62,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":430.86,"speaker_name":"Rob Whalen"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":121,"end_time":431.94,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":431.62,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Let me check if I remember correct.","index":122,"end_time":433.5,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":431.94,"speaker_name":"Rob Whalen"},{"text":"I think you.","index":123,"end_time":434.66,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":433.98,"speaker_name":"Rob Whalen"},{"text":"You''re the one who told me that.","index":124,"end_time":435.82,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":434.66,"speaker_name":"Rob Whalen"},{"text":"Actually, it looks like they''re going to issue you an invoice on January 22.","index":125,"end_time":444.7,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":439.18,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It looks like you pay quarterly.","index":126,"end_time":445.98,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":444.7,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Oh, yeah, we do.","index":127,"end_time":448.3,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":447.26,"speaker_name":"Rob Whalen"},{"text":"I know we pay quarterly.","index":128,"end_time":449.62,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":448.7,"speaker_name":"Rob Whalen"},{"text":"So.","index":129,"end_time":449.82,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":449.62,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":130,"end_time":450.06,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":449.82,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So that''s January 22nd.","index":131,"end_time":451.1,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":450.06,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"If there''s anything we can do, like, if there''s anything that.","index":132,"end_time":453.66,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":451.1,"speaker_name":"Rob Whalen"},{"text":"I know if maybe moving through you is.","index":133,"end_time":456.62,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":453.66,"speaker_name":"Rob Whalen"},{"text":"Is cheaper.","index":134,"end_time":457.34,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":456.62,"speaker_name":"Rob Whalen"},{"text":"I don''t know.","index":135,"end_time":458.22,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":457.58,"speaker_name":"Rob Whalen"},{"text":"Yeah, I don''t.","index":136,"end_time":459.14,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":458.38,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I don''t know what that looks like, but certainly open to any.","index":137,"end_time":463.1,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":459.14,"speaker_name":"Rob Whalen"},{"text":"Any ideas about how to save money and on that and then.","index":138,"end_time":466.94,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":463.26,"speaker_name":"Rob Whalen"},{"text":"And then utilize it better to.","index":139,"end_time":468.54,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":466.94,"speaker_name":"Rob Whalen"},{"text":"Again.","index":140,"end_time":469.18,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":468.78,"speaker_name":"Rob Whalen"},{"text":"And I know you.","index":141,"end_time":471.22,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":470.46,"speaker_name":"Rob Whalen"},{"text":"You''ve heard this a million times, but it is a really big piece to this company is first meetings.","index":142,"end_time":476.73,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":471.22,"speaker_name":"Rob Whalen"},{"text":"Like, yep, we.","index":143,"end_time":478.17,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":476.73,"speaker_name":"Rob Whalen"},{"text":"We live and that''s.","index":144,"end_time":480.25,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":478.33,"speaker_name":"Rob Whalen"},{"text":"We judge everything by a first meeting.","index":145,"end_time":481.85,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":480.25,"speaker_name":"Rob Whalen"},{"text":"And I know that in marketing, there''s a lot of awareness and other things that you guys have done, which have been awesome.","index":146,"end_time":488.25,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":481.85,"speaker_name":"Rob Whalen"},{"text":"I mean, as far as I can tell, you''ve done a great job.","index":147,"end_time":492.25,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":489.13,"speaker_name":"Rob Whalen"},{"text":"I wish there was more first meetings out of what you guys have done, and I think, you know, that''s kind of a mutual thing.","index":148,"end_time":497.93,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":492.25,"speaker_name":"Rob Whalen"},{"text":"But, you know, as we kind of leverage moving Sam''s role over to you guys, it''s.","index":149,"end_time":507.22,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":497.93,"speaker_name":"Rob Whalen"},{"text":"It''s.","index":150,"end_time":507.94,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":507.38,"speaker_name":"Rob Whalen"},{"text":"It''s really how we''re going to grade you, and we''re.","index":151,"end_time":510.38,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":508.18,"speaker_name":"Rob Whalen"},{"text":"How we''re going to continue to grade this relationship.","index":152,"end_time":512.5,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":510.38,"speaker_name":"Rob Whalen"},{"text":"So that is.","index":153,"end_time":514.98,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":512.5,"speaker_name":"Rob Whalen"},{"text":"That''s just something that''s important.","index":154,"end_time":516.66,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":515.46,"speaker_name":"Rob Whalen"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":155,"end_time":517.54,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":517.06,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":156,"end_time":518.02,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":517.54,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"For everyone in your organization who''s touching this account to understand.","index":157,"end_time":522.1,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":518.34,"speaker_name":"Rob Whalen"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah, absolutely.","index":158,"end_time":524.82,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":522.58,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You know, our.","index":159,"end_time":526.75,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":524.98,"speaker_name":"Rob Whalen"},{"text":"Our salespeople need to be having first meetings demoing, and that''s.","index":160,"end_time":531.95,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":526.99,"speaker_name":"Rob Whalen"},{"text":"That''s where our revenue is coming in from.","index":161,"end_time":533.79,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":532.03,"speaker_name":"Rob Whalen"},{"text":"Yeah, absolutely.","index":162,"end_time":535.31,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":533.79,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":163,"end_time":536.19,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":535.71,"speaker_name":"Rob Whalen"},{"text":"So, I mean, from that standpoint, I, I like the idea of you guys doing it.","index":164,"end_time":543.55,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":536.67,"speaker_name":"Rob Whalen"},{"text":"You know, Sam had a weekly marketing meeting with me and Josh and our PR person.","index":165,"end_time":550.91,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":544.51,"speaker_name":"Rob Whalen"},{"text":"And I don''t know, Josh, I''m not quite sure how you''re thinking this might work with them from a Cadence standpoint, you know, kind of the weekly.","index":166,"end_time":564.7,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":554.02,"speaker_name":"Rob Whalen"},{"text":"Whether we just have them join your sales and marketing meeting or we have a.","index":167,"end_time":569.38,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":564.7,"speaker_name":"Rob Whalen"},{"text":"We continue to do a half an hour sales meeting.","index":168,"end_time":573.7,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":569.7,"speaker_name":"Rob Whalen"},{"text":"So, Colin, what does that look like when you do this for other organizations?","index":169,"end_time":586.32,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":582.16,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"So like, like Rob saying in when it was.","index":170,"end_time":589.56,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":586.48,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"And I had would have like a half an hour one on one every Monday where we would talk about you guys, we talk about 11x, we talk about the stuff the salespeople need.","index":171,"end_time":601.84,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":591.56,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"You know, we commiserate about the Eagles.","index":172,"end_time":604.82,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":601.92,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Then that afternoon we would have like a half an hour marketing meeting, which would be me, Sam, Rob, and Kristen, who''s our PR partner.","index":173,"end_time":620.66,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":607.46,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Then on Wednesdays, we run a 45 minute sales and marketing calls, primarily sales.","index":174,"end_time":629.54,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":623.22,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"There''s a section for channel and there''s a section for marketing.","index":175,"end_time":634.38,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":631.1,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"And I would say we probably do like 30 minutes of sales and then the other 15 minutes is marketing and channel.","index":176,"end_time":645.02,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":634.54,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Those are kind of all the meetings.","index":177,"end_time":648.1,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":646.3,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"And then obviously.","index":178,"end_time":648.82,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":648.1,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"And then we meet twice a week, like, like we have on the calendar now.","index":179,"end_time":651.7,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":648.82,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"So there''s probably a way to shift some of that around so it''s like a little bit more efficient.","index":180,"end_time":656.54,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":651.7,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Mm.","index":181,"end_time":657.27,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":656.95,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"But do you typically join those calls, like the ones I''m describing?","index":182,"end_time":662.31,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":657.43,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Yeah, I mean, it comes in all flavors, the relationships that we have.","index":183,"end_time":665.15,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":662.55,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So yeah, I mean, there''s some where we join internal calls and we can even be like a fly on the wall for like, the sales marketing side of things where, like, we''re picking up what the sales team is talking about their current week, and it generates marketing ideas for us.","index":184,"end_time":676.31,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":665.15,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We have calls where we just go through, like, how contacts are flowing through, new leads that have come in this week, you know, different things that we''ve changed on the HubSpot workflow side of things, all of that.","index":185,"end_time":687.61,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":677.03,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then oftentimes, honestly, Josh, we start out kind of heavy with those meetings.","index":186,"end_time":693.25,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":688.25,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then as clients get, like, more comfortable, they start to go towards like async of like, all right, you guys got it now I know.","index":187,"end_time":699.17,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":693.25,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I can see clearly through all of these dashboards and everything that we''ve built, like, everything that''s operating in the system.","index":188,"end_time":703.69,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":699.17,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So they tend to move more towards like an async after the first, you know, month, two months, three months.","index":189,"end_time":709.85,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":704.33,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":190,"end_time":710.74,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":710.34,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Just.","index":191,"end_time":711.42,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":711.06,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Just to give you like, a little bit of flavor for what those Wednesday meetings are.","index":192,"end_time":716.58,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":711.42,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"So, like, I''m just picking a random day from last year.","index":193,"end_time":719.9,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":716.98,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"But, like, we''ll come in, we''ll talk about the deals that are in commit right now and like, what do we need to do to get these done?","index":194,"end_time":726.379,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":719.9,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Is there any support that they need?","index":195,"end_time":728.82,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":726.379,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Dave, we''ll talk about what he''s working on in channel.","index":196,"end_time":732.5,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":729.54,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"And then Sam would be like, okay, HubSpot, we do this, this and this.","index":197,"end_time":736.9,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":732.5,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Here are some things that we''re working on, we''re working on the calendly integration.","index":198,"end_time":740.95,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":737.59,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"We have this Wednesday webinar that''s coming up.","index":199,"end_time":743.67,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":741.27,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"You know, in this case, we were working on like a customer survey that was getting sent out that you guys supported.","index":200,"end_time":749.75,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":744.87,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Do we have the list ready for it?","index":201,"end_time":751.43,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":749.83,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Who''s sending it, what is it coming from?","index":202,"end_time":753.67,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":751.91,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"You know, that''s the kind of stuff, I mean, I can just like, you know, like randomly pull in other, other dates.","index":203,"end_time":759.43,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":753.91,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"But like, here are some of the campaigns that we''re working on.","index":204,"end_time":762.71,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":759.43,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Here''s the people that have like, historically we were looking to, to run a report on who has requested a demo because Dan, at that time, Dan and John wanted to see how many of those converted to first meetings and how much of that was like low hanging fruit that they should set up a campaign for.","index":205,"end_time":780.77,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":763.57,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Right.","index":206,"end_time":781.17,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":780.77,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Here were the things that we had asked Sam for, like a retirement one pager.","index":207,"end_time":785.41,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":781.33,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"We had created this LinkedIn group, you know, like all of this kind of this, this is basically like what his portion is on the weekly call.","index":208,"end_time":793.42,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":785.81,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Right.","index":209,"end_time":794.14,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":793.74,"speaker_name":"Rob Whalen"},{"text":"That I would assume falls to you then.","index":210,"end_time":798.38,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":795.18,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah.","index":211,"end_time":799.42,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":798.7,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I mean all that stuff is, you know, happy to chat through all of it on a weekly basis.","index":212,"end_time":803.74,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":799.42,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":213,"end_time":804.38,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":803.9,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"And I took a screenshot while you had it up.","index":214,"end_time":808.74,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":807.1,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But also if you have that just to share as a document, that''d be great.","index":215,"end_time":811.58,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":808.74,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I wonder, can I share, I can share onenote outside of the organization, right, Rob?","index":216,"end_time":817.59,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":812.62,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Yeah, you just, it''ll, it''ll tell you that you''re sharing it outside the organization.","index":217,"end_time":822.79,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":818.39,"speaker_name":"Rob Whalen"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":218,"end_time":823.75,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":823.27,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"So.","index":219,"end_time":825.91,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":825.51,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"And you know, that was, those were the ones from, from last year.","index":220,"end_time":830.79,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":825.99,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Like, you know, today obviously we''re, we did ours, we did our meeting today.","index":221,"end_time":835.63,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":831.43,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Today we''re lighter on the marketing stuff, but it was like, okay, here''s the big deals in our pipeline.","index":222,"end_time":841.63,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":835.63,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Steph and Dan were sharing things that happened in those meetings that like maybe were somewhat unique so that if it comes up for the other one, they can kind of hear a little bit of the backstory.","index":223,"end_time":852.27,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":843.07,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"We were talking about how we''re changing our pricing.","index":224,"end_time":854.35,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":852.27,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"We''re talking about some of the stuff we need to do from a forecasting perspective.","index":225,"end_time":858.43,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":854.35,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Dave is talking about his channels.","index":226,"end_time":860.31,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":858.91,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"And then the marketing stuff that I put together is like, here''s what we''re working on with 11x.","index":227,"end_time":865.87,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":860.31,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"I gave them links to the copy for them to review and, and edit if they want to, making sure everybody knew we have those 11 pages that you sent us so that we can provide some feedback for it.","index":228,"end_time":878.14,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":866.78,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Right.","index":229,"end_time":878.78,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":878.38,"speaker_name":"Rob Whalen"},{"text":"You know, reminded them that we''re waiting on that cheat sheet for the current campaigns of what they need to do.","index":230,"end_time":883.18,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":878.78,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"You know, this is like what it''s looking like now but it''s me putting it together and then quite honestly not really having that much time to work on this kind of stuff.","index":231,"end_time":891.3,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":884.7,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"It''s more of like.","index":232,"end_time":891.9,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":891.3,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Right.","index":233,"end_time":892.22,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":891.9,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"The stuff that I need to almost like a reminder to myself of the stuff that I need to bring to you.","index":234,"end_time":897.31,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":892.91,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":235,"end_time":897.79,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":897.47,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And you need someone to own this.","index":236,"end_time":898.87,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":897.79,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":237,"end_time":899.15,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":898.87,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And that''s absolutely what we would do.","index":238,"end_time":900.31,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":899.15,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":239,"end_time":900.75,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":900.31,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But so that''s, that''s, you know, and then the, you know, like right now I need a one pager on instant cash which we''re rolling out later this year because Sam has done these for us and he''s still working for us like on a contract basis.","index":240,"end_time":924.41,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":906.11,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"I sent that to him to say like, you know, can you work on this?","index":241,"end_time":930.85,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":924.73,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"And Rob, we need to get him the stuff that he said.","index":242,"end_time":932.81,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":930.85,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"But ideally I would be sending that to you.","index":243,"end_time":934.65,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":932.81,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":244,"end_time":935.25,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":934.81,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And yeah, I know like we use, have used FIGMA historically.","index":245,"end_time":940.13,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":935.25,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Do you use something else?","index":246,"end_time":941.45,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":940.13,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"No, we use figma.","index":247,"end_time":942.53,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":941.53,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Use figma.","index":248,"end_time":943.37,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":942.53,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":249,"end_time":943.77,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":943.37,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Oh yeah, there''s CANVA and figma.","index":250,"end_time":946.05,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":943.77,"speaker_name":"Rob Whalen"},{"text":"Yeah, that was a fractional CMO that said canva.","index":251,"end_time":948.81,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":946.05,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":252,"end_time":949.91,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":949.59,"speaker_name":"Rob Whalen"},{"text":"And you have access to FIGMA now.","index":253,"end_time":951.91,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":949.99,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah, Sam got us that.","index":254,"end_time":953.83,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":952.15,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So it would be like, you know, let''s take a look at the emergency savings data sheet that we created in the past and kind of like replicate that to make one for instant cash.","index":255,"end_time":965.43,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":954.07,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Right.","index":256,"end_time":966.23,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":965.83,"speaker_name":"Rob Whalen"},{"text":"But again ideally I''d rather send it to you than send it to Sam, but it would just seem easier because of the familiarity he has with it to send it to him now.","index":257,"end_time":976.66,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":967.59,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"But at some point just gotta cut the cord and move it.","index":258,"end_time":981.06,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":976.66,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah, we just have.","index":259,"end_time":982.46,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":981.06,"speaker_name":"Rob Whalen"},{"text":"That''s exactly what we''re trying to do here is cut the cord.","index":260,"end_time":985.54,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":982.46,"speaker_name":"Rob Whalen"},{"text":"So.","index":261,"end_time":987.06,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":986.66,"speaker_name":"Rob Whalen"},{"text":"But can you, can you also kind of like alluded to this a little bit but like I think I was joking with you guys last week of like I''m saying the words HubSpot Audit but I don''t really even know like what I''m asking for.","index":262,"end_time":1001.46,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":987.54,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Yeah, you''re pretty familiar with our, our HubSpot at this point.","index":263,"end_time":1006.42,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1003.46,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Like what would you do?","index":264,"end_time":1008.42,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1006.42,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"So honestly, so I, I kind of listed there''s three main objects that I want to look at inside you guys HubSpot and that''s just the custom properties that have been set up, the workflows and the automated nurture campaigns in a high capacity.","index":265,"end_time":1022.86,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1009.78,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Because you know, to be totally frank, when I hopped in first into your guys HubSpot account, the amount of properties that Seem almost duplicative is very high, which leads to confusion for the marketing and the sales team and executive leadership of, like, where''s the source of truth in all of this?","index":266,"end_time":1040.879,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1022.86,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we''d start by cleaning all of those up, and then that leads into, you know, I''m working on the workflow document for, like, where it stands right now.","index":267,"end_time":1047.799,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1041.359,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But that would lead into, like, a new adjusted workflow that is much easier for everyone to understand and that basically the sales team would marketing pass a lead over to sales.","index":268,"end_time":1057.7,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1047.799,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Sales would know exactly what to do with it, and then the workflow would take care of the rest is how HubSpot should operate.","index":269,"end_time":1063.1,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1057.7,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But the way that it''s been right now is creating, it seems, more questions than answers sometimes for the sales team.","index":270,"end_time":1069.66,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1063.1,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So, yeah, in that audit, we would call out all of our findings and make our recommendations, and then if you guys sign off on our recommendations, then we would just build it all.","index":271,"end_time":1080.62,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1073.9,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"How long do you think that would take?","index":272,"end_time":1090.63,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1089.43,"speaker_name":"Rob Whalen"},{"text":"I mean, you know, for signed this week, I have the audit done early next week, and we could start doing the work the week after.","index":273,"end_time":1098.87,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1092.39,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Probably pretty quickly.","index":274,"end_time":1100.47,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1099.11,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":275,"end_time":1101.11,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1100.79,"speaker_name":"Rob Whalen"},{"text":"How much time do you think the audit would.","index":276,"end_time":1102.59,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1101.11,"speaker_name":"Rob Whalen"},{"text":"Will take, though?","index":277,"end_time":1103.23,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1102.59,"speaker_name":"Rob Whalen"},{"text":"I mean, when I.","index":278,"end_time":1103.79,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1103.23,"speaker_name":"Rob Whalen"},{"text":"When I think about these points and other stuff, you know, just in my brain.","index":279,"end_time":1107.27,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1103.79,"speaker_name":"Rob Whalen"},{"text":"Yeah, the audit would probably take about two days, just running through everything.","index":280,"end_time":1110.94,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1107.58,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So 16 hours of work.","index":281,"end_time":1113.02,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1111.42,"speaker_name":"Rob Whalen"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":282,"end_time":1114.5,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1114.14,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I mean.","index":283,"end_time":1114.94,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1114.5,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":284,"end_time":1115.86,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1115.5,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":285,"end_time":1116.22,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1115.86,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Roughly.","index":286,"end_time":1116.86,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1116.22,"speaker_name":"Rob Whalen"},{"text":"Okay.","index":287,"end_time":1117.74,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1117.1,"speaker_name":"Rob Whalen"},{"text":"And then the work to change it all would be, you know, many more hours, if you''re thinking at terms of hours.","index":288,"end_time":1128.94,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1121.82,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But then there''s also the upkeep, the new needs, you know, that arise all the time for what the system needs to do.","index":289,"end_time":1136.77,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1130.54,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":290,"end_time":1138.85,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1138.37,"speaker_name":"Rob Whalen"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":291,"end_time":1145.45,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1145.01,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Because I''m like, I''m okay in HubSpot, but there''s, you know, stuff that I know that I would want to do that I would just send it to Sam because he could do it in half the time that I wanted to.","index":292,"end_time":1158.57,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1145.45,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"So not even like this stuff that you''re talking about, which is more like custom properties and workflows and stuff, but it''s like, you know, some reports and some dashboards and things like that that we''ve created for the team.","index":293,"end_time":1170.12,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1158.57,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Although actually, I think I created those dashboards, so that''s not a good example.","index":294,"end_time":1173.6,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1170.6,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"But whatever.","index":295,"end_time":1174.64,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1173.6,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"You kind of know, I mean, like, I would just be like, just kind of shoveling stuff over to Sam and saying, yeah, you know, this is.","index":296,"end_time":1179.88,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1174.64,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"We need this, or.","index":297,"end_time":1181.6,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1180.44,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Or, you know, there''s a property we need to include in the deal so that we can track to Dave, can track the channel partners can you take this list of the 200 people that we know have already referred us a deal and start with that on the property?","index":298,"end_time":1200.01,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1181.6,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"And then every time we need to add somebody to the property, either I''m doing it or Sam''s doing it or whatever.","index":299,"end_time":1204.77,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1200.01,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Right.","index":300,"end_time":1205.329,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1204.93,"speaker_name":"Rob Whalen"},{"text":"Yeah, we would absolutely do that.","index":301,"end_time":1206.57,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1205.329,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then, you know, even the conversations we have of like, all right, well, let''s build, you know, four main industry nurture campaigns.","index":302,"end_time":1212.21,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1206.57,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Cool.","index":303,"end_time":1212.61,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1212.21,"speaker_name":"Rob Whalen"},{"text":"All right.","index":304,"end_time":1212.97,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1212.61,"speaker_name":"Rob Whalen"},{"text":"Log off that meeting and build.","index":305,"end_time":1214.69,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1212.97,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I mean, that''s what we''re working on as well.","index":306,"end_time":1216.21,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1214.69,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":307,"end_time":1219.29,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1218.85,"speaker_name":"Rob Whalen"},{"text":"The other thing that I need to ask is just what''s the.","index":308,"end_time":1222.61,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1219.29,"speaker_name":"Rob Whalen"},{"text":"The out in the agreement?","index":309,"end_time":1224.77,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1223.09,"speaker_name":"Rob Whalen"},{"text":"Let''s say we get three months, four months down in this relationship and we decide to go and hire someone like a Sam internally instead.","index":310,"end_time":1232.45,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1224.77,"speaker_name":"Rob Whalen"},{"text":"You know, what is.","index":311,"end_time":1235.33,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1234.61,"speaker_name":"Rob Whalen"},{"text":"What does that look like?","index":312,"end_time":1236.29,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1235.33,"speaker_name":"Rob Whalen"},{"text":"Yeah, on that.","index":313,"end_time":1237.97,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1237.25,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I would have to confirm with Justin on the contract because I know he just sent over, like, a plan option to Josh.","index":314,"end_time":1245.75,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1237.97,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I just have to confirm the contract language with him and get back to you.","index":315,"end_time":1248.43,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1245.75,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, I thought it''d be great.","index":316,"end_time":1249.99,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1248.75,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Standing from the conversation was like, we can just bring it back down to the same level that we''re at now.","index":317,"end_time":1255.31,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1249.99,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Yeah, probably.","index":318,"end_time":1257.71,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1256.43,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":319,"end_time":1258.03,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1257.71,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I just want to confirm with them.","index":320,"end_time":1259.15,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1258.03,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, well, let''s get it rolling.","index":321,"end_time":1264.35,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1262.99,"speaker_name":"Rob Whalen"},{"text":"Let''s.","index":322,"end_time":1265.07,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1264.51,"speaker_name":"Rob Whalen"},{"text":"Let''s.","index":323,"end_time":1265.79,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1265.23,"speaker_name":"Rob Whalen"},{"text":"Let''s get this thing rolling and let''s get.","index":324,"end_time":1267.99,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1266.27,"speaker_name":"Rob Whalen"},{"text":"Get moving.","index":325,"end_time":1268.55,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1267.99,"speaker_name":"Rob Whalen"},{"text":"It''s already January 15th, and I can''t.","index":326,"end_time":1271.74,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1268.55,"speaker_name":"Rob Whalen"},{"text":"We can''t wait.","index":327,"end_time":1272.7,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1271.74,"speaker_name":"Rob Whalen"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah, Totally hear you.","index":328,"end_time":1273.94,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1272.78,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we''ll get an amendment drafted up.","index":329,"end_time":1275.22,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1273.94,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I. I''ll get that answer to your question first, Rob.","index":330,"end_time":1277.34,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1275.22,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then, I mean, we''ll.","index":331,"end_time":1280.18,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1278.06,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We can start the work ahead of time.","index":332,"end_time":1281.74,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1280.18,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That amendment will reflect starting in February, but we can start the audit and everything right away.","index":333,"end_time":1285.82,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1281.98,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":334,"end_time":1286.86,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1286.38,"speaker_name":"Rob Whalen"},{"text":"And.","index":335,"end_time":1287.42,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1287.02,"speaker_name":"Rob Whalen"},{"text":"And, you know, just again, put in your notes.","index":336,"end_time":1291.02,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1288.06,"speaker_name":"Rob Whalen"},{"text":"We are evaluating you on first meeting.","index":337,"end_time":1292.86,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1291.02,"speaker_name":"Rob Whalen"},{"text":"Yeah, just.","index":338,"end_time":1293.82,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1293.02,"speaker_name":"Rob Whalen"},{"text":"We.","index":339,"end_time":1294.3,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1293.98,"speaker_name":"Rob Whalen"},{"text":"We evaluate our channel on first meeting.","index":340,"end_time":1296.63,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1294.3,"speaker_name":"Rob Whalen"},{"text":"We evaluate everyone on meeting.","index":341,"end_time":1298.67,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1296.87,"speaker_name":"Rob Whalen"},{"text":"So just know that.","index":342,"end_time":1300.63,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1298.67,"speaker_name":"Rob Whalen"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":343,"end_time":1301.11,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1300.71,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You''ll be.","index":344,"end_time":1301.55,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1301.11,"speaker_name":"Rob Whalen"},{"text":"You''ll be graded on first meeting.","index":345,"end_time":1303.03,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1301.55,"speaker_name":"Rob Whalen"},{"text":"Absolutely.","index":346,"end_time":1304.15,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1303.43,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So Josh.","index":347,"end_time":1306.43,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1304.47,"speaker_name":"Rob Whalen"},{"text":"Josh hates me.","index":348,"end_time":1307.35,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1306.43,"speaker_name":"Rob Whalen"},{"text":"No, I mean, it''s just what it is.","index":349,"end_time":1310.95,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1308.15,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"It is what it is.","index":350,"end_time":1311.87,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1310.95,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"I mean, the thing.","index":351,"end_time":1312.63,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1311.87,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Yeah, it is what it is.","index":352,"end_time":1314.79,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1313.35,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"The thing we know is, like, Dan and I were talking about this yesterday.","index":353,"end_time":1319.43,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1315.19,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Is like some of these BDR groups that we work with.","index":354,"end_time":1327.28,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1319.59,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"As Dan likes to say, it''s like, stick a quarter in the machine and get a gumball.","index":355,"end_time":1331.6,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1328.08,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Like, that''s.","index":356,"end_time":1332.24,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1331.6,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"That''s the way that they''re designed.","index":357,"end_time":1333.68,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1332.24,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"We know some of the kind of work you''re doing is more like, go to the gym.","index":358,"end_time":1338.8,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1333.68,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"The results show over time.","index":359,"end_time":1340.8,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1339.12,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"But to Rob''s point, like I do think that we''ve been working together now at a.","index":360,"end_time":1346.72,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1341.68,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Long enough at a point that we just, we just need to see the actual conversion of this.","index":361,"end_time":1351.29,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1347.09,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Of the stuff.","index":362,"end_time":1352.13,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1351.29,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Yep.","index":363,"end_time":1352.77,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1352.21,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":364,"end_time":1353.33,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1352.85,"speaker_name":"Rob Whalen"},{"text":"And there''s certainly a lot more that we''re going to be asking you to do that''s, that''s foundational to marketing.","index":365,"end_time":1359.65,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1353.89,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"But at the end of the day we, we need to.","index":366,"end_time":1361.73,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1359.81,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"We did not get very many marketing generated first meetings last year.","index":367,"end_time":1368.93,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1362.929,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"We were overly reliant on channel and we did a good job of closing those deals.","index":368,"end_time":1373.85,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1369.01,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"But like if we can get the marketing arm to generate what it used to in the past, we''ll just freaking kill it.","index":369,"end_time":1383.39,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1373.85,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"So.","index":370,"end_time":1384.75,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1384.43,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Yeah, absolutely.","index":371,"end_time":1386.19,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1384.75,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":372,"end_time":1387.47,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1386.99,"speaker_name":"Rob Whalen"},{"text":"And that''s, that''s kind of, kind of how we got to operate.","index":373,"end_time":1390.67,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1387.71,"speaker_name":"Rob Whalen"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah.","index":374,"end_time":1392.71,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1391.55,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Same page.","index":375,"end_time":1393.31,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1392.71,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":376,"end_time":1394.23,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1393.79,"speaker_name":"Rob Whalen"},{"text":"So and the other thing is my urgency.","index":377,"end_time":1398.51,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1394.23,"speaker_name":"Rob Whalen"},{"text":"Right.","index":378,"end_time":1398.99,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1398.59,"speaker_name":"Rob Whalen"},{"text":"Q1, the first part of the year from January till end of April.","index":379,"end_time":1405.88,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1398.99,"speaker_name":"Rob Whalen"},{"text":"It''s just critical because that''s when people are looking at their new benefits that they''re going to launch in next year.","index":380,"end_time":1412.6,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1406.36,"speaker_name":"Rob Whalen"},{"text":"They''ll close in June, July, August, launch in October, November, December type deal.","index":381,"end_time":1421.08,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1413.8,"speaker_name":"Rob Whalen"},{"text":"So it''s really important that we get hammering and investing in Q1 marketing and, and deal flow.","index":382,"end_time":1428.08,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1421.08,"speaker_name":"Rob Whalen"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah.","index":383,"end_time":1428.84,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1428.24,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And that''s why we''re excited to launch these new pages and send people to some new landing pages with more conversion optimization in them.","index":384,"end_time":1435.52,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1428.84,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":385,"end_time":1436.56,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1436,"speaker_name":"Rob Whalen"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":386,"end_time":1437.2,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1436.72,"speaker_name":"Rob Whalen"},{"text":"Okay, I''m done.","index":387,"end_time":1439.52,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1437.68,"speaker_name":"Rob Whalen"},{"text":"All right, Rob, send me the agreement.","index":388,"end_time":1442.92,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1441.28,"speaker_name":"Rob Whalen"},{"text":"Let''s get it rolling.","index":389,"end_time":1443.68,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1442.92,"speaker_name":"Rob Whalen"},{"text":"Will do.","index":390,"end_time":1444.4,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1443.84,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":391,"end_time":1445.76,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1445.28,"speaker_name":"Rob Whalen"},{"text":"What''s the instacash meeting that we''re about to have?","index":392,"end_time":1448.24,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1445.84,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"You don''t have to be there if you don''t want to.","index":393,"end_time":1451.76,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1449.92,"speaker_name":"Rob Whalen"},{"text":"It''s.","index":394,"end_time":1452.24,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1451.76,"speaker_name":"Rob Whalen"},{"text":"We''re looking at what Gordon has built from an instacach already and talking through exactly what needs to be built for engineering.","index":395,"end_time":1458.95,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1453.11,"speaker_name":"Rob Whalen"},{"text":"Okay.","index":396,"end_time":1459.91,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1459.43,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Rob, I might just be listening off camera.","index":397,"end_time":1463.55,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1459.91,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"I gotta.","index":398,"end_time":1464.15,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1463.55,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"But yeah, yeah, yeah.","index":399,"end_time":1466.47,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1465.27,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Okay.","index":400,"end_time":1467.03,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1466.47,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"I just didn''t not want to invite you being that you''re gonna have to be selling the.","index":401,"end_time":1471.59,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1468.39,"speaker_name":"Rob Whalen"},{"text":"Yeah, good idea.","index":402,"end_time":1475.11,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1472.55,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"I figured.","index":403,"end_time":1477.27,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1476.63,"speaker_name":"Rob Whalen"},{"text":"So the other thing, Colin, just in your tuck away in the back of your mind, we are going to be doing like we''re bringing in every, all the salespeople really everybody from the company for like an all hands meeting Most likely on February 10th.","index":404,"end_time":1497.87,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1477.27,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Yep.","index":405,"end_time":1498.75,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1498.19,"speaker_name":"Rob Whalen"},{"text":"If we can try to reserve some of your time so that you can join virtually.","index":406,"end_time":1503.03,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1499.07,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"I mean I don''t know if you want to make the trip to Seattle, but if you want to join virtually for, for some of it or whatever, we would love to have you in There.","index":407,"end_time":1511.61,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1503.03,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Because there''s gonna be a lot of stuff we''re talking about.","index":408,"end_time":1513.29,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1511.61,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah, that''d be great.","index":409,"end_time":1514.81,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1513.37,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":410,"end_time":1516.65,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1516.09,"speaker_name":"Rob Whalen"},{"text":"Okay, thanks for the time.","index":411,"end_time":1520.41,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1517.45,"speaker_name":"Rob Whalen"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":412,"end_time":1520.93,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1520.57,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Thank you guys.","index":413,"end_time":1521.53,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1520.93,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"To join if you wanted to be there in person and meet.","index":414,"end_time":1524.01,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1521.53,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Meet everybody.","index":415,"end_time":1525.09,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1524.25,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"But yeah, I know that''s a lot for, you know, probably what would end up being like a half a day.","index":416,"end_time":1529.93,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1525.09,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":417,"end_time":1530.89,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1530.33,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So maybe.","index":418,"end_time":1533.06,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1531.86,"speaker_name":"Rob Whalen"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":419,"end_time":1533.62,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1533.14,"speaker_name":"Rob Whalen"},{"text":"The other thing, Colin, I do want to let you know, like, since we''re doing this, if you see things that, that you''re not getting from us, that, that are going to help deliver on what you think might be first, you know, that.","index":420,"end_time":1545.9,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1533.94,"speaker_name":"Rob Whalen"},{"text":"That objective, then, then we need to hear about it and we need to make sure that you''re getting the data, the information, whatever it is to be able to do your job.","index":421,"end_time":1557.95,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1545.9,"speaker_name":"Rob Whalen"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":422,"end_time":1558.51,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1558.11,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Period.","index":423,"end_time":1558.83,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1558.51,"speaker_name":"Rob Whalen"},{"text":"Okay.","index":424,"end_time":1559.63,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1559.15,"speaker_name":"Rob Whalen"},{"text":"So.","index":425,"end_time":1560.11,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1559.71,"speaker_name":"Rob Whalen"},{"text":"So feel confident that we want to give you everything that we have to.","index":426,"end_time":1564.67,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1560.43,"speaker_name":"Rob Whalen"},{"text":"To make your job easier.","index":427,"end_time":1565.87,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1564.67,"speaker_name":"Rob Whalen"},{"text":"Yeah, I appreciate that.","index":428,"end_time":1567.19,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1566.11,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And I think joining those sales and marketing meetings adds all the benefit to that as well.","index":429,"end_time":1571.15,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1567.19,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":430,"end_time":1571.99,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1571.55,"speaker_name":"Rob Whalen"},{"text":"Okay.","index":431,"end_time":1572.51,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1571.99,"speaker_name":"Rob Whalen"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":432,"end_time":1573.23,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1572.67,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"All right, well, thank you guys both for your time.","index":433,"end_time":1575.39,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1573.47,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, real quick, when, when we''re reviewing or Rob, you can drop.","index":434,"end_time":1581.19,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1575.39,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"I just.","index":435,"end_time":1581.43,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1581.19,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"I got a couple questions for, For Colin.","index":436,"end_time":1583.67,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1581.43,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"You got it.","index":437,"end_time":1584.19,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1583.67,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Later, Colin.","index":438,"end_time":1584.91,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1584.19,"speaker_name":"Rob Whalen"},{"text":"See you.","index":439,"end_time":1585.47,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1584.91,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So for the, the industry or like the 11 pages that you send or whatever it was, I haven''t really like jumped into looking at them yet and I haven''t done much of this kind of review, but when I, like when I come into this page, this pop up is showing up and so you.","index":440,"end_time":1603.83,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1587.07,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"See at the top of the page it says browse.","index":441,"end_time":1605.39,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1603.83,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":442,"end_time":1606.19,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1605.71,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"So you can click that and then you can basically use it as a web page now.","index":443,"end_time":1609.63,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1606.43,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":444,"end_time":1610.52,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1610.12,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"And then if we have suggestions, then.","index":445,"end_time":1613.6,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1610.68,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"You just hit the comment button at the top and then just drop it wherever.","index":446,"end_time":1616.84,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1613.6,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Just click and type.","index":447,"end_time":1618.2,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1617.08,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":448,"end_time":1618.84,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1618.28,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"And that''s the best way for us to do it is to drop.","index":449,"end_time":1622.04,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1619.72,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":450,"end_time":1623.16,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1622.76,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Comments directly in here.","index":451,"end_time":1624.32,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1623.16,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":452,"end_time":1624.84,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1624.32,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Sweet.","index":453,"end_time":1627.72,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1627.16,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"So this is a live view of the web page.","index":454,"end_time":1630.44,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1628.28,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Do you have a deadline?","index":455,"end_time":1632.2,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1630.84,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"So, so where would this be?","index":456,"end_time":1634.96,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1633.08,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"This is the.","index":457,"end_time":1635.64,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1634.96,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"This is the like main industry page.","index":458,"end_time":1639.51,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1637.35,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we would add this to the navigation and then there would be a drop down for all of the other industry pages.","index":459,"end_time":1644.79,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1640.15,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, so we would add industries up there in the menu.","index":460,"end_time":1648.83,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1646.71,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But this isn''t the home page.","index":461,"end_time":1650.19,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1648.83,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"This is the home industry page.","index":462,"end_time":1651.83,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1650.19,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Or this is the homepage.","index":463,"end_time":1653.03,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1651.83,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"No, that is just the.","index":464,"end_time":1654.31,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1653.11,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So there''s like an industries like parent page and that''s what you''re looking at.","index":465,"end_time":1658.95,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1654.31,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then, so like if someone clicked on industries in the navigation, that''s where they would be.","index":466,"end_time":1666.75,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1660.07,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":467,"end_time":1667.79,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1667.15,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"And then I thought I clicked on homepage, but maybe I clicked.","index":468,"end_time":1671.15,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1668.11,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"No, no, the one that''s listed as homepage.","index":469,"end_time":1675.07,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1671.15,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Maybe the link got messed up is bringing me here.","index":470,"end_time":1678.03,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1675.63,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That''s why I was confused then.","index":471,"end_time":1681.27,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1679.07,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"The one that''s.","index":472,"end_time":1682.27,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1681.27,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"That''s labeled as Industries is the same.","index":473,"end_time":1685.63,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1683.07,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"It''s the same URL.","index":474,"end_time":1687.39,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1686.19,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"So.","index":475,"end_time":1688.12,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1687.88,"speaker_name":"Rob Whalen"},{"text":"Okay.","index":476,"end_time":1689.08,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1688.52,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, it looks like the home page.","index":477,"end_time":1691.4,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1689.96,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":478,"end_time":1692.2,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1691.64,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Actually integrations looks like it''s the same URL also, those three.","index":479,"end_time":1701.08,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1692.2,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Yeah, I''ll have Nina correct that.","index":480,"end_time":1703.48,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1701.8,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":481,"end_time":1704.2,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1703.639,"speaker_name":"Rob Whalen"},{"text":"Yep.","index":482,"end_time":1704.92,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1704.36,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Do you have a, like a deadline for us to review this?","index":483,"end_time":1710.76,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1705.32,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"I would like to get these up within maybe the next week or two because this is going to be part of the new campaign ideas that I''m going to be pitching tomorrow.","index":484,"end_time":1721.51,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1711.64,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":485,"end_time":1723.67,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1723.11,"speaker_name":"Rob Whalen"},{"text":"All right.","index":486,"end_time":1725.59,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1725.19,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"If you can get Nina to send the updated ones, that would be great.","index":487,"end_time":1728.75,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1725.59,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"And then we''ll get to.","index":488,"end_time":1729.63,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1728.75,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"We''ll get to work on it.","index":489,"end_time":1730.63,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1729.63,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":490,"end_time":1731.349,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1730.79,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right, thanks.","index":491,"end_time":1733.51,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1732.31,"speaker_name":"Rob Whalen"},{"text":"Go get some food.","index":492,"end_time":1734.39,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1733.51,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Thank you.","index":493,"end_time":1735.27,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1734.63,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"See ya.","index":494,"end_time":1736.35,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1735.83,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Bye.","index":495,"end_time":1736.79,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1736.35,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"}],"dateString":"2026-01-14T20:30:00.000Z","host_email":"colin.costigan@marketersindemand.com","meeting_link":"https://us02web.zoom.us/j/83190423914?pwd=3xQmGfpJHM0DYk8qWbb2SbuaAWe9fY.1","participants":["rob@ptoexchange.com,josh@ptoexchange.com,colin.costigan@marketersindemand.com","rob@ptoexchange.com","josh@ptoexchange.com"],"transcript_url":"https://app.fireflies.ai/view/01KET2R1APCG3CJMH8AZQNA7HD","organizer_email":"colin.costigan@marketersindemand.com"}'::jsonb,
    '{"label":"positive","confidence":0.92,"bullets":["Approved HubSpot audit to begin immediately, with implementation planned to start the following week.","Colin confirmed marketing will be assessed on first meetings; alignment reinforced by Rob and Josh.","Weekly cadence and integration into sales/marketing meetings established to streamline workflow.","Colin identified property duplication, offering cleanup to clarify sales-marketing handoff in HubSpot.","Leadership approved increased point-based service tier to expand capacity while reducing marginal cost."],"highlights":[{"quote":"Let''s get this thing rolling and let''s get moving.","speaker":"Rob Whalen"},{"quote":"We can start the audit and everything right away.","speaker":"Colin Costigan"},{"quote":"We are evaluating you on first meeting.","speaker":"Rob Whalen"}],"topics":["delivery","workflow","hubspot","metrics","sales"],"model":"gpt-4-1106-preview","version":1,"generated_at":"2026-01-14T23:28:00Z"}'::jsonb,
    '{"fireflies_summary":{"notes":"## **HubSpot System Audit and Optimization**\n\nThe team agreed to conduct a thorough **HubSpot audit** to clean up properties, workflows, and campaigns for clearer sales-marketing alignment and cost savings (04:14).\n\n- **Colin Costigan** outlined that the audit will focus on reducing duplicative custom properties, simplifying workflows, and optimizing automated nurture campaigns to reduce confusion and improve lead handoff (16:49).\n- The audit is expected to take **two days (16 hours)**, with results delivered early next week and implementation starting the following week once signed (18:27).\n- The cleanup aims to streamline sales processes, ensuring leads pass smoothly from marketing to sales with clear roles and automated follow-ups (18:58).\n- This effort will also identify data cleanup opportunities that could reduce storage costs and improve system efficiency, aligning with **Rob Whalen’s** priority to maximize HubSpot ROI (06:41).\n\n## **Marketing and Sales Meeting Cadence Integration**\n\nThey decided to integrate the marketing and sales meeting rhythms to improve communication and ownership of marketing deliverables (09:42).\n\n- **Josh Reinhard** described the current weekly structure: a Monday one-on-one, a Monday marketing meeting, and a Wednesday joint sales-marketing call focusing primarily on sales but including marketing and channel updates (09:42).\n- **Colin Costigan** emphasized starting with heavier meeting involvement, then shifting toward asynchronous updates as trust and dashboard transparency grow over 1-3 months (11:02).\n- The team agreed that **Colin’s group would take over Sam’s marketing tasks**, including campaign updates, collateral like one-pagers, and HubSpot maintenance, improving efficiency and accountability (13:15).\n- They plan to share living documents via OneNote and use Figma for campaign design, ensuring smooth handoffs and centralized feedback (15:34).\n\n## **Contract Amendment and Partnership Expectations**\n\nThe group committed to moving forward with a contract amendment starting in **February**, with the audit work to begin immediately upon approval (21:02).\n\n- **Rob Whalen** stressed the importance of measuring success by the number of **first meetings generated**, defining this as the key metric for ongoing evaluation of the partnership (21:26).\n- **Colin Costigan** will confirm contract exit terms with Justin to understand the flexibility if the company hires internally later (20:37).\n- The amendment will reflect a service upgrade from **80 points ($8,000) to 130 points ($10,000)** monthly, increasing service scope by **$5,000** while raising cost by $2,000, improving value (05:33).\n- Rob emphasized urgency to ramp up marketing efforts in **Q1 (January to April)** because that is when clients plan new benefit launches for the second half of the year (23:13).\n\n## **First Meeting Pipeline and Lead Management**\n\nThey identified issues with lifecycle stage mismanagement and inconsistent lead tagging, causing confusion and inefficiencies in deal tracking (01:00).\n\n- **Josh Reinhard** noted the need to correct reps’ misunderstanding of lifecycle stages, clarifying that first meetings should not move contacts directly to opportunity without a deal created in HubSpot (02:19).\n- There is currently no evidence of deals tagged to the **New North** lead source despite ongoing activity, indicating a need for workflow cleanup and accurate source tracking (03:04).\n- The team acknowledged that improving lead qualification and pipeline hygiene will directly support the goal of increasing first meetings, the primary revenue driver (01:09).\n- Rob highlighted the importance of the sales team focusing on first meetings and demos as the primary revenue lever, reinforcing that all marketing and sales efforts must align with this objective (08:44).\n\n## **Product and Campaign Development Timeline**\n\nThe team plans to launch new **industry pages and landing pages** with conversion optimization within the next **one to two weeks** to support upcoming campaigns (27:02).\n\n- Colin requested feedback on the draft pages via comments directly on the live pages, aiming for quick iteration and deployment ahead of a campaign pitch scheduled the following day (27:55).\n- They will fix navigation and URL issues promptly to avoid confusion during review (28:21).\n- Josh confirmed that past marketing assets like one-pagers (e.g., for instant cash) will be transitioned from Sam to Colin’s team, ensuring continuity and easier future updates (15:06).\n- The team uses Figma for design work and plans to replicate successful past assets to accelerate development of new campaign materials (15:41).\n\n## **Leadership Visibility and Collaboration**\n\nThere is a plan for **Colin Costigan** to virtually join an all-hands meeting on **February 10th** to increase visibility and alignment across the company (24:58).\n\n- Rob emphasized the need for open communication and data sharing to support the marketing team’s work, committing to provide all necessary info to achieve first meeting goals (25:31).\n- Colin confirmed that joining regular sales and marketing calls will help uncover insights and enable more targeted marketing efforts, improving responsiveness to sales needs (26:06).\n- The collaboration aims to create a feedback loop where marketing ideas directly respond to sales team challenges, driving improved deal flow and conversion (11:02).","outline":null,"keywords":["HubSpot audit","first meetings","marketing optimization","point system pricing","workflow cleanup","sales and marketing integration"],"overview":"- **HubSpot Audit:** The team will audit HubSpot to streamline processes, reduce confusion, and enhance cost efficiency.  \n- **Timeline:** Audit expected to last 16 hours, with results early next week and implementation available soon after approval.  \n- **Meeting Integration:** Marketing and sales meetings will align for better communication, starting with increased involvement and later asynchronous updates.  \n- **Contract Changes:** Contract amendment will begin in February, raising service scope and cost while prioritizing first meetings as a success metric.  \n- **Lead Management Issues:** Lifecycle mismanagement and inconsistent lead tagging need correction to improve first meeting generation and deal tracking.  \n- **Campaign Development:** New industry pages aimed for launch in one to two weeks, using Figma for design and feedback for quick iteration.","action_items":"\n**Colin Costigan**\nDraft and send amendment confirming contract terms and start date; clarify out clause regarding internal hire scenario (20:37)\nBegin HubSpot audit immediately upon contract finalization, targeting completion early next week (18:12)\nConduct detailed cleanup of HubSpot custom properties, workflows, and nurture campaigns post-audit, pending client approval (17:59)\nJoin sales and marketing meetings regularly to stay informed and foster collaboration (26:06)\nPrepare to participate virtually in the all-hands meeting on February 10th (24:58)\nCoordinate with Nina to fix URL errors on industry pages and share updated links for review (27:47)\nLaunch new industry landing pages with conversion optimization within 1-2 weeks to support upcoming campaigns (23:48)\n\n**Josh Reinhard**\nShare past meeting documentation and OneNote notes with Colin to facilitate transition (13:32)\nProvide content and feedback for the new industry pages once updated links are shared (28:45)\nTransfer marketing task requests, such as the instant cash one-pager, to Colin and his team going forward (15:34)\nAssist in coordinating internal stakeholder communications and feedback loops during audit and implementation phases (15:34)\n\n**Rob Whalen**\nApprove amendment and push to get agreement finalized to enable audit and work to start immediately (21:02)\nEnsure open communication of data, information, and resources needed by Colin’s team to meet first meeting and marketing goals (25:31)\nFacilitate scheduling for Instacash engineering meetings and inclusion of appropriate team members (24:05)\nSupport coordination of all-hands meeting participation and company alignment (24:58)\n"},"migrated_from":"contract_meetings","original_id":"e4d6f370-79ca-4056-83f7-b52c8de7157d","master_marketer":{"status":"migrated"}}'::jsonb,
