WITH new_meeting AS (
  INSERT INTO compass_meetings (contract_id, meeting_date, source, external_id, title, participants, duration_seconds, recording_url, transcript, sentiment, raw_metadata, created_at, updated_at)
  VALUES (
    '965b21f3-8748-420c-aaf3-b3fdcaa2f504',
    '2026-01-14 15:30:00+00',
    'fireflies',
    '01KESH6CZ2KN6PCCC2B7YA42SF',
    'iCorps + New North Weekly',
    '{"Jeffery Lauria","Samuel Bagnall","Colin Costigan","Nathalie Mintjens","Ruby Pontbriand"}'::text[],
    1472,
    'https://teams.microsoft.com/l/meetup-join/19:meeting_NWVjNDBkODktN2I3OS00ZWQ0LTgzMDEtMWNkNDk5OGVlYjQ2@thread.v2/0?context={"Tid":"0188564a-93de-489c-bf54-1927d4a9ed28","Oid":"bdae9fd3-d481-4c5e-aeea-7272e37b7d07"}',
    '{"id":"01KESH6CZ2KN6PCCC2B7YA42SF","title":"iCorps + New North Weekly","summary":{"notes":"## **SEO and Content Strategy**\n\nThe team is advancing SEO efforts to boost top-of-funnel traffic and align content with market demand.\n\n- **Three new location-based SEO landing pages were published** this month to improve local search visibility and drive traffic to the site (12:00)\n    - These pages target geographic keywords to attract region-specific prospects.\n    - The glossary section was launched with **two informational definition pages** to enhance keyword breadth and technical authority (12:50)\n    - Colin explained that glossary pages help capture AI-driven search queries on platforms like ChatGPT, bringing qualified traffic directly to these pages.\n    - Jeffery emphasized that content must reflect real market language, noting the example of the “Encompass” service, which lacks industry recognition and thus requires rebranding to improve search relevance.\n\n- **SEO updates are ongoing for the Microsoft Copilot consulting page**, with a preview to be shared for review (12:00)\n    - The team is incorporating Jeffery’s suggested changes to better position AI consulting services.\n    - Nathalie proposed linking new AI campaign landing pages within existing site sections to increase visibility and user flow.\n    - The team agreed to develop preview pages and share PDFs for Jeffery’s feedback to streamline review and iteration (16:00).\n\n## **Lead Generation and Marketing Performance**\n\nLead management and campaign tracking are being refined to improve conversion rates and sales alignment.\n\n- The **ABM campaign’s highly engaged leads increased to 253** following targeted follow-up emails and LinkedIn outreach (10:00)\n    - Ruby and Sam will now handle lead follow-ups after Kristin’s departure to maintain continuity.\n    - Lead communication emails and LinkedIn messages will be sent from Sam’s account to improve personalization and response rates.\n    - January MQLs reached **12 leads with 2 converting to SQLs**, resulting in a **16-17% conversion rate**, which Nathalie noted is above average for the company (11:00).\n    - Jeffery requested additional context for these numbers to evaluate quality, noting that without industry benchmarks, raw percentages lack meaning.\n\n- Jeffery stressed the need for **industry benchmarking on lead conversion** to provide meaningful insights to sales leadership and align expectations (20:00)\n    - This will help clarify whether current rates outperform or lag behind market norms.\n    - Ruby acknowledged this and planned to incorporate comparative data in future reporting.\n\n## **Dashboard Development and Reporting**\n\nThe marketing team is building dashboards to provide transparent, actionable insights for leadership.\n\n- Ruby confirmed the **dashboard draft will be ready by early next week**, with initial work starting Friday (7:00)\n    - The dashboard will integrate key metrics such as SEO performance, lead quality, and campaign engagement.\n    - Jeffery shared a reporting template listing important KPIs like top keywords, underperforming pages, and lead sources to guide dashboard content (04:00).\n    - The goal is to align metrics with business needs, ensuring marketing efforts support service offerings and market trends.\n\n- Ruby is preparing a **2025 marketing recap report for January 22nd** that will use Pulse dashboard and HubSpot data, focusing on campaign-level analysis (18:00)\n    - She requested assistance breaking down results by campaign (financial services, construction) across channels like email, ads, and LinkedIn.\n    - Nathalie agreed to provide detailed campaign data from tools including Smartly Reach to support this report.\n    - Jeffery emphasized that clear, contextual reporting will help sales and marketing teams track progress and adjust strategies effectively.\n\n## **AI Campaign Integration and Website Updates**\n\nThe AI-focused marketing campaign involves new assets and site updates to highlight readiness and consulting services.\n\n- Two AI campaign landing pages are live: the **assessments page** and the **development and AI page** (15:00)\n    - Nathalie outlined plans to add linked callout boxes on related pages, such as the FAQ and ungoverned AI use sections, to drive traffic to new content.\n    - The approach aims to guide visitors through the funnel starting from AI readiness to consulting offerings.\n    - The team decided preview pages will be developed and shared with leadership for annotation and feedback before full deployment.\n\n- Jeffery confirmed PDF versions of pages are acceptable for review to avoid disrupting the team''s workflow (16:00)\n    - Ruby proposed a joint review call with Jeffery and Sam to discuss page flow and content clarity before finalizing changes.\n    - Nathalie will clearly mark new content sections to streamline feedback and reduce confusion during review.\n\n## **Team and Process Updates**\n\nAdjustments to team roles and communication channels aim to maintain momentum and improve coordination.\n\n- Following Kristin’s exit, **Sam and Ruby will take over lead follow-ups** to ensure no drop in engagement with highly engaged leads (10:20)\n    - Changing email and LinkedIn messages to come from Sam’s account should increase personalization and trust in outreach.\n    - Jeffery’s emphasis on contextual data reflects a culture shift toward data-driven decision-making and transparent communication with sales.\n    - Ruby encouraged flexible meeting attendance, noting that once dashboards are operational, many questions will be answered through reporting, reducing meeting frequency.\n\n- The team continues to prioritize aligning marketing output with business goals, ensuring that service offerings match market demand as Jeffery highlighted repeatedly throughout the discussion.","outline":null,"keywords":["SEO","Dashboards","Marketing Qualified Leads","Campaign Performance","ABM","Glossary Pages"],"overview":"- **SEO Enhancements:** Three new location-based SEO pages launched to increase local search visibility and attract specific prospects.\n\n- **Lead Generation Success:** ABM campaign engaged 253 leads; January saw 12 MQLs with a 16-17% conversion rate.\n\n- **Benchmarking Importance:** Need for industry benchmarking on lead conversion emphasized to align sales expectations and improve strategy.\n\n- **Dashboard Development:** Draft dashboard ready next week, highlighting SEO, lead quality, and campaign engagement metrics.\n\n- **AI Campaign Updates:** Two AI landing pages launched; linked callout boxes planned to guide visitors through the funnel.\n\n- **Team Coordination:** Sam and Ruby take over lead follow-ups post-Kristin''s exit, focusing on personalized outreach and data-driven decisions.","action_items":"\n**Nathalie Mintjens**\nNathalie Mintjens to start building the dashboard with her team by Friday and provide a draft early next week (07:32)\nNathalie Mintjens and team to update Microsoft Copilot consulting SEO page and send a preview to Jeffery for feedback (11:30)\nNathalie Mintjens to send updated website additions via preview pages and PDFs to Jeffery and schedule review call with Sam and Jeffery to discuss (16:00)\n\n**Ruby Pontbriand**\nRuby Pontbriand to receive and review Jeffery’s document on reporting metrics and integrate insights into dashboard planning (04:50)\nRuby Pontbriand and Nathalie Mintjens to coordinate on gathering detailed campaign performance data from Smartly Reach and HubSpot for 2024/2025 recap presentations (18:30)\nRuby Pontbriand to present the 2024 marketing recap to stakeholders on January 22nd (19:53)\n\n**Unassigned**\nMarketing team to change the sender of LinkedIn messages and emails to Jeffery’s account for consistency in lead follow-ups (10:40)\n\n**Jeffery Lauria**\nJeffery Lauria to provide industry benchmarking data context to Ruby and Nathalie for better interpretation of conversion rates and marketing metrics (20:50)\n\n**Samuel Bagnall**\nSamuel Bagnall to provide Jeffery with additional materials and one-pager from Mike Hadley as requested (23:00)\n"},"duration":24.540000915527344,"speakers":[{"id":0,"name":"Jeffery Lauria"},{"id":1,"name":"Samuel Bagnall"},{"id":2,"name":"Colin Costigan"},{"id":3,"name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"id":4,"name":"Ruby Pontbriand"}],"sentences":[{"text":"Hey, Sam.","index":0,"end_time":13.04,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":12.48,"speaker_name":"Jeffery Lauria"},{"text":"Hey, Colin.","index":1,"end_time":13.84,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":13.2,"speaker_name":"Samuel Bagnall"},{"text":"How you doing?","index":2,"end_time":14.32,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":13.84,"speaker_name":"Samuel Bagnall"},{"text":"Doing all right.","index":3,"end_time":15.24,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":14.56,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"How about yourself?","index":4,"end_time":15.92,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":15.24,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Doing good.","index":5,"end_time":17.2,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":16.48,"speaker_name":"Samuel Bagnall"},{"text":"Hello, Natalie.","index":6,"end_time":24.96,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":23.2,"speaker_name":"Samuel Bagnall"},{"text":"How''s it going?","index":7,"end_time":26.97,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":26.41,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Going pretty well.","index":8,"end_time":28.93,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":28.17,"speaker_name":"Samuel Bagnall"},{"text":"How are you?","index":9,"end_time":29.45,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":28.93,"speaker_name":"Samuel Bagnall"},{"text":"Good.","index":10,"end_time":30.57,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":30.17,"speaker_name":"Jeffery Lauria"},{"text":"Hey, Jeff.","index":11,"end_time":32.49,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":31.77,"speaker_name":"Samuel Bagnall"},{"text":"Hey.","index":12,"end_time":33.61,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":33.13,"speaker_name":"Jeffery Lauria"},{"text":"More importantly, Natalie, how was Ann?","index":13,"end_time":36.65,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":33.85,"speaker_name":"Jeffery Lauria"},{"text":"Colin, how was your holidays?","index":14,"end_time":38.97,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":36.65,"speaker_name":"Jeffery Lauria"},{"text":"Did you go to Aruba?","index":15,"end_time":41.25,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":39.45,"speaker_name":"Jeffery Lauria"},{"text":"Not someplace nice and warm, Natalie, I''ll let you start.","index":16,"end_time":45.53,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":41.25,"speaker_name":"Jeffery Lauria"},{"text":"Yeah, I was stuck in Chicago, so I was freezing, but it was good.","index":17,"end_time":49.85,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":46.25,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"I had family come and visit me.","index":18,"end_time":52.01,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":49.85,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"That''s a cop out.","index":19,"end_time":54.2,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":53.32,"speaker_name":"Jeffery Lauria"},{"text":"I mean, I couldn''t go anywhere.","index":20,"end_time":55.44,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":54.2,"speaker_name":"Jeffery Lauria"},{"text":"I was stuck and, you know, all these people came and bothered me.","index":21,"end_time":58.36,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":55.44,"speaker_name":"Jeffery Lauria"},{"text":"Fair enough.","index":22,"end_time":58.92,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":58.36,"speaker_name":"Jeffery Lauria"},{"text":"Now, that''s right.","index":23,"end_time":60.88,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":59.88,"speaker_name":"Jeffery Lauria"},{"text":"You work out of Chicago, right?","index":24,"end_time":62.28,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":60.88,"speaker_name":"Jeffery Lauria"},{"text":"That''s right.","index":25,"end_time":63.4,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":62.92,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":26,"end_time":63.8,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":63.4,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"You only live in Chicago, Right.","index":27,"end_time":66.04,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":63.88,"speaker_name":"Jeffery Lauria"},{"text":"See, I can see your window out the side.","index":28,"end_time":68.52,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":66.12,"speaker_name":"Jeffery Lauria"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":29,"end_time":69.48,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":69,"speaker_name":"Jeffery Lauria"},{"text":"Coming down.","index":30,"end_time":70.84,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":70.04,"speaker_name":"Jeffery Lauria"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":31,"end_time":71.64,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":71.16,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Snowstorm right now.","index":32,"end_time":73,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":71.72,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Paula, how about yourself?","index":33,"end_time":74.84,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":73.64,"speaker_name":"Jeffery Lauria"},{"text":"I.","index":34,"end_time":75.88,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":75.48,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"It was my daughter''s first Christmas so we tried to do as little travel as possible.","index":35,"end_time":80.44,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":76.2,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Nice.","index":36,"end_time":81.59,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":81.35,"speaker_name":"Jeffery Lauria"},{"text":"Now you know Santa doesn''t wrap.","index":37,"end_time":83.43,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":81.59,"speaker_name":"Jeffery Lauria"},{"text":"Keep that in mind.","index":38,"end_time":85.91,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":84.87,"speaker_name":"Jeffery Lauria"},{"text":"Yeah, we learned that.","index":39,"end_time":87.91,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":86.39,"speaker_name":"Samuel Bagnall"},{"text":"That''s for sure.","index":40,"end_time":88.55,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":87.91,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Santa doesn''t rap.","index":41,"end_time":90.31,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":89.11,"speaker_name":"Jeffery Lauria"},{"text":"Yeah, he delivers things in Amazon boxes.","index":42,"end_time":93.11,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":90.47,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Hey, Santa uses Amazon.","index":43,"end_time":96.749,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":94.87,"speaker_name":"Jeffery Lauria"},{"text":"He''s up in his game.","index":44,"end_time":98.07,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":96.749,"speaker_name":"Jeffery Lauria"},{"text":"Yeah, There you go.","index":45,"end_time":99.43,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":98.23,"speaker_name":"Jeffery Lauria"},{"text":"How about you, Jeff?","index":46,"end_time":100.99,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":100.23,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"How was your holiday season?","index":47,"end_time":101.99,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":100.99,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Oh, it was great.","index":48,"end_time":103.15,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":102.15,"speaker_name":"Jeffery Lauria"},{"text":"I have so I have two, two grandchildren and they''re now at an age where they kind of enjoy the stuff.","index":49,"end_time":113.2,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":103.15,"speaker_name":"Jeffery Lauria"},{"text":"But here''s really the funny part.","index":50,"end_time":115.08,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":113.2,"speaker_name":"Jeffery Lauria"},{"text":"After opening like two or three gifts, they''re kind of done.","index":51,"end_time":117.36,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":115.08,"speaker_name":"Jeffery Lauria"},{"text":"Oh yeah, I''m done.","index":52,"end_time":119,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":118,"speaker_name":"Jeffery Lauria"},{"text":"I want to go play one of these toys.","index":53,"end_time":120.44,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":119,"speaker_name":"Jeffery Lauria"},{"text":"Leave me alone.","index":54,"end_time":121.2,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":120.44,"speaker_name":"Jeffery Lauria"},{"text":"Yeah, and that''s what they do.","index":55,"end_time":122.96,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":121.36,"speaker_name":"Jeffery Lauria"},{"text":"And if you have a friend like Mike Hadley, he will give your grandchildren gifts to make noise like pianos or little, little flutes and all this stuff which by the way isn''t really awesome.","index":56,"end_time":139.84,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":122.96,"speaker_name":"Jeffery Lauria"},{"text":"But take them and go like the furthest part of the house.","index":57,"end_time":143.84,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":141.2,"speaker_name":"Jeffery Lauria"},{"text":"Just don''t go play them down there.","index":58,"end_time":145.84,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":144.16,"speaker_name":"Jeffery Lauria"},{"text":"So his latest was a digital like little drum thing and which is great and it''s awesome kind and don''t get me wrong, and I think music is awesome for little kids.","index":59,"end_time":156,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":146.32,"speaker_name":"Jeffery Lauria"},{"text":"Noise, noise.","index":60,"end_time":158.8,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":157.6,"speaker_name":"Jeffery Lauria"},{"text":"He does it on purpose, but that''s beside the point.","index":61,"end_time":162.64,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":159.76,"speaker_name":"Jeffery Lauria"},{"text":"But all good.","index":62,"end_time":163.68,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":162.88,"speaker_name":"Jeffery Lauria"},{"text":"Speaking of which movie, is Mike Halley joining us?","index":63,"end_time":166.22,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":163.68,"speaker_name":"Jeffery Lauria"},{"text":"That''s a good question.","index":64,"end_time":168.62,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":167.58,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"I think.","index":65,"end_time":169.06,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":168.62,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"So he accepted.","index":66,"end_time":170.38,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":169.06,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Okay.","index":67,"end_time":171.74,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":171.1,"speaker_name":"Jeffery Lauria"},{"text":"Well, there you go.","index":68,"end_time":172.62,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":171.82,"speaker_name":"Jeffery Lauria"},{"text":"I know it''s only got a little 15 minute meeting, so the hell awesome is that Our baby''s only 15 minutes for me and then you had enough of me to get rid of me.","index":69,"end_time":181.14,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":172.62,"speaker_name":"Jeffery Lauria"},{"text":"So fair enough.","index":70,"end_time":181.9,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":181.14,"speaker_name":"Jeffery Lauria"},{"text":"I noticed Chris is on there too, so there you go.","index":71,"end_time":188.78,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":183.5,"speaker_name":"Jeffery Lauria"},{"text":"Ruby.","index":72,"end_time":189.94,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":189.34,"speaker_name":"Jeffery Lauria"},{"text":"Hey.","index":73,"end_time":190.22,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":189.94,"speaker_name":"Jeffery Lauria"},{"text":"It''s all good.","index":74,"end_time":190.7,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":190.22,"speaker_name":"Jeffery Lauria"},{"text":"I don''t think.","index":75,"end_time":191.26,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":190.7,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"I don''t think Cook will.","index":76,"end_time":192.38,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":191.26,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"He doesn''t know how to.","index":77,"end_time":195.61,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":194.89,"speaker_name":"Jeffery Lauria"},{"text":"He doesn''t know how to use technology, so he doesn''t know how to get to a meeting.","index":78,"end_time":198.73,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":195.61,"speaker_name":"Jeffery Lauria"},{"text":"There you go.","index":79,"end_time":200.97,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":200.25,"speaker_name":"Jeffery Lauria"},{"text":"We can probably get started, I think.","index":80,"end_time":205.21,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":201.69,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Yeah, we can get started.","index":81,"end_time":206.81,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":205.77,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"And I think, like, for.","index":82,"end_time":209.01,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":206.81,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"For Jeff and Mike being on the call, Natalie, we were just mostly looking at kind of giving them.","index":83,"end_time":216.01,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":209.01,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Oh, sorry.","index":84,"end_time":218.69,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":218.01,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"That was an echo.","index":85,"end_time":219.45,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":218.69,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"The overview of what we''re looking at for dashboards and making sure that we have exactly what, like, you guys have exactly what you need to build those accurately to what they''re looking for so that by, like next week or so, we can have something.","index":86,"end_time":237.33,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":220.93,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Did I send you a document earlier this week about reports and maybe certain things?","index":87,"end_time":242.13,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":238.21,"speaker_name":"Jeffery Lauria"},{"text":"I don''t have anything.","index":88,"end_time":244.29,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":243.33,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Okay.","index":89,"end_time":245.37,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":244.85,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"So my apologies.","index":90,"end_time":246.53,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":245.37,"speaker_name":"Jeffery Lauria"},{"text":"So what I had done, and I apologize because this is not the place to kind of say, hey, look at all this.","index":91,"end_time":258.17,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":247.93,"speaker_name":"Jeffery Lauria"},{"text":"But what I had done is I had put together a kind of a. I don''t want to say, but a template, but a template on.","index":92,"end_time":268.97,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":258.41,"speaker_name":"Jeffery Lauria"},{"text":"Let me see if I can find it monthly.","index":93,"end_time":271.93,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":269.45,"speaker_name":"Jeffery Lauria"},{"text":"Oh, here we go.","index":94,"end_time":272.73,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":271.93,"speaker_name":"Jeffery Lauria"},{"text":"So kind of some items that I thought, you know, might be important.","index":95,"end_time":279.98,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":273.05,"speaker_name":"Jeffery Lauria"},{"text":"And these are kind of the things.","index":96,"end_time":282.98,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":281.58,"speaker_name":"Jeffery Lauria"},{"text":"And again, I''m going to send this over to you right now, Ruby, why don''t you just take a look at it.","index":97,"end_time":288.02,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":282.98,"speaker_name":"Jeffery Lauria"},{"text":"We''ll bring it up.","index":98,"end_time":288.78,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":288.02,"speaker_name":"Jeffery Lauria"},{"text":"But here''s what I did do and I will show you, Ruby, it should be in your mailbox.","index":99,"end_time":294.78,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":288.78,"speaker_name":"Jeffery Lauria"},{"text":"But let me just share my screen real quick.","index":100,"end_time":298.3,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":296.06,"speaker_name":"Jeffery Lauria"},{"text":"One of the things.","index":101,"end_time":300.14,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":299.18,"speaker_name":"Jeffery Lauria"},{"text":"And I tried to understand the justification of these things.","index":102,"end_time":303.34,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":300.14,"speaker_name":"Jeffery Lauria"},{"text":"So, for example, let me just share this.","index":103,"end_time":307.16,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":303.34,"speaker_name":"Jeffery Lauria"},{"text":"And you know, some.","index":104,"end_time":311.68,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":308.44,"speaker_name":"Jeffery Lauria"},{"text":"This is kind of just a reporting, but, you know, SEO performance keywords.","index":105,"end_time":316.76,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":311.68,"speaker_name":"Jeffery Lauria"},{"text":"Right.","index":106,"end_time":317.08,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":316.76,"speaker_name":"Jeffery Lauria"},{"text":"So keywords are very important to me.","index":107,"end_time":319.8,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":317.56,"speaker_name":"Jeffery Lauria"},{"text":"And this is some of the things that I want to look at is keywords.","index":108,"end_time":324.16,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":320.92,"speaker_name":"Jeffery Lauria"},{"text":"Because ultimately keywords for me are going to, you know, awareness, you know, decision making.","index":109,"end_time":332.04,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":324.16,"speaker_name":"Jeffery Lauria"},{"text":"If I know that people are searching on these words.","index":110,"end_time":335.28,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":332.2,"speaker_name":"Jeffery Lauria"},{"text":"Our blogs can be very much targeted, but also it helps us mold our business.","index":111,"end_time":340.18,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":335.28,"speaker_name":"Jeffery Lauria"},{"text":"If we, you know, if we''re doing this and the market, both our market coming to us, but also our competitors.","index":112,"end_time":349.38,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":340.98,"speaker_name":"Jeffery Lauria"},{"text":"Market.","index":113,"end_time":349.7,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":349.38,"speaker_name":"Jeffery Lauria"},{"text":"Right.","index":114,"end_time":350.18,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":349.78,"speaker_name":"Jeffery Lauria"},{"text":"Is all looking at this and we''re not aligned with the business, then that''s not going to help us grow.","index":115,"end_time":355.22,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":350.58,"speaker_name":"Jeffery Lauria"},{"text":"With that.","index":116,"end_time":356.34,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":355.7,"speaker_name":"Jeffery Lauria"},{"text":"And maybe this is stuff you already deal with, but with that, I personally have no insight.","index":117,"end_time":361.86,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":357.06,"speaker_name":"Jeffery Lauria"},{"text":"And because the content sometimes I help with, because our programs and services, specifically around AI and cybersecurity fall within my domain, I can put together.","index":118,"end_time":378.22,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":362.34,"speaker_name":"Jeffery Lauria"},{"text":"We can put together the best service offering, but if it''s not matching the market need, then just doesn''t work.","index":119,"end_time":384.94,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":378.46,"speaker_name":"Jeffery Lauria"},{"text":"So these are some of the things that I am kind of looking to better understand so I can help provide, you know, again, top five pages, you know, underperforming content.","index":120,"end_time":398.69,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":385.26,"speaker_name":"Jeffery Lauria"},{"text":"Why are we doing that?","index":121,"end_time":399.93,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":398.85,"speaker_name":"Jeffery Lauria"},{"text":"You know, what''s wrong with this content?","index":122,"end_time":401.57,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":399.93,"speaker_name":"Jeffery Lauria"},{"text":"Why are we wasting.","index":123,"end_time":402.53,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":401.57,"speaker_name":"Jeffery Lauria"},{"text":"So I had sent her a list.","index":124,"end_time":404.05,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":402.85,"speaker_name":"Jeffery Lauria"},{"text":"I''m not going to go over this.","index":125,"end_time":405.33,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":404.05,"speaker_name":"Jeffery Lauria"},{"text":"But, you know, these are some of the things from a reporting perspective I think are going to be in my mind are important.","index":126,"end_time":412.29,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":405.65,"speaker_name":"Jeffery Lauria"},{"text":"And then I try to explain why they''re important.","index":127,"end_time":414.93,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":412.61,"speaker_name":"Jeffery Lauria"},{"text":"If I''m misaligned and by all means say, hey, you''re misaligned.","index":128,"end_time":418.85,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":415.01,"speaker_name":"Jeffery Lauria"},{"text":"But between Mike, Chris and I.","index":129,"end_time":421.67,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":419.09,"speaker_name":"Jeffery Lauria"},{"text":"So Mike Chris, Mike does too.","index":130,"end_time":424.51,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":421.91,"speaker_name":"Jeffery Lauria"},{"text":"As do I.","index":131,"end_time":425.43,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":424.51,"speaker_name":"Jeffery Lauria"},{"text":"But you know, he, he''s more about kind of obviously, you know, mocking qualify leads to whatever those type that lead structure, which as am I.","index":132,"end_time":435.43,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":425.51,"speaker_name":"Jeffery Lauria"},{"text":"But you know, that lead structure is based on everything I had before.","index":133,"end_time":440.63,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":435.43,"speaker_name":"Jeffery Lauria"},{"text":"Right.","index":134,"end_time":441.11,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":440.71,"speaker_name":"Jeffery Lauria"},{"text":"Content, keywords, things of that nature.","index":135,"end_time":444.47,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":441.35,"speaker_name":"Jeffery Lauria"},{"text":"So a kind of a holistic view.","index":136,"end_time":446.23,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":444.55,"speaker_name":"Jeffery Lauria"},{"text":"So that''s kind of hopefully the goal.","index":137,"end_time":448.07,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":446.23,"speaker_name":"Jeffery Lauria"},{"text":"Enough said.","index":138,"end_time":451.13,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":450.49,"speaker_name":"Jeffery Lauria"},{"text":"Okay, cool.","index":139,"end_time":453.57,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":452.81,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Yeah, we''ll take a look at that document.","index":140,"end_time":455.05,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":453.57,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"I actually already have some time for our team to start building that dashboard on Friday, so we should have a draft for you early next week.","index":141,"end_time":464.25,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":455.05,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Perfect.","index":142,"end_time":465.53,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":464.97,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":143,"end_time":466.73,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":466.33,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And Jeff, one thing for keywords is I don''t think it''s going to.","index":144,"end_time":470.57,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":466.73,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I mean, it could.","index":145,"end_time":471.77,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":471.05,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So I''m not going to say it''s not going to happen at all, but it''s likely that it''s not going to show a misalignment of your service offerings.","index":146,"end_time":477.25,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":471.77,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But what we always say is you are absolutely the expert in the services that you guys provide.","index":147,"end_time":481.35,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":477.25,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"The people you''re selling to are calling it different things and that''s what they''re searching.","index":148,"end_time":484.71,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":481.43,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So that''s what we need to expose of where is that?","index":149,"end_time":487.19,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":484.71,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yes, yes, exactly.","index":150,"end_time":489.43,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":487.27,"speaker_name":"Jeffery Lauria"},{"text":"And that is, you know what.","index":151,"end_time":490.55,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":489.43,"speaker_name":"Jeffery Lauria"},{"text":"So that is.","index":152,"end_time":491.23,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":490.55,"speaker_name":"Jeffery Lauria"},{"text":"You are 100% right.","index":153,"end_time":492.95,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":491.23,"speaker_name":"Jeffery Lauria"},{"text":"And the best possible example there is we have a service often called Encompass.","index":154,"end_time":497.43,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":492.95,"speaker_name":"Jeffery Lauria"},{"text":"Nobody knows what the hell that is.","index":155,"end_time":499.83,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":497.75,"speaker_name":"Jeffery Lauria"},{"text":"Right.","index":156,"end_time":500.23,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":499.91,"speaker_name":"Jeffery Lauria"},{"text":"It''s not a word used anywhere within the industry and means absolutely nothing to anybody.","index":157,"end_time":506.23,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":500.23,"speaker_name":"Jeffery Lauria"},{"text":"So, you know, marketing our Encompass agreement is useless.","index":158,"end_time":511.06,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":506.95,"speaker_name":"Jeffery Lauria"},{"text":"And, and that is.","index":159,"end_time":512.58,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":511.46,"speaker_name":"Jeffery Lauria"},{"text":"Those are the things that I''m.","index":160,"end_time":513.86,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":512.58,"speaker_name":"Jeffery Lauria"},{"text":"Those are the things that we need to be aware of.","index":161,"end_time":520.34,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":514.1,"speaker_name":"Jeffery Lauria"},{"text":"And I know that Ruby is aware of those things.","index":162,"end_time":523.7,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":520.34,"speaker_name":"Jeffery Lauria"},{"text":"I want to make sure that the offerings that I''m presenting up not falling into those same gaps.","index":163,"end_time":530.74,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":524.98,"speaker_name":"Jeffery Lauria"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah, totally with you.","index":164,"end_time":533.94,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":531.06,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You know, so like we, like, you know, we''ll write in the past this has changed a lot since movies come on board.","index":165,"end_time":542.29,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":535.06,"speaker_name":"Jeffery Lauria"},{"text":"But in the past, you know, we Write something for LinkedIn and we reference encompass.","index":166,"end_time":546.45,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":542.29,"speaker_name":"Jeffery Lauria"},{"text":"It''s a compass.","index":167,"end_time":549.17,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":548.21,"speaker_name":"Jeffery Lauria"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":168,"end_time":549.69,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":549.25,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So those are things.","index":169,"end_time":550.49,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":549.69,"speaker_name":"Jeffery Lauria"},{"text":"Yes.","index":170,"end_time":551.01,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":550.49,"speaker_name":"Jeffery Lauria"},{"text":"Cool.","index":171,"end_time":555.09,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":554.61,"speaker_name":"Jeffery Lauria"},{"text":"All right, so just looking at your points so far for this month.","index":172,"end_time":564.61,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":558.13,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"So we got those three SEO landing pages published, the location based ones.","index":173,"end_time":569.57,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":564.61,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"So those are all live on the site.","index":174,"end_time":571.89,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":570.05,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"And then for the rest of January we will be doing the management tasks and just looking at the performance of our current ABM campaign.","index":175,"end_time":580.13,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":572.53,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"And then looking at abm.","index":176,"end_time":585.97,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":584.61,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"So for our highly engaged leads, we jumped up to 253 since last week.","index":177,"end_time":591.57,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":586.21,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"I saw that you, Ruby, you and Kristin did some follow up for these leads that came from the paid ads.","index":178,"end_time":598.54,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":592.05,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"So just sent another email to them seeing if they''d like to meet and then also followed up with this one that came from LinkedIn organic messages.","index":179,"end_time":606.94,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":598.62,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"I did see that this lead followed the email and went to the booking page, the meeting booking page.","index":180,"end_time":613.66,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":607.66,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Looks like they didn''t book anything.","index":181,"end_time":615.42,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":613.98,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"But they, they got there at least.","index":182,"end_time":617.18,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":615.42,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"At least they went there.","index":183,"end_time":618.38,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":617.18,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"That''s good.","index":184,"end_time":620.26,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":619.66,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Yeah, I put that together the other day and then update, as you know, is that Kristin''s no longer with iCore, so Sam and myself will be taking over follow ups on the existing highly engaged leads as well as the ones that come in.","index":185,"end_time":635.61,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":620.26,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"And yeah, we did change the emails that are going out to come from you again and then just to confirm that we should change LinkedIn as well to go to come from your account.","index":186,"end_time":650.75,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":640.17,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Yeah, makes sense.","index":187,"end_time":653.23,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":651.47,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":188,"end_time":653.95,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":653.39,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Okay, so we will make that change then.","index":189,"end_time":657.55,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":654.19,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Yeah, so we''ll just keep doing follow up with these ones and then looking at our MQL so far in January we have 12 that came in, two that turn into SQLs and we''re at a 16%, almost 17% conversion rate.","index":190,"end_time":672.35,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":658.51,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":191,"end_time":675.64,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":675.16,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Just, just, just for context for me please, if you don''t mind, what does that actually mean?","index":192,"end_time":682.44,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":676.52,"speaker_name":"Jeffery Lauria"},{"text":"So a 17% conversion rate, is that a good number?","index":193,"end_time":685.64,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":682.44,"speaker_name":"Jeffery Lauria"},{"text":"Yeah, that''s higher than most months.","index":194,"end_time":690.52,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":687.8,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Usually we''re at around 10% but it''s also dependent on the number of MQLs we''re bringing in as well.","index":195,"end_time":697.32,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":690.68,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"We had, we had talked about this if few weeks ago, but we have seen with the holiday season it slowed down a little bit, especially with the LinkedIn ads.","index":196,"end_time":705.93,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":697.88,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"But from the MQLs that are coming in, a 17% conversion rate to SQL is strong.","index":197,"end_time":711.13,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":706.73,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Excellent.","index":198,"end_time":712.97,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":712.33,"speaker_name":"Jeffery Lauria"},{"text":"All right, and then for SEO, so we got those location pages published here.","index":199,"end_time":722.65,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":717.37,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"We received the updates that Jeff made for the Microsoft Copilot consulting page.","index":200,"end_time":728.73,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":723.21,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"So our team is going to work on updating those and we''ll send over the updated preview page to you.","index":201,"end_time":734.87,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":728.81,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"And then all that''s left in review right now is these two glossary definition pages.","index":202,"end_time":740.87,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":735.91,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Glossary definition pages.","index":203,"end_time":746.23,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":744.55,"speaker_name":"Jeffery Lauria"},{"text":"And what are those?","index":204,"end_time":747.91,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":747.03,"speaker_name":"Jeffery Lauria"},{"text":"I guess they are what they are.","index":205,"end_time":750.15,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":748.95,"speaker_name":"Jeffery Lauria"},{"text":"Glossary definition pages.","index":206,"end_time":751.55,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":750.15,"speaker_name":"Jeffery Lauria"},{"text":"What does this mean?","index":207,"end_time":752.31,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":751.55,"speaker_name":"Jeffery Lauria"},{"text":"What does that mean?","index":208,"end_time":752.99,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":752.31,"speaker_name":"Jeffery Lauria"},{"text":"Okay, that was kind of stupid question from the side, but all right, I got it.","index":209,"end_time":756.95,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":752.99,"speaker_name":"Jeffery Lauria"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":210,"end_time":758,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":757.84,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"We recently stood up a glossary section of the website.","index":211,"end_time":761.04,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":758,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"It''s not published yet until we have a few keywords or definitions in there.","index":212,"end_time":765.52,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":761.04,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"And these are the first two that we created.","index":213,"end_time":768.08,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":765.6,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Makes sense.","index":214,"end_time":770.24,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":769.52,"speaker_name":"Jeffery Lauria"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":215,"end_time":771.8,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":771.44,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"And then the purpose behind that one was.","index":216,"end_time":773.52,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":771.8,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Natalie, if you can recap for Jeff, the was kind of behind SEO.","index":217,"end_time":780.24,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":773.84,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Yeah, it was more for, from a technical standpoint is to make sure that the website just has a breadth of keywords that we''re covering.","index":218,"end_time":788.4,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":781.92,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"And these like definition pages are.","index":219,"end_time":791.02,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":789.5,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"They''re definitely more information, informational than commercial.","index":220,"end_time":794.66,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":791.26,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"So people aren''t getting on those pages looking to necessarily buy a service at that moment.","index":221,"end_time":799.18,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":794.66,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"But it does help bring more traffic to the site.","index":222,"end_time":802.7,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":800.46,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Just helps with the top of funnel brand awareness as well.","index":223,"end_time":806.54,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":803.5,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"And like technical authority and credibility.","index":224,"end_time":808.94,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":806.94,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Yes.","index":225,"end_time":810.38,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":809.9,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"When it brings more traffic to the site, is it bringing more.","index":226,"end_time":815.34,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":810.86,"speaker_name":"Jeffery Lauria"},{"text":"So this is.","index":227,"end_time":816.18,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":815.58,"speaker_name":"Jeffery Lauria"},{"text":"This is an interesting question.","index":228,"end_time":817.58,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":816.18,"speaker_name":"Jeffery Lauria"},{"text":"Again, really just my own education.","index":229,"end_time":819.42,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":817.66,"speaker_name":"Jeffery Lauria"},{"text":"If I have a go page of all these words, is it bringing people to that page?","index":230,"end_time":825.64,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":820.06,"speaker_name":"Jeffery Lauria"},{"text":"Because that''s where it''s getting linked at with an SEO, or is it bringing people to.","index":231,"end_time":831.64,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":826.76,"speaker_name":"Jeffery Lauria"},{"text":"Or do you redirect to another page?","index":232,"end_time":833.72,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":831.64,"speaker_name":"Jeffery Lauria"},{"text":"So should people be landing on that page directly or should they go in someplace else?","index":233,"end_time":839.24,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":834.2,"speaker_name":"Jeffery Lauria"},{"text":"So it would depend on their search query.","index":234,"end_time":842.44,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":840.2,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But the real strong point of these glossary definition pages is not only bolstering the search engine for Google and Bing, but also for AI tools like ChatGPT and Claude, where people are transitioning and doing much more of their searching because you can do longer prompts.","index":235,"end_time":856.74,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":842.84,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So this is where we have the opportunity to become an AI citation on ChatGPT, which again, brings more qualified traffic.","index":236,"end_time":863.54,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":857.06,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But they would land on the glossary definition page because that is the page with the, you know, question, answer, and definition of what they''re looking for from a term.","index":237,"end_time":870.26,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":863.54,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Oh, perfect.","index":238,"end_time":871.86,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":870.98,"speaker_name":"Jeffery Lauria"},{"text":"Got it.","index":239,"end_time":872.58,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":871.94,"speaker_name":"Jeffery Lauria"},{"text":"Thank you.","index":240,"end_time":876.58,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":875.94,"speaker_name":"Jeffery Lauria"},{"text":"Okay, and then next, so we just discussed this executive dashboard, so the key stats that you, Jeff and Mike and Chris will want to see.","index":241,"end_time":888.81,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":877.86,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"So I''ll review the notes that you sent over.","index":242,"end_time":892.33,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":889.29,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"And then we also discussed how.","index":243,"end_time":895.21,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":893.29,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"So for this new AI campaign, we created a lot of assets a couple of new landing pages as well as PDFs.","index":244,"end_time":902.09,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":895.69,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"And we discussed kind of mapping how we want to add those onto our current site.","index":245,"end_time":906.49,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":902.33,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"So as a starting point, I have the two pages that are currently live on the website.","index":246,"end_time":913.5,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":907.69,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"So the assessments page and the development and AI page.","index":247,"end_time":917.34,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":913.74,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Those are two places where we think the new landing pages should be linked.","index":248,"end_time":921.1,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":917.5,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"So I came up with a plan.","index":249,"end_time":923.14,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":921.98,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"A few areas where we should include the information.","index":250,"end_time":926.54,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":923.14,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"So these text boxes would be linked and take people to the respective landing pages.","index":251,"end_time":931.9,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":927.5,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Extra information here calling out ungoverned AI use as well as the FAQ section.","index":252,"end_time":938.62,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":933.18,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"And then same for the development page.","index":253,"end_time":941.7,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":939.46,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"This one is.","index":254,"end_time":942.98,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":942.18,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Or development and AI page, this one.","index":255,"end_time":944.9,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":942.98,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"So reading through it, it''s more focused on AI consulting.","index":256,"end_time":950.82,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":945.78,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"And then in this section, I just included.","index":257,"end_time":954.5,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":952.1,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Before consulting, let''s start with AI readiness as a first step.","index":258,"end_time":959.14,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":954.58,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"So I was wondering, what''s the best way to get these additions over to you?","index":259,"end_time":965.26,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":959.22,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Would you like us to develop it in a preview page and then send it over?","index":260,"end_time":968.42,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":965.26,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"I think that would be good.","index":261,"end_time":974.84,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":973,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Okay.","index":262,"end_time":976.72,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":976.2,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":263,"end_time":977.16,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":976.72,"speaker_name":"Samuel Bagnall"},{"text":"Okay.","index":264,"end_time":979.08,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":978.68,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Jeff, what do you think?","index":265,"end_time":980,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":979.08,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"What''s best for.","index":266,"end_time":980.92,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":980,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"For you for review.","index":267,"end_time":982.04,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":981,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"This format?","index":268,"end_time":987.32,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":986.28,"speaker_name":"Jeffery Lauria"},{"text":"Like.","index":269,"end_time":987.64,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":987.32,"speaker_name":"Jeffery Lauria"},{"text":"Yeah, just like PDF format''s perfect.","index":270,"end_time":989.84,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":987.64,"speaker_name":"Jeffery Lauria"},{"text":"But whatever works, whatever''s easier for you.","index":271,"end_time":993.96,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":989.84,"speaker_name":"Jeffery Lauria"},{"text":"I don''t want you to redo your workflow.","index":272,"end_time":995.72,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":993.96,"speaker_name":"Jeffery Lauria"},{"text":"Whatever is easy.","index":273,"end_time":997.46,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":996.5,"speaker_name":"Jeffery Lauria"},{"text":"You know, this system is fine too, because I guess I can go ahead and notate stuff.","index":274,"end_time":1002.18,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":998.34,"speaker_name":"Jeffery Lauria"},{"text":"Doesn''t matter.","index":275,"end_time":1004.58,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1003.94,"speaker_name":"Jeffery Lauria"},{"text":"Just tell me, what do you need?","index":276,"end_time":1006.18,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1004.98,"speaker_name":"Jeffery Lauria"},{"text":"Well, I think, by the way, it''ll probably end up being PDF ish for you because we''ll.","index":277,"end_time":1012.419,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1007.06,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"They''ll.","index":278,"end_time":1013.3,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1012.82,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"They can develop the pages themselves.","index":279,"end_time":1015.02,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1013.3,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"There''ll be a preview link and then we can PDF that preview link for you.","index":280,"end_time":1019.7,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1015.02,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"But it, it will be helpful, I think, for you to see the developed page.","index":281,"end_time":1026.03,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1022.67,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"So, you know, like, oh, I click on AI assessments here in this box and it goes to this page kind of a thing.","index":282,"end_time":1033.47,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1026.03,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"But maybe when we review, we just have a.","index":283,"end_time":1036.19,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1033.87,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Maybe we have a call me, you and Sam and review them together.","index":284,"end_time":1039.79,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1036.83,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Perfect.","index":285,"end_time":1041.47,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1040.91,"speaker_name":"Jeffery Lauria"},{"text":"Okay.","index":286,"end_time":1042.75,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1042.11,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":287,"end_time":1044.31,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1043.87,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"And I''ll.","index":288,"end_time":1045.07,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1044.31,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"When I send this over, I''ll also indicate which sections are new because you''ve already reviewed this page a long time ago.","index":289,"end_time":1051.26,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1045.55,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"So just showing you what are the actual new additions.","index":290,"end_time":1053.9,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1051.26,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"All right, so that was everything I had.","index":291,"end_time":1060.82,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1057.66,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Was there anything else you wanted to discuss?","index":292,"end_time":1062.46,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1060.82,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"I think that is good.","index":293,"end_time":1070.46,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1068.54,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"I''m working on like a 2025 marketing recap and obviously like using the dash, the Pulse dashboard a bit as well as HubSpot reports.","index":294,"end_time":1082.99,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1071.9,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"And this will be something that I''ll share with Mike and Cook and Jeff, and I''m Also, they''re wanting to see 2024 numbers.","index":295,"end_time":1092.99,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1084.67,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"So I guess the reason I bring that up with you is just as FYI, like, hey, that''s what I''m doing.","index":296,"end_time":1099.07,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1094.83,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"But also that I wondered if we have a good space for me to go to collect results from the financial services campaign, the construction campaign from 2025.","index":297,"end_time":1114.04,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1099.71,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":298,"end_time":1117.8,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1117.32,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Or if that''s just a matter of like.","index":299,"end_time":1120.92,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1119.16,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Sorry, go ahead.","index":300,"end_time":1122.76,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1122.04,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Yeah, like results meaning like the number.","index":301,"end_time":1125.08,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1123.4,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Of MQLs, I think overall general, like performance of the campaign itself.","index":302,"end_time":1131.93,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1125.08,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"So, you know, I guess like zoom out on the campaign.","index":303,"end_time":1137.29,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1132.25,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"What were all the pieces of it?","index":304,"end_time":1140.13,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1137.45,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Right.","index":305,"end_time":1140.41,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1140.13,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"And how did they perform?","index":306,"end_time":1141.29,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1140.41,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"So how did the emails perform, the ads, LinkedIn messages, and then obviously at the end of the day, the leads.","index":307,"end_time":1150.57,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1142.09,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Yeah, we have, we have all that information on the dashboard, but it''s not broken out by campaign, so we can take that on and help you do that.","index":308,"end_time":1162.49,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1152.89,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"So that will be pulling from the actual tools themselves, like smartly reach.","index":309,"end_time":1167.29,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1162.57,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Yeah, so it can help you with that.","index":310,"end_time":1169.37,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1167.45,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Okay, that''d be awesome.","index":311,"end_time":1170.73,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1169.69,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Because that''s what I was wondering if, like there''s some stuff I can get HubSpot just because we named it as like campaign.","index":312,"end_time":1176.41,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1170.73,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"But I figured there''s probably more detail in heyreach and smart lead.","index":313,"end_time":1182.01,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1177.13,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"So.","index":314,"end_time":1182.49,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1182.09,"speaker_name":"Samuel Bagnall"},{"text":"Yeah, that''d be great if you want to help me out.","index":315,"end_time":1185.13,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1183.53,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"That''d be great.","index":316,"end_time":1185.78,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1185.29,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Fabulous.","index":317,"end_time":1186.73,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1186.25,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"I need to present.","index":318,"end_time":1188.57,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1187.53,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Sorry, go ahead.","index":319,"end_time":1190.73,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1189.93,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"No, no, go ahead, please.","index":320,"end_time":1192.17,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1191.05,"speaker_name":"Jeffery Lauria"},{"text":"I''m sorry.","index":321,"end_time":1192.81,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1192.17,"speaker_name":"Jeffery Lauria"},{"text":"I plan to present to them on January 22nd.","index":322,"end_time":1198.01,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1193.85,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Okay.","index":323,"end_time":1200.01,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1199.45,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"So one of the things that may be helpful is you notice I asked for context to the 17% lead.","index":324,"end_time":1211.61,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1202.89,"speaker_name":"Jeffery Lauria"},{"text":"Cross generation calls MQL.","index":325,"end_time":1214.09,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1211.61,"speaker_name":"Jeffery Lauria"},{"text":"You know, throwing out numbers are great, but unless there''s some context to these numbers.","index":326,"end_time":1221.53,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1215.85,"speaker_name":"Jeffery Lauria"},{"text":"And you know, to me, context is not just, well, you know, last year we did 20, and this year we''re doing 30.","index":327,"end_time":1229.13,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1221.93,"speaker_name":"Jeffery Lauria"},{"text":"So there''s a 10% or 20% increase.","index":328,"end_time":1231.21,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1229.29,"speaker_name":"Jeffery Lauria"},{"text":"That''s great.","index":329,"end_time":1232.01,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1231.369,"speaker_name":"Jeffery Lauria"},{"text":"That''s awesome.","index":330,"end_time":1232.81,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1232.01,"speaker_name":"Jeffery Lauria"},{"text":"It kind of really doesn''t mean much relevant to our market.","index":331,"end_time":1236.57,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1233.05,"speaker_name":"Jeffery Lauria"},{"text":"So, you know, if industry is, you know, closing at a rate of 10% and we''re closing rate is 12, then we''re definitely being awesome.","index":332,"end_time":1244.81,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1237.21,"speaker_name":"Jeffery Lauria"},{"text":"If we''re closing at a rate of eight, we''re not.","index":333,"end_time":1247.05,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1244.97,"speaker_name":"Jeffery Lauria"},{"text":"And again, so contextually, I think that''s important to help our team understand.","index":334,"end_time":1253.43,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1247.35,"speaker_name":"Jeffery Lauria"},{"text":"You know what?","index":335,"end_time":1254.95,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1254.15,"speaker_name":"Jeffery Lauria"},{"text":"Chris Cook, I''m gonna pick on him.","index":336,"end_time":1257.11,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1255.43,"speaker_name":"Jeffery Lauria"},{"text":"Cause I''d love to pick on him, but what he''s gonna look at is gonna go, oh, we only had marketing qualified leads.","index":337,"end_time":1262.67,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1257.11,"speaker_name":"Jeffery Lauria"},{"text":"When we had 10, that turned into five.","index":338,"end_time":1264.31,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1262.67,"speaker_name":"Jeffery Lauria"},{"text":"You know, sales Qualified leads.","index":339,"end_time":1266.15,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1264.31,"speaker_name":"Jeffery Lauria"},{"text":"That seems like a weak number.","index":340,"end_time":1268.23,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1266.39,"speaker_name":"Jeffery Lauria"},{"text":"Cause it''s not contextual.","index":341,"end_time":1269.87,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1268.47,"speaker_name":"Jeffery Lauria"},{"text":"Anything else.","index":342,"end_time":1270.71,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1269.87,"speaker_name":"Jeffery Lauria"},{"text":"So I think that helps.","index":343,"end_time":1272.39,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1271.19,"speaker_name":"Jeffery Lauria"},{"text":"Yes, it''s a great number, but I think that that helps.","index":344,"end_time":1278.28,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1274.88,"speaker_name":"Jeffery Lauria"},{"text":"So, you know, industry benchmarking would be good.","index":345,"end_time":1282.56,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1278.28,"speaker_name":"Jeffery Lauria"},{"text":"Yeah, it''s a great point.","index":346,"end_time":1285.52,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1283.28,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Now, you know, Mike.","index":347,"end_time":1287,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1286.08,"speaker_name":"Jeffery Lauria"},{"text":"Mike has a, you know, great thought process of, you know, we''re really only focused on us.","index":348,"end_time":1293.24,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1287,"speaker_name":"Jeffery Lauria"},{"text":"And I get it, we are only focused on us.","index":349,"end_time":1295.16,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1293.24,"speaker_name":"Jeffery Lauria"},{"text":"But if we don''t know what our industry is looking at.","index":350,"end_time":1299.12,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1295.16,"speaker_name":"Jeffery Lauria"},{"text":"So that''s my $0.02, $0.12 more specific.","index":351,"end_time":1307.26,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1302.14,"speaker_name":"Jeffery Lauria"},{"text":"Okay.","index":352,"end_time":1311.9,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1311.34,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Perfect.","index":353,"end_time":1316.38,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1315.9,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"I think that''s everything.","index":354,"end_time":1317.5,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1316.62,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":355,"end_time":1319.02,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1318.38,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Okay.","index":356,"end_time":1319.54,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1319.1,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"But yeah, Jeff, this is how these meetings go.","index":357,"end_time":1321.42,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1319.54,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"So great stuff.","index":358,"end_time":1325.62,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1324.62,"speaker_name":"Jeffery Lauria"},{"text":"They''re optional.","index":359,"end_time":1326.65,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1326.01,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"You can come every other week if you want.","index":360,"end_time":1328.81,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1326.73,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Pop in, pop out.","index":361,"end_time":1331.85,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1329.37,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Once they get these dashboards drafted up, then hopefully that''ll help close some of those gaps.","index":362,"end_time":1338.25,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1333.13,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"And.","index":363,"end_time":1338.65,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1338.25,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":364,"end_time":1340.09,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1339.61,"speaker_name":"Jeffery Lauria"},{"text":"And I think, you know, with that said, I also think, you know, once we get into a more monthly reporting, a bi weekly reporting cycle that answers all the questions that would be asked.","index":365,"end_time":1350.85,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1340.09,"speaker_name":"Jeffery Lauria"},{"text":"And I think myself and Mike, you know, maybe, you know, maybe a little less, but, you know, I don''t want to speak to those guys either, so.","index":366,"end_time":1359.5,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1350.85,"speaker_name":"Jeffery Lauria"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":367,"end_time":1363.1,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1362.46,"speaker_name":"Jeffery Lauria"},{"text":"Excuse me.","index":368,"end_time":1364.3,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1363.66,"speaker_name":"Jeffery Lauria"},{"text":"So perfect.","index":369,"end_time":1364.94,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1364.3,"speaker_name":"Jeffery Lauria"},{"text":"And just so you know, Sam, that''s what I left at home.","index":370,"end_time":1370.22,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1366.78,"speaker_name":"Jeffery Lauria"},{"text":"Oh, you did?","index":371,"end_time":1372.62,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1371.9,"speaker_name":"Samuel Bagnall"},{"text":"Yeah, of course.","index":372,"end_time":1373.82,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1373.1,"speaker_name":"Jeffery Lauria"},{"text":"It''s all right.","index":373,"end_time":1374.54,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1373.9,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It''s all right.","index":374,"end_time":1375.18,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1374.54,"speaker_name":"Jeffery Lauria"},{"text":"Like I said, we have some more time and I put something up on your desk too, so.","index":375,"end_time":1379.19,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1375.42,"speaker_name":"Samuel Bagnall"},{"text":"Oh, I see this.","index":376,"end_time":1380.55,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1379.59,"speaker_name":"Jeffery Lauria"},{"text":"Yeah, that''s a little.","index":377,"end_time":1382.23,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1380.79,"speaker_name":"Samuel Bagnall"},{"text":"Yeah, that''s a little one pager.","index":378,"end_time":1384.95,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1382.23,"speaker_name":"Samuel Bagnall"},{"text":"Perfect.","index":379,"end_time":1385.91,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1385.51,"speaker_name":"Jeffery Lauria"},{"text":"Mike asked me to get that to you.","index":380,"end_time":1387.35,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1385.91,"speaker_name":"Samuel Bagnall"},{"text":"All right.","index":381,"end_time":1388.31,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1387.83,"speaker_name":"Jeffery Lauria"},{"text":"Awesome, awesome, awesome, awesome.","index":382,"end_time":1390.31,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1388.39,"speaker_name":"Jeffery Lauria"},{"text":"Well, this has been fun.","index":383,"end_time":1393.51,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1391.67,"speaker_name":"Jeffery Lauria"},{"text":"Now, Colin, where do you reside?","index":384,"end_time":1395.51,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1393.59,"speaker_name":"Jeffery Lauria"},{"text":"I''m in Maryland.","index":385,"end_time":1396.79,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1395.83,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":386,"end_time":1398.47,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1398.07,"speaker_name":"Jeffery Lauria"},{"text":"At least a little closer to us.","index":387,"end_time":1399.71,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1398.47,"speaker_name":"Jeffery Lauria"},{"text":"Well, I don''t know.","index":388,"end_time":1400.51,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1399.71,"speaker_name":"Jeffery Lauria"},{"text":"Yeah, it''s a little closer.","index":389,"end_time":1401.75,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1400.51,"speaker_name":"Jeffery Lauria"},{"text":"Same time zone, though.","index":390,"end_time":1402.83,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1401.75,"speaker_name":"Jeffery Lauria"},{"text":"This is.","index":391,"end_time":1403.23,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1402.83,"speaker_name":"Jeffery Lauria"},{"text":"Oh, except finale.","index":392,"end_time":1404.51,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1403.23,"speaker_name":"Jeffery Lauria"},{"text":"Sorry.","index":393,"end_time":1404.87,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1404.51,"speaker_name":"Jeffery Lauria"},{"text":"Yeah, I''m in Central.","index":394,"end_time":1407.94,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1407.06,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Yeah, so.","index":395,"end_time":1409.94,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1408.98,"speaker_name":"Jeffery Lauria"},{"text":"Well, hello.","index":396,"end_time":1412.82,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1411.06,"speaker_name":"Jeffery Lauria"},{"text":"You guys continue if you like, but I''m going away.","index":397,"end_time":1416.18,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1413.38,"speaker_name":"Jeffery Lauria"},{"text":"Great to see you again, Natalie.","index":398,"end_time":1419.02,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1417.62,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It was a pleasure.","index":399,"end_time":1419.7,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1419.02,"speaker_name":"Jeffery Lauria"},{"text":"Sam, if you''re in the office, I''ll swing by and harass you.","index":400,"end_time":1422.26,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1419.7,"speaker_name":"Jeffery Lauria"},{"text":"Ruby, have a great, great day.","index":401,"end_time":1423.94,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1422.26,"speaker_name":"Jeffery Lauria"},{"text":"Thank you.","index":402,"end_time":1425.1,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1424.5,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"You too.","index":403,"end_time":1425.58,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1425.1,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Bye, guys.","index":404,"end_time":1426.34,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1425.58,"speaker_name":"Jeffery Lauria"},{"text":"All right, thank you.","index":405,"end_time":1427.38,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1426.34,"speaker_name":"Jeffery Lauria"},{"text":"Bye.","index":406,"end_time":1427.78,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1427.38,"speaker_name":"Samuel Bagnall"}],"dateString":"2026-01-14T15:30:00.000Z","host_email":"rpontbriand@icorps.com","meeting_link":"https://teams.microsoft.com/l/meetup-join/19:meeting_NWVjNDBkODktN2I3OS00ZWQ0LTgzMDEtMWNkNDk5OGVlYjQ2@thread.v2/0?context={\"