    '{"label":"positive","confidence":0.92,"bullets":["Confirmed SEO landing pages are live; team to monitor ABM campaign through January.","Agreed to build executive dashboards using Jeff''s template; draft expected early next week.","Identified mismatch between internal product terms and customer language; keyword strategy aligned.","Kristin''s departure noted; Ruby and Sam now handling all highly engaged lead follow-ups.","Ruby to present 2025 marketing recap January 22; Nathalie to extract campaign data by then."],"highlights":[{"quote":"If we''re doing this and the market... we''re not aligned with the business, then that''s not going to help us grow.","speaker":"Jeffery Lauria"},{"quote":"We should have a draft for you early next week.","speaker":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"quote":"The real strong point of these glossary definition pages is... to become an AI citation on ChatGPT.","speaker":"Colin Costigan"}],"topics":["SEO","dashboards","ABM","content","reporting"],"model":"openai/gpt-4-1106-preview","version":1,"generated_at":"2026-01-14T23:29:53Z"}'::jsonb,
    '{"fireflies_summary":{"notes":"## **SEO and Content Strategy**\n\nThe team is advancing SEO efforts to boost top-of-funnel traffic and align content with market demand.\n\n- **Three new location-based SEO landing pages were published** this month to improve local search visibility and drive traffic to the site (12:00)\n    - These pages target geographic keywords to attract region-specific prospects.\n    - The glossary section was launched with **two informational definition pages** to enhance keyword breadth and technical authority (12:50)\n    - Colin explained that glossary pages help capture AI-driven search queries on platforms like ChatGPT, bringing qualified traffic directly to these pages.\n    - Jeffery emphasized that content must reflect real market language, noting the example of the “Encompass” service, which lacks industry recognition and thus requires rebranding to improve search relevance.\n\n- **SEO updates are ongoing for the Microsoft Copilot consulting page**, with a preview to be shared for review (12:00)\n    - The team is incorporating Jeffery’s suggested changes to better position AI consulting services.\n    - Nathalie proposed linking new AI campaign landing pages within existing site sections to increase visibility and user flow.\n    - The team agreed to develop preview pages and share PDFs for Jeffery’s feedback to streamline review and iteration (16:00).\n\n## **Lead Generation and Marketing Performance**\n\nLead management and campaign tracking are being refined to improve conversion rates and sales alignment.\n\n- The **ABM campaign’s highly engaged leads increased to 253** following targeted follow-up emails and LinkedIn outreach (10:00)\n    - Ruby and Sam will now handle lead follow-ups after Kristin’s departure to maintain continuity.\n    - Lead communication emails and LinkedIn messages will be sent from Sam’s account to improve personalization and response rates.\n    - January MQLs reached **12 leads with 2 converting to SQLs**, resulting in a **16-17% conversion rate**, which Nathalie noted is above average for the company (11:00).\n    - Jeffery requested additional context for these numbers to evaluate quality, noting that without industry benchmarks, raw percentages lack meaning.\n\n- Jeffery stressed the need for **industry benchmarking on lead conversion** to provide meaningful insights to sales leadership and align expectations (20:00)\n    - This will help clarify whether current rates outperform or lag behind market norms.\n    - Ruby acknowledged this and planned to incorporate comparative data in future reporting.\n\n## **Dashboard Development and Reporting**\n\nThe marketing team is building dashboards to provide transparent, actionable insights for leadership.\n\n- Ruby confirmed the **dashboard draft will be ready by early next week**, with initial work starting Friday (7:00)\n    - The dashboard will integrate key metrics such as SEO performance, lead quality, and campaign engagement.\n    - Jeffery shared a reporting template listing important KPIs like top keywords, underperforming pages, and lead sources to guide dashboard content (04:00).\n    - The goal is to align metrics with business needs, ensuring marketing efforts support service offerings and market trends.\n\n- Ruby is preparing a **2025 marketing recap report for January 22nd** that will use Pulse dashboard and HubSpot data, focusing on campaign-level analysis (18:00)\n    - She requested assistance breaking down results by campaign (financial services, construction) across channels like email, ads, and LinkedIn.\n    - Nathalie agreed to provide detailed campaign data from tools including Smartly Reach to support this report.\n    - Jeffery emphasized that clear, contextual reporting will help sales and marketing teams track progress and adjust strategies effectively.\n\n## **AI Campaign Integration and Website Updates**\n\nThe AI-focused marketing campaign involves new assets and site updates to highlight readiness and consulting services.\n\n- Two AI campaign landing pages are live: the **assessments page** and the **development and AI page** (15:00)\n    - Nathalie outlined plans to add linked callout boxes on related pages, such as the FAQ and ungoverned AI use sections, to drive traffic to new content.\n    - The approach aims to guide visitors through the funnel starting from AI readiness to consulting offerings.\n    - The team decided preview pages will be developed and shared with leadership for annotation and feedback before full deployment.\n\n- Jeffery confirmed PDF versions of pages are acceptable for review to avoid disrupting the team''s workflow (16:00)\n    - Ruby proposed a joint review call with Jeffery and Sam to discuss page flow and content clarity before finalizing changes.\n    - Nathalie will clearly mark new content sections to streamline feedback and reduce confusion during review.\n\n## **Team and Process Updates**\n\nAdjustments to team roles and communication channels aim to maintain momentum and improve coordination.\n\n- Following Kristin’s exit, **Sam and Ruby will take over lead follow-ups** to ensure no drop in engagement with highly engaged leads (10:20)\n    - Changing email and LinkedIn messages to come from Sam’s account should increase personalization and trust in outreach.\n    - Jeffery’s emphasis on contextual data reflects a culture shift toward data-driven decision-making and transparent communication with sales.\n    - Ruby encouraged flexible meeting attendance, noting that once dashboards are operational, many questions will be answered through reporting, reducing meeting frequency.\n\n- The team continues to prioritize aligning marketing output with business goals, ensuring that service offerings match market demand as Jeffery highlighted repeatedly throughout the discussion.","outline":null,"keywords":["SEO","Dashboards","Marketing Qualified Leads","Campaign Performance","ABM","Glossary Pages"],"overview":"- **SEO Enhancements:** Three new location-based SEO pages launched to increase local search visibility and attract specific prospects.\n\n- **Lead Generation Success:** ABM campaign engaged 253 leads; January saw 12 MQLs with a 16-17% conversion rate.\n\n- **Benchmarking Importance:** Need for industry benchmarking on lead conversion emphasized to align sales expectations and improve strategy.\n\n- **Dashboard Development:** Draft dashboard ready next week, highlighting SEO, lead quality, and campaign engagement metrics.\n\n- **AI Campaign Updates:** Two AI landing pages launched; linked callout boxes planned to guide visitors through the funnel.\n\n- **Team Coordination:** Sam and Ruby take over lead follow-ups post-Kristin''s exit, focusing on personalized outreach and data-driven decisions.","action_items":"\n**Nathalie Mintjens**\nNathalie Mintjens to start building the dashboard with her team by Friday and provide a draft early next week (07:32)\nNathalie Mintjens and team to update Microsoft Copilot consulting SEO page and send a preview to Jeffery for feedback (11:30)\nNathalie Mintjens to send updated website additions via preview pages and PDFs to Jeffery and schedule review call with Sam and Jeffery to discuss (16:00)\n\n**Ruby Pontbriand**\nRuby Pontbriand to receive and review Jeffery’s document on reporting metrics and integrate insights into dashboard planning (04:50)\nRuby Pontbriand and Nathalie Mintjens to coordinate on gathering detailed campaign performance data from Smartly Reach and HubSpot for 2024/2025 recap presentations (18:30)\nRuby Pontbriand to present the 2024 marketing recap to stakeholders on January 22nd (19:53)\n\n**Unassigned**\nMarketing team to change the sender of LinkedIn messages and emails to Jeffery’s account for consistency in lead follow-ups (10:40)\n\n**Jeffery Lauria**\nJeffery Lauria to provide industry benchmarking data context to Ruby and Nathalie for better interpretation of conversion rates and marketing metrics (20:50)\n\n**Samuel Bagnall**\nSamuel Bagnall to provide Jeffery with additional materials and one-pager from Mike Hadley as requested (23:00)\n"},"migrated_from":"contract_meetings","original_id":"48532e2b-10ba-44c6-8741-9fce5eaf26bc","master_marketer":{"status":"migrated"}}'::jsonb,
