want to make sure that we.","index":858,"end_time":2221.14,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2217.94,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"We agree as a team.","index":859,"end_time":2222.34,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2221.22,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"So you get the lead, you call and you have.","index":860,"end_time":2228.72,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2224.42,"speaker_name":"Ryan Fisher"},{"text":"You don''t even have a meeting.","index":861,"end_time":2229.92,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2228.72,"speaker_name":"Ryan Fisher"},{"text":"Yeah, you might get them for like, a half hour.","index":862,"end_time":2232.44,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2230.8,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Quick conversation and it''s nothing.","index":863,"end_time":2234.08,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2232.44,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Man.","index":864,"end_time":2234.48,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2234.08,"speaker_name":"Ryan Fisher"},{"text":"That doesn''t feel like a loss.","index":865,"end_time":2237.52,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2236.16,"speaker_name":"Ryan Fisher"},{"text":"So we can talk about this in our marketing call tomorrow morning with it.","index":866,"end_time":2243.96,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2239.36,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"All right, got it.","index":867,"end_time":2244.88,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2243.96,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"All right, we''re getting off track.","index":868,"end_time":2246.52,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2245.44,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"We don''t need Colin for this.","index":869,"end_time":2247.6,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2246.52,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Yeah, we are.","index":870,"end_time":2248.96,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2248.24,"speaker_name":"Ryan Fisher"},{"text":"We''ve been a little bit all over the place today.","index":871,"end_time":2251.6,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2249.84,"speaker_name":"Ryan Fisher"},{"text":"I''m gonna get.","index":872,"end_time":2252.64,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2251.92,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"I''m gonna fill in some of these gaps a little bit on this, and we''ll talk about it and see if our win rate is really 22.","index":873,"end_time":2257.76,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2252.64,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"I mean, just removing that one.","index":874,"end_time":2260.06,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2258.7,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Are we up to 33%?","index":875,"end_time":2262.7,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2261.26,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"Well, that''s the other thing is you have a smaller sample size at that area, too.","index":876,"end_time":2268.78,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2265.66,"speaker_name":"Ryan Fisher"},{"text":"Yep.","index":877,"end_time":2269.9,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2269.34,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"So it''s going to move a lot more based off that stuff.","index":878,"end_time":2273.06,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2270.94,"speaker_name":"Ryan Fisher"},{"text":"But, yeah, we can talk about it.","index":879,"end_time":2273.979,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2273.06,"speaker_name":"Ryan Fisher"},{"text":"I think it''s worth talking about.","index":880,"end_time":2275.1,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2273.979,"speaker_name":"Ryan Fisher"},{"text":"I think it''s worth talking about because we''re treating it as a.","index":881,"end_time":2277.66,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2275.26,"speaker_name":"Ryan Fisher"},{"text":"As a pretty big line in the sand for us and not saying it''s not, but we probably owe it a little bit of polishing.","index":882,"end_time":2286.3,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2277.66,"speaker_name":"Ryan Fisher"},{"text":"Yeah, fair enough.","index":883,"end_time":2287.54,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2286.3,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"The thing I don''t want to do is you''d be biased and slant stuff towards.","index":884,"end_time":2290.98,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2287.54,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"I don''t want to bias to the data.","index":885,"end_time":2292.5,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2291.06,"speaker_name":"Ryan Fisher"},{"text":"To the data we want to hear.","index":886,"end_time":2293.94,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2292.66,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Right.","index":887,"end_time":2294.22,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2293.94,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"I''m willing to say that we have a gap there, but I just want to look at it.","index":888,"end_time":2297.38,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2294.22,"speaker_name":"Ryan Fisher"},{"text":"I. I mean, I think I have enough information to say that I think it''s probably true, but also, too, I don''t want to really, you know, hurt ourselves on it either, so.","index":889,"end_time":2306.98,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2297.38,"speaker_name":"Ryan Fisher"},{"text":"Yep.","index":890,"end_time":2307.58,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2306.98,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"All right.","index":891,"end_time":2308.02,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2307.58,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"All right.","index":892,"end_time":2309.02,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2308.66,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I think we''re good.","index":893,"end_time":2309.7,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2309.02,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":894,"end_time":2310.42,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2309.94,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right, I''ll get working on the pitch.","index":895,"end_time":2311.86,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2310.42,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Thanks.","index":896,"end_time":2312.55,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2312.31,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Thank you.","index":897,"end_time":2312.99,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2312.55,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"All right, See you guys.","index":898,"end_time":2313.75,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2312.99,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"See you.","index":899,"end_time":2314.35,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2313.91,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"Take care.","index":900,"end_time":2314.79,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2314.35,"speaker_name":"Christopher Quigley"},{"text":"Of.","index":901,"end_time":2321.91,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2321.75,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"}],"dateString":"2026-01-13T20:00:00.000Z","host_email":"colin.costigan@marketersindemand.com","meeting_link":"https://teams.microsoft.com/l/meetup-join/19:meeting_ODBmZWFjMWYtMWIxYi00NmZmLTgyMDEtOWFiZWJhYWEwYzVh@thread.v2/0?context={\"Tid\":\"3801011d-e732-48ee-be2a-e499b1a29ba4\",\"Oid\":\"e804fbe9-a623-4d26-a887-992e62fb92d1\"}","participants":["cquigley@techmode.com,michael.lewis@techmode.com,colin.costigan@marketersindemand.com,lhall@techmode.com,mlook@techmode.com,rfisher@techmode.com","cquigley@techmode.com","michael.lewis@techmode.com","colin.costigan@marketersindemand.com","mlook@techmode.com","rfisher@techmode.com"],"transcript_url":"https://app.fireflies.ai/view/01KEDG6KENV9NNCD9C6F4PHPZ6","organizer_email":"colin.costigan@marketersindemand.com"}'::jsonb,
    '{"label":"positive","confidence":0.88,"bullets":["Agreed to develop targeted SMB landing page after data showed higher win rate under 100 seats.","Colin confirmed Microsoft Ads campaign is ready; budget decision deferred to next week.","Team aligned on auditing Google Ads keywords to better reflect SMB-focused strategy.","Matthew cited 45% win rate for 1-50 user deals; shift from enterprise to SMB acknowledged.","Decision made to add summary sections to blog posts to improve AI search discoverability."],"highlights":[{"quote":"What we''re learning is that we win pretty well under 100.","speaker":"Matthew Look"},{"quote":"I agree with you, Matt. I think in the short term we got to play to our strength.","speaker":"Ryan Fisher"},{"quote":"I''ve been going through the site page by page...we refer to ourselves as a UCaaS.","speaker":"Lindsay Hall"}],"topics":["delivery","audience","strategy","ads","analytics"],"model":"gpt-4-1106-preview","version":1,"generated_at":"2026-01-14T22:31:00Z"}'::jsonb,
    '{"fireflies_summary":{"notes":"## **Sales Performance and Market Focus**\n\nThe team uncovered that their highest **win rate of 45%** occurs with deals under **100 stations**, while deals over **100 stations drop to a 22% win rate**, prompting a strategic shift toward smaller clients (14:58).\n\n- **Matthew Look** highlighted this unexpected shift in customer success, showing the need to reconsider their traditional enterprise focus on accounts over 100 stations.\n- They found the best segment is actually **1 to 50 stations**, with win rates declining incrementally above that.\n- This data calls for adjusting Google Ads and marketing efforts toward the **under 100 market**, especially **small and medium businesses (SMBs)**, to better reflect where they are winning.\n- The team agreed to build dedicated **SMB landing pages** and campaigns to target this segment, rather than rewriting the whole website immediately (18:50, 20:25, 27:45).\n\nMatthew also noted inconsistencies and mislabeling in deal data (e.g., a deal mislabeled as TechMode.Go), which Lindsay is fixing to improve accuracy for future analysis (16:17).\n\n## **Sales Process and Buyer Engagement**\n\nThe team discussed how to better communicate company legitimacy and value during sales, especially for larger deals.\n\n- A recent deal for **132 stations** showed that after presenting pricing, the prospect still asked about company size and reputation, indicating that current messaging may not stick (21:52).\n- **Ryan Fisher** suggested adding more visible **case studies and customer logos** to build trust quickly.\n- Matthew pointed out that the team already shares NPS scores (around **85 based on thousands of ratings**) and Better Business Bureau ratings but suspects the message may not resonate strongly (23:44).\n- The group considered flipping the sales script to lead with pricing and then reinforce company credibility to avoid losing prospects’ attention.\n- Colin emphasized tailoring conversations by starting with customer needs and then highlighting relevant features and credibility elements near the end of the sales cycle (26:27).\n\nThe overall takeaway is that sales messaging may need refinement to better hold buyers’ attention and answer their trust questions promptly.\n\n## **Marketing and Website Strategy**\n\nMarketing efforts will pivot to better address the SMB segment and improve SEO and AI content strategies.\n\n- The team is updating the **price hover page** and reducing header sizes per Lindsay’s notes, with campaigns ready to launch, including Microsoft Ads, price offer, virtual IP phone system, and MSP search campaigns (05:13, 06:37).\n- Matthew shared they are changing blog formats to include **executive summaries at the top** to improve AI-driven SEO on platforms like ChatGPT and Claude, enhancing content discoverability (07:31).\n- Lindsay is systematically reviewing the site to ensure consistent self-identification as a **UCaaS company**, which supports clearer positioning for search engines and customers (13:42).\n- The plan is to create **SMB-focused landing pages** linked from targeted Google Ads campaigns to better attract and convert small business leads without overhauling the entire site immediately (19:59, 27:45).\n- Colin confirmed an audit of Google Ads keywords is underway to refocus on the **under 100 stations market** as the primary target (30:48).\n\n## **Data Cleanup and Deal Validation**\n\nImproving CRM data quality is essential to understanding true sales performance.\n\n- Lindsay is working on correcting mislabeled deals and cleaning HubSpot records, especially for deals created around the HubSpot adoption period in early 2024 (16:21, 33:27).\n- The team agreed that leads without demos or meaningful engagement should not be marked as lost deals but rather as opportunities or discarded to avoid skewing win/loss rates (36:32).\n- This cleanup will help refine the actual win rate, which may rise from **22% to around 33%** once inaccurate entries are removed (37:41).\n- Matthew plans to follow up with sales reps for missing information and clarification to ensure data accuracy (36:18).\n\n## **Trademark and Brand Protection**\n\nThe company secured a broad **registered trademark** covering technology-related terms including UCaaS and AI, protecting their brand widely (29:01).\n\n- Matthew chose to apply broadly despite warnings, ensuring competitors cannot easily claim related technology terms.\n- Lindsay will coordinate swapping out the registered logos on the website to reflect this new status, with Colin managing the updates (28:45, 30:28).\n\n## **Next Steps and Priorities**\n\nThe team confirmed focus on the **under 100 stations market** moving forward, with marketing and sales efforts aligned accordingly (30:48).\n\n- Google Ads campaigns will be adjusted to emphasize this segment, with dedicated landing pages launching soon.\n- Data cleanup and deal validation will continue to ensure accurate sales metrics.\n- Sales messaging will be reviewed to improve buyer trust and engagement, especially for larger accounts.\n- Trademark updates and branding changes will be completed promptly to solidify market identity.","outline":null,"keywords":["SMB market","Google Ads campaigns","sales data analysis","AI content strategy","branding consistency","pricing presentation"],"overview":"- **Sales Focus Shift:** Focus on clients with under 100 stations due to a 45% win rate, compared to 22% for larger accounts.\n- **Marketing Alignment:** New campaigns for small and medium businesses will include dedicated landing pages and targeted Google Ads.\n- **Sales Messaging Improvement:** Refining messaging to enhance credibility and buyer trust, particularly for larger deals, is a priority.\n- **Data Quality Enhancement:** Cleaning up CRM data is crucial for accurate sales metrics; win rate may increase from 22% to 33%.\n- **Trademark Protection:** A broad registered trademark secures technology-related terms, strengthening brand defense against competitors.","action_items":"\n**Colin Costigan**\nImplement updates to the price hover page and tech mode go page as per Lindsay’s feedback (05:13)\nLaunch Microsoft ads campaign with current assets and budget, pending next week’s budget review (06:39)\nBegin development of SMB-focused landing page to target Google Ads traffic effectively (28:41)\nConduct audit of Google Ads keywords and campaigns to realign toward under-100 seat market segment (31:02)\nTake responsibility for swapping registered trademarked logos on website once Lindsay sends the updated files (30:37)\nPerform sales data cleanup in HubSpot for mislabeled deals and coordinate with sales team to confirm qualification of leads (36:07)\n\n**Lindsay Hall**\nContinue reviewing website pages to ensure consistent UCaaS branding and company references (13:42)\nProvide copy and updated registered trademark logos for website update (30:37)\nInvestigate and correct deal record inaccuracies in CRM, especially relating to unpitched or lost deals (30:37)\n\n**Matthew Look**\nContinue reviewing two-year sales data to verify win rates and deal qualification accuracy, specifically cleaning up dubious over-100 seat losses (14:04)\nShare insights and data with team to inform SMB landing page and campaign strategy (14:04)\nCoordinate with sales team (Mike and Kurt) post-call to get details on unclear deals and update CRM data accordingly (36:18)\n\n**Ryan Fisher**\nContribute perspective on developing case studies and logos to reinforce trust messaging during sales process (22:40)\n\n**All Participants**\nMonitor effectiveness of AI-generated blog content improvements focusing on executive summaries to improve SEO and AI relevance (07:31)\n"},"migrated_from":"contract_meetings","original_id":"f6c6bb99-7fe1-47f2-88f7-c71d0749baca","master_marketer":{"status":"migrated"}}'::jsonb,
