-- Meeting: KTC // MiD: Weekly Marketing Meeting (2026-01-13 18:00:00+00)
WITH new_meeting AS (
  INSERT INTO compass_meetings (contract_id, meeting_date, source, external_id, title, participants, duration_seconds, recording_url, transcript, sentiment, raw_metadata, created_at, updated_at)
  VALUES (
    '72cdc11e-fd4f-4d90-8688-1fc1484de2b0',
    '2026-01-13 18:00:00+00',
    'fireflies',
    '01KEF6QKCX3CDW43W91TPHX3G0',
    'KTC // MiD: Weekly Marketing Meeting',
    '{"Colin Costigan","Kristen Baller","Michael Kersten","Colin Costigan","Colin Costigan"}'::text[],
    2073,
    'https://us02web.zoom.us/j/83519004309?pwd=JvKSZR6BzSlyNxK5WTgZHYayMsLSKi.1&jst=2',
    '{"id":"01KEF6QKCX3CDW43W91TPHX3G0","title":"KTC // MiD: Weekly Marketing Meeting","summary":{"notes":"## **Account-Based Marketing (ABM) Strategy and Execution**\n\nThe ABM initiative is progressing with targeted messaging and rapid iteration planned to engage time-sensitive growth-stage companies.\n\n- **The team finalized email and LinkedIn messaging sequences targeting private equity partners, infrastructure, and manufacturing CEOs, focusing on operational momentum and gap-filling roles** (08:14)  \n    - Michael Kersten confirmed no initial feedback, allowing list-building of companies and contacts to begin.  \n    - Automated LinkedIn connection requests will vary by prospect profile to increase relevance and response rates.  \n    - Kristen Baller requested removing \"Hi\" from LinkedIn greetings to avoid appearing generic due to platform AI habits.  \n    - The approach aims for fast data collection with four initial emails to enable quick campaign adjustments, improving conversion speed.\n\n- **The ABM campaign budget is set at approximately $19,000 for 2026, with a $2,000 initial spend planned for February split between $1,500 on LinkedIn and $500 on programmatic display ads** (27:24)  \n    - Kristen Baller will add the additional $2,000 to the Q2 budget and review spend in one-on-one discussions with Michael.  \n    - The campaign launch is tied to the website going live, targeted for February, to maximize visitor conversion potential.\n\n## **Website Development and SEO Strategy**\n\nWebsite development is advancing into the build phase with SEO-focused structural choices to enhance search visibility and lead generation.\n\n- **Development is underway to finalize the website’s theme and pages, incorporating varied keyword terms like \"retained search\" and \"executive search\" for broad search engine reach** (11:13)  \n    - Colin Costigan explained distributing FAQs across multiple pages improves searchability and aligns with ChatGPT’s preference for question-based content, driving more relevant traffic.  \n    - Michael Kersten agreed with the SEO rationale despite initial preference for a single FAQ page.  \n    - Kristen emphasized consistent service naming, confirming “retained search” leads service descriptions aligned with its higher revenue potential.  \n    - Footer content will be globally updated for easier management and consistency.\n\n- **Contact details and branding updates are planned, including switching the office address to Parker and replacing RingCentral phone service with live receptionist support during business hours** (15:15)  \n    - Michael will provide the new phone number once activated for footer updates.  \n    - Multiple email mailboxes will be consolidated to a single primary address to maintain site cleanliness, with contact forms preferred over clickable email links to reduce spam exposure.\n\n## **Podcast Video Series and Content Marketing**\n\nThe Executive Advantage podcast series is being developed with professional audio and visual branding to support marketing and lead generation.\n\n- **Intro and outro music assets are being sourced from Premium Beats, and voiceover samples from male, middle-aged voices will be provided for approval** (18:08)  \n    - Visual branding including updated logos will be applied uniformly across all episodes to create a cohesive look and feel.  \n    - Colin Costigan highlighted podcast content’s power to open conversations and build trust, citing a client landing a major deal after a podcast guest appearance.  \n    - Michael Kersten shared progress on securing testimonials from senior industry veterans and executives, with plans to gather video or written testimonials for the website and ABM use.\n\n- **Kristen Baller will provide recordings from an upcoming executive speaking engagement to repurpose content snippets for marketing** (21:30)  \n    - Colin confirmed the ability to upload and edit these sessions for promotional clips or podcast guest invitations, expanding content reach.\n\n## **CRM, HubSpot Integration, and Data Management**\n\nHubSpot and ATS integration is being optimized to centralize client data and streamline reporting, with ongoing technical adjustments planned.\n\n- **The team will build a custom HubSpot integration using N8N and Clay to enrich contact data and automate syncing without disrupting existing Zoom mappings during transition** (24:26)  \n    - Michael Kersten’s Zoom subscription ends January, with Richie May providing a replacement license; mappings will require reset and reconfiguration.  \n    - Colin will coordinate with HubSpot reps on subscription renewal due May 2026, planning discussions to optimize costs and services starting April.\n\n- **Michael requested a future audit of the ATS-HubSpot integration and data workflows to ensure long-term stability and address reporting needs** (29:25)  \n    - Koolate ATS with open API will sync job and client data bidirectionally, but currently lacks export flexibility needed for BI and Looker tools.  \n    - Centralizing reporting in HubSpot is preferred to provide a single source of truth for revenue and client activity, enabling better segmentation and analysis.\n\n## **Budgeting, Vendor Relationships, and Billing Arrangements**\n\nBudget allocations and vendor invoicing were clarified to maintain financial transparency and operational efficiency.\n\n- **The ABM and marketing budget includes $3,000 for Q2, increasing to $8,000 for Q3 and Q4, totaling around $19,000 for 2026, deemed sufficient by Colin Costigan** (27:24)  \n    - Spend pacing and allocations will be reviewed quarterly to optimize campaign effectiveness.\n\n- **Michael Kersten arranged for Richie May to pay KTC invoices directly, simplifying financial flows without changing invoicing procedures** (31:17)  \n    - Colin will notify internal owners Justin and Tristan to expect payments from Richie May, ensuring smooth processing.  \n    - This arrangement reduces administrative complexity while keeping accounting transparent.\n\n## **Branding and Marketing Collateral Development**\n\nEfforts to unify branding across client-facing materials aim to enhance professional presentation and market positioning.\n\n- **Colin Costigan committed to delivering finalized logo assets for email signatures and document letterheads once complete** (33:08)  \n    - Kristen Baller requested branded Google or PowerPoint templates for KTC to streamline creation of future presentations and collateral.  \n    - Michael will share existing Richie May slide decks to be adapted into KTC versions with additional RPO-related content, supporting sales and marketing efforts.","outline":null,"keywords":["ABM plan","Website development","LinkedIn campaigns","HubSpot integration","Podcast assets","Retained search","Testimonial sourcing"],"overview":"- **ABM Campaign Progress:** Targeted messaging for growth-stage companies; $19,000 total budget set for 2026, with $2,000 initial spend in February.  \n- **SEO Strategy Development:** Website themes finalized, with diverse keywords to boost search visibility and lead generation, focusing on \"retained search\".  \n- **Podcast Series Branding:** Professional audio and visuals will enhance content quality; clients gain trust and leads, facilitating business conversations.  \n- **HubSpot Integration Optimization:** Custom integration with N8N and Clay underway; focus on centralizing client data and ensuring reporting stability.  \n- **Budget Clarity:** Marketing budget for 2026 confirmed at $19,000, with quarterly reviews planned to maximize campaign effectiveness.  \n- **Unified Branding Development:** Finalized logo assets promised; branded templates requested to improve professional presentation across all materials.","action_items":"\n**Colin Costigan**\nShare ABM target company and contact list for review this week (08:39)\nRemove ''Hi'' from LinkedIn message templates before sending (10:29)\nBegin website theme setup and page building, incorporating minor feedback, especially on FAQ and footer consistency (11:13)\nUpdate footer globally with new office address and contact changes once Michael provides details (15:00)\nRecommend and implement contact form email strategy and maintain an info@ mailbox (16:00)\nSend over voiceover samples and intro/outro podcast music options for approval (18:59)\nDeliver list of contact edits and LinkedIn profile recommendations to Michael this week (23:45)\nPlan and implement HubSpot integration with Clay enrichment tool; maintain Zoom integration during transition (24:20)\nCoordinate with HubSpot rep on subscription renewal process and cost-saving opportunities (26:55)\nAdd initial $2,000 ad spend budget to Q2 for launching campaigns early 2026 (28:04)\nPlan and conduct CRM and ATS integration audit and workflow review in February (29:25)\nDeliver final logo assets for KTC branding and develop slide deck templates for KTC consistent with Richie May designs (33:00)\n\n**Kristen Baller**\nProvide slide decks previously created for Richie May to Colin for adaptation to KTC (33:29)\nAdd $2,000 ad spend to 2026 budget as initial campaign funding and discuss adjustments in upcoming one-on-one with Michael (28:10)\nSend details about Kristen’s speaking engagement recording or any usable content snippets (21:30)\n\n**Michael Kersten**\nProvide new Regis office address and updated phone number for website footer as soon as available (15:00)\nSupply details of Zoom subscription transition and collaborate with Colin on HubSpot and ATS integration setup (24:43)\nEngage contacts for testimonials post-search completion and share with Colin for content use (19:23)\nCoordinate with Richie May on payment of invoices and communicate if any issues arise (31:17)\n"},"duration":34.54999923706055,"speakers":[{"id":0,"name":"Colin Costigan"},{"id":1,"name":"Kristen Baller"},{"id":2,"name":"Michael Kersten"},{"id":3,"name":"Colin Costigan"},{"id":4,"name":"Colin Costigan"}],"sentences":[{"text":"Hi, Kristen.","index":0,"end_time":259.06,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":258.34,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Hey, how are you doing?","index":1,"end_time":261.22,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":259.54,"speaker_name":"Kristen Baller"},{"text":"All right.","index":2,"end_time":261.5,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":261.22,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"How about yourself?","index":3,"end_time":262.18,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":261.5,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I am hanging in there.","index":4,"end_time":263.86,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":262.42,"speaker_name":"Kristen Baller"},{"text":"I''m just trying to get a few things done before Michael gets on the road.","index":5,"end_time":270.1,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":264.42,"speaker_name":"Kristen Baller"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":6,"end_time":270.82,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":270.26,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Sorry about the delay in getting back to you.","index":7,"end_time":273.1,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":271.3,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I was an annual planning on Thursday, Friday.","index":8,"end_time":275.86,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":273.1,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I assumed you made something.","index":9,"end_time":278.58,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":276.74,"speaker_name":"Kristen Baller"},{"text":"Either had pulled you away or we would just end up talking about it.","index":10,"end_time":282.9,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":278.58,"speaker_name":"Kristen Baller"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":11,"end_time":283.8,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":283.4,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Today.","index":12,"end_time":284.16,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":283.8,"speaker_name":"Kristen Baller"},{"text":"But I just knew I owed you something and so I didn''t want to be too far out.","index":13,"end_time":290.36,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":284.16,"speaker_name":"Kristen Baller"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah.","index":14,"end_time":291.28,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":290.6,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All good.","index":15,"end_time":291.6,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":291.28,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And Michael gave me a call and.","index":16,"end_time":293.08,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":291.6,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Cleared up any questions that he had too.","index":17,"end_time":295,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":293.4,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Oh, good, good, good, good.","index":18,"end_time":296.76,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":295.16,"speaker_name":"Kristen Baller"},{"text":"Hopefully he''ll be.","index":19,"end_time":305.96,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":304.92,"speaker_name":"Kristen Baller"},{"text":"He''ll be joining.","index":20,"end_time":308.04,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":307.08,"speaker_name":"Kristen Baller"},{"text":"He''s usually here pretty.","index":21,"end_time":309.56,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":308.36,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Pretty close to the start.","index":22,"end_time":311.08,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":310.2,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"How was your weekend?","index":23,"end_time":313.72,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":312.76,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It was good.","index":24,"end_time":315.48,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":314.68,"speaker_name":"Kristen Baller"},{"text":"We went to.","index":25,"end_time":316.44,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":315.56,"speaker_name":"Kristen Baller"},{"text":"We here.","index":26,"end_time":318.44,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":317.48,"speaker_name":"Kristen Baller"},{"text":"Where are you guys located?","index":27,"end_time":319.88,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":318.68,"speaker_name":"Kristen Baller"},{"text":"We''re all in different locations.","index":28,"end_time":322.84,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":321,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I am in Maryland and then Paula and then Guille.","index":29,"end_time":327.8,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":322.84,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I''m in Mexico.","index":30,"end_time":330.28,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":329.08,"speaker_name":"Kristen Baller"},{"text":"Oh, okay.","index":31,"end_time":331.8,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":330.84,"speaker_name":"Kristen Baller"},{"text":"We''re in Mexico.","index":32,"end_time":332.84,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":331.8,"speaker_name":"Kristen Baller"},{"text":"In Merida.","index":33,"end_time":334.24,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":333.24,"speaker_name":"Kristen Baller"},{"text":"It''s next to Cancun.","index":34,"end_time":335.4,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":334.24,"speaker_name":"Kristen Baller"},{"text":"Yep.","index":35,"end_time":336.09,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":335.69,"speaker_name":"Kristen Baller"},{"text":"Okay.","index":36,"end_time":337.13,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":336.57,"speaker_name":"Kristen Baller"},{"text":"Now Maine, Columbia.","index":37,"end_time":339.05,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":337.77,"speaker_name":"Kristen Baller"},{"text":"Okay.","index":38,"end_time":340.89,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":340.25,"speaker_name":"Kristen Baller"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":39,"end_time":341.41,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":341.05,"speaker_name":"Kristen Baller"},{"text":"Paul is in Colombia.","index":40,"end_time":342.57,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":341.41,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That''s awesome.","index":41,"end_time":343.69,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":342.89,"speaker_name":"Kristen Baller"},{"text":"So I''m here in Colorado.","index":42,"end_time":345.85,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":344.01,"speaker_name":"Kristen Baller"},{"text":"And in Colorado, we have a ton of mountains and it''s known for essentially people being out in the wilderness, whether.","index":43,"end_time":356.05,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":346.09,"speaker_name":"Kristen Baller"},{"text":"Whether they''re camping or skiing or climbing or whatever.","index":44,"end_time":360.69,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":356.05,"speaker_name":"Kristen Baller"},{"text":"And so this weekend they had a big expo.","index":45,"end_time":363.41,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":360.69,"speaker_name":"Kristen Baller"},{"text":"It''s called the outdoor Expo.","index":46,"end_time":365.09,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":363.41,"speaker_name":"Kristen Baller"},{"text":"And so they bring in RVs and all sorts of things into our convention center.","index":47,"end_time":372.07,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":365.09,"speaker_name":"Kristen Baller"},{"text":"And so we did that this weekend.","index":48,"end_time":375.15,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":372.07,"speaker_name":"Kristen Baller"},{"text":"And thank gosh, my husband was with me because I was looking at these RVs and RVs are becoming more, I don''t know if you want to say affordable, but they''re not as expensive as they once.","index":49,"end_time":390.91,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":375.63,"speaker_name":"Kristen Baller"},{"text":"They once were.","index":50,"end_time":392.19,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":391.31,"speaker_name":"Kristen Baller"},{"text":"So, for example, they had an RV that was basically.","index":51,"end_time":396.11,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":392.99,"speaker_name":"Kristen Baller"},{"text":"I mean, you could live in this thing full time.","index":52,"end_time":398.75,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":396.11,"speaker_name":"Kristen Baller"},{"text":"And it was about $39,000.","index":53,"end_time":401.15,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":398.91,"speaker_name":"Kristen Baller"},{"text":"And I told Ryan, Gosh, I have two Littles and as much as it costs to travel, I said, this is.","index":54,"end_time":410.83,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":401.15,"speaker_name":"Kristen Baller"},{"text":"This is just so much cheaper.","index":55,"end_time":412.15,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":410.83,"speaker_name":"Kristen Baller"},{"text":"This is the way to go.","index":56,"end_time":413.07,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":412.15,"speaker_name":"Kristen Baller"},{"text":"And my husband says, that''s exactly what, you know, that''s what people say every year.","index":57,"end_time":416.79,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":413.07,"speaker_name":"Kristen Baller"},{"text":"And end up walking away with a brand new rv and then two years later have used it twice.","index":58,"end_time":422.64,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":416.79,"speaker_name":"Kristen Baller"},{"text":"Yeah, that makes sense.","index":59,"end_time":424.56,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":422.96,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":60,"end_time":425.36,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":424.88,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"My wife and I were actually just talking.","index":61,"end_time":427.32,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":425.84,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We have a travel wedding in Colorado in July.","index":62,"end_time":430,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":427.32,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It''s an Estes Park.","index":63,"end_time":433.52,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":432.08,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I''ve never been there.","index":64,"end_time":434.719,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":433.68,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But the week before we have another.","index":65,"end_time":437.6,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":436.08,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Travel wedding in Connecticut and I''m actually going to be in that wedding.","index":66,"end_time":441.32,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":437.6,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we got to figure out what we''re doing with our baby.","index":67,"end_time":443.6,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":441.32,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And if we can.","index":68,"end_time":445.04,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":443.6,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Even if we can both go to both weddings, it''s gonna be a lot.","index":69,"end_time":447.64,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":445.04,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, I think you just run an RV maybe, or, you know, your.","index":70,"end_time":452.16,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":447.88,"speaker_name":"Kristen Baller"},{"text":"It''ll turn into your annual cross country, you know, little.","index":71,"end_time":458.68,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":452.16,"speaker_name":"Kristen Baller"},{"text":"Little vacation.","index":72,"end_time":459.56,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":458.68,"speaker_name":"Kristen Baller"},{"text":"Yeah, maybe she''ll be one in two weeks.","index":73,"end_time":464.44,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":459.8,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Oh, that''s not fun.","index":74,"end_time":466.04,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":464.76,"speaker_name":"Kristen Baller"},{"text":"Meaning.","index":75,"end_time":467.48,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":466.84,"speaker_name":"Kristen Baller"},{"text":"I don''t know if I could do a car trip with a. Yeah.","index":76,"end_time":471.16,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":467.56,"speaker_name":"Kristen Baller"},{"text":"What''s a one year old?","index":77,"end_time":472.61,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":471.81,"speaker_name":"Kristen Baller"},{"text":"I''ve got a. I''ve got a three and a four year old.","index":78,"end_time":475.41,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":472.61,"speaker_name":"Kristen Baller"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":79,"end_time":476.93,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":476.37,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Hey, Michael.","index":80,"end_time":477.89,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":477.09,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Hey.","index":81,"end_time":479.49,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":479.17,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"How are you doing?","index":82,"end_time":480.41,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":479.49,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"All right.","index":83,"end_time":480.73,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":480.41,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"How about yourself?","index":84,"end_time":481.33,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":480.73,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I''m all right.","index":85,"end_time":482.53,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":481.65,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"All right.","index":86,"end_time":483.17,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":482.53,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"All right, well, let''s dive in.","index":87,"end_time":485.41,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":484.13,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right, everyone see my screen?","index":88,"end_time":491.49,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":489.97,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":89,"end_time":492.13,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":491.65,"speaker_name":"Kristen Baller"},{"text":"All right, so a few updates on the ABM process as well as the website design and the podcast video series.","index":90,"end_time":502.37,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":494.85,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So for the ABM plan, Michael, you let me know that you had no feedback, so we started moving forward.","index":91,"end_time":506.79,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":503.43,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And so, Kristen, to answer your question from that email, we''ll be working on.","index":92,"end_time":510.59,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":507.19,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"The list build and sharing that with you guys to review so that I''ll.","index":93,"end_time":514.71,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":510.59,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Have a list of companies and a.","index":94,"end_time":515.83,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":514.71,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"List of contacts at those companies based on all of our conversations to date.","index":95,"end_time":519.51,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":515.83,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":96,"end_time":520.31,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":519.83,"speaker_name":"Kristen Baller"},{"text":"That''s what we assumed.","index":97,"end_time":521.75,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":520.31,"speaker_name":"Kristen Baller"},{"text":"And then, Michael, you probably both saw me going back and forth with Ryan, so there were some tools that we.","index":98,"end_time":528.63,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":523.11,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Had to get access to and some others that he hadn''t set up yet.","index":99,"end_time":530.95,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":528.63,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we got those set up.","index":100,"end_time":531.99,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":530.95,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So he''s been very responsive, which has been great to work with.","index":101,"end_time":535.46,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":532.66,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And we''ll also be sharing after this meeting.","index":102,"end_time":538.42,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":535.62,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We have written the email and LinkedIn messaging copy that would be going out from Michael.","index":103,"end_time":546.18,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":538.42,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we have subject line variations baked into this.","index":104,"end_time":550.82,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":548.179,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then once we launch the new.","index":105,"end_time":552.78,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":550.82,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Website, we''ll update these CTAs.","index":106,"end_time":554.9,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":552.78,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But we kind of have a consistent.","index":107,"end_time":559.09,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":555.78,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Focus through these of really identifying the.","index":108,"end_time":562.21,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":559.09,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Gap and filling roles, making sure that.","index":109,"end_time":564.93,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":562.21,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Companies understand the operational momentum and what.","index":110,"end_time":566.85,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":564.93,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It''S like to work with Kirsten.","index":111,"end_time":568.49,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":566.85,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So this is a series of four emails to start out because I don''t like to put campaigns together where it''s.","index":112,"end_time":573.81,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":569.29,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Like, cool, we''ll come back in a.","index":113,"end_time":575.29,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":573.81,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Month or two and see how it did.","index":114,"end_time":576.73,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":575.29,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I like to collect data a lot faster and make iterations as we go.","index":115,"end_time":580.17,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":577.13,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Then on the LinkedIn side, you''ll see down here, so we''ll be sending out automated connection requests from Michael''s profile.","index":116,"end_time":589.41,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":581.85,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So there''s a connection request message.","index":117,"end_time":591.35,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":589.41,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then based on their profile, we''re going to have different messaging sequences for what they likely are dealing with.","index":118,"end_time":598.55,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":591.35,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So private equity operating partners being one infrastructure and manufacturing CEOs being another and.","index":119,"end_time":604.59,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":598.63,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Then for as much data as we.","index":120,"end_time":606.47,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":604.59,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Can utilize, making sure that we''re tagging on to anyone that has really stepped into the growth stage of their company, which is a much more time.","index":121,"end_time":615.27,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":606.47,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Well, I mean they''re all time sensitive, but this is a very time pressing audience.","index":122,"end_time":618.39,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":615.27,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":123,"end_time":620.62,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":620.14,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":124,"end_time":624.86,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":624.3,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Any questions on anything for the ABM plan or the emails or anything?","index":125,"end_time":628.06,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":625.1,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"This is just little.","index":126,"end_time":630.06,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":629.1,"speaker_name":"Kristen Baller"},{"text":"Can you remove so you know how you have high name?","index":127,"end_time":633.26,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":630.3,"speaker_name":"Kristen Baller"},{"text":"Yes, I could you remove hi and I only ask because LinkedIn when they do their AI or their like standard messages of to mass it always says hi name like hi you know, hi Colin.","index":128,"end_time":649.4,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":633.9,"speaker_name":"Kristen Baller"},{"text":"So and I think for, for many they probably like kind of gotten the see that so often.","index":129,"end_time":656.92,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":649.4,"speaker_name":"Kristen Baller"},{"text":"So if it''s just their name, I don''t know if you can just do the name message, it might feel a little bit more personal.","index":130,"end_time":663.24,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":657,"speaker_name":"Kristen Baller"},{"text":"No problem.","index":131,"end_time":665.8,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":665.16,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Unless you think different.","index":132,"end_time":668.52,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":667.4,"speaker_name":"Kristen Baller"},{"text":"Michael.","index":133,"end_time":669.16,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":668.6,"speaker_name":"Kristen Baller"},{"text":"No, that''s fine.","index":134,"end_time":670.44,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":669.56,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"All right, we''ll make that change before we send it over then.","index":135,"end_time":675.64,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":673.64,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then on the website side.","index":136,"end_time":680.6,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":679.24,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we are moving into developing everything, so setting up the theme and foundation and everything.","index":137,"end_time":688.16,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":680.6,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then we can just start building out all of the pages that you guys have reviewed from a content design perspective, which should be a relatively quick process since there hasn''t been much feedback on other than Kristen, I saw that you left a few comments as well.","index":138,"end_time":699.56,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":688.16,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Go ahead, Paula.","index":139,"end_time":702.07,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":700.47,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Is there anything I''m missing here that.","index":140,"end_time":702.99,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":702.07,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You guys wanted to dive into?","index":141,"end_time":703.99,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":702.99,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We''re moving to development.","index":142,"end_time":709.03,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":707.83,"speaker_name":"Kristen Baller"},{"text":"Okay.","index":143,"end_time":710.47,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":709.83,"speaker_name":"Kristen Baller"},{"text":"One of the things Michael and I talked about yesterday was Instead of having FAQs on every page, maybe have one FAQ page.","index":144,"end_time":719.11,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":710.63,"speaker_name":"Kristen Baller"},{"text":"So there is a reason why we.","index":145,"end_time":722.43,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":720.63,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We recommend FAQs on every page.","index":146,"end_time":724.23,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":722.43,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It''s for searchability.","index":147,"end_time":725.19,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":724.23,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So oftentimes people aren''t looking for, for.","index":148,"end_time":729.22,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":725.59,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"The direct solution, they are searching a question.","index":149,"end_time":731.42,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":729.22,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And if we have that type of relevant content on various pages, so having it on multiple pages allows us to have like this is relevant to this information and then they land there and then you know, the page is geared towards what they''re looking for in the first place.","index":150,"end_time":744.46,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":731.9,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, that makes sense.","index":151,"end_time":746.3,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":744.86,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Okay.","index":152,"end_time":746.94,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":746.3,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"But yeah, great question.","index":153,"end_time":749.26,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":748.14,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I kind of thought the other way.","index":154,"end_time":751.74,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":750.3,"speaker_name":"Kristen Baller"},{"text":"I was thinking, gosh, how, you know, what if, how do they find their question if it''s on.","index":155,"end_time":757.48,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":752.14,"speaker_name":"Kristen Baller"},{"text":"But what I''m hearing is it''s mostly like somebody''s going into the either doing a Google query or they''re in our actual search bar asking that or chatgpt.","index":156,"end_time":770.6,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":758.6,"speaker_name":"Kristen Baller"},{"text":"So chatgpt loves FAQs because as you guys may know, people are Doing longer prompts.","index":157,"end_time":777.6,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":770.84,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That''s why Google is losing share to.","index":158,"end_time":779.2,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":777.6,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"ChatGPT as a search engine because people.","index":159,"end_time":781.96,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":779.2,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Are able to ask like multiple questions in one.","index":160,"end_time":784.04,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":781.96,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And so when we get popping up there as a citation or on the.","index":161,"end_time":788.43,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":785.15,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Google side, you know, they search their.","index":162,"end_time":789.87,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":788.43,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Question, it pops up as KTC search with a result.","index":163,"end_time":792.35,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":789.87,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We''re going to get more traffic that way and very relevant traffic too.","index":164,"end_time":796.83,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":793.23,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Gotcha.","index":165,"end_time":797.71,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":797.07,"speaker_name":"Kristen Baller"},{"text":"And then the feedback that you were looking for for this go around for the website, was it just on the structure or the content?","index":166,"end_time":806.67,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":798.03,"speaker_name":"Kristen Baller"},{"text":"Just any feedback that you have in general?","index":167,"end_time":808.71,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":807.07,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I mean, we can make content changes pretty easily if you guys wanted to tweak anything.","index":168,"end_time":812.59,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":808.71,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But I would like us to get.","index":169,"end_time":814.55,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":813.47,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Into development so that we can make any tweaks and go live as soon as possible.","index":170,"end_time":818.41,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":814.55,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":171,"end_time":819.45,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":818.89,"speaker_name":"Kristen Baller"},{"text":"I think the biggest content change we had discussed was really more in the footer as well as there''s some places we talk about executive search and then there''s others where we say.","index":172,"end_time":835.69,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":820.17,"speaker_name":"Kristen Baller"},{"text":"Retain.","index":173,"end_time":838.89,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":838.25,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Retained.","index":174,"end_time":839.73,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":839.13,"speaker_name":"Kristen Baller"},{"text":"Thank you.","index":175,"end_time":840.25,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":839.73,"speaker_name":"Kristen Baller"},{"text":"Retained.","index":176,"end_time":841.09,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":840.57,"speaker_name":"Kristen Baller"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":177,"end_time":841.53,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":841.09,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Search.","index":178,"end_time":842.26,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":841.86,"speaker_name":"Kristen Baller"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":179,"end_time":842.98,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":842.58,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So another effort on purpose because we.","index":180,"end_time":846.38,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":842.98,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Want to have search.","index":181,"end_time":847.66,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":846.38,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, exactly.","index":182,"end_time":848.14,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":847.66,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Search engine results.","index":183,"end_time":848.94,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":848.14,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we want to.","index":184,"end_time":849.66,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":848.94,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"For the way that I always put.","index":185,"end_time":851.66,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":849.66,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"This is you guys are absolutely the expert in everything that you do.","index":186,"end_time":854.5,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":851.66,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"The people that you work with are.","index":187,"end_time":856.14,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":854.66,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Using you guys for a reason.","index":188,"end_time":857.1,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":856.14,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"They don''t know those exact terms all the time.","index":189,"end_time":859.7,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":857.1,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"They''re going to use some different terms.","index":190,"end_time":860.94,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":859.7,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we wanted to have as many.","index":191,"end_time":862.3,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":860.94,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Different representations of that type of like keyword, like parent topic as possible.","index":192,"end_time":868.89,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":862.3,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":193,"end_time":869.93,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":869.37,"speaker_name":"Kristen Baller"},{"text":"And then Michael had talked about always leading with retained search.","index":194,"end_time":873.77,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":870.09,"speaker_name":"Kristen Baller"},{"text":"Like when we''re showing.","index":195,"end_time":874.97,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":873.77,"speaker_name":"Kristen Baller"},{"text":"I didn''t put it on every page, but can we look at the.","