 makes sense.","index":372,"end_time":1397.46,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1395.86,"speaker_name":"Kristen Baller"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":373,"end_time":1398.5,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1398.02,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So, yeah, great opportunity.","index":374,"end_time":1399.7,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1398.5,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And let us know if.","index":375,"end_time":1400.9,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1399.86,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Well, one, when you have any snippets to share with us and then to.","index":376,"end_time":1406.14,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1401.06,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"If they would be interested in coming on as a guest.","index":377,"end_time":1408.46,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1406.38,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":378,"end_time":1410.86,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1410.22,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right.","index":379,"end_time":1411.78,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1411.34,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then we have our portal.","index":380,"end_time":1413.14,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1411.78,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we''ll be sending over.","index":381,"end_time":1414.5,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1413.14,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I''ll make some edits to the emails.","index":382,"end_time":1416.98,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1414.5,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"To and the messages to remove the highs from those before we send them over.","index":383,"end_time":1420.38,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1416.98,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We''re making great progress on the website.","index":384,"end_time":1422.78,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1421.1,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then, Michael, the one thing I.","index":385,"end_time":1424.18,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1422.86,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Owe you, besides the list of contacts, is just the edits to your LinkedIn profile, and I''ll be sharing those this week as well.","index":386,"end_time":1431.16,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1424.18,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, cool.","index":387,"end_time":1432,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1431.4,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"And then.","index":388,"end_time":1432.24,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1432,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Hey, Colin, I know we had talked about it.","index":389,"end_time":1434.2,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1432.24,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"I don''t know if you need to put it in your plan just so for.","index":390,"end_time":1436.96,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1434.6,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"You guys can budget for hours, but in our HubSpot instance, you''ll.","index":391,"end_time":1441.8,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1436.96,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"You guys will work that stuff behind the scenes.","index":392,"end_time":1443.6,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1441.88,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"So if we add content fi and contacts in there, you''ll populate the feeds of fields or whatever.","index":393,"end_time":1447.84,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1443.6,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Okay, cool.","index":394,"end_time":1448.32,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1447.84,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"And then right now, they have all that stuff mapped to Zoom.","index":395,"end_time":1452.4,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1448.32,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"So I don''t.","index":396,"end_time":1453,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1452.4,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"You would have to tell me is, can you map.","index":397,"end_time":1455.57,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1453,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"You know, can I keep my mappings to my Zoom stuff so if stuff is still there or do we.","index":398,"end_time":1460.61,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1456.05,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Or will you guys just go in there and unplug all the Zoom stuff and just set it all up to, you know, your other tool?","index":399,"end_time":1466.69,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1460.61,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":400,"end_time":1467.29,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1466.93,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So what we would do is set.","index":401,"end_time":1468.25,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1467.29,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Up an integration with Clay from that to.","index":402,"end_time":1471.21,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1468.25,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"For the enrichment, we wouldn''t just break the Zoom one.","index":403,"end_time":1473.65,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1471.21,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I like to have, like, while we build, we would still have Zoom running.","index":404,"end_time":1476.61,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1473.65,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then we would just talk and.","index":405,"end_time":1478.29,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1476.93,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Be like, all right, cool.","index":406,"end_time":1479.01,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1478.29,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Clear cutoff date.","index":407,"end_time":1479.97,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1479.01,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Let''s unplug Zoom if it''s not needed at all.","index":408,"end_time":1483.1,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1480.3,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, cool.","index":409,"end_time":1483.78,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1483.18,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"And then question for you is, you guys can probably answer quicker than my folks in India.","index":410,"end_time":1489.1,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1483.78,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"So are so my My, I have a subscription through KTC through Zoom, but my Zoom subscription is going to end at the end of January and then I, Richie May has given me a seat for their Zoom environment.","index":411,"end_time":1503.98,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1489.1,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"If all the mappings are already set up, can you, is it, can you just repeat.","index":412,"end_time":1508.19,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1504.78,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Is it an easy search and replace that you''re logging in?","index":413,"end_time":1511.54,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1508.98,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"You know, when you go into HubSpot and I log in with a different credential, does it keep all the mappings the same or does it now because it''s a different instance, you have to be able to map those out over there.","index":414,"end_time":1520.74,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1511.54,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"It''ll probably reset the map.","index":415,"end_time":1522.98,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1521.06,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, okay, okay, okay.","index":416,"end_time":1525.02,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1523.06,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"So then what I may ask, I guess question for you guys and is if, since that''s going to break and if, if you guys are really essentially going to enrich my data with Clay, maybe I have you guys, you know, see what you can.","index":417,"end_time":1538.97,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1525.02,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Well, you guys are in there now, but you can see what we''re mapping.","index":418,"end_time":1541.61,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1538.97,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Maybe just go ahead and set that stuff up for Clay because I was going to start populating stuff into that and if the connection is going to break, you know, the.","index":419,"end_time":1552.17,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1541.77,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"I had an enterprise license and Richie Mae only has a professional license and I''m not an admin on there, so I''m not obviously going to be able to change stuff.","index":420,"end_time":1559.73,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1552.57,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"So for purposes of not having a headache and if, you know, like we talked about, if you guys can enrich it, which is really all I had it was using it for anyhow, you know, I''ll let you guys just remap it and just put that into, you know, my hours or whatever.","index":421,"end_time":1572.51,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1559.73,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah.","index":422,"end_time":1573.43,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1572.75,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we''ll build a workflow that we basically, it''s called building an app is how HubSpot refers to it.","index":423,"end_time":1579.43,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1573.43,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we build that to route through an automation tool called N8N and Claude for the enrichment and then basically just automatically filter that content back into HubSpot.","index":424,"end_time":1588.17,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1579.43,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, cool.","index":425,"end_time":1589,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1588.48,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"And then one more question on HubSpot is you can probably tell me is I can''t Remember with my HubSpot if I signed a multi year deal or just a single deal, does my.","index":426,"end_time":1597.96,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1589,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Does HubSpot say if I''m a multi deal or just a year by year?","index":427,"end_time":1601.12,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1597.96,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Because obviously if I''m renewing, since you guys are a HubSpot provider, would.","index":428,"end_time":1605.72,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1601.28,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Would you guys be, you know, basically be able to take.","index":429,"end_time":1608.2,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1605.72,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Help me broker that relationship and then I''ll have to deal with HubSpot.","index":430,"end_time":1610.68,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1608.2,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"I just deal with you guys from there.","index":431,"end_time":1612.04,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1610.68,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":432,"end_time":1612.44,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1612.04,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":433,"end_time":1612.76,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1612.44,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":434,"end_time":1613,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1612.76,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So I can reach out to our.","index":435,"end_time":1614.04,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1613,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"HubSpot rep it looks like you get billed every three months and your subscription term is May 13, 2025 to May 12, 2026.","index":436,"end_time":1622.07,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1614.04,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":437,"end_time":1622.75,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1622.31,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"All right.","index":438,"end_time":1623.07,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1622.75,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"So I just did a year.","index":439,"end_time":1623.87,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1623.07,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Okay, cool.","index":440,"end_time":1624.35,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1623.87,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Yep.","index":441,"end_time":1624.67,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1624.35,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So okay, so just I guess put that in thing and then when did we.","index":442,"end_time":1629.27,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1624.67,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Because Kristen was updating all my budget stuff.","index":443,"end_time":1631.87,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1629.51,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"When did we say we were going to start using.","index":444,"end_time":1633.59,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1631.87,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Ad spend?","index":445,"end_time":1637.03,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1636.23,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah.","index":446,"end_time":1637.71,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1637.11,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Spend, yeah.","index":447,"end_time":1638.43,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1637.71,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"So where did you put that into the budget at?","index":448,"end_time":1640.47,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1638.43,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Oh, Kristen, I was Q2.","index":449,"end_time":1647.8,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1644.24,"speaker_name":"Kristen Baller"},{"text":"I have budgeted about 3,000 and then I upped it to 8,000 for Q4 or Q3 and Q4.","index":450,"end_time":1654.48,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1647.8,"speaker_name":"Kristen Baller"},{"text":"So I think a 16, 19,000 total for 2026.","index":451,"end_time":1660.96,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1654.8,"speaker_name":"Kristen Baller"},{"text":"Do you feel like that''s enough?","index":452,"end_time":1662,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1660.96,"speaker_name":"Kristen Baller"},{"text":"Yeah, I mean I think that budget is good.","index":453,"end_time":1665.44,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1663.52,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"The timeline though.","index":454,"end_time":1667.04,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1665.92,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So as soon as we get the.","index":455,"end_time":1668.12,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1667.04,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Website live, we would be good to turn on the campaign which I''m hoping to be able to do in February.","index":456,"end_time":1672.8,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1668.12,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":457,"end_time":1673.43,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1673.19,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"That''s why it is back.","index":458,"end_time":1674.43,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1673.43,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"It will move it back forward then.","index":459,"end_time":1675.59,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1674.43,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Okay.","index":460,"end_time":1675.99,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1675.59,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Or even maybe if you just want.","index":461,"end_time":1677.07,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1675.99,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"To take from some of the Q3, Q4 that you distributed.","index":462,"end_time":1679.75,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1677.07,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"How much do you typically like to put in the initial campaign to get.","index":463,"end_time":1684.95,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1680.55,"speaker_name":"Kristen Baller"},{"text":"In the first campaign?","index":464,"end_time":1685.79,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1684.95,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I would like to have about 2000 and that''ll be 1500 towards LinkedIn and 500 towards the programmatic display advertising.","index":465,"end_time":1691.51,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1685.79,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I will add.","index":466,"end_time":1692.55,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1691.75,"speaker_name":"Kristen Baller"},{"text":"Michael, I''m going to add 2,000.","index":467,"end_time":1694.63,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1693.11,"speaker_name":"Kristen Baller"},{"text":"Okay.","index":468,"end_time":1695.67,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1695.11,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Add it as a talking point in our one on one to see if we need to pull back.","index":469,"end_time":1699.03,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1695.67,"speaker_name":"Kristen Baller"},{"text":"Yep, that''s fine.","index":470,"end_time":1700.38,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1699.5,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":471,"end_time":1704.14,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1703.5,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right.","index":472,"end_time":1709.18,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1708.7,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Any other question?","index":473,"end_time":1709.94,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1709.18,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Yeah, no, that was it.","index":474,"end_time":1710.82,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1709.94,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"And then.","index":475,"end_time":1711.26,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1710.82,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Oh, one more quick question.","index":476,"end_time":1714.58,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1712.06,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"HubSpot.","index":477,"end_time":1715.26,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1714.58,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"So there what I''ve done just to give you for our conversation you and you and I had, Colin, is I''ve killed my monthly with them because obviously like you said, you guys could take that over now they are almost done.","index":478,"end_time":1727.76,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1715.34,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"If you can.","index":479,"end_time":1728.32,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1727.76,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"You''ll probably see they''re in there, you know, doing the development.","index":480,"end_time":1730.68,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1728.32,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"So my stuff will transport in back and forth between my ATS and obviously CRM.","index":481,"end_time":1736.68,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1730.84,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"But once they''re done with that, I know they''re using webhooks and I had to procure something through aws.","index":482,"end_time":1742.2,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1737.72,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Once that''s done, I may have you guys take a quick look.","index":483,"end_time":1747.32,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1742.68,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"And just so if you''re going to take all that stuff over for my CRM and then also that integration, just kind of see if there''s anything that''s going to break what you guys are trying to do.","index":484,"end_time":1756.87,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1747.32,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"And then more importantly, maybe just a quick audit to see if there''s something we might have done differently.","index":485,"end_time":1763.03,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1756.87,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Just so Long term, it doesn''t cause me any grief.","index":486,"end_time":1765.75,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1763.43,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah, no worries.","index":487,"end_time":1767.03,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1765.99,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"What is your ats?","index":488,"end_time":1768.47,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1767.19,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"What''s this?","index":489,"end_time":1769.39,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1768.869,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It''s Koolate.","index":490,"end_time":1770.15,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1769.39,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"C R E. Yep.","index":491,"end_time":1772.91,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1771.83,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"C R E L A T E. Yeah.","index":492,"end_time":1776.03,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1772.91,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"And they, they''re, they have open API, so if you want to get into that, you can.","index":493,"end_time":1779.67,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1776.03,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"But they''re basically, they''re.","index":494,"end_time":1781.27,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1779.67,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"What they''re going to do is all.","index":495,"end_time":1783.11,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1781.35,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"If you go in, rats.","index":496,"end_time":1784.07,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1783.11,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"We have all the jobs based on clients.","index":497,"end_time":1785.97,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1784.07,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"It''s just going to be a sync going back and forth.","index":498,"end_time":1788.45,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1786.29,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"So that way I can use HubSpot to track, you know, everything we''re doing in regards from more of a system of record for revenue standpoint.","index":499,"end_time":1798.05,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1788.45,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Hey, we did this much with Richie, man.","index":500,"end_time":1799.49,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1798.05,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"We did this much here.","index":501,"end_time":1800.45,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1799.49,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"You know, obviously it''s got a lot more bells and whistles and charts which obviously I''d probably come back to you guys and say, hey, can you help me develop some of that?","index":502,"end_time":1807.21,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1800.45,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"But we''re using BI and Looker for some other stuff because right now, you know, Kool Aid has some decent reports, but you can''t export them.","index":503,"end_time":1814.65,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1807.21,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"When you export them, it''s just Excel.","index":504,"end_time":1816.13,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1814.65,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"So we have a couple developers that are, you know, doing stuff in BI and stuff.","index":505,"end_time":1819.99,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1816.29,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"But I really need a systems or record.","index":506,"end_time":1822.19,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1819.99,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"So if I come up and say, hey, here''s what we did, you know, per Richie May, per all our other clients, I can carve it up and it''s, it doesn''t carve out that well in their system.","index":507,"end_time":1831.15,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1822.19,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"So.","index":508,"end_time":1831.55,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1831.15,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah, that makes sense.","index":509,"end_time":1832.83,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1831.55,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":510,"end_time":1833.11,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1832.83,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And BI and Google Looker Studio have their fair share of issues as well, correct?","index":511,"end_time":1838.35,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1833.11,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yep, yep.","index":512,"end_time":1839.11,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1838.35,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"So I figured if we''re, if we''re centralizing on HubSpot, you know, once we get done with some of the stuff and Looker, I can show you what I, what I need.","index":513,"end_time":1845.55,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1839.11,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":514,"end_time":1846.16,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1845.96,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then ideally maybe we could come back and build that into HubSpot.","index":515,"end_time":1849.64,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1846.16,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"So once again, I got one.","index":516,"end_time":1850.8,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1849.64,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"One, you know, one.","index":517,"end_time":1851.96,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1850.8,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"One central owner of everything, so.","index":518,"end_time":1854.4,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1851.96,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah, of course.","index":519,"end_time":1855.64,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1854.4,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":520,"end_time":1857.64,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1857,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right, well, I''ll make the changes.","index":521,"end_time":1860.52,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1858.04,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"To that document and then send that over to you guys to review.","index":522,"end_time":1862.44,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1860.52,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then, yeah, I''ll send over the.","index":523,"end_time":1864.16,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1862.52,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"List this week as well as edits to your LinkedIn profile.","index":524,"end_time":1867.48,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1864.16,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Perfect, perfect.","index":525,"end_time":1868.92,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1868.04,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"And then.","index":526,"end_time":1869.28,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1868.92,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Hey, quickly, quick question, Colin, for you.","index":527,"end_time":1873.76,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1869.28,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"And I don''t know if I need to get back to.","index":528,"end_time":1875.04,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1873.76,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"I forget that your two owners that.","index":529,"end_time":1877.16,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1875.04,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"I talked to, but Tristan and Justin.","index":530,"end_time":1878.84,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1877.16,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, Chris and Justin.","index":531,"end_time":1879.88,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1878.84,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"So let Justin know is starting probably this month or next month.","index":532,"end_time":1885.6,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1879.88,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Keep sitting when they send my retainers come back.","index":533,"end_time":1888.28,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1886.08,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"But part of my deal Brokering, since we''re moving.","index":534,"end_time":1890.48,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1888.28,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"This is.","index":535,"end_time":1891.12,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1890.48,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"You guys still invoice me, but then I worked a deal where Richie May''s going to offset me, so.","index":536,"end_time":1897.32,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1891.28,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"And so instead of them paying me to pay you, we''re just, they''re going to pay my.","index":537,"end_time":1901.09,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1897.32,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Pay those invoices on my behalf.","index":538,"end_time":1903.29,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1901.09,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"So no different.","index":539,"end_time":1904.37,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1903.53,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"They''re still coming in, but instead of seeing a wire coming from ktc, they''ll see a wire coming from Richie.","index":540,"end_time":1909.93,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1904.37,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"So if they have any questions, just let me know.","index":541,"end_time":1912.41,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1909.93,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"But you know, they don''t reference saying, hey, we''re paying KTC''s influence, but part of what I negotiated with them, you know, since we''re building this out, they''re going to pay the bills.","index":542,"end_time":1921.53,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1912.41,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"So.","index":543,"end_time":1921.85,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1921.53,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Okay, well that''s awesome.","index":544,"end_time":1923.37,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1922.01,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yep.","index":545,"end_time":1924.01,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1923.45,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"All right, cool.","index":546,"end_time":1924.85,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1924.33,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, I''ll let them know.","index":547,"end_time":1925.77,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1924.85,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Should be totally fine.","index":548,"end_time":1926.71,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1925.77,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, I figured you guys could care less long as the money''s coming.","index":549,"end_time":1929.98,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1927.1,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"I like green.","index":550,"end_time":1931.86,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1931.02,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I like green for sure.","index":551,"end_time":1932.7,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1931.86,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Exactly.","index":552,"end_time":1933.06,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1932.7,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":553,"end_time":1933.34,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1933.06,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Most people could care less who pays as long as it hits their account.","index":554,"end_time":1936.14,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1933.34,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"So, yes, awesome.","index":555,"end_time":1937.9,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1936.14,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But yeah, and then as any HubSpot.","index":556,"end_time":1939.98,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1938.14,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Questions or as your renewal comes up and we''ll, we''ll make a note in our system that that''s coming up in May.","index":557,"end_time":1944.62,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1939.98,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So in April we''ll probably start having some conversations with you around anything you.","index":558,"end_time":1948.34,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1945.1,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Want to switch or getting a conversation.","index":559,"end_time":1949.74,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1948.34,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Started with our rep, see if we can save you any money.","index":560,"end_time":1952.51,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1949.74,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, cool.","index":561,"end_time":1953.26,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1952.82,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Yeah, so I think the biggest thing is since you guys have that is I''ve cut them off is you know, obviously build into the hours you guys are using to get the, the, the data cleansing or whatever.","index":562,"end_time":1964.26,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1953.26,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"And then I think they''ll be done with the project for the integration at the end of the month.","index":563,"end_time":1968.82,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1964.26,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"So maybe, you know, on the February calendar it''s kind of maybe you guys taking a look in there and then maybe, you know, we have a quick 30 minute call just on HubSpot to say, okay, hey, here''s what I have, here''s what they''ve done, here''s some things that I would like to be have done and then you guys can kind of build that into my budget for the year.","index":564,"end_time":1984.85,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1968.82,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Yeah, sounds good.","index":565,"end_time":1986.93,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1985.01,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That works perfect.","index":566,"end_time":1989.25,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1988.13,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"And then you''re going to also once you guys are done with our logo, you''ll get it, you''ll give us like a logo thing.","index":567,"end_time":1994.01,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1989.25,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"So for emails and then all our other document letterheads and all that stuff.","index":568,"end_time":2000.89,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1994.01,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Okay, cool.","index":569,"end_time":2001.37,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2000.89,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Yep.","index":570,"end_time":2001.81,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2001.37,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":571,"end_time":2002.17,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2001.81,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then I know that you shared.","index":572,"end_time":2003.57,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2002.17,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Some slide decks, so let us know if you have like content for a specific slide deck that you would like.","index":573,"end_time":2007.49,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2003.57,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Us to develop in your branding as well.","index":574,"end_time":2008.85,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2007.49,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yep.","index":575,"end_time":2009.44,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2009.16,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Hey, Kristen, can you send them the one that the other Kristen did?","index":576,"end_time":2012.48,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2009.44,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"And then right now it''s in the Richie Mate.","index":577,"end_time":2014.12,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2012.48,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Ta stuff.","index":578,"end_time":2014.8,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2014.12,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"But you guys can.","index":579,"end_time":2015.68,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2014.8,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Obviously that''s the version we use for.","index":580,"end_time":2018.04,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2015.68,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"For rm, but if we could take that same thing and flip it to a ktc, that''d be good.","index":581,"end_time":2024.04,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2018.04,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"And then we would want to add some additional content because we talk about the internal stuff we did at Richie Mae.","index":582,"end_time":2028.92,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2024.2,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"But our example for the KTC would be more of.","index":583,"end_time":2031.68,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2029,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"That''s an rpo.","index":584,"end_time":2032.48,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2031.68,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Example of what we''ve done from an rpo.","index":585,"end_time":2034.28,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2032.48,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Gotcha.","index":586,"end_time":2035.25,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2034.77,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, go ahead, Kristen.","index":587,"end_time":2036.97,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2035.33,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"I cut you off.","index":588,"end_time":2037.49,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2036.97,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Sorry.","index":589,"end_time":2037.89,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2037.49,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"I will.","index":590,"end_time":2038.49,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2037.97,"speaker_name":"Kristen Baller"},{"text":"No, I''ll send that over.","index":591,"end_time":2039.73,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2038.49,"speaker_name":"Kristen Baller"},{"text":"I was going to ask if you guys do like a Google template or a PowerPoint template just of the KTC.","index":592,"end_time":2046.29,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2040.05,"speaker_name":"Kristen Baller"},{"text":"Right.","index":593,"end_time":2046.93,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2046.53,"speaker_name":"Kristen Baller"},{"text":"So that we can leverage that every time we make a new.","index":594,"end_time":2049.97,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2046.93,"speaker_name":"Kristen Baller"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah.","index":595,"end_time":2050.97,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2050.289,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We build templates all the time.","index":596,"end_time":2052.05,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2050.97,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, perfect.","index":597,"end_time":2052.93,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2052.05,"speaker_name":"Kristen Baller"},{"text":"That would be super helpful.","index":598,"end_time":2055.25,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2053.01,"speaker_name":"Kristen Baller"},{"text":"Yeah, of course.","index":599,"end_time":2056.29,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2055.49,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":600,"end_time":2057.73,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2057.17,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right, I do have to jump.","index":601,"end_time":2059.49,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2058.13,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"To it on the meeting, but thank you both so much for your time.","index":602,"end_time":2061.41,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2059.49,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And we''ll send over everything we talked about.","index":603,"end_time":2063.57,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2061.97,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Sounds good.","index":604,"end_time":2064.17,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2063.65,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Thanks.","index":605,"end_time":2064.45,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2064.17,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Appreciate it.","index":606,"end_time":2064.89,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2064.45,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Thanks, guys.","index":607,"end_time":2065.37,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2064.89,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Have a good day.","index":608,"end_time":2065.77,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2065.37,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"We''ll be.","index":609,"end_time":2066.02,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2065.77,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"}],"dateString":"2026-01-13T18:00:00.000Z","host_email":"colin.costigan@marketersindemand.com","meeting_link":"https://us02web.zoom.us/j/83519004309?pwd=JvKSZR6BzSlyNxK5WTgZHYayMsLSKi.1&jst=2","participants":["colin.costigan@marketersindemand.com,guille.santana@marketersindemand.com,michael@kerstentalentcapital.com,kristen@kerstentalentcapitals.co,kristen.baller@richeymay.com,paula.ocampo@marketersindemand.com","guille.santana@marketersindemand.com","michael@kerstentalentcapital.com","kristen@kerstentalentcapitals.co","kristen.baller@richeymay.com","paula.ocampo@marketersindemand.com"],"transcript_url":"https://app.fireflies.ai/view/01KEF6QKCX3CDW43W91TPHX3G0","organizer_email":"colin.costigan@marketersindemand.com"}'::jsonb,
    '{"label":"positive","confidence":0.95,"bullets":["Confirmed ABM emails and LinkedIn messages ready; launch contingent on website go-live in February.","Decided to move ad spend forward to February with $2,000 initial investment approved.","Aligned on website structure, including SEO FAQs and global footer edits for contact consistency.","Agreed HubSpot integration will use Clay and N8N with a clear switch plan post Zoom subscription.","Secured testimonial sources and promotional assets for podcast series; voice talent and music underway."],"highlights":[{"quote":"We''re making great progress on the website.","speaker":"Colin Costigan"},{"quote":"The search with him has gone extremely well... he''ll be willing to give a spokesperson.","speaker":"Michael Kersten"},{"quote":"I''m also doing a speaking engagement... with three other HR executives across Fortune 200 organizations.","speaker":"Kristen Baller"}],"topics":["campaign","website","testimonials","hubspot","ads","content"],"model":"openai/gpt-4-1106-preview","version":1,"generated_at":"2026-01-13T00:00:00Z"}'::jsonb,
    '{"fireflies_summary":{"notes":"## **Account-Based Marketing (ABM) Strategy and Execution**\n\nThe ABM initiative is progressing with targeted messaging and rapid iteration planned to engage time-sensitive growth-stage companies.\n\n- **The team finalized email and LinkedIn messaging sequences targeting private equity partners, infrastructure, and manufacturing CEOs, focusing on operational momentum and gap-filling roles** (08:14)  \n    - Michael Kersten confirmed no initial feedback, allowing list-building of companies and contacts to begin.  \n    - Automated LinkedIn connection requests will vary by prospect profile to increase relevance and response rates.  \n    - Kristen Baller requested removing \"Hi\" from LinkedIn greetings to avoid appearing generic due to platform AI habits.  \n    - The approach aims for fast data collection with four initial emails to enable quick campaign adjustments, improving conversion speed.\n\n- **The ABM campaign budget is set at approximately $19,000 for 2026, with a $2,000 initial spend planned for February split between $1,500 on LinkedIn and $500 on programmatic display ads** (27:24)  \n    - Kristen Baller will add the additional $2,000 to the Q2 budget and review spend in one-on-one discussions with Michael.  \n    - The campaign launch is tied to the website going live, targeted for February, to maximize visitor conversion potential.\n\n## **Website Development and SEO Strategy**\n\nWebsite development is advancing into the build phase with SEO-focused structural choices to enhance search visibility and lead generation.\n\n- **Development is underway to finalize the website’s theme and pages, incorporating varied keyword terms like \"retained search\" and \"executive search\" for broad search engine reach** (11:13)  \n    - Colin Costigan explained distributing FAQs across multiple pages improves searchability and aligns with ChatGPT’s preference for question-based content, driving more relevant traffic.  \n    - Michael Kersten agreed with the SEO rationale despite initial preference for a single FAQ page.  \n    - Kristen emphasized consistent service naming, confirming “retained search” leads service descriptions aligned with its higher revenue potential.  \n    - Footer content will be globally updated for easier management and consistency.\n\n- **Contact details and branding updates are planned, including switching the office address to Parker and replacing RingCentral phone service with live receptionist support during business hours** (15:15)  \n    - Michael will provide the new phone number once activated for footer updates.  \n    - Multiple email mailboxes will be consolidated to a single primary address to maintain site cleanliness, with contact forms preferred over clickable email links to reduce spam exposure.\n\n## **Podcast Video Series and Content Marketing**\n\nThe Executive Advantage podcast series is being developed with professional audio and visual branding to support marketing and lead generation.\n\n- **Intro and outro music assets are being sourced from Premium Beats, and voiceover samples from male, middle-aged voices will be provided for approval** (18:08)  \n    - Visual branding including updated logos will be applied uniformly across all episodes to create a cohesive look and feel.  \n    - Colin Costigan highlighted podcast content’s power to open conversations and build trust, citing a client landing a major deal after a podcast guest appearance.  \n    - Michael Kersten shared progress on securing testimonials from senior industry veterans and executives, with plans to gather video or written testimonials for the website and ABM use.\n\n- **Kristen Baller will provide recordings from an upcoming executive speaking engagement to repurpose content snippets for marketing** (21:30)  \n    - Colin confirmed the ability to upload and edit these sessions for promotional clips or podcast guest invitations, expanding content reach.\n\n## **CRM, HubSpot Integration, and Data Management**\n\nHubSpot and ATS integration is being optimized to centralize client data and streamline reporting, with ongoing technical adjustments planned.\n\n- **The team will build a custom HubSpot integration using N8N and Clay to enrich contact data and automate syncing without disrupting existing Zoom mappings during transition** (24:26)  \n    - Michael Kersten’s Zoom subscription ends January, with Richie May providing a replacement license; mappings will require reset and reconfiguration.  \n    - Colin will coordinate with HubSpot reps on subscription renewal due May 2026, planning discussions to optimize costs and services starting April.\n\n- **Michael requested a future audit of the ATS-HubSpot integration and data workflows to ensure long-term stability and address reporting needs** (29:25)  \n    - Koolate ATS with open API will sync job and client data bidirectionally, but currently lacks export flexibility needed for BI and Looker tools.  \n    - Centralizing reporting in HubSpot is preferred to provide a single source of truth for revenue and client activity, enabling better segmentation and analysis.\n\n## **Budgeting, Vendor Relationships, and Billing Arrangements**\n\nBudget allocations and vendor invoicing were clarified to maintain financial transparency and operational efficiency.\n\n- **The ABM and marketing budget includes $3,000 for Q2, increasing to $8,000 for Q3 and Q4, totaling around $19,000 for 2026, deemed sufficient by Colin Costigan** (27:24)  \n    - Spend pacing and allocations will be reviewed quarterly to optimize campaign effectiveness.\n\n- **Michael Kersten arranged for Richie May to pay KTC invoices directly, simplifying financial flows without changing invoicing procedures** (31:17)  \n    - Colin will notify internal owners Justin and Tristan to expect payments from Richie May, ensuring smooth processing.  \n    - This arrangement reduces administrative complexity while keeping accounting transparent.\n\n## **Branding and Marketing Collateral Development**\n\nEfforts to unify branding across client-facing materials aim to enhance professional presentation and market positioning.\n\n- **Colin Costigan committed to delivering finalized logo assets for email signatures and document letterheads once complete** (33:08)  \n    - Kristen Baller requested branded Google or PowerPoint templates for KTC to streamline creation of future presentations and collateral.  \n    - Michael will share existing Richie May slide decks to be adapted into KTC versions with additional RPO-related content, supporting sales and marketing efforts.","outline":null,"keywords":["ABM plan","Website development","LinkedIn campaigns","HubSpot integration","Podcast assets","Retained search","Testimonial sourcing"],"overview":"- **ABM Campaign Progress:** Targeted messaging for growth-stage companies; $19,000 total budget set for 2026, with $2,000 initial spend in February.  \n- **SEO Strategy Development:** Website themes finalized, with diverse keywords to boost search visibility and lead generation, focusing on \"retained search\".  \n- **Podcast Series Branding:** Professional audio and visuals will enhance content quality; clients gain trust and leads, facilitating business conversations.  \n- **HubSpot Integration Optimization:** Custom integration with N8N and Clay underway; focus on centralizing client data and ensuring reporting stability.  \n- **Budget Clarity:** Marketing budget for 2026 confirmed at $19,000, with quarterly reviews planned to maximize campaign effectiveness.  \n- **Unified Branding Development:** Finalized logo assets promised; branded templates requested to improve professional presentation across all materials.","action_items":"\n**Colin Costigan**\nShare ABM target company and contact list for review this week (08:39)\nRemove ''Hi'' from LinkedIn message templates before sending (10:29)\nBegin website theme setup and page building, incorporating minor feedback, especially on FAQ and footer consistency (11:13)\nUpdate footer globally with new office address and contact changes once Michael provides details (15:00)\nRecommend and implement contact form email strategy and maintain an info@ mailbox (16:00)\nSend over voiceover samples and intro/outro podcast music options for approval (18:59)\nDeliver list of contact edits and LinkedIn profile recommendations to Michael this week (23:45)\nPlan and implement HubSpot integration with Clay enrichment tool; maintain Zoom integration during transition (24:20)\nCoordinate with HubSpot rep on subscription renewal process and cost-saving opportunities (26:55)\nAdd initial $2,000 ad spend budget to Q2 for launching campaigns early 2026 (28:04)\nPlan and conduct CRM and ATS integration audit and workflow review in February (29:25)\nDeliver final logo assets for KTC branding and develop slide deck templates for KTC consistent with Richie May designs (33:00)\n\n**Kristen Baller**\nProvide slide decks previously created for Richie May to Colin for adaptation to KTC (33:29)\nAdd $2,000 ad spend to 2026 budget as initial campaign funding and discuss adjustments in upcoming one-on-one with Michael (28:10)\nSend details about Kristen’s speaking engagement recording or any usable content snippets (21:30)\n\n**Michael Kersten**\nProvide new Regis office address and updated phone number for website footer as soon as available (15:00)\nSupply details of Zoom subscription transition and collaborate with Colin on HubSpot and ATS integration setup (24:43)\nEngage contacts for testimonials post-search completion and share with Colin for content use (19:23)\nCoordinate with Richie May on payment of invoices and communicate if any issues arise (31:17)\n"},"migrated_from":"contract_meetings","original_id":"4e65b957-6640-4956-b0c5-2425cf12e24a","master_marketer":{"status":"migrated"}}'::jsonb,
