INSERT INTO compass_notes (contract_id, meeting_id, note_type, title, content_raw, note_date, status, action_items, is_auto_generated)
SELECT
  new_meeting.contract_id,
  new_meeting.meeting_id,
  'meeting',
  'Meeting Notes: KTC // MiD: Weekly Marketing Meeting',
  '## **Account-Based Marketing (ABM) Strategy and Execution**

The ABM initiative is progressing with targeted messaging and rapid iteration planned to engage time-sensitive growth-stage companies.

- **The team finalized email and LinkedIn messaging sequences targeting private equity partners, infrastructure, and manufacturing CEOs, focusing on operational momentum and gap-filling roles** (08:14)  
    - Michael Kersten confirmed no initial feedback, allowing list-building of companies and contacts to begin.  
    - Automated LinkedIn connection requests will vary by prospect profile to increase relevance and response rates.  
    - Kristen Baller requested removing "Hi" from LinkedIn greetings to avoid appearing generic due to platform AI habits.  
    - The approach aims for fast data collection with four initial emails to enable quick campaign adjustments, improving conversion speed.

- **The ABM campaign budget is set at approximately $19,000 for 2026, with a $2,000 initial spend planned for February split between $1,500 on LinkedIn and $500 on programmatic display ads** (27:24)  
    - Kristen Baller will add the additional $2,000 to the Q2 budget and review spend in one-on-one discussions with Michael.  
    - The campaign launch is tied to the website going live, targeted for February, to maximize visitor conversion potential.

## **Website Development and SEO Strategy**

Website development is advancing into the build phase with SEO-focused structural choices to enhance search visibility and lead generation.

- **Development is underway to finalize the website’s theme and pages, incorporating varied keyword terms like "retained search" and "executive search" for broad search engine reach** (11:13)  
    - Colin Costigan explained distributing FAQs across multiple pages improves searchability and aligns with ChatGPT’s preference for question-based content, driving more relevant traffic.  
    - Michael Kersten agreed with the SEO rationale despite initial preference for a single FAQ page.  
    - Kristen emphasized consistent service naming, confirming “retained search” leads service descriptions aligned with its higher revenue potential.  
    - Footer content will be globally updated for easier management and consistency.

- **Contact details and branding updates are planned, including switching the office address to Parker and replacing RingCentral phone service with live receptionist support during business hours** (15:15)  
    - Michael will provide the new phone number once activated for footer updates.  
    - Multiple email mailboxes will be consolidated to a single primary address to maintain site cleanliness, with contact forms preferred over clickable email links to reduce spam exposure.

## **Podcast Video Series and Content Marketing**

The Executive Advantage podcast series is being developed with professional audio and visual branding to support marketing and lead generation.

- **Intro and outro music assets are being sourced from Premium Beats, and voiceover samples from male, middle-aged voices will be provided for approval** (18:08)  
    - Visual branding including updated logos will be applied uniformly across all episodes to create a cohesive look and feel.  
    - Colin Costigan highlighted podcast content’s power to open conversations and build trust, citing a client landing a major deal after a podcast guest appearance.  
    - Michael Kersten shared progress on securing testimonials from senior industry veterans and executives, with plans to gather video or written testimonials for the website and ABM use.

- **Kristen Baller will provide recordings from an upcoming executive speaking engagement to repurpose content snippets for marketing** (21:30)  
    - Colin confirmed the ability to upload and edit these sessions for promotional clips or podcast guest invitations, expanding content reach.

## **CRM, HubSpot Integration, and Data Management**

HubSpot and ATS integration is being optimized to centralize client data and streamline reporting, with ongoing technical adjustments planned.

- **The team will build a custom HubSpot integration using N8N and Clay to enrich contact data and automate syncing without disrupting existing Zoom mappings during transition** (24:26)  
    - Michael Kersten’s Zoom subscription ends January, with Richie May providing a replacement license; mappings will require reset and reconfiguration.  
    - Colin will coordinate with HubSpot reps on subscription renewal due May 2026, planning discussions to optimize costs and services starting April.

- **Michael requested a future audit of the ATS-HubSpot integration and data workflows to ensure long-term stability and address reporting needs** (29:25)  
    - Koolate ATS with open API will sync job and client data bidirectionally, but currently lacks export flexibility needed for BI and Looker tools.  
    - Centralizing reporting in HubSpot is preferred to provide a single source of truth for revenue and client activity, enabling better segmentation and analysis.

## **Budgeting, Vendor Relationships, and Billing Arrangements**

Budget allocations and vendor invoicing were clarified to maintain financial transparency and operational efficiency.

- **The ABM and marketing budget includes $3,000 for Q2, increasing to $8,000 for Q3 and Q4, totaling around $19,000 for 2026, deemed sufficient by Colin Costigan** (27:24)  
    - Spend pacing and allocations will be reviewed quarterly to optimize campaign effectiveness.

- **Michael Kersten arranged for Richie May to pay KTC invoices directly, simplifying financial flows without changing invoicing procedures** (31:17)  
    - Colin will notify internal owners Justin and Tristan to expect payments from Richie May, ensuring smooth processing.  
    - This arrangement reduces administrative complexity while keeping accounting transparent.

## **Branding and Marketing Collateral Development**

Efforts to unify branding across client-facing materials aim to enhance professional presentation and market positioning.

- **Colin Costigan committed to delivering finalized logo assets for email signatures and document letterheads once complete** (33:08)  
    - Kristen Baller requested branded Google or PowerPoint templates for KTC to streamline creation of future presentations and collateral.  
    - Michael will share existing Richie May slide decks to be adapted into KTC versions with additional RPO-related content, supporting sales and marketing efforts.',
  '2026-01-13 18:00:00+00',
  'published',
  '[{"text":"Share ABM target company and contact list for review this week (08:39)","completed":false},{"text":"Remove ''Hi'' from LinkedIn message templates before sending (10:29)","completed":false},{"text":"Begin website theme setup and page building, incorporating minor feedback, especially on FAQ and footer consistency (11:13)","completed":false},{"text":"Update footer globally with new office address and contact changes once Michael provides details (15:00)","completed":false},{"text":"Recommend and implement contact form email strategy and maintain an info@ mailbox (16:00)","completed":false},{"text":"Send over voiceover samples and intro/outro podcast music options for approval (18:59)","completed":false},{"text":"Deliver list of contact edits and LinkedIn profile recommendations to Michael this week (23:45)","completed":false},{"text":"Plan and implement HubSpot integration with Clay enrichment tool; maintain Zoom integration during transition (24:20)","completed":false},{"text":"Coordinate with HubSpot rep on subscription renewal process and cost-saving opportunities (26:55)","completed":false},{"text":"Add initial $2,000 ad spend budget to Q2 for launching campaigns early 2026 (28:04)","completed":false},{"text":"Plan and conduct CRM and ATS integration audit and workflow review in February (29:25)","completed":false},{"text":"Deliver final logo assets for KTC branding and develop slide deck templates for KTC consistent with Richie May designs (33:00)","completed":false},{"text":"Provide slide decks previously created for Richie May to Colin for adaptation to KTC (33:29)","completed":false},{"text":"Add $2,000 ad spend to 2026 budget as initial campaign funding and discuss adjustments in upcoming one-on-one with Michael (28:10)","completed":false},{"text":"Send details about Kristen’s speaking engagement recording or any usable content snippets (21:30)","completed":false},{"text":"Provide new Regis office address and updated phone number for website footer as soon as available (15:00)","completed":false},{"text":"Supply details of Zoom subscription transition and collaborate with Colin on HubSpot and ATS integration setup (24:43)","completed":false},{"text":"Engage contacts for testimonials post-search completion and share with Colin for content use (19:23)","completed":false},{"text":"Coordinate with Richie May on payment of invoices and communicate if any issues arise (31:17)","completed":false}]'::jsonb,
