-- Meeting: PTO Exchange Weekly (2026-01-12 20:30:00+00)
WITH new_meeting AS (
  INSERT INTO compass_meetings (contract_id, meeting_date, source, external_id, title, participants, duration_seconds, recording_url, transcript, sentiment, raw_metadata, created_at, updated_at)
  VALUES (
    '3f032f15-833e-4d7d-9347-381febf6d953',
    '2026-01-12 20:30:00+00',
    'fireflies',
    '01KE8CGZM49S9S6K4P72CAYZJC',
    'PTO Exchange Weekly',
    '{"Josh Reinhard","Dan Igo","Colin Costigan","Stephanie Lucchesi"}'::text[],
    1823,
    'https://us02web.zoom.us/j/86093865913?pwd=ajXSuerDGmcROjfezSWYYGsa7iPOWd.1',
    '{"id":"01KE8CGZM49S9S6K4P72CAYZJC","title":"PTO Exchange Weekly","summary":{"notes":"## **Lead Generation and Campaign Development**\n\nThe team is actively refining lead flow and exploring new campaign strategies to diversify lead sources and improve engagement.\n\n- **Memorial Herman and Northwell Health leads** recently came through **Heyreach**, the LinkedIn automation tool connecting profiles for messaging and connection requests (06:07).\n    - Dan Igo owns the Memorial Herman lead, aligning with his Houston base.\n    - There are some inactive leads, such as retired CHROs, signaling a need for lead quality filtering.\n    - Colin Costigan is ideating a new campaign to expand lead sources beyond current approaches.\n    - The goal is to find better calls to action and assets that encourage more meaningful engagement than just “request a demo.”\n\n- The **PTO benchmark report campaign** generates qualified leads by providing companies with customized performance PDFs based on multi-year data, triggering meeting links when engaged (10:08).\n    - Leads become marketing qualified once they download their customized report.\n    - Josh Reinhard and Colin discussed moving from automated message sequences to more personalized LinkedIn follow-ups after connection acceptance.\n    - Stephanie Lucchesi raised concerns about premature notifications and suggested postponing outreach until leads become actionable.\n    - Dan sees aligning this with a planned **HubSpot audit and cleanup** to improve lead status accuracy and workflow efficiency (11:09).\n\n- The team agreed on creating a **document outlining workflows for key lead triggers** like demo requests, benchmark reports, LinkedIn connections, and ads to clarify task generation and follow-up steps (11:50).\n    - Josh stressed the importance of defining what actions sales should take per lead type.\n    - Dan supported industry-specific email sequences to leverage relevant company and industry references to boost response rates.\n    - Stephanie emphasized that leads who download benchmark reports are already warm and require minimal customization in outreach.\n    - Colin suggested automating personalized content fields in HubSpot using company data enrichment to simulate tailored outreach without heavy manual effort (18:06).\n\n## **Email Sequence Optimization and Personalization**\n\nThe group plans to simplify and improve email sequences to increase conversion rates while minimizing manual work.\n\n- Current sequences are **too long and generic**, leading to low engagement; Dan referenced average reading times of 3–7 seconds, advocating for shorter, more focused emails (20:39).\n    - Josh wants to replace generic sequences with shorter, industry-relevant emails highlighting proof points and clear, easy meeting requests.\n    - Dan and Stephanie prefer a **set of four industry-specific templates plus one general template** to avoid manual customization but retain relevance (14:20).\n    - Colin warned against heavy email content with many links due to deliverability risks but confirmed that one-to-one outreach with company links is less likely to be flagged (17:16).\n    - The team agreed that emails need to feel personal, even if automated, by including brief company summaries and direct calendar links (19:19).\n\n- Josh proposed establishing a **nurture track for leads who don''t immediately convert**, sending educational content weekly or biweekly over several weeks to maintain engagement (21:50).\n    - Colin confirmed this is easy to implement with HubSpot workflows based on lifecycle stages and opportunity status.\n    - This approach targets long sales cycles common in the market and keeps the company top of mind.\n    - The lack of ongoing nurture for lost or cold leads was seen as a missed opportunity (22:40).\n\n## **Website Development and Content Updates**\n\nSignificant progress is underway to expand and improve website content tailored to client and industry needs.\n\n- Colin announced the completion of **about 10 new web pages**, including a new home page, pricing, integrations, and detailed industry-specific pages covering the primary sectors served (06:54).\n    - These are full website pages, not just pillar pages, enhancing SEO and user experience.\n    - The team will review these pages, with Rob Schwend specifically reviewing the integrations page for accuracy (07:30).\n    - Additional pages target HR leaders and employees to help current clients better use the PTO Exchange platform and reduce demo requests from existing users (08:00).\n    - This content aims to educate both prospects and existing clients, reducing confusion and support workload.\n\n## **HubSpot Audit and Marketing Infrastructure**\n\nThe need for a thorough HubSpot cleanup and restructuring is urgent to improve operational efficiency and lead management.\n\n- Josh described the current HubSpot setup as a **“Frankenstein” with over 400 sequences**, many outdated or redundant, complicating sales and marketing workflows (24:00).\n    - There is a problematic \"go live quarter\" field containing outdated data, indicating poor data hygiene.\n    - Colin recommended focusing the audit on **properties, workflows, and segments** as key areas to streamline (25:21).\n    - The audit could uncover cost savings and better system organization.\n    - Josh suggested waiting for the incoming **fractional CMO hire** to provide strategic input but stressed immediate fixes on low-hanging fruit to avoid losing the critical first two quarters of the year for revenue generation (26:50).\n    - Dan and Josh agreed that sequence cleanup and workflow fixes can proceed before the CMO starts, allowing faster impact (27:21).\n\n- Colin committed to producing a **workflow and sequence cheat sheet document this week** to clarify and optimize lead handling processes (28:55).\n    - The document will serve as a foundation for rebuilding workflows and identifying missing sequences.\n    - Josh will schedule a meeting with Colin and Rob to prioritize and align on next steps (23:45).\n\n## **Sales and Marketing Collaboration and Future Planning**\n\nThe team emphasized strengthening collaboration between sales and marketing for better outcomes and planning joint sessions.\n\n- Dan suggested including a segment with the **New North team during a future Seattle sales meeting** to align sales and marketing efforts more closely (29:43).\n    - This would foster deeper understanding and improve campaign effectiveness.\n    - Josh and Colin supported the idea, recognizing the value of face-to-face or focused time together.\n\n- Colin is preparing **documentation of new marketing offers and campaign flows** to present in the upcoming Thursday meeting, aiming to share fresh ideas and gather feedback (29:30).\n    - This will help guide upcoming campaigns and ensure alignment with sales priorities.\n    - The team sees this as part of ongoing efforts to improve lead quality and conversion.\n\n- Josh, Dan, and Stephanie conveyed readiness to act quickly on improvements that will increase first meeting conversions, targeting a **33% conversion rate on inbound leads** to significantly boost sales pipeline volume (27:59).","outline":null,"keywords":["HubSpot audit","Lead generation","Email sequences","Heyreach LinkedIn integration","Website development","Marketing automation"],"overview":"- **Lead Generation Focus:** Team refining lead strategies; exploring diverse sources, current inactive leads highlight need for quality filtering.\n- **PTO Benchmark Campaign Success:** Custom performance PDFs generate qualified leads; leads become marketing qualified upon download, enhancing engagement efforts.\n- **Email Sequence Improvement:** Current generic emails hinder engagement; shorter, tailored sequences with industry relevance proposed to increase response rates.\n- **Website Content Progress:** Ten new pages launched, including pricing and industry-specific sections, aiming to educate clients and reduce support requests.\n- **HubSpot Cleanup Needed:** Current setup is outdated; focus on properties and workflows to streamline operations and improve lead management efficiency.\n- **Collaboration Initiatives:** Plans for joint meetings with sales to align efforts; focusing on improving inbound lead conversion rates to 33%.","action_items":"\n**Colin Costigan**\nSend new website pages link to Josh, Dan, and Steph for review and feedback (06:30)\nCompile and deliver a workflow document outlining main lead sources, automatic task generation, and email sequence recommendations by end of week (28:55)\nSend calendar scheduling link (SavvyCal) to Josh for booking time with Rob Schwend and Josh to discuss HubSpot audit and sequence improvements (28:40)\nPrepare documentation of marketing campaign offers and flow concepts for Thursday’s meeting (29:30)\n\n**Josh Reinhard**\nReview new website pages when provided and coordinate feedback from sales and Rob Schwend (07:10)\nSchedule and attend HubSpot audit meeting with Colin and Rob Schwend (28:39)\n\n**Dan Igo**\nProvide feedback on email sequences, especially regarding the balance between automation and personalization, with focus on industry-specific approaches (14:10)\n\n**Stephanie Lucchesi**\nContinue feedback on sequence personalization and understand campaign activation timing related to LinkedIn connections and benchmark reports (10:00)\n"},"duration":30.389999389648438,"speakers":[{"id":0,"name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"id":1,"name":"Dan Igo"},{"id":2,"name":"Colin Costigan"},{"id":3,"name":"Stephanie Lucchesi"}],"sentences":[{"text":"It.","index":0,"end_time":25.93,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":25.69,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Hey, colin.","index":1,"end_time":56.74,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":56.18,"speaker_name":"Dan Igo"},{"text":"How you doing?","index":2,"end_time":57.3,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":56.74,"speaker_name":"Dan Igo"},{"text":"Hey, dan.","index":3,"end_time":58.06,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":57.38,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"How''s it going?","index":4,"end_time":58.66,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":58.06,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Good.","index":5,"end_time":59.86,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":59.46,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"That was your holiday season?","index":6,"end_time":93.31,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":92.19,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It was good.","index":7,"end_time":96.27,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":95.55,"speaker_name":"Dan Igo"},{"text":"Yeah, it was good.","index":8,"end_time":98.03,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":96.91,"speaker_name":"Dan Igo"},{"text":"We had family in town.","index":9,"end_time":99.15,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":98.03,"speaker_name":"Dan Igo"},{"text":"It was nice.","index":10,"end_time":100.43,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":99.63,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"It''s awesome.","index":11,"end_time":101.59,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":100.91,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And where are you based out of?","index":12,"end_time":102.67,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":101.59,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Houston.","index":13,"end_time":104.15,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":103.75,"speaker_name":"Dan Igo"},{"text":"Gotcha.","index":14,"end_time":105.27,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":104.55,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yep.","index":15,"end_time":106.39,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":105.75,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Y'' all are up in the east coast, right?","index":16,"end_time":109.59,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":108.07,"speaker_name":"Dan Igo"},{"text":"We''re actually.","index":17,"end_time":110.79,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":110.15,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We''re all over but three quarters of the leadership team, I''m in Maryland, and two of the others are in Virginia.","index":18,"end_time":118.15,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":111.11,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":19,"end_time":119.99,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":119.51,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Yeah, we got United States, Argentina, Serbia, Mexico, Brazil.","index":20,"end_time":129.419,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":122.07,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We''re kind of all over the place.","index":21,"end_time":130.859,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":129.659,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Wow.","index":22,"end_time":132.939,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":132.539,"speaker_name":"Dan Igo"},{"text":"That is all over the place.","index":23,"end_time":133.979,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":132.939,"speaker_name":"Dan Igo"},{"text":"Hi, Steph.","index":24,"end_time":138.139,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":137.339,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Hey, Colin.","index":25,"end_time":139.659,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":139.019,"speaker_name":"Stephanie Lucchesi"},{"text":"How''s it going?","index":26,"end_time":140.219,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":139.659,"speaker_name":"Stephanie Lucchesi"},{"text":"Good.","index":27,"end_time":140.699,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":140.379,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"How are you?","index":28,"end_time":141.259,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":140.699,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Good.","index":29,"end_time":141.899,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":141.499,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"How was your holiday break?","index":30,"end_time":144.379,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":143.099,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It was fun.","index":31,"end_time":146.299,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":145.499,"speaker_name":"Stephanie Lucchesi"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":32,"end_time":147.019,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":146.539,"speaker_name":"Stephanie Lucchesi"},{"text":"Lots of family and friends and traveling, but it''s all good.","index":33,"end_time":151.419,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":147.019,"speaker_name":"Stephanie Lucchesi"},{"text":"What about yours?","index":34,"end_time":152.299,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":151.419,"speaker_name":"Stephanie Lucchesi"},{"text":"Yeah, a lot of the same.","index":35,"end_time":154.539,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":152.859,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Luckily, didn''t have to travel too far, but.","index":36,"end_time":157.9,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":155.9,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, it was my daughter''s first Christmas, so it was a fun time.","index":37,"end_time":161.5,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":158.7,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Oh, that''s fun.","index":38,"end_time":162.54,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":161.5,"speaker_name":"Stephanie Lucchesi"},{"text":"I''m getting a call from my doctor real quick, so I will be right back.","index":39,"end_time":176.94,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":174.3,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"No worries.","index":40,"end_time":178.06,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":177.42,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"How you doing, Dano?","index":41,"end_time":181.66,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":180.3,"speaker_name":"Stephanie Lucchesi"},{"text":"Good.","index":42,"end_time":182.86,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":182.66,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Yourself?","index":43,"end_time":183.38,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":182.86,"speaker_name":"Dan Igo"},{"text":"Good.","index":44,"end_time":184.74,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":184.34,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Busy Monday.","index":45,"end_time":185.54,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":184.82,"speaker_name":"Stephanie Lucchesi"},{"text":"That''s a good thing.","index":46,"end_time":187.22,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":186.5,"speaker_name":"Dan Igo"},{"text":"Did you get everything you needed for credit union?","index":47,"end_time":190.1,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":187.22,"speaker_name":"Dan Igo"},{"text":"Okay?","index":48,"end_time":190.58,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":190.1,"speaker_name":"Dan Igo"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":49,"end_time":190.9,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":190.58,"speaker_name":"Stephanie Lucchesi"},{"text":"I appreciate that.","index":50,"end_time":191.74,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":190.9,"speaker_name":"Stephanie Lucchesi"},{"text":"Thank you.","index":51,"end_time":192.26,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":191.74,"speaker_name":"Stephanie Lucchesi"},{"text":"I just keep that in a folder and, like, frequently shared document folder where I have, like, sock data and then I just copy and paste it.","index":52,"end_time":199.7,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":193.38,"speaker_name":"Dan Igo"},{"text":"Yeah, that''s perfect.","index":53,"end_time":200.94,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":199.94,"speaker_name":"Stephanie Lucchesi"},{"text":"That''s what I did.","index":54,"end_time":201.78,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":200.94,"speaker_name":"Stephanie Lucchesi"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":55,"end_time":202.58,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":202.1,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"What''s up, guys?","index":56,"end_time":209.39,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":208.59,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"What''s up, man?","index":57,"end_time":210.75,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":209.95,"speaker_name":"Dan Igo"},{"text":"We just got Collins.","index":58,"end_time":215.23,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":214.03,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"He just said he had to grab.","index":59,"end_time":218.03,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":216.75,"speaker_name":"Dan Igo"},{"text":"His doctor was calling him.","index":60,"end_time":219.11,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":218.03,"speaker_name":"Dan Igo"},{"text":"He had to grab a phone call.","index":61,"end_time":220.19,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":219.11,"speaker_name":"Dan Igo"},{"text":"I was gonna say, is that just an AI generated.","index":62,"end_time":222.83,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":220.59,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"I like that picture.","index":63,"end_time":225.79,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":224.67,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Very stoic, Colin.","index":64,"end_time":229.47,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":227.95,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":65,"end_time":230.67,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":230.19,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"G. Cube.","index":66,"end_time":233.31,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":232.43,"speaker_name":"Dan Igo"},{"text":"That''s right.","index":67,"end_time":234.29,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":233.73,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Rough day yesterday for you, Josh.","index":68,"end_time":238.93,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":237.17,"speaker_name":"Dan Igo"},{"text":"Telling Steph earlier, game''s over.","index":69,"end_time":244.73,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":241.89,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"I''m, like, texting my brother and another one of my buddies who''s an Eagles fan, and I look like my son hasn''t said anything since the game was over.","index":70,"end_time":252.05,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":244.73,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"And I look over the couch and he''s just quietly crying.","index":71,"end_time":255.25,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":252.13,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"He was.","index":72,"end_time":256.37,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":255.81,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"That''s too bad.","index":73,"end_time":257.57,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":256.69,"speaker_name":"Dan Igo"},{"text":"Rough day in the Reinhardt house?","index":74,"end_time":261.79,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":260.35,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"We.","index":75,"end_time":262.43,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":262.03,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"We got that out of our system very.","index":76,"end_time":264.19,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":262.51,"speaker_name":"Dan Igo"},{"text":"At a very young age at our house.","index":77,"end_time":265.71,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":264.19,"speaker_name":"Dan Igo"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":78,"end_time":266.75,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":266.27,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"I like your passion, but we''re gonna.","index":79,"end_time":271.79,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":268.75,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"We''re gonna be okay.","index":80,"end_time":272.83,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":271.79,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Well, Dan, you''re a Vikings fan, right?","index":81,"end_time":275.95,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":274.19,"speaker_name":"Stephanie Lucchesi"},{"text":"I am, but I. I''ve jumped on the bandwagon, so I''m ready for tonight.","index":82,"end_time":280.43,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":276.99,"speaker_name":"Dan Igo"},{"text":"I''m actually suited up for tonight, so.","index":83,"end_time":282.71,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":280.51,"speaker_name":"Dan Igo"},{"text":"All right.","index":84,"end_time":283.15,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":282.71,"speaker_name":"Stephanie Lucchesi"},{"text":"Oh, look at you.","index":85,"end_time":283.95,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":283.15,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Yeah, but I''m.","index":86,"end_time":285.67,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":284.51,"speaker_name":"Dan Igo"},{"text":"I''m.","index":87,"end_time":285.99,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":285.67,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":88,"end_time":286.31,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":285.99,"speaker_name":"Dan Igo"},{"text":"Die hard Vikings fan, but I''ll root For the Texans and the Astros if the Twins and the Vikings are out of it.","index":89,"end_time":290.99,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":286.31,"speaker_name":"Dan Igo"},{"text":"Nice.","index":90,"end_time":292.1,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":291.78,"speaker_name":"Stephanie Lucchesi"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":91,"end_time":294.02,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":293.54,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Sorry, Josh.","index":92,"end_time":294.82,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":294.02,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":93,"end_time":295.78,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":295.22,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"I just want to say Pats are gonna win it all, so don''t.","index":94,"end_time":299.22,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":295.86,"speaker_name":"Stephanie Lucchesi"},{"text":"You''re a Pat fan.","index":95,"end_time":300.98,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":299.86,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You didn''t have to go through enough pain, in my opinion.","index":96,"end_time":303.7,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":300.98,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I mean, five years was tough because, you know, I''m like, It was a 2001 when we.","index":97,"end_time":311.7,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":304.42,"speaker_name":"Stephanie Lucchesi"},{"text":"The Brady era, so that was like.","index":98,"end_time":313.94,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":311.78,"speaker_name":"Stephanie Lucchesi"},{"text":"I don''t know.","index":99,"end_time":315.38,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":314.66,"speaker_name":"Stephanie Lucchesi"},{"text":"I was, like, 15 or 14, so that was like, my whole childhood.","index":100,"end_time":320.1,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":315.38,"speaker_name":"Stephanie Lucchesi"},{"text":"We were just, like, great, and then just, like, pure misery for five years.","index":101,"end_time":325.02,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":320.1,"speaker_name":"Stephanie Lucchesi"},{"text":"So.","index":102,"end_time":325.5,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":325.1,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"We''re back, baby.","index":103,"end_time":326.5,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":325.5,"speaker_name":"Stephanie Lucchesi"},{"text":"Just rub it in.","index":104,"end_time":327.38,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":326.5,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Rub it in.","index":105,"end_time":328.14,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":327.38,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I''m a Washington fan, so maybe one day I''ll know what winning''s like.","index":106,"end_time":333.66,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":328.78,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":107,"end_time":335.82,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":335.26,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Josh, how are you doing?","index":108,"end_time":337.34,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":336.38,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I''m doing good.","index":109,"end_time":338.42,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":337.74,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"How you doing?","index":110,"end_time":338.94,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":338.42,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Doing all right.","index":111,"end_time":339.9,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":339.02,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So one thing I want to start out.","index":112,"end_time":342.82,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":341.34,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So I saw some.","index":113,"end_time":343.54,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":342.82,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Some more leads coming through.","index":114,"end_time":344.78,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":343.54,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Have you guys any issues?","index":115,"end_time":346.1,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":344.86,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I haven''t noticed any questions or anything coming through, so feel good about those?","index":116,"end_time":350.3,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":346.1,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":117,"end_time":352.02,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":351.66,"speaker_name":"Dan Igo"},{"text":"Just for some context.","index":118,"end_time":353.38,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":352.02,"speaker_name":"Dan Igo"},{"text":"Colin, what exactly is Heyreach?","index":119,"end_time":355.66,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":353.38,"speaker_name":"Dan Igo"},{"text":"It''s a tool that we use that connects your LinkedIn profile so that we can send automated connection requests or LinkedIn messages.","index":120,"end_time":362.46,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":356.14,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":121,"end_time":363.62,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":363.1,"speaker_name":"Dan Igo"},{"text":"So the Heyreach is coordinated to LinkedIn.","index":122,"end_time":366.18,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":363.62,"speaker_name":"Dan Igo"},{"text":"That makes sense.","index":123,"end_time":366.78,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":366.18,"speaker_name":"Dan Igo"},{"text":"Okay.","index":124,"end_time":367.14,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":366.78,"speaker_name":"Dan Igo"},{"text":"Yep.","index":125,"end_time":367.58,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":367.14,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":126,"end_time":369.22,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":368.86,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I mean, a few good ones.","index":127,"end_time":370.1,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":369.22,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So even just today, Memorial Herman came in.","index":128,"end_time":373.14,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":370.1,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Dan.","index":129,"end_time":373.58,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":373.14,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So that one''s assigned to you.","index":130,"end_time":374.7,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":373.58,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, they''re down here in Houston.","index":131,"end_time":376.92,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":375.32,"speaker_name":"Dan Igo"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":132,"end_time":377.4,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":376.92,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":133,"end_time":378.04,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":377.56,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Northwell Health.","index":134,"end_time":379.88,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":378.6,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So some good ones that we''ve seen coming through over the last couple days.","index":135,"end_time":383.64,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":381.16,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then also those bookings and people filling out, they want to get more of those emails and everything.","index":136,"end_time":389.56,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":383.64,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, I''ve got a couple.","index":137,"end_time":391.8,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":390.68,"speaker_name":"Dan Igo"},{"text":"Which is not a big deal.","index":138,"end_time":392.68,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":391.8,"speaker_name":"Dan Igo"},{"text":"A couple spatterings of, like, retired chros from some of these hospitals.","index":139,"end_time":396.84,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":392.68,"speaker_name":"Dan Igo"},{"text":"Yeah, I got a couple of those, too.","index":140,"end_time":398.44,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":397,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":141,"end_time":399.16,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":398.68,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"This is interesting.","index":142,"end_time":401.04,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":400.2,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Now that I''m out of the game, I want to learn.","index":143,"end_time":402.64,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":401.04,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"I was like, wait, what?","index":144,"end_time":403.48,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":402.64,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"I know.","index":145,"end_time":404.39,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":404.11,"speaker_name":"Dan Igo"},{"text":"It''s like, get off LinkedIn, buddy.","index":146,"end_time":406.27,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":404.39,"speaker_name":"Dan Igo"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":147,"end_time":407.67,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":407.31,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Go play some golf.","index":148,"end_time":408.63,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":407.67,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":149,"end_time":408.91,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":408.63,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"They got too much time in their day.","index":150,"end_time":410.19,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":408.91,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Cool.","index":151,"end_time":413.47,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":412.99,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"And then, Josh, just an update.","index":152,"end_time":416.67,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":414.67,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So tomorrow, we''re finalizing the last industry page that we were building, so we''ll have about 10 new web pages that we''ve built and can start rolling out live.","index":153,"end_time":428.11,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":416.75,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":154,"end_time":429.47,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":428.91,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"What do we need to do for that?","index":155,"end_time":430.99,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":429.55,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"I''m just going to give you a link to review them all, see if you have any feedback on anything you want to change.","index":156,"end_time":435.32,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":431.4,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But, yeah, new home page, a pricing page, an integrations page, industry pages for all the industry.","index":157,"end_time":441,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":435.96,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"The Primary industries that you guys work in.","index":158,"end_time":442.84,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":441,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That''s awesome.","index":159,"end_time":445.24,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":444.36,"speaker_name":"Dan Igo"},{"text":"Integrations.","index":160,"end_time":446.04,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":445.32,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"These aren''t just pillar pages, they''re legit pages for our website.","index":161,"end_time":449.88,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":447,"speaker_name":"Dan Igo"},{"text":"Yep.","index":162,"end_time":450.6,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":450.12,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":163,"end_time":453.12,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":452.76,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we will probably need a little bit of time to review that.","index":164,"end_time":455.88,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":453.12,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Like.","index":165,"end_time":456.16,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":455.88,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Yeah, you know, I''ll probably review it.","index":166,"end_time":458.29,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":456.16,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"If either of you two want to review it.","index":167,"end_time":460.21,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":458.45,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Rob''s going to want to review it.","index":168,"end_time":461.45,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":460.21,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"We''re going to have to get.","index":169,"end_time":462.21,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":461.45,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Probably Rob Schwend on the integration page to review it.","index":170,"end_time":464.69,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":462.21,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"So we will get to it as fast as we can, Colin, because I want.","index":171,"end_time":469.49,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":464.77,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"I want an update on the page.","index":172,"end_time":473.089,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":469.65,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Yeah, but that''s awesome.","index":173,"end_time":475.57,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":473.33,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Yeah, I think everything''s looking good.","index":174,"end_time":477.41,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":475.73,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":175,"end_time":481.09,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":480.53,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And Dan and Steph, I''m not sure how much you guys have been brought into the website process, but we started building out pages also for.","index":176,"end_time":489.39,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":481.09,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"For HR leaders so that they can go and find all of their information or even if they''re a company that''s working with you already and they want to know how can they help their team better utilize PTO exchange as a platform.","index":177,"end_time":500.83,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":490.27,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"There''ll be information there for that.","index":178,"end_time":502.43,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":500.83,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And same for.","index":179,"end_time":503.71,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":502.83,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I know one of the pain points you guys expressed was current clients coming on and hitting this request a demo, even though they already have access to your tool.","index":180,"end_time":511.79,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":503.71,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we created a for employees page as well to educate them.","index":181,"end_time":515.23,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":511.79,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":182,"end_time":516.69,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":516.21,"speaker_name":"Stephanie Lucchesi"},{"text":"That''s great.","index":183,"end_time":517.57,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":516.85,"speaker_name":"Dan Igo"},{"text":"So a lot of stuff in motion there.","index":184,"end_time":521.73,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":519.41,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, that''s great.","index":185,"end_time":523.09,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":522.21,"speaker_name":"Dan Igo"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":186,"end_time":524.85,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":524.37,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Great.","index":187,"end_time":525.65,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":525.25,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"All right.","index":188,"end_time":526.93,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":526.29,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then, Josh, I know you wanted to go through a few items as well.","index":189,"end_time":531.369,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":527.49,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"The one thing that I''ll say before we hop into that is that I''m also just ideating, thinking through a new campaign that we can run new lead list to attack and just, you know, not.","index":190,"end_time":542.72,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":531.369,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Not put all our eggs in one basket of like, we''ve seen these leads filtering through.","index":191,"end_time":546.48,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":542.96,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I want to see what we can amplify and what new thing we can get out there to attract people.","index":192,"end_time":550.8,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":546.48,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":193,"end_time":552.48,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":551.92,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Well, let me know what you''re thinking.","index":194,"end_time":554.44,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":552.64,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"I mean, I. I think that''s what we''re trying to figure out.","index":195,"end_time":558.92,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":554.44,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Like, what are better calls to action?","index":196,"end_time":560.24,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":558.92,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"What are better assets that people are going to want?","index":197,"end_time":562.96,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":560.24,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"So it''s not just meet with us or request a demo, so.","index":198,"end_time":565.92,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":563.04,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Exactly.","index":199,"end_time":566.56,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":565.92,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":200,"end_time":567.45,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":567.13,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"I was just going to say from my side, like, obviously being new just kind of to one of Josh''s like, bullet points, like just understanding more about the campaign.","index":201,"end_time":578.89,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":569.21,"speaker_name":"Stephanie Lucchesi"},{"text":"So, like when we get campaign name benchmark report, like, what is being sent out and at what point are they turning into a lead?","index":202,"end_time":587.45,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":578.97,"speaker_name":"Stephanie Lucchesi"},{"text":"Is it just when they accept the connection on LinkedIn?","index":203,"end_time":590.01,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":587.45,"speaker_name":"Stephanie Lucchesi"},{"text":"And like, I had Asked you the other day, you know when we get the reach out to hey, reach contact and then you''re like, well, there''s kind of nothing to do.","index":204,"end_time":598.62,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":590.57,"speaker_name":"Stephanie Lucchesi"},{"text":"So I was wondering like, is there a way to kind of postpone those until like there''s actually an actionable thing for us to do?","index":205,"end_time":605.54,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":598.62,"speaker_name":"Stephanie Lucchesi"},{"text":"So I don''t know if we want to like talk through that today or.","index":206,"end_time":608.02,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":605.7,"speaker_name":"Stephanie Lucchesi"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah.","index":207,"end_time":608.819,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":608.02,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So one thing.","index":208,"end_time":609.62,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":608.819,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So the PTO benchmark report is a campaign that we came up with a few months ago where we worked very closely with the PTO team, PTO exchange team to understand what your guys benchmarks are across all of your clients for.","index":209,"end_time":621.54,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":609.62,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Um, this could be over like at three years, what is your average X.","index":210,"end_time":626.79,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":622.15,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"At five years, what is your average.","index":211,"end_time":628.11,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":626.87,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Blah, blah, blah.","index":212,"end_time":628.75,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":628.11,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So they fill out this form, it leads to a customized PDF that they are able to download that says whether they are below average, average or above average in three categories and then points them and customizes the link based on their company HQ to one of your sales rep meeting links.","index":213,"end_time":647.03,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":628.75,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"At that point they are considered a marketing qualified lead because they have engaged so much on the Haybreach side.","index":214,"end_time":653.75,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":647.83,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"The change that we made there, we used to send a sequence of messages but Josh wanted to make it more personalized.","index":215,"end_time":659.65,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":653.97,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So what we set up was a notification for anytime someone had accepted your guys LinkedIn request to notify you guys and then you can follow up with a more personalized message.","index":216,"end_time":668.85,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":659.65,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And I think Steph and Colin, that kind of fits in well with our HubSpot discussion today and kind of doing a HubSpot audit and cleaning it up because like I''m almost at the point where I''m, I''m happy to get rid of almost every sequence in there and start over because it''s just kind of gotten out of control and then just the, you know, changing qualified lead status.","index":217,"end_time":694.61,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":669.969,"speaker_name":"Dan Igo"},{"text":"Those types of things I think are all pieces of kind of that HubSpot piece I think that Josh had mentioned we wanted to talk about.","index":218,"end_time":700.21,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":694.61,"speaker_name":"Dan Igo"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":219,"end_time":701.17,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":700.69,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Because I think there''s a lot more we can be doing with sequences and workflows in HubSpot when these come in.","index":220,"end_time":706.69,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":702.21,"speaker_name":"Dan Igo"},{"text":"I think so too.","index":221,"end_time":708.2,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":707.4,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And Josh, I''m not sure if there''s anything you wanted to lead into there as well.","index":222,"end_time":712.76,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":709.4,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"No, I mean before we jump into like the HubSpot audit and that kind of thing, I do think going back to what Steph was saying and what Dan was saying a little bit too, it''s like, can we get a, or create a, like a workflow document that the main ways that that they''re getting automatic tasks generated for them is if it''s like a requested demo, a benchmark report, a LinkedIn connection or the LinkedIn ads.","index":223,"end_time":753.97,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":713.64,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Yep.","index":224,"end_time":755.01,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":754.45,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I think those are the four.","index":225,"end_time":756.69,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":755.09,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"I don''t know.","index":226,"end_time":757.17,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":756.69,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Those are the components.","index":227,"end_time":758.01,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":757.17,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":228,"end_time":758.37,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":758.01,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Fifth.","index":229,"end_time":759.09,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":758.81,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"I don''t know if there''s a fifth one, but kind of like what, you know, here''s what you should do, here''s where it''s coming from, and here''s what you should do.","index":230,"end_time":767.93,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":759.09,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"And then the other part that, you know, we were saying Steph and I were talking about last week is like if somebody asks for a benchmark report, we put them in the request a demo sequence and then highly modify the request to demos.","index":231,"end_time":783.61,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":768.33,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Like what?","index":232,"end_time":784.25,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":783.61,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"We should just create a sequence that''s like for the benchmark report.","index":233,"end_time":786.93,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":784.25,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"We just did.","index":234,"end_time":787.49,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":786.93,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"We just didn''t do that.","index":235,"end_time":789.46,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":787.49,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"We didn''t have that many that were coming in and then once they started coming in with the tail end of Sam being here and we just never created another sequence for it.","index":236,"end_time":797.26,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":789.46,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":237,"end_time":797.82,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":797.26,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"And then this is a little bit of a question more for Dan and for Steph, but I, I feel like the generic sequences that get sent out when someone does something, like in the past it used to be for like white papers that they downloaded or whatever.","index":238,"end_time":820.85,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":799.5,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"When it''s the same message that goes out to everybody, they seem to be very ineffective.","index":239,"end_time":824.85,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":820.93,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Whereas when we do a little bit of customization, at least you''re putting some of your own personality into it.","index":240,"end_time":830.73,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":825.09,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"You''re putting a little bit of like research on the company into it.","index":241,"end_time":833.81,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":830.73,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Whatever.","index":242,"end_time":834.29,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":833.81,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Is the increase in enhanced email worth the effort that it takes to do those things or should they just be automated?","index":243,"end_time":847.48,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":835.41,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"It''s the same thing that goes out every single time and we don''t worry about the customization so that it''s that.","index":244,"end_time":854.6,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":848.36,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Can I just drop a couple thoughts in before Colin answers?","index":245,"end_time":857.72,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":855,"speaker_name":"Dan Igo"},{"text":"No, no, that question was for you and for Steph.","index":246,"end_time":860.28,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":857.8,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Oh, okay.","index":247,"end_time":861.24,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":860.36,"speaker_name":"Dan Igo"},{"text":"Or do we create industry specific responses where we''re name dropping companies in those specific industries?","index":248,"end_time":869.64,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":862.119,"speaker_name":"Dan Igo"},{"text":"If we do that so that we have a generic one and then four industry ones that are like the industries that we see most often and it makes it so that you don''t have to customize it and, and we still see the same results.","index":249,"end_time":886.55,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":872.95,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Like, I''m all for that.","index":250,"end_time":888.39,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":887.19,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"I just, I just was always so hesitant of like when it''s this stale message that we''re not even looking at really, and we''re just like hitting a button and it''s going out.","index":251,"end_time":898.47,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":888.39,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"I just don''t know if that''s the best Way to convert, because we need to convert now.","index":252,"end_time":904.06,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":900.34,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"These people that are like very interested, I don''t want to just send them like a very basic, you know, email sequence.","index":253,"end_time":912.3,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":904.06,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"That that''s my concern with, like, we need to make sure that we''re converting the request to demo hand raisers at like 75% or whatever, you know, whatever our, our goal is.","index":254,"end_time":923.58,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":912.3,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"It''s just like we have to make that more effective than it''s been.","index":255,"end_time":927.91,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":923.58,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"And just from my experience and like, Steph, you''ve probably seen me do this on calls.","index":256,"end_time":935.55,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":930.39,"speaker_name":"Dan Igo"},{"text":"Like, I love to name drop.","index":257,"end_time":936.87,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":935.55,"speaker_name":"Dan Igo"},{"text":"I love the FOMO to give them like the fear of missing out.","index":258,"end_time":939.83,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":936.87,"speaker_name":"Dan Igo"},{"text":"So that''s why I''m.","index":259,"end_time":941.67,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":940.71,"speaker_name":"Dan Igo"},{"text":"To your point, Josh?","index":260,"end_time":942.63,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":941.67,"speaker_name":"Dan Igo"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":261,"end_time":942.91,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":942.63,"speaker_name":"Dan Igo"},{"text":"Four industry specifics and then like one generic one.","index":262,"end_time":945.51,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":942.91,"speaker_name":"Dan Igo"},{"text":"That would be the route that I would probably want to take without having.","index":263,"end_time":948.95,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":945.51,"speaker_name":"Dan Igo"},{"text":"To do any customization.","index":264,"end_time":949.99,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":948.95,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah, yeah.","index":265,"end_time":952.82,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":951.34,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"I think at that point, like my opinion on it is if you make it just like you''re saying, customize enough where they''re already, they''re already somewhat interested.","index":266,"end_time":963.26,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":952.82,"speaker_name":"Stephanie Lucchesi"},{"text":"Like just taking, for example, if they''ve done the benchmark report thing, like they already know your name, they''re somewhat interested, really.","index":267,"end_time":972.26,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":963.26,"speaker_name":"Stephanie Lucchesi"},{"text":"They''re just looking for like you to reach out to them and then that''s going to spark like a conversation.","index":268,"end_time":977.58,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":972.26,"speaker_name":"Stephanie Lucchesi"},{"text":"So I don''t feel like there''s a need.","index":269,"end_time":980.04,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":977.66,"speaker_name":"Stephanie Lucchesi"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":270,"end_time":980.76,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":980.36,"speaker_name":"Stephanie Lucchesi"},{"text":"For Dan and I to be.","index":271,"end_time":981.92,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":980.76,"speaker_name":"Stephanie Lucchesi"},{"text":"If we''re getting six of these a day, to be customizing each one.","index":272,"end_time":984.84,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":981.92,"speaker_name":"Stephanie Lucchesi"},{"text":"I mean, it''d be great if it was just.","index":273,"end_time":988.44,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":984.84,"speaker_name":"Stephanie Lucchesi"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":274,"end_time":989.16,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":988.76,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Something that we could send out.","index":275,"end_time":991.96,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":989.16,"speaker_name":"Stephanie Lucchesi"},{"text":"Because I feel like, Josh, when we went to the customized decks for specific industries, that was like moving light years ahead from where we were the year prior, where we were just using the same generic deck.","index":276,"end_time":1002.28,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":992.12,"speaker_name":"Dan Igo"},{"text":"Okay, I''m fine with that.","index":277,"end_time":1008.25,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1004.45,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"I mean, that doesn''t seem to be that difficult to do.","index":278,"end_time":1013.09,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1008.25,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"I think it''s a matter of getting the right email sequence, you know, the right content in the emails where it''s short, succinct, making sure that we''re asking, giving them the easiest opportunity to set up the meeting, but also sprinkling in some industry stuff and some like, proof points to make it worth their while.","index":279,"end_time":1035.739,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1013.09,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Colin, I know attaching things to emails creates deliverability issues.","index":280,"end_time":1041.179,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1036.219,"speaker_name":"Dan Igo"},{"text":"Does links if we''re linking to something.","index":281,"end_time":1044.379,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1041.739,"speaker_name":"Dan Igo"},{"text":"So linking can be flagged by an email firewall if you haven''t had prior communication.","index":282,"end_time":1053.899,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1046.859,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":283,"end_time":1055.59,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1055.19,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"So the only reason I brought that up is because now that we''ve got these awesome industry specific pages, like, we can be linking to those.","index":284,"end_time":1064.31,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1056.23,"speaker_name":"Dan Igo"},{"text":"Well, that''s What I think now it''s like, this isn''t like what we''re doing with 11X or Demand Inc. Where it''s like mass amounts of emails that are going.","index":285,"end_time":1075.99,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1066.63,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Yeah, it''s not super cold.","index":286,"end_time":1077.15,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1075.99,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Right.","index":287,"end_time":1077.51,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1077.15,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"They''re like one to one.","index":288,"end_time":1078.79,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1077.51,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":289,"end_time":1080.03,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1079.59,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So you have more likelihood of that link being able to pass through their email firewall.","index":290,"end_time":1083.41,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1080.03,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":291,"end_time":1084.28,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1083.8,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"So you guys are open to my feedback.","index":292,"end_time":1088.48,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1086.68,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I have some thoughts.","index":293,"end_time":1089.16,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1088.48,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, so I think we don''t have to go either like this is what every healthcare company gets or this is a super personalized.","index":294,"end_time":1097.44,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1089.16,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I think that there''s a few options that we can tap into that don''t take a lot of Dan and Steph''s time still makes it like personalized.","index":295,"end_time":1104.44,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1097.44,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Or we could even automate all of it.","index":296,"end_time":1107,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1105.24,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So, Josh, you''ve seen the types of enrichment that we can get on a company on anything.","index":297,"end_time":1111.92,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1107,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I mean, we can get descriptions of everything that they do from A to Z and we can even just write a formula to say like, okay, take a couple of those paragraphs and distill it into like one sentence where I''m summing up their company.","index":298,"end_time":1123.8,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1111.92,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Like, it looks like I really did a lot of research.","index":299,"end_time":1125.56,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1123.8,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We could develop a personal field for that in HubSpot and like a lead comes through.","index":300,"end_time":1131.32,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1126.04,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We want to put them into that campaign.","index":301,"end_time":1132.84,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1131.32,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We just have a placeholder for that info.","index":302,"end_time":1134.68,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1132.84,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That''s the email that they get.","index":303,"end_time":1136.28,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1134.76,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"What I will say is that looking through a lot of the emails that you guys do send out through those automated sequences, they''re heavy.","index":304,"end_time":1142.89,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1136.44,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It''s.","index":305,"end_time":1143.41,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1142.89,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It looks like it''s an automated sequence.","index":306,"end_time":1145.37,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1143.41,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It doesn''t look like Dan or Steph took the five minutes to just send me an email to me.","index":307,"end_time":1150.09,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1145.37,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So what I would recommend is I think using the industry page links are great, but also just having some basic, like, hey, saw you filled this out.","index":308,"end_time":1159.21,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1150.81,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Checked out your company.","index":309,"end_time":1160.73,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1159.77,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Let me know if you have a few questions.","index":310,"end_time":1162.09,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1160.73,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Here''s a link to book on my calendar.","index":311,"end_time":1163.85,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1162.09,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Feels really personal.","index":312,"end_time":1164.97,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1163.93,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Even though we can send it to a thousand people and they would never know.","index":313,"end_time":1167.93,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1165.37,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But when you have like a.","index":314,"end_time":1169.72,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1168.56,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Here''s a paragraph and then a bunch of bullets and then a paragraph and then a nice, really looking nice button, it just feels kind of inorganic.","index":315,"end_time":1176.56,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1169.72,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I agree.","index":316,"end_time":1177.92,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1177.36,"speaker_name":"Stephanie Lucchesi"},{"text":"I''ve kind of been shortening my outreach too to kind of remove some of that.","index":317,"end_time":1182.48,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1178.96,"speaker_name":"Stephanie Lucchesi"},{"text":"Because I feel the same way.","index":318,"end_time":1184.08,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1182.48,"speaker_name":"Stephanie Lucchesi"},{"text":"Especially in that first outreach of like, yeah, I guess I was looking at the ABM channel and like, I noticed Dan had one that''s like HR Dan is the campaign name, but most of them are the Benchmark report and they''re coming to us at the point that they''re connecting on LinkedIn.","index":319,"end_time":1207.1,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1184.319,"speaker_name":"Stephanie Lucchesi"},{"text":"So do those two things happen like simultaneously?","index":320,"end_time":1209.62,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1207.1,"speaker_name":"Stephanie Lucchesi"},{"text":"Like is there a reason that they''re coming to us right after they connect on LinkedIn?","index":321,"end_time":1213.66,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1209.62,"speaker_name":"Stephanie Lucchesi"},{"text":"So that''s, that''s the trigger.","index":322,"end_time":1215.78,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1214.38,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So as soon as they accept your connection request, that''s what Josh wanted us to set up as a notification so you guys could send them that customized.","index":323,"end_time":1221.66,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1215.78,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Message and the benchmarking report could have happened a while ago.","index":324,"end_time":1226.8,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1221.66,"speaker_name":"Stephanie Lucchesi"},{"text":"Like do we have information on like when that happened?","index":325,"end_time":1229.68,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1226.96,"speaker_name":"Stephanie Lucchesi"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":326,"end_time":1230.32,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1229.92,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So in HubSpot we''ll track any, any benchmark reports have been filled out and you guys should get an automated task anytime someone does.","index":327,"end_time":1236.04,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1230.32,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Sam, I believe had set that up before we do.","index":328,"end_time":1238.96,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1236.04,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, I''m, I''m with you, Colin.","index":329,"end_time":1245.04,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1239.44,"speaker_name":"Dan Igo"},{"text":"I think a lot of our stuff is too heavy.","index":330,"end_time":1247.04,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1245.04,"speaker_name":"Dan Igo"},{"text":"I was always taught like three to seven seconds is the average time people spend reading an email.","index":331,"end_time":1251.68,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1247.04,"speaker_name":"Dan Igo"},{"text":"Yep.","index":332,"end_time":1252.47,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1252.07,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So that''s why a lot of those sequences in HubSpot I think we can just get rid of because they''re just too much.","index":333,"end_time":1259.83,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1254.79,"speaker_name":"Dan Igo"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":334,"end_time":1260.87,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1260.31,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But one of the things, and this is more of like a bigger picture thing that I think we need to do is the people that we''re putting into, if we''re shortening these sequences and the people that we''re putting through the sequence to try to generate a first meeting and that''s again not white paper downloads.","index":335,"end_time":1282.08,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1262.55,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"This is like request the demo.","index":336,"end_time":1283.4,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1282.08,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"This is benchmark report.","index":337,"end_time":1284.48,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1283.4,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"This is like the, the things that, that are currently going to you guys immediately upon them completing the I''m trying to get a meeting with you sequence.","index":338,"end_time":1296.24,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1284.56,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"They should be going into some kind of nurture educational route where it''s like, okay, my short messages to you to try to get you to set a meeting with me didn''t work.","index":339,"end_time":1308.57,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1296.72,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"I''m going to send you a little like a little bit of information once a week or once every other week for a six week period or, or a three week period or whatever, you know.","index":340,"end_time":1318.81,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1308.89,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"But there needs to be like directly into some other kind of educational mode that we''re.","index":341,"end_time":1325.53,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1319.85,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Absolutely, yeah.","index":342,"end_time":1326.81,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1325.53,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Which is very easy to build from a workflow standpoint.","index":343,"end_time":1329.05,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1326.81,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we would just have a field that we would say like and we could even just use their life cycle stage field or something like that to understand if they''ve become an opportunity or not.","index":344,"end_time":1338.79,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1329.05,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Once they were passed over to Dan or Steph, if they haven''t within a week or two weeks, whatever time interval we set, then yeah, enroll in a monthly newsletter, enroll in their industry nurture campaign that we can build, things like that.","index":345,"end_time":1351.67,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1338.79,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":346,"end_time":1352.23,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1351.75,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"And that''s like a area that I think we have not done a.","index":347,"end_time":1356.31,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1352.95,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"A good job is like we''re just trying to get the meeting and if we don''t get the meeting, it''s like.","index":348,"end_time":1360.37,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1356.53,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":349,"end_time":1361.09,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1360.61,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And that''s why I''ve always asked about your cold closed lost as well.","index":350,"end_time":1365.25,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1361.17,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I think that.","index":351,"end_time":1365.93,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1365.25,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I mean, it''s ripe for the picking because you guys haven''t like kind of stayed up on that in their inbox, educating them constantly.","index":352,"end_time":1374.21,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1365.93,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I mean, these companies oftentimes can need months or years to make a decision on a tool like this.","index":353,"end_time":1379.65,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1374.21,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So being constantly back of mind is going to be important.","index":354,"end_time":1383.41,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1380.53,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":355,"end_time":1385.26,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1384.94,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":356,"end_time":1388.54,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1387.9,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"So, yeah, can definitely put together a workflow document and talk through the industry email workflows as well.","index":357,"end_time":1396.7,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1390.54,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Josh, did you want to go into your bullets?","index":358,"end_time":1400.62,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1398.78,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, I mean, that''s basically bullet number three is like.","index":359,"end_time":1403.9,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1401.26,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"And then I think if you put together like a sequence kind of thing of like what''s happening that will highlight for us where we''re missing sequences that we need to create.","index":360,"end_time":1417.84,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1404.38,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"So that was number three.","index":361,"end_time":1419.8,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1418.8,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Number one is like, we just need to get on.","index":362,"end_time":1423.76,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1419.8,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Yeah, I think.","index":363,"end_time":1424.88,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1424.08,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Do you want me to share my.","index":364,"end_time":1426.08,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1425.12,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"My calendar link so you can book whatever time.","index":365,"end_time":1427.76,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1426.08,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I''m sure I have it somewhere, but if you could send it to me again, that would be helpful.","index":366,"end_time":1430.68,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1427.92,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"I''ll get time for me, you and Rob.","index":367,"end_time":1432.4,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1430.68,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Perfect.","index":368,"end_time":1433.44,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1432.8,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"And then the HubSpot audit.","index":369,"end_time":1438.17,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1435.77,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"So I''m saying these words together.","index":370,"end_time":1441.61,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1438.81,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"I don''t really even know what I mean when I''m saying it.","index":371,"end_time":1445.61,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1442.57,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"But, like, there''s a lot that we need to do inside of HubSpot, and I don''t know what you guys do if you did something like this, but it''s everything.","index":372,"end_time":1454.33,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1445.77,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"I mean, like Dan''s saying, we probably have 400 sequences that if we can just hit delete and get them out, then they''re out.","index":373,"end_time":1462.35,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1454.33,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"And not only that, you may have opportunities for cost savings in some sort of ways too.","index":374,"end_time":1467.91,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1462.99,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Or what you''re paying HubSpot even better.","index":375,"end_time":1470.19,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1467.91,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But like, it''s just a mess.","index":376,"end_time":1473.03,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1471.39,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"It''s like Frankenstein where we built on top of it, built on top of it.","index":377,"end_time":1476.67,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1473.03,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Like Steph and I were looking the other day and we have a field that says go live quarter.","index":378,"end_time":1483.23,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1476.83,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"We run reports on this and there are still some deals, especially loss and delay deals that enter in A.","index":379,"end_time":1490.91,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1484.03,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"But now it''s Q3 of 2024.","index":380,"end_time":1494.03,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1491.07,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Like, I don''t even know.","index":381,"end_time":1496.03,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1495.07,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Is there a way could we have to keep that data in there?","index":382,"end_time":1498.99,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1496.03,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Because if we delete them, then it''s going to probably cause an error in HubSpot.","index":383,"end_time":1502.55,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1498.99,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"But is there a way to like hide them so that they don''t see that when they open the drop down?","index":384,"end_time":1506.47,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1502.55,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"We have like my understanding from Sam was that they ought to be there.","index":385,"end_time":1511.39,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1506.47,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"It''s like, like we just have these like inefficiencies and maybe there''s just a better way to do it.","index":386,"end_time":1515.31,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1511.47,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah.","index":387,"end_time":1517.15,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1515.67,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"There''s ways to deprecate information but not lose it.","index":388,"end_time":1519.91,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1517.15,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":389,"end_time":1521.03,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1520.63,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"And so I would have to talk to Justin and see what he would want to do as far as like the audit and how that would work into like points and everything.","index":390,"end_time":1527.19,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1521.03,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Because an audit to your question, to us, it could also mean a million different things.","index":391,"end_time":1531.549,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1527.67,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Right.","index":392,"end_time":1531.91,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1531.549,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"What I''m thinking is properties and workflows and segments that you guys have set up being like the main three things that I really want to dig into.","index":393,"end_time":1541.67,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1532.31,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I think if we can clean those up, the rest of HubSpot sort starts to come together.","index":394,"end_time":1546.45,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1542.61,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":395,"end_time":1547.65,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1547.09,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"I mean the other part of this too is whether we decide we''re doing this expansion of New north and we''re not hiring an internal FTE or we are you''re supplementing NFTE to backfill Sam''s role.","index":396,"end_time":1565.69,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1547.65,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Like either way we''re going to be hiring fractional cmo.","index":397,"end_time":1569.51,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1565.69,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"So it makes sense to wait to do the audit until they''re hired because they''re going to have their own perspective of it.","index":398,"end_time":1576.95,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1569.75,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"I mean that stuff probably whenever we schedule time with Rob that we''ll talk with him about, but like there''s a couple competing forces here is we need to get our together as fast as we can because the first two quarters of the year are when we typically like run the most meetings, create the most opportunities for business that we can close in 2026.","index":399,"end_time":1601.88,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1577.43,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"So like we have to fix this soon.","index":400,"end_time":1604.08,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1601.88,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"But I also don''t want to run at a problem and then we hire a fractional CMO in three weeks and then they want to go back and like do it all over again.","index":401,"end_time":1612.08,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1604.56,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"So I don''t know what the, what the best thing is, but like a lot of the stuff we just, we need to fix up, there''s low hanging fruit that we can fix immediately where whoever we hire doesn''t really matter.","index":402,"end_time":1624.08,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1612.24,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Let''s get on that stuff as fast as we can.","index":403,"end_time":1626.65,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1624.65,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"But like, you know, the timing of this whole transition out of Salmon into whatever the next phase of marketing is going to look like isn''t the best timing because this is such an important time of the year for us.","index":404,"end_time":1638.53,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1626.65,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"But it is what it is.","index":405,"end_time":1639.33,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1638.53,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"And we just gotta figure it out.","index":406,"end_time":1641.01,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1639.33,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":407,"end_time":1641.21,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1641.01,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"We''re here to be your partner and obviously helping you any way we can.","index":408,"end_time":1644.49,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1641.21,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Do you think, Josh and Colin, that the sequence sequences in the workflow piece is probably something that is.","index":409,"end_time":1651.05,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1644.57,"speaker_name":"Dan Igo"},{"text":"We wouldn''t need the fractional CMOs to go ahead and jump on.","index":410,"end_time":1657.48,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1652.28,"speaker_name":"Dan Igo"},{"text":"Yes.","index":411,"end_time":1658.12,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1657.64,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":412,"end_time":1659.32,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1658.84,"speaker_name":"Dan Igo"},{"text":"Okay.","index":413,"end_time":1659.96,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1659.32,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"But they may have opinions on, like.","index":414,"end_time":1662.92,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1661.08,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Yeah, they may want to change the stuff that we sent, you know, set up.","index":415,"end_time":1666.28,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1663.24,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":416,"end_time":1666.8,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1666.28,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Or like, what is ner, you know, how are we segmenting our contact database so that we''re nurturing some people?","index":417,"end_time":1676.16,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1666.8,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Like, if I''m a cmo, I would certainly have opinions on.","index":418,"end_time":1679.22,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1676.16,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"On that of, like, marketing qualified leads compared to sales qualified leads and what kind of content is going out to.","index":419,"end_time":1686.14,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1679.22,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"But in terms of, like, the sequences of, like, the four or five main things, like, I don''t.","index":420,"end_time":1691.46,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1686.14,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"I feel comfortable with us creating new sequences and running it at a problem like that.","index":421,"end_time":1697.06,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1692.34,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"The faster we can fix that.","index":422,"end_time":1699.7,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1698.18,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Again, like, if you guys are getting five or six of these a day, if we can convert 33% of them, we''re going to have way more first meetings than we had from inbound last year.","index":423,"end_time":1712.51,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1700.5,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"So if we can fix that stuff quick, that would be great.","index":424,"end_time":1715.71,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1712.51,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":425,"end_time":1717.59,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1717.23,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So let''s get that meeting on the books then.","index":426,"end_time":1719.07,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1717.59,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":427,"end_time":1719.71,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1719.15,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":428,"end_time":1720.43,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1720.11,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"I''ll send you my savvy Cal and you can.","index":429,"end_time":1722.03,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1720.43,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You can book whatever time works for you and Rob.","index":430,"end_time":1723.95,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1722.03,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":431,"end_time":1724.83,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1724.19,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"How.","index":432,"end_time":1727.71,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1727.31,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"How soon do you think you can put together that.","index":433,"end_time":1732.12,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1727.79,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"The thing for number three?","index":434,"end_time":1733.92,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1732.6,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Like the cheat sheet for number three?","index":435,"end_time":1735.4,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1733.92,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"I''ll have that this week.","index":436,"end_time":1736.68,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1735.56,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":437,"end_time":1739.32,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1738.76,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Okay.","index":438,"end_time":1742.8,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1742.2,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"That was all the stuff on my checklist.","index":439,"end_time":1747.32,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1742.8,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"All right, well, it''s exciting stuff then, so.","index":440,"end_time":1751.4,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1748.36,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":441,"end_time":1751.68,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1751.4,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I love digging into this and ripping out what''s unnecessary and rebuilding it so everything makes sense.","index":442,"end_time":1757.52,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1751.68,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So cool.","index":443,"end_time":1759.35,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1757.52,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right, I''ll send you my savvy cal and then I''ll start to work on those documents and then we''ll go from there on the HubSpot side of things.","index":444,"end_time":1766.43,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1759.35,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then.","index":445,"end_time":1766.79,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1766.43,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, for the marketing campaigns, I''ll let you know.","index":446,"end_time":1769.35,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1766.79,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I''m putting together some documentation of different offers and things that I have in mind and flows of how the marketing campaign can come together.","index":447,"end_time":1776.71,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1769.91,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So I''ll share that with you for our meeting Thursday.","index":448,"end_time":1778.95,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1776.95,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, perfect.","index":449,"end_time":1780.79,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1779.59,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"You guys have anything else?","index":450,"end_time":1782.47,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1781.27,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"No, No, I think we hit on.","index":451,"end_time":1785.52,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1783.43,"speaker_name":"Dan Igo"},{"text":"This was a good meeting.","index":452,"end_time":1786.56,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1785.52,"speaker_name":"Dan Igo"},{"text":"I. I think if we get together as a.","index":453,"end_time":1790,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1786.72,"speaker_name":"Dan Igo"},{"text":"A sales.","index":454,"end_time":1790.6,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1790,"speaker_name":"Dan Igo"},{"text":"Org.","index":455,"end_time":1791.04,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1790.6,"speaker_name":"Dan Igo"},{"text":"Josh, in the future, I know we''re planning on getting together in Seattle.","index":456,"end_time":1793.68,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1791.04,"speaker_name":"Dan Igo"},{"text":"Like, we should include a segment where we spend maybe a half hour.","index":457,"end_time":1796.48,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1793.68,"speaker_name":"Dan Igo"},{"text":"An hour with New North.","index":458,"end_time":1797.44,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1796.48,"speaker_name":"Dan Igo"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":459,"end_time":1799.04,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1798.48,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Yeah, that''d be great.","index":460,"end_time":1801.12,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1799.36,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right, cool.","index":461,"end_time":1803.4,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1802.32,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":462,"end_time":1803.92,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1803.4,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right, well, thank you all for your time.","index":463,"end_time":1805.6,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1804.08,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And, Josh, sorry about.","index":464,"end_time":1807.12,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1805.6,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Sorry about the birds.","index":465,"end_time":1808.24,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1807.36,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, I''m not really sorry.","index":466,"end_time":1810.32,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1808.48,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I know you''re not, but I appreciate you saying those words out loud.","index":467,"end_time":1813.2,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1810.4,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"All right, I''ll see you guys.","index":468,"end_time":1815.28,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1814,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Take it easy.","index":469,"end_time":1815.87,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1815.28,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"}],"dateString":"2026-01-12T20:30:00.000Z","host_email":"colin.costigan@marketersindemand.com","meeting_link":"https://us02web.zoom.us/j/86093865913?pwd=ajXSuerDGmcROjfezSWYYGsa7iPOWd.1","participants":["colin.costigan@marketersindemand.com,josh@ptoexchange.com,dan@ptoexchange.com,davids@ptoexchange.com,stephanie@ptoexchange.com","josh@ptoexchange.com","dan@ptoexchange.com","davids@ptoexchange.com","stephanie@ptoexchange.com"],"transcript_url":"https://app.fireflies.ai/view/01KE8CGZM49S9S6K4P72CAYZJC","organizer_email":"colin.costigan@marketersindemand.com"}'::jsonb,
    '{"label":"positive","confidence":0.95,"bullets":["Finalized ten new industry and integration pages set to go live following team review.","Colin proposed new campaign strategy to diversify lead sources beyond current inbound flow.","Agreed to simplify and modernize email sequences to improve personalization and conversion rates.","Planned HubSpot workflow audit targeting property cleanup, sequence pruning, and segment alignment.","Team to draft clear documentation for lead triggers and actions to optimize campaign responses."],"highlights":[{"quote":"We need to make sure that we''re converting the request to demo hand raisers at like 75%","speaker":"Josh Reinhard"},{"quote":"We created a ''for employees'' page as well to educate them.","speaker":"Colin Costigan"},{"quote":"I think a lot of our stuff is too heavy.","speaker":"Dan Igo"}],"topics":["lead gen","workflow","email","HubSpot","campaigns"],"model":"openai/gpt-4-1106-preview","version":1,"generated_at":"2026-01-13T00:00:00Z"}'::jsonb,
    '{"fireflies_summary":{"notes":"## **Lead Generation and Campaign Development**\n\nThe team is actively refining lead flow and exploring new campaign strategies to diversify lead sources and improve engagement.\n\n- **Memorial Herman and Northwell Health leads** recently came through **Heyreach**, the LinkedIn automation tool connecting profiles for messaging and connection requests (06:07).\n    - Dan Igo owns the Memorial Herman lead, aligning with his Houston base.\n    - There are some inactive leads, such as retired CHROs, signaling a need for lead quality filtering.\n    - Colin Costigan is ideating a new campaign to expand lead sources beyond current approaches.\n    - The goal is to find better calls to action and assets that encourage more meaningful engagement than just “request a demo.”\n\n- The **PTO benchmark report campaign** generates qualified leads by providing companies with customized performance PDFs based on multi-year data, triggering meeting links when engaged (10:08).\n    - Leads become marketing qualified once they download their customized report.\n    - Josh Reinhard and Colin discussed moving from automated message sequences to more personalized LinkedIn follow-ups after connection acceptance.\n    - Stephanie Lucchesi raised concerns about premature notifications and suggested postponing outreach until leads become actionable.\n    - Dan sees aligning this with a planned **HubSpot audit and cleanup** to improve lead status accuracy and workflow efficiency (11:09).\n\n- The team agreed on creating a **document outlining workflows for key lead triggers** like demo requests, benchmark reports, LinkedIn connections, and ads to clarify task generation and follow-up steps (11:50).\n    - Josh stressed the importance of defining what actions sales should take per lead type.\n    - Dan supported industry-specific email sequences to leverage relevant company and industry references to boost response rates.\n    - Stephanie emphasized that leads who download benchmark reports are already warm and require minimal customization in outreach.\n    - Colin suggested automating personalized content fields in HubSpot using company data enrichment to simulate tailored outreach without heavy manual effort (18:06).\n\n## **Email Sequence Optimization and Personalization**\n\nThe group plans to simplify and improve email sequences to increase conversion rates while minimizing manual work.\n\n- Current sequences are **too long and generic**, leading to low engagement; Dan referenced average reading times of 3–7 seconds, advocating for shorter, more focused emails (20:39).\n    - Josh wants to replace generic sequences with shorter, industry-relevant emails highlighting proof points and clear, easy meeting requests.\n    - Dan and Stephanie prefer a **set of four industry-specific templates plus one general template** to avoid manual customization but retain relevance (14:20).\n    - Colin warned against heavy email content with many links due to deliverability risks but confirmed that one-to-one outreach with company links is less likely to be flagged (17:16).\n    - The team agreed that emails need to feel personal, even if automated, by including brief company summaries and direct calendar links (19:19).\n\n- Josh proposed establishing a **nurture track for leads who don''t immediately convert**, sending educational content weekly or biweekly over several weeks to maintain engagement (21:50).\n    - Colin confirmed this is easy to implement with HubSpot workflows based on lifecycle stages and opportunity status.\n    - This approach targets long sales cycles common in the market and keeps the company top of mind.\n    - The lack of ongoing nurture for lost or cold leads was seen as a missed opportunity (22:40).\n\n## **Website Development and Content Updates**\n\nSignificant progress is underway to expand and improve website content tailored to client and industry needs.\n\n- Colin announced the completion of **about 10 new web pages**, including a new home page, pricing, integrations, and detailed industry-specific pages covering the primary sectors served (06:54).\n    - These are full website pages, not just pillar pages, enhancing SEO and user experience.\n    - The team will review these pages, with Rob Schwend specifically reviewing the integrations page for accuracy (07:30).\n    - Additional pages target HR leaders and employees to help current clients better use the PTO Exchange platform and reduce demo requests from existing users (08:00).\n    - This content aims to educate both prospects and existing clients, reducing confusion and support workload.\n\n## **HubSpot Audit and Marketing Infrastructure**\n\nThe need for a thorough HubSpot cleanup and restructuring is urgent to improve operational efficiency and lead management.\n\n- Josh described the current HubSpot setup as a **“Frankenstein” with over 400 sequences**, many outdated or redundant, complicating sales and marketing workflows (24:00).\n    - There is a problematic \"go live quarter\" field containing outdated data, indicating poor data hygiene.\n    - Colin recommended focusing the audit on **properties, workflows, and segments** as key areas to streamline (25:21).\n    - The audit could uncover cost savings and better system organization.\n    - Josh suggested waiting for the incoming **fractional CMO hire** to provide strategic input but stressed immediate fixes on low-hanging fruit to avoid losing the critical first two quarters of the year for revenue generation (26:50).\n    - Dan and Josh agreed that sequence cleanup and workflow fixes can proceed before the CMO starts, allowing faster impact (27:21).\n\n- Colin committed to producing a **workflow and sequence cheat sheet document this week** to clarify and optimize lead handling processes (28:55).\n    - The document will serve as a foundation for rebuilding workflows and identifying missing sequences.\n    - Josh will schedule a meeting with Colin and Rob to prioritize and align on next steps (23:45).\n\n## **Sales and Marketing Collaboration and Future Planning**\n\nThe team emphasized strengthening collaboration between sales and marketing for better outcomes and planning joint sessions.\n\n- Dan suggested including a segment with the **New North team during a future Seattle sales meeting** to align sales and marketing efforts more closely (29:43).\n    - This would foster deeper understanding and improve campaign effectiveness.\n    - Josh and Colin supported the idea, recognizing the value of face-to-face or focused time together.\n\n- Colin is preparing **documentation of new marketing offers and campaign flows** to present in the upcoming Thursday meeting, aiming to share fresh ideas and gather feedback (29:30).\n    - This will help guide upcoming campaigns and ensure alignment with sales priorities.\n    - The team sees this as part of ongoing efforts to improve lead quality and conversion.\n\n- Josh, Dan, and Stephanie conveyed readiness to act quickly on improvements that will increase first meeting conversions, targeting a **33% conversion rate on inbound leads** to significantly boost sales pipeline volume (27:59).","outline":null,"keywords":["HubSpot audit","Lead generation","Email sequences","Heyreach LinkedIn integration","Website development","Marketing automation"],"overview":"- **Lead Generation Focus:** Team refining lead strategies; exploring diverse sources, current inactive leads highlight need for quality filtering.\n- **PTO Benchmark Campaign Success:** Custom performance PDFs generate qualified leads; leads become marketing qualified upon download, enhancing engagement efforts.\n- **Email Sequence Improvement:** Current generic emails hinder engagement; shorter, tailored sequences with industry relevance proposed to increase response rates.\n- **Website Content Progress:** Ten new pages launched, including pricing and industry-specific sections, aiming to educate clients and reduce support requests.\n- **HubSpot Cleanup Needed:** Current setup is outdated; focus on properties and workflows to streamline operations and improve lead management efficiency.\n- **Collaboration Initiatives:** Plans for joint meetings with sales to align efforts; focusing on improving inbound lead conversion rates to 33%.","action_items":"\n**Colin Costigan**\nSend new website pages link to Josh, Dan, and Steph for review and feedback (06:30)\nCompile and deliver a workflow document outlining main lead sources, automatic task generation, and email sequence recommendations by end of week (28:55)\nSend calendar scheduling link (SavvyCal) to Josh for booking time with Rob Schwend and Josh to discuss HubSpot audit and sequence improvements (28:40)\nPrepare documentation of marketing campaign offers and flow concepts for Thursday’s meeting (29:30)\n\n**Josh Reinhard**\nReview new website pages when provided and coordinate feedback from sales and Rob Schwend (07:10)\nSchedule and attend HubSpot audit meeting with Colin and Rob Schwend (28:39)\n\n**Dan Igo**\nProvide feedback on email sequences, especially regarding the balance between automation and personalization, with focus on industry-specific approaches (14:10)\n\n**Stephanie Lucchesi**\nContinue feedback on sequence personalization and understand campaign activation timing related to LinkedIn connections and benchmark reports (10:00)\n"},"migrated_from":"contract_meetings","original_id":"271f05fd-d4a6-40b5-ad49-57098201fba5","master_marketer":{"status":"migrated"}}'::jsonb,
