8,"end_time":1285.799,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1285.16,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So sorry, that''s what I keep saying.","index":269,"end_time":1287.04,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1285.799,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we''re, we''re working on.","index":270,"end_time":1288.16,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1287.04,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"This isn''t the final like broken out list.","index":271,"end_time":1290.48,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1288.16,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"This is.","index":272,"end_time":1291,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1290.48,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We''re working through making this more granular to have everyone''s like your approval.","index":273,"end_time":1295.08,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1291,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Our next step.","index":274,"end_time":1295.76,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1295.08,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":275,"end_time":1296.1,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1295.76,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":276,"end_time":1296.53,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1296.33,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Okay.","index":277,"end_time":1296.85,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1296.53,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"All right.","index":278,"end_time":1297.09,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1296.85,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So that, that''s fine.","index":279,"end_time":1298.01,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1297.09,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Just background.","index":280,"end_time":1298.85,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1298.01,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"I had asked MiD to start to work on that this morning.","index":281,"end_time":1301.45,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1298.85,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So that''s why it''s just not 100 done yet.","index":282,"end_time":1304.17,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1301.53,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"But as long as for the next meeting, you know, specifically more Friday, we can make sure like everything is in sequence and Good.","index":283,"end_time":1310.73,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1304.17,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":284,"end_time":1310.97,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1310.73,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then you can see like next step would be uploading that sample CSV of those contacts, things like that.","index":285,"end_time":1315.93,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1310.97,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay so then the three items that are due today so define masking rules and then 1 is the complete and then the review mapping.","index":286,"end_time":1327.48,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1316.17,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"How.","index":287,"end_time":1329.36,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1329,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"How do those look?","index":288,"end_time":1330.36,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1329.36,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":289,"end_time":1331.16,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1330.68,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Kia, could you pull up the phase?","index":290,"end_time":1332.84,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1331.32,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yep, there you go.","index":291,"end_time":1333.72,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1332.84,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then just walk through the phases that you set up.","index":292,"end_time":1337,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1333.88,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":293,"end_time":1337.96,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1337.4,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"So for the encompass we divided it through three phases.","index":294,"end_time":1345.32,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1338.28,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"Phase A basically means go live day one.","index":295,"end_time":1348.44,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1345.56,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"Phase B post launch and face C later or nice to have everything seen here.","index":296,"end_time":1355.29,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1349.29,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"And then we talked about sync frequency.","index":297,"end_time":1359.05,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1356.01,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"This is something that we''ll have to.","index":298,"end_time":1360.85,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1359.05,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"Review with you guys.","index":299,"end_time":1361.85,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1360.85,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Like what is high priority, what maybe could be on a daily batch etc etc.","index":300,"end_time":1369.61,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1361.85,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"And I think that''s it for encompassing.","index":301,"end_time":1374.97,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1370.49,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"I did.","index":302,"end_time":1375.84,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1375.28,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"There''s some fields that I think we shouldn''t be uploading so I marked them in yellow and I didn''t even put a face on them because I know or like for example if they like their borrower, marital status and stuff like that, family income.","index":303,"end_time":1396,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1376.4,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"I think you guys just need to review this so that we can confirm what fields the faces.","index":304,"end_time":1404.13,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1396.96,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"So and this is, this is just encompass or is there the same document for Mulesoft side?","index":305,"end_time":1414.05,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1406.69,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"This is just Encompass.","index":306,"end_time":1418.05,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1416.29,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"Yes.","index":307,"end_time":1419.09,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1418.61,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"So did we do the same exercise on for the other.","index":308,"end_time":1423.73,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1419.81,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Yeah, got it.","index":309,"end_time":1426.77,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1424.69,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And everything is here.","index":310,"end_time":1428.62,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1427.5,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"If we''re allowing them in cubspot I wrote true and if we need mapping, yes or no and we can filter this here.","index":311,"end_time":1436.46,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1429.1,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"Okay.","index":312,"end_time":1437.74,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1437.1,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So you know, obviously then we''re not going to be able to, you know, complete this by today.","index":313,"end_time":1443.66,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1438.38,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So I would say Colin and, and Ashley, I''m going to ask you this too.","index":314,"end_time":1449.18,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1444.46,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"If marketing, if I looked at this and added in some of my suggest, you know, suggestions and then you looked, you know, at this more from the frequency side and also the, you know, if it needs to be masked or not.","index":315,"end_time":1461.19,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1449.5,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Can we say by Friday or is that, you know.","index":316,"end_time":1466.95,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1462.47,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Yeah, I mean by Friday''s meeting.","index":317,"end_time":1470.95,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1469.27,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Sorry for the, for the masking.","index":318,"end_time":1475.75,"speaker_id":6,"start_time":1473.67,"speaker_name":"Ashlie Taska"},{"text":"I''m not sure if that needs to be reviewed by compliance or it.","index":319,"end_time":1479.35,"speaker_id":6,"start_time":1476.55,"speaker_name":"Ashlie Taska"},{"text":"I mean like we can take a stab at it, but it''s really IT and compliance that will need to, you know, 100 stay but from our part, I think so.","index":320,"end_time":1492.37,"speaker_id":6,"start_time":1480.15,"speaker_name":"Ashlie Taska"},{"text":"Okay.","index":321,"end_time":1493.37,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1492.77,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"All right.","index":322,"end_time":1493.69,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1493.37,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"You know, then what I''m thinking maybe you guys focus on the data frequency and then what we could do is just anything that''s considered pii, which is confidential to the customer, we just automatically mask it.","index":323,"end_time":1509.81,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1493.69,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So let me just, let me ask Liz for a quick.","index":324,"end_time":1519.96,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1512.2,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Just overage a definition of pii.","index":325,"end_time":1523.4,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1519.96,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"I mean I''m pretty sure that anything that''s not public, so a lot of this would be pii, but like there is certain tiers to it, so I''ll take that away.","index":326,"end_time":1534.28,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1523.4,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So I think when we get the overall timeline back, let''s just add two subtasks to that card.","index":327,"end_time":1541.14,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1534.36,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So Gabe and Ashley will look at that document for the, the frequency and just to confirm that they''re comfortable with the stages of when they need the data into the system, I''ll look at it from the masking and the looking at any of the yellow flagged items and then we''ll, we''ll try to get that done, you know, by, by Friday.","index":328,"end_time":1567.83,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1541.54,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Okay.","index":329,"end_time":1568.95,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1568.31,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":330,"end_time":1569.39,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1569.03,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Great.","index":331,"end_time":1569.59,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1569.39,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then really, I mean from the custom field side and HubSpot.","index":332,"end_time":1573.51,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1569.59,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, I mean if we had that information like beginning of the day Thursday just as an example, then we could have it built, you know, for a meeting Friday.","index":333,"end_time":1581.59,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1574.31,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":334,"end_time":1582.47,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1581.99,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"When you say, you know, custom fields, I''m, I''m assuming that that means that any field that we''ve identified in HubSpot that''s not available as a direct like sync in the system.","index":335,"end_time":1597.47,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1582.87,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So that''s not, not anything that marketing would need to provide support in, it''s more or less like, if it''s not available in new soft and.","index":336,"end_time":1605.31,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1597.79,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And HubSpot, it''s an automatic.","index":337,"end_time":1607.71,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1605.95,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Like, I don''t know.","index":338,"end_time":1608.35,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1607.71,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"No, it''s actually simpler.","index":339,"end_time":1609.31,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1608.35,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"What I mean by custom fields is that HubSpot has out of the box, like email, first name, last name, but if it''s like, you know, amount in their bank account, that''s not something that HubSpot has out of the box.","index":340,"end_time":1619.15,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1609.31,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That''s a custom field that we create.","index":341,"end_time":1620.51,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1619.15,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Got it.","index":342,"end_time":1622.1,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1621.7,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Okay.","index":343,"end_time":1622.58,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1622.1,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Did you already.","index":344,"end_time":1623.62,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1622.9,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Did you already mark off on that chart what is.","index":345,"end_time":1628.02,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1623.62,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"What would need to be a custom field and so we can zone in on and make a decision on it?","index":346,"end_time":1633.3,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1628.26,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Yeah, it''s virtually everything in that sheet.","index":347,"end_time":1635.7,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1633.46,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"HubSpot doesn''t have, like.","index":348,"end_time":1637.34,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1636.1,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I mean, it''s.","index":349,"end_time":1637.98,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1637.34,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"They have like 150 properties that come out of the box, but it''s mainly around, like, have they opted into marketing?","index":350,"end_time":1643.58,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1637.98,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"What''s their first name?","index":351,"end_time":1644.3,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1643.58,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"What''s their last name?","index":352,"end_time":1644.98,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1644.3,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Like, everything else that we''re basically downloading from mulesoft and all that is going to be custom fields.","index":353,"end_time":1651.17,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1644.98,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But.","index":354,"end_time":1652.37,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1651.97,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"But custom fields in HubSpot.","index":355,"end_time":1654.73,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1652.53,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"In HubSpot, correct?","index":356,"end_time":1655.89,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1654.73,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, you already have.","index":357,"end_time":1656.85,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1655.89,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, we have to create them as custom fields in HubSpot because they already exist in Mulesoft and.","index":358,"end_time":1660.93,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1656.93,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Got it.","index":359,"end_time":1662.13,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1661.65,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Okay.","index":360,"end_time":1662.77,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1662.21,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So.","index":361,"end_time":1663.69,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1663.33,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So then what I would say is that, you know, we can just start to build that in alignment with the.","index":362,"end_time":1670.69,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1663.69,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"The groupings.","index":363,"end_time":1671.57,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1670.69,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Like, you guys could prioritize group A the same way as the, you know, Ashley''s team is going to prioritize.","index":364,"end_time":1679.11,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1671.81,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"As long as it''s not a decision that Ashley and Gabe would have to make that would require any customizations on HubSpot and Mulesoft side.","index":365,"end_time":1689.51,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1679.83,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"I think we''re.","index":366,"end_time":1690.07,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1689.51,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"We''re good because at the end and end of the day, we''re going to want all those fields somehow in the system anyways.","index":367,"end_time":1695.35,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1690.07,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Right.","index":368,"end_time":1696.07,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1695.67,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Mulesoft could send the data, then we''re good.","index":369,"end_time":1698.47,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1696.15,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Yeah, we''re not looking to create any custom fields or anything inside of mulesoft.","index":370,"end_time":1702.91,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1698.63,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It''s utilizing the data that Ashley and Gabe have already created over the years.","index":371,"end_time":1706.83,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1702.91,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And the field that you guys are utilizing, making sure that''s passing through to HubSpot.","index":372,"end_time":1710.57,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1706.83,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That''s.","index":373,"end_time":1710.89,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1710.57,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That''s really the bulk of this.","index":374,"end_time":1712.05,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1710.89,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":375,"end_time":1713.09,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1712.45,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"All right, so then anything that''s there, we can just say is we''re good to go on you guys building custom.","index":376,"end_time":1720.05,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1713.17,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"But.","index":377,"end_time":1720.57,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1720.21,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"But I would say just for your own sake, prioritize it based off of the same priority weighting that we''re.","index":378,"end_time":1726.09,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1720.57,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"We''re assigning it in the system.","index":379,"end_time":1728.61,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1726.09,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Perfect.","index":380,"end_time":1729.57,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1729.01,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":381,"end_time":1730.29,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1729.73,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then asset yeah, we''re taking a look at the frequency right.","index":382,"end_time":1735.58,"speaker_id":6,"start_time":1731.17,"speaker_name":"Ashlie Taska"},{"text":"And we know future that''s what is ideal for or requested right.","index":383,"end_time":1744.78,"speaker_id":6,"start_time":1736.22,"speaker_name":"Ashlie Taska"},{"text":"To have a daily sync.","index":384,"end_time":1745.9,"speaker_id":6,"start_time":1744.78,"speaker_name":"Ashlie Taska"},{"text":"But I just want to go back to the email that I sent out on Thursday.","index":385,"end_time":1749.82,"speaker_id":6,"start_time":1746.22,"speaker_name":"Ashlie Taska"},{"text":"It''s and it''s about the initial.","index":386,"end_time":1752.46,"speaker_id":6,"start_time":1750.46,"speaker_name":"Ashlie Taska"},{"text":"Upload.","index":387,"end_time":1754.86,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1754.22,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So is the expectation for a daily sync there or.","index":388,"end_time":1758.54,"speaker_id":6,"start_time":1755.42,"speaker_name":"Ashlie Taska"},{"text":"So I agree with your guys recommendation of the one time data import and then the real time or bi directional sync.","index":389,"end_time":1767.11,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1759.39,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I think that''s, that''s the smoothest way for all of these systems to communicate.","index":390,"end_time":1769.95,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1767.11,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"If we find that it''s making a massive task load on your guys system though that''s another conversation to have.","index":391,"end_time":1776.59,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1770.03,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":392,"end_time":1777.55,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1776.99,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"Yeah and I think Ashley and Gabe just so you guys kind of have an understanding and then you.","index":393,"end_time":1784.07,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1777.95,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"I''ll leave it to you guys to tell me like what the priority level should be because you guys know the system is better and I''m not going to have things get broken just because you know we need data because we''re not going to always action on it.","index":394,"end_time":1794.73,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1784.07,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Right.","index":395,"end_time":1795.05,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1794.73,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"For, for us I think having any kind of transaction or account opening data would be important right.","index":396,"end_time":1805.93,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1795.61,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Because that''s going to be some of the information that we''re going to use to trigger communications and all that kind of stuff.","index":397,"end_time":1812.25,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1805.93,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Other stuff like you know new customer records or, or updates and things like that.","index":398,"end_time":1821.04,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1813.29,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"I think that we can discuss the, the frequency or maybe not new new should be maybe instantaneous.","index":399,"end_time":1826.36,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1821.04,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So we could do like the welcome letters but you know things like I think the count record field like addresses and all that kind of stuff.","index":400,"end_time":1839.44,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1826.36,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Like if we get those every day I think that''s fine.","index":401,"end_time":1842.84,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1839.44,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Like we don''t, we''re not gonna you know change a marketing mail list just in the middle of the day right when we run it we''ll, we''ll run it whatever the data is as of that morning that that''s what it is.","index":402,"end_time":1853.11,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1842.84,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"I''m trying to think of any other use cases like email opt out would probably be one where you know if possible if there''s any tracking that the branches do in the system you know that is helpful to be real time because you know we send out emails on you know frequent basis and you know we don''t want to miss their, you know their preferences.","index":403,"end_time":1877.23,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1855.19,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"There a lot of like the account information fields like balances and all that kind of stuff.","index":404,"end_time":1887.43,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1877.23,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"I think like whatever the frequency you guys are suggesting there is fine because it''s going to be not a big driver in terms of like us data mining but I think like if they have an account or they, or any type of, like, activity with their account would be, Would be helpful.","index":405,"end_time":1904.04,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1887.43,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Updates to, like, their email address record, I think should be instantaneous in case of any issues there and then really anything else that you think, I would just go with your recommendation, to be honest.","index":406,"end_time":1919.16,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1904.84,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And we''ll, we''ll modify, like, our marketing approach from there.","index":407,"end_time":1922.44,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1919.16,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"But my only question would be like, let''s just say down the line, if we, you know, realize that maybe we need to tweak something, is it hard for you guys to change the data frequency like, once it''s set up?","index":408,"end_time":1934.78,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1922.76,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Not necessarily.","index":409,"end_time":1937.98,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1936.86,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Go ahead.","index":410,"end_time":1938.62,"speaker_id":6,"start_time":1938.14,"speaker_name":"Ashlie Taska"},{"text":"Yeah, well, the data frequency, it depends.","index":411,"end_time":1943.54,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1939.18,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"For example, we have a flow that runs.","index":412,"end_time":1945.74,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1943.54,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"We have flows that run at the beginning of every morning right before the branches or, or the bank becomes operational.","index":413,"end_time":1952.97,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1945.98,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"So that frequency itself, we can tweak it on our side to kind of like whenever, whenever it needs to be launched.","index":414,"end_time":1962.53,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1953.05,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"We can actually launch it ad hoc if needed.","index":415,"end_time":1964.53,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1962.53,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"But yeah, there shouldn''t be a big thing to change the frequency if we go by frequencies.","index":416,"end_time":1968.49,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1964.53,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"When I say go by frequencies.","index":417,"end_time":1970.93,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1969.37,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"If we got, for example, if I set up a schedule to run on a daily basis, I could change that schedule to maybe run every four hours, for example.","index":418,"end_time":1978.24,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1970.93,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Okay.","index":419,"end_time":1978.96,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1978.4,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Having to change any configuration, but if we do it by triggers, meaning something needs to happen in the system so that it goes over to the hotspot, then it might be.","index":420,"end_time":1986.72,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1979.04,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"We might have to make meals of changes on that.","index":421,"end_time":1990.52,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1987.76,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"On that side.","index":422,"end_time":1991.16,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1990.52,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"So we''re gonna have to kind of align it specifically when we say, you know, how we want to send the information, what information should be on a schedule and what information should be based on a trigger.","index":423,"end_time":2001.28,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1991.16,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"And so that one.","index":424,"end_time":2002.44,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2001.44,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"On triggers, we kind of have deployments and we want to make changes, and we want to make sure we track those changes as well.","index":425,"end_time":2007.69,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2002.44,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"So it.","index":426,"end_time":2008.45,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2007.69,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Okay, but it shouldn''t be too crazy.","index":427,"end_time":2010.65,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2008.45,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":428,"end_time":2011.05,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2010.65,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Okay.","index":429,"end_time":2011.85,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2011.37,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"All right.","index":430,"end_time":2012.25,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2011.85,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So down the line, you know, we can, we can build like a sort of a. I don''t want to say a full, like, blown, you know, procedure just for this component.","index":431,"end_time":2020.17,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2012.25,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"We''ll want to have that as an element of, you know, our overall process.","index":432,"end_time":2024.57,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2020.33,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"But definitely, like, give me your process for how that would.","index":433,"end_time":2028.25,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2024.65,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Would work and like, the lead time for each.","index":434,"end_time":2029.93,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2028.25,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Just so if we ever needed to do anything like that, we could have an understanding.","index":435,"end_time":2034.23,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2029.93,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"But I think, I think the, those few that I said like, the instantaneously would be helpful.","index":436,"end_time":2041.79,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2034.23,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"The rest, you know, if it''s daily, I think that would be.","index":437,"end_time":2045.83,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2041.79,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Would be fine.","index":438,"end_time":2046.55,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2045.83,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"But again, even if you need to kind of stagger between the day, the timing of the, of the updates.","index":439,"end_time":2052.91,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2046.55,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Just so not everything is, you know, flowing through the system at what, 9:00am to, you know, to overload would be, would be fine.","index":440,"end_time":2059.96,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2052.91,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"You guys could let us know.","index":441,"end_time":2061.52,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2059.96,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"The only thing that we''ll want to make sure that we sync on is that schedule.","index":442,"end_time":2065.92,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2061.6,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So we could use it as a way to make decisions.","index":443,"end_time":2069.92,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2065.92,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So for example, like if Victor''s going to pull a mail list and we know that an update happens to the fields that are going to be within our mail list at 9am like we''re going to not pull a list, you know, 6pm the night before.","index":444,"end_time":2083.72,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2069.92,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"We''ll wait until, you know, maybe 10am or however long the update needs to happen.","index":445,"end_time":2090.48,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2083.72,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So I think that also just syncing up with, with that for our own information, it''ll help us to pull data or look at the system at the right time.","index":446,"end_time":2099.12,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2090.88,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And then also just how we would go about, you know, making sure that none of the sinks get broken.","index":447,"end_time":2108.8,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2100.24,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Is there some type of report that we''re going to look at or is there flags that you would get on your side when things are off or is it something that we have to monitor in HubSpot?","index":448,"end_time":2118.87,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2108.8,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"That was a question we had asked last week.","index":449,"end_time":2121.22,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2119.98,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So Gabe had mentioned that they do get an alert and then on the HubSpot we would monitor for those because we would get an alert as well.","index":450,"end_time":2127.18,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2121.22,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":451,"end_time":2128.3,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2127.82,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"All right, so then we''ll just have to make sure that we keep our teams in sync on both sides, you know.","index":452,"end_time":2134.1,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2128.3,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And then what, like the process would be to fix them?","index":453,"end_time":2137.02,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2134.1,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"That seems like it''s pretty straightforward.","index":454,"end_time":2141.1,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2139.02,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":455,"end_time":2141.82,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2141.34,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"All right, cool.","index":456,"end_time":2142.86,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2142.06,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So I guess if we go back to the project planning because we''re, we''re at time, does everyone feel comfortable with kind of the open immediate tasks and then I guess on Friday what we can do is just align on just the rest of the tasks because there''s I think an end date to this component.","index":457,"end_time":2164.29,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2143.02,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And then Ashley, you know, and Gabe, you guys could let us know if that works.","index":458,"end_time":2168.85,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2165.89,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Okay.","index":459,"end_time":2170.59,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2170.05,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":460,"end_time":2171.54,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2171.14,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, so we''ll go through and update the spreadsheet just to finalize all the breaking out that we''re doing and then building those custom fields in HubSpot.","index":461,"end_time":2179.78,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2171.7,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And Ashley and Gabe please, as you have any questions or anything pops up on the HubSpot side of things, as you''re reading through documentation, let me know.","index":462,"end_time":2186.58,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2179.78,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But yeah, really just for your guys side, it''s just going to be making sure that the information is flowing from system to system.","index":463,"end_time":2194.42,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2187.3,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Once we load in those sample contacts with all the custom fields that we''re building inside of HubSpot.","index":464,"end_time":2200.05,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2194.42,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then from there it''s really just setting our sync frequency and turning it on.","index":465,"end_time":2204.65,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2200.05,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, can you just.","index":466,"end_time":2207.33,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2206.01,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Colin, make sure that.","index":467,"end_time":2208.21,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2207.33,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Or Guille, if it''s going to come from you, just the latest spreadsheet version, just send it over to me, Ashley, Gabe and team, just so we know exactly like, you know, the latest.","index":468,"end_time":2220.49,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2208.21,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"That the way to look at it.","index":469,"end_time":2221.49,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2220.49,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So we can get that to you guys by Friday?","index":470,"end_time":2222.89,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2221.49,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Absolutely, yeah.","index":471,"end_time":2224.25,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2223.49,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Got it.","index":472,"end_time":2224.85,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2224.25,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":473,"end_time":2225.81,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2225.25,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Ashley, I hope this cleared up any questions or I hope this didn''t cause any.","index":474,"end_time":2230.77,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2226.53,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Any anxiety of timeline pressure or anything.","index":475,"end_time":2234.29,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2231.01,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"No, Christina actually cleared that up last week.","index":476,"end_time":2237.73,"speaker_id":6,"start_time":2234.85,"speaker_name":"Ashlie Taska"},{"text":"So me and Gabe were relieved after that, that conversation and we''re like, okay, this makes a lot more sense now.","index":477,"end_time":2248.69,"speaker_id":6,"start_time":2238.05,"speaker_name":"Ashlie Taska"},{"text":"Now it seems like we''re in a month now.","index":478,"end_time":2250.44,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2248.69,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It''s like, we''re not crazy, right?","index":479,"end_time":2251.52,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2250.44,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Like, we.","index":480,"end_time":2252,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2251.52,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah, yeah.","index":481,"end_time":2253.6,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2252.4,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Okay.","index":482,"end_time":2254.4,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2253.84,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"What''s going on with them?","index":483,"end_time":2255.56,"speaker_id":6,"start_time":2254.4,"speaker_name":"Ashlie Taska"},{"text":"We''re only a team of three and one person is not on this project.","index":484,"end_time":2259.04,"speaker_id":6,"start_time":2255.56,"speaker_name":"Ashlie Taska"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah, no, I.","index":485,"end_time":2261.76,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2259.84,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Me and Ashley had a, like a hot moment of like, holy cow.","index":486,"end_time":2266.72,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2262.08,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"You know, we both were probably thinking each other was crazy because, like, in my mind I''m like, wait a minute, this is not a lot.","index":487,"end_time":2272.48,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2267.44,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And then she''s thinking like, oh, my God, wait, this is like too much.","index":488,"end_time":2275.6,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2272.48,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And then so, yeah, we were always.","index":489,"end_time":2278.2,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2275.6,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Always good to get on the same page.","index":490,"end_time":2279.48,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2278.2,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Always good for alignment.","index":491,"end_time":2280.48,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2279.48,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah.","index":492,"end_time":2281.26,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2280.74,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And I think honestly, it''s just sometimes when you speak the different, like, like language, the tech is the marketing lingo.","index":493,"end_time":2287.74,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2281.26,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So anytime we say like journey or.","index":494,"end_time":2290.18,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2287.74,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Or, you know, anything like that, like, we''ll just be super clear, like what the intention of it.","index":495,"end_time":2295.66,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2290.18,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Because even like workflow, like, when I think of workflow, it''s probably totally different than, you know, so the language we can clear.","index":496,"end_time":2304.66,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2295.66,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":497,"end_time":2306.1,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2305.46,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And yeah, I mean, I guess, like, for future, just if there''s any issues or concerns or, you know, other things that impact the timeline, just.","index":498,"end_time":2315.85,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2307.13,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Just feel free, you know, to reach out or just send an email so we can get the, you know, that.","index":499,"end_time":2320.73,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2315.85,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah.","index":500,"end_time":2321.45,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2320.89,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"This is open line of communication between all of us.","index":501,"end_time":2323.41,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2321.45,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We''re all working to get this project done not only in time, but done very well.","index":502,"end_time":2327.25,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2323.41,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So, you know, if ever anything pops up, just let us know.","index":503,"end_time":2330.89,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2327.25,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Let''s work together as a team to resolve it.","index":504,"end_time":2332.65,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2330.97,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":505,"end_time":2334,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2333.6,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Perfect.","index":506,"end_time":2334.36,"speaker_id":6,"start_time":2334,"speaker_name":"Ashlie Taska"},{"text":"All right, cool.","index":507,"end_time":2335.28,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2334.36,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"All right, well, thank you guys for the extra five minutes, but I think we''re in a.","index":508,"end_time":2339.48,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2335.44,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"In a good, you know, spot, so we''ll try to get everything done before, you know, we meet Friday.","index":509,"end_time":2345.36,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2339.48,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So when Louie and Betty join, could have a good update for for them on status.","index":510,"end_time":2351.28,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2345.52,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":511,"end_time":2352.16,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2351.6,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right, thank you, everybody, for your time.","index":512,"end_time":2353.64,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2352.24,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Thank you, everyone.","index":513,"end_time":2354.32,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2353.64,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Bye.","index":514,"end_time":2354.96,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2354.48,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Bye.","index":515,"end_time":2355.4,"speaker_id":6,"start_time":2355.04,"speaker_name":"Ashlie Taska"},{"text":"Bye.","index":516,"end_time":2355.76,"speaker_id":6,"start_time":2355.4,"speaker_name":"Ashlie Taska"}],"dateString":"2026-01-12T18:30:00.000Z","host_email":"guille.santana@marketersindemand.com","meeting_link":"https://us02web.zoom.us/j/86748325083?pwd=KZXr4Ib0dDLtPiGMrTJIoavjgUhHYR.1","participants":["guille.santana@marketersindemand.com,tristan.pelligrino@marketersindemand.com,colin.costigan@marketersindemand.com,luis.gonzalez@poncebank.net,victor.garcia@poncebank.net,gabriel.bencosme@poncebank.net,christina.zanca@poncebank.net,ashlie.taska@poncebank.net,betty.campiz@poncebank.net","tristan.pelligrino@marketersindemand.com","colin.costigan@marketersindemand.com","luis.gonzalez@poncebank.net","victor.garcia@poncebank.net","gabriel.bencosme@poncebank.net","christina.zanca@poncebank.net","ashlie.taska@poncebank.net","betty.campiz@poncebank.net"],"transcript_url":"https://app.fireflies.ai/view/01KEJ9JSGVBS0DRBZ7S491AKR7","organizer_email":"guille.santana@marketersindemand.com"}'::jsonb,
    '{"label":"positive","confidence":0.91,"bullets":["Confirmed alignment on current project phase, with approved custom fields ready for next build step","Agreed to finalize masking and data sync frequency decisions by Friday for smooth integration","Colin committed to updating spreadsheet with field priorities and building custom fields in HubSpot","Ashley and Gabe to review data frequency plan and validate PII elements for masking","Established real-time communication protocol for sync errors across HubSpot and internal systems"],"highlights":[{"quote":"I think we’re in a good spot, so we''ll try to get everything done before Friday.","speaker":"christinazanca"},{"quote":"We''re all working to get this project done not only in time, but done very well.","speaker":"Colin Costigan"},{"quote":"Christina actually cleared that up last week... me and Gabe were relieved after that.","speaker":"Ashlie Taska"}],"topics":["sync","delivery","timeline","data","HubSpot"],"model":"openai/gpt-4-0613","version":1,"generated_at":"2026-01-12T00:00:00Z"}'::jsonb,
    '{"fireflies_summary":{"notes":"## **Project Timeline and Task Alignment**\n\nThe team agreed on a clear phased timeline with defined deliverables to ensure alignment and progress tracking (06:47).\n\n- **Christina Zanca** outlined the need to review the timeline regularly to track completed tasks, identify delays, and understand downstream impacts (11:19).  \n    - The timeline breaks down into three phases: Phase A (go-live day one), Phase B (post-launch), and Phase C (nice-to-have features) as explained by **Guille Santana** (22:17).  \n    - Tasks related to data components were extracted from the overall timeline to allow focused progress monitoring and prioritization.  \n    - **Colin Costigan** and **Christina** emphasized the importance of sequencing tasks and adjusting due dates as needed to maintain flow and avoid bottlenecks (17:47).  \n    - The team committed to providing the latest, more granular timeline version by Friday’s meeting to ensure all parties have up-to-date visibility (36:46).  \n\n- The team confirmed the **custom fields approval deadline as the 19th**, with the expectation that these fields will be built in HubSpot shortly after (20:56).  \n    - **Colin** clarified that nearly all fields from the spreadsheet require custom creation in HubSpot, as only about 150 default properties exist out-of-the-box (27:13).  \n    - Prioritization of these fields will align with marketing needs and system importance to avoid unnecessary customization or delays (28:15).  \n    - The team agreed to break down larger tasks like HubSpot API enablement into subtasks for clarity and easier workload planning, with input from **Ashley Taska** and **Christina** (13:45).  \n\n## **Data Integration and API Sync Strategy**\n\nThe team aligned on API connectivity and sync frequency to balance system load and marketing responsiveness (09:47).\n\n- **Gabriel Bencosme** and **Ashley Taska** reviewed HubSpot’s private app setup for API access, confirming that a legacy app with defined scopes and keys will be used for integration (15:35).  \n    - Access permissions were addressed, with **Colin** checking if switching seats to developer roles would resolve access issues for API testing (16:52).  \n    - The team agreed to finalize API authentication configuration as part of the data model and custom fields task, slated for imminent completion within the timeline (18:01).  \n\n- Sync frequency was discussed in detail, balancing marketing urgency with system capacity:  \n    - A **daily batch sync** is preferred for most data, while some key updates like email opt-outs and account changes require **instantaneous or near real-time sync** to avoid customer experience issues (30:29).  \n    - **Gabriel** confirmed that scheduled flows run early each morning and can be adjusted ad hoc or more frequently (32:18).  \n    - Trigger-based syncs may require more complex changes but remain feasible with alignment on what data should be sync-scheduled versus event-triggered (32:59).  \n    - The team plans to document this sync strategy, including lead times and change processes, as part of their broader operating procedures (33:31).  \n\n- Monitoring and alerting for sync failures will be handled both on **HubSpot** and integration sides, with alerts triggering investigations and fixes to maintain data integrity and uptime (35:19).  \n    - Continuous communication between teams will support rapid response to any issues, avoiding disruptions to marketing activities (38:00).  \n\n## **Data Field Prioritization and Masking**\n\nThe team focused on prioritizing data fields and defining masking rules to protect sensitive information and streamline integration (22:40).\n\n- **Guille Santana** highlighted that some fields (e.g., borrower marital status, family income) should be reviewed for exclusion or masking, with these flagged in yellow for compliance review (23:26).  \n    - This initial review applies specifically to Encompass data; a similar exercise is planned or underway for Mulesoft data (23:36).  \n    - **Christina** will seek compliance definitions of personally identifiable information (PII) to guide masking decisions and add subtasks related to masking and frequency review to the timeline (25:45).  \n\n- **Ashley** noted that masking decisions ultimately require IT and compliance approval, but the team can draft preliminary frequency settings and masking suggestions by Friday (24:33).  \n    - The team agreed to automatically mask all PII, pending compliance input, to reduce risk and simplify data handling (25:45).  \n    - Ashley and Gabe will focus on data frequency and masking frequency alignment, while Christina will review flagged fields for privacy concerns (26:08).  \n\n- The team expects to have masking rules defined and priority groupings agreed upon before the next major milestone, supporting streamlined data flow and regulatory compliance (24:52).  \n\n## **Cross-Team Communication and Role Clarity**\n\nClear communication and role definitions were emphasized to reduce confusion and keep the project on schedule (38:00).\n\n- **Christina** stressed the importance of speaking the same language across marketing, tech, and compliance teams to avoid misunderstandings, especially around terms like “workflow” and “journey” (38:00).  \n    - She suggested that future meetings clarify terminology upfront to align expectations and reduce friction.  \n    - Open communication lines were encouraged, with all participants agreeing to promptly raise issues or changes via email to prevent delays (38:27).  \n\n- **Colin** reassured the team that the workload is manageable and the timeline reasonable, helping relieve pressure and boost confidence in meeting deliverables (37:05).  \n    - Ashley agreed that recent clarifications reduced anxiety and improved understanding of the project scope (37:14).  \n    - The team acknowledged their small size and need to stay focused and coordinated to meet deadlines without burnout (37:34).  \n\n## **Next Steps and Meeting Cadence**\n\nThe team set expectations for immediate deliverables and the upcoming Friday meeting to maintain momentum (06:26).\n\n- The immediate focus is on finalizing the custom fields list, masking rules, and data frequency review by Friday to enable building and testing (18:53).  \n    - Uploading test contacts and enabling API sync are the next steps following field approvals (19:18).  \n    - **Colin** and **Guille** will circulate the latest detailed timeline and spreadsheet versions to all stakeholders to keep everyone updated (36:46).  \n\n- The Friday meeting will serve as a checkpoint to review progress, adjust timelines if necessary, and incorporate feedback from Louie and Betty when they join (06:46).  \n    - The team agreed to keep this meeting as the main forum for status updates and deeper discussions, avoiding unnecessary interim meetings that may cause confusion (06:26).  \n\n- Ongoing collaboration between technical and marketing teams will continue to ensure alignment on priorities and smooth integration (38:54).","outline":null,"keywords":["HubSpot integration","custom fields","data synchronization","API authentication","masking rules","sync frequency"],"overview":"- **Project Timeline Defined:** Three phased timeline established: Phase A (launch), Phase B (post-launch), Phase C (additional features).  \n- **Custom Fields Deadline:** Custom fields approval due on the 19th; most require custom creation in HubSpot, aligning with marketing needs.  \n- **API Sync Strategy:** Daily batch sync preferred; key updates need real-time sync; monitoring for failures will ensure data integrity.  \n- **Data Masking Rules:** Compliance reviews needed for sensitive fields; automatic PII masking agreed pending compliance input for risk reduction.  \n- **Communication Strategy:** Emphasis on clear role definitions and terminology; open lines encouraged for prompt issue reporting to avoid delays.  \n- **Immediate Next Steps:** Focus on finalizing custom fields, data frequency, and testing by Friday; regular status updates to maintain project momentum.","action_items":"\n**Guille Santana**\nContinue breaking down the project timeline into detailed subtasks and update the team by Friday (21:50)\n\n**Colin Costigan**\nProvide updated detailed timeline spreadsheet showing task breakdown and statuses to Ponce Bank team by Friday (37:04)\nBuild custom fields in HubSpot based on approved field list once confirmation is received (36:11)\nRespond promptly to queries from Ashley and Gabe regarding HubSpot API and workflow documentation (10:20)\n\n**Ashley Taska**\nReview data sync frequency requirements and provide feedback ahead of Friday meeting (24:33)\nCollaborate with Gabe on confirming necessary custom fields and masking priorities (24:30)\n\n**Gabriel Bencosme**\nContinue review of HubSpot API documentation and discuss access for private app setup/testing (15:21)\nCoordinate with Ashley on masking rules and frequency for data synchronization (24:30)\nProvide status updates and questions for upcoming Friday meeting (36:10)\n\n**Christina Zanca**\nReview and finalize flagged PII and masking fields with compliance input before Friday meeting (24:45)\nMonitor deliverable progression and ensure alignment on timeline and task sequencing for next steps (17:04)\nCommunicate meeting updates and progress to Louie and Betty (06:30)\n"},"migrated_from":"contract_meetings","original_id":"8475d207-cc54-45ee-b0a9-2bbb97d96920","master_marketer":{"status":"migrated"}}'::jsonb,
