    '{"id":"01KE7TXRGCJPBZB1RBX6YR24GY","title":"Gallagher & Mohan // MiD: Weekly Marketing Meeting","summary":{"notes":"## **Account-Based Marketing (ABM) Strategy and Targeting**\n\nThe team is finalizing a detailed ABM plan focusing on institutional retail-oriented real estate companies to target precise contacts for personalized outreach.\n\n- **Colin Costigan confirmed** they are writing a **50-page ABM plan this week** detailing email sources, content types, channels, and user journeys to engage prospects for **Gallagher and Mohan** (01:50).  \n    - The ABM approach uses email, LinkedIn outreach, ads, and landing pages to control the full customer journey.  \n    - Data sourcing is from **Clay**, aggregating Apollo, ZoomInfo, LinkedIn, and other platforms to build targeted lists.  \n    - The campaign targets **1,000 to 1,500 contacts** across **500 to 1,000 companies**, emphasizing multiple job titles per company for tailored messaging.  \n    - This detailed segmentation aims to improve engagement by addressing specific pain points per role and industry segment.\n\n- **Doug and David Willett emphasized** focusing on **pure retail investors** (e.g., Simon Property Group, Federal Realty) rather than broad diversified asset managers to improve lead quality and message relevance (06:00).  \n    - Colin explained personalization fields allow emails to adapt content based on industry, sub-industry, or job title for flexibility.  \n    - They plan to manually refine lists using LinkedIn research to drill into specific retail vertical contacts within large diversified firms like Blackstone.  \n    - Recognizing challenges in job title clarity and contact specificity, they will blend automated lists with manual vetting to ensure accuracy.  \n    - The goal is a focused, high-value list to maximize outreach effectiveness against \"institutional retail\" buyers.\n\n## **Content and Outreach Execution**\n\nThe marketing team will leverage efficient 30-minute interview sessions to produce rich content assets that support brand awareness and nurture leads.\n\n- **Colin proposed** a **content series** based on short interviews generating multiple outputs: four blog posts, ten social media posts, white papers, and videos from a single 30-minute conversation (23:50).  \n    - Content can be rotated among hosts, including sales or back-office team members, to avoid burnout and diversify perspectives.  \n    - The team will use **Riverside**, a podcast recording platform, to capture high-quality audio/video remotely without the need for new equipment.  \n    - Content serves as branded assets to amplify ABM efforts via social media syndication and email campaigns, driving awareness at the top of the funnel.  \n    - This content strategy complements ABM’s precision targeting by building broader brand recognition.\n\n- Doug expressed mixed feelings about LinkedIn outreach but acknowledged its value when combined with content-driven campaigns to create engagement (24:15).  \n    - Colin highlighted that LinkedIn messaging volume is controlled (15-18 messages per day from Doug’s profile) to avoid flags and maintain authenticity.  \n    - Social media and content efforts mainly target brand awareness, while ABM focuses on direct, personalized outreach to decision makers and influencers.\n\n## **Lead List Development and Targeting Refinement**\n\nThe team agreed to provide a refined list of target companies this week to enable finalization of contacts and campaign parameters.\n\n- Doug and David will deliver a **company list by end of week** prioritizing institutional retail-focused firms (23:00).  \n    - Colin has pre-filtered about **13,000 companies** from Clay but needs a smaller, precise subset to start.  \n    - Focus will be on companies that fit the institutional retail asset class and have the right scale and fit for Gallagher and Mohan’s services.  \n    - The list will support building a contact list of **~1,000 to 1,500 individual contacts** to address multiple roles.  \n    - The subscription to additional data sources like **CoStar** and a private real estate database will supplement this effort.\n\n- They plan to use **lookalike audiences** based on key accounts like Federal Realty to expand the relevant pool while maintaining focus (14:50).  \n    - This data-driven approach ensures the outreach targets prospects with similar profiles and high potential fit.\n\n## **Value Proposition and Engagement Tools**\n\nTo reduce resistance and improve conversion, the team will develop interactive tools and tangible proof elements demonstrating cost savings.\n\n- Colin stressed prospects prefer concrete, quantifiable value before committing to calls, citing that **75% of the decision is made before a 15-minute discovery call** (16:00).  \n    - David and Doug agreed that highlighting **average cost savings or ROI** upfront is critical to lowering barriers.  \n    - They discussed building a **website calculator** where prospects input metrics (e.g., number of lease administrators, properties) to estimate potential savings (18:00).  \n    - The calculator would generate a downloadable PDF report with customized benchmarks and direct sales contact info to facilitate internal championing.  \n    - Colin shared examples of clients using interactive calculators paired with downloadable content to push prospects toward sales calls.\n\n- This tool aims to empower prospects to justify internal buy-in by quantifying benefits, turning contacts into internal champions.  \n    - The calculator will be developed by Colin’s team and then handed off for website integration to save time and resources.\n\n## **Process and Operational Coordination**\n\nClear next steps and process ownership were established to keep the campaign on track and ensure asset readiness.\n\n- Colin confirmed he will verify the **asset intake form** completed by Doug’s team and send a status update via email today (15:30).  \n    - After receiving the company list, they will finalize the ABM plan and build the detailed contact list.  \n    - They will simultaneously start branding, design, and naming concepts for the content series to align with campaign messaging.  \n    - Colin’s team uses **Fireflies** for call transcription, sentiment analysis, and tracking next steps automatically, improving follow-up and leadership visibility (27:40).  \n    - Doug requested a demo of Fireflies to evaluate its fit for their internal workflows.\n\n- The team emphasized flexibility in service usage, with Colin explaining the **points-based payment model** that fixes cost per deliverable regardless of back-end effort (27:00).  \n    - This model encourages efficient resource use and allows the client to prioritize high-impact activities within a fixed budget.\n\n## **Strategic Insights and Market Positioning**\n\nThe focus on institutional retail buyers reflects a deliberate strategy to engage decision makers who control significant budgets and are receptive to targeted, data-driven outreach.\n\n- David highlighted the variability in organizational structures across target firms, noting that financial decision makers (CFOs, heads of asset management) are typically the key contacts (12:00).  \n    - The team acknowledged the need for multiple outreach paths, including procurement and operational contacts, to navigate complex buying processes.  \n    - Doug shared prior success stories where direct CEO outreach or vendor managers led to conversions, underscoring the importance of tailored approaches.  \n    - Colin stressed empowering internal champions by targeting staff who can present Gallagher and Mohan as problem solvers to senior management.\n\n- The ABM and content strategies aim to differentiate Gallagher and Mohan by combining precise targeting with compelling proof of value and broad brand presence.  \n    - This dual approach addresses both the top and middle of the funnel, improving lead quality and accelerating decision timelines.","outline":null,"keywords":["Account Based Marketing","Institutional Retail Real Estate","Lead Generation","Interactive Calculator","Content Series","LinkedIn Outreach"],"overview":"- **ABM Plan Finalization:** A 50-page ABM plan targeting 1,000-1,500 contacts from 500-1,000 institutions is being drafted.  \n- **Campaign Focus:** Targeted outreach prioritizes pure retail investors to improve lead quality and messaging relevance.  \n- **Content Strategy:** Short interviews will create diverse content assets to support brand awareness and nurture leads effectively.  \n- **Lead List Refinement:** A precise company list targeting institutional retail firms will be provided this week for campaign setup.  \n- **Value Proposition Tools:** An interactive calculator will help prospects quantify benefits and justify internal support before calls.  \n- **Market Positioning Strategy:** Targeting key financial decision-makers within firms to streamline the buying process and improve outreach effectiveness.","action_items":"\n**Doug Gallagher**\nProvide a handpicked list of institutional retail-oriented companies (target 500-1000 companies) to Colin and David for campaign targeting (23:00)\nReview and respond to Colin’s email confirming asset intake details (15:35)\nConsider and decide on participation and hosts for content series production (25:30)\nReview and share feedback on Fireflies transcription and automation tool (28:20)\n\n**David Willett**\nCollaborate with Doug on curating a refined company list focused on pure retail investors for ABM targeting (23:00)\nShare feedback about toolkits and content offers such as one-pagers and calculator concepts (16:30)\nReview and help prioritize target decision-maker profiles within companies (12:00)\nReview Fireflies tool and collaborate with Doug on adoption (28:15)\n\n**Colin Costigan**\nFinalize ABM plan document integrating Doug and David’s company list and detailed campaign parameters (23:00)\nDevelop contact list from provided company list and build tailored outreach messaging (23:00)\nPropose branding, design, and naming concepts for content series production (23:30)\nShare Fireflies transcription and analysis sample with Doug and David (28:25)\nSupport development and transfer of interactive calculator web tool, including code handoff if needed (19:00)\n"},"duration":30.219999313354492,"speakers":[{"id":0,"name":"Doug"},{"id":1,"name":"Colin Costigan"},{"id":2,"name":"David Willett"}],"sentences":[{"text":"Hi there.","index":0,"end_time":6.96,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":6.48,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"Hey, David.","index":1,"end_time":8.88,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":8.16,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"How''s it going?","index":2,"end_time":9.44,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":8.88,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Good, good.","index":3,"end_time":10.24,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":9.44,"speaker_name":"David Willett"},{"text":"Nice to see you.","index":4,"end_time":12,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":10.96,"speaker_name":"David Willett"},{"text":"Yeah, you as well.","index":5,"end_time":13.2,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":12.32,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Great to meet you.","index":6,"end_time":14,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":13.2,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I wanted to let you know Doug''s gonna, is running a few minutes late.","index":7,"end_time":18.48,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":15.36,"speaker_name":"David Willett"},{"text":"Okay.","index":8,"end_time":19.28,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":18.72,"speaker_name":"David Willett"},{"text":"But nice to meet you, Colin.","index":9,"end_time":22.64,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":20,"speaker_name":"David Willett"},{"text":"And, and you know, and in fact, Doug gave me a little heads up in terms of like what you guys have been doing together and what he''s looking to do.","index":10,"end_time":31.65,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":22.64,"speaker_name":"David Willett"},{"text":"But you know, while we''re waiting, I''d love to hear kind of what the background is and you know, in terms of the work with Gallagher and Mohan, what, what he''s, what he''s conveyed to you in terms of what he''s thinking of doing and what the objectives are.","index":11,"end_time":45.81,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":31.65,"speaker_name":"David Willett"},{"text":"So I can, so can match up with what I''m thinking too?","index":12,"end_time":48.41,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":45.81,"speaker_name":"David Willett"},{"text":"Yeah, absolutely.","index":13,"end_time":49.85,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":48.73,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So the primary thing that we''re working on is building an account based marketing campaign.","index":14,"end_time":54.25,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":49.85,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And so that enables us to do outreach through a few different channels at once with a few different types of messaging, but really basically broad broadcasting our message to hand selected individuals at hand selected companies.","index":15,"end_time":67.83,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":54.57,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So to do that we''ve worked with Doug to identify the parameters.","index":16,"end_time":72.71,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":69.19,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"He did just add in the email where he asked for you to join the call a new audience to pull into that as well.","index":17,"end_time":78.31,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":72.71,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And so out of that we this week are writing our ABM plan document that is about a 50 page document that outlines everything into really fine detail of.","index":18,"end_time":90.38,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":78.95,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"These are the email addresses we''re going to be sending from.","index":19,"end_time":92.5,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":90.38,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"This is the type of content we''re going to be sending.","index":20,"end_time":94.54,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":92.5,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"These are the people we''re going to be talking to.","index":21,"end_time":96.46,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":94.62,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"This is where we''re sending them for landing pages or how we communicate on LinkedIn, et cetera.","index":22,"end_time":100.86,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":96.46,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So it''s going to go into a lot of detail, but at a high level.","index":23,"end_time":104.46,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":101.18,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"What we do is develop ad programs, email campaigns and LinkedIn campaigns as well as landing pages on your website so that we can control the full user journey from end to end of getting these prospects to engage with Gallagher and Mohan.","index":24,"end_time":118.22,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":104.46,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, that''s great.","index":25,"end_time":119.44,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":118.64,"speaker_name":"David Willett"},{"text":"What are the sort, I mean, where''s the source of the lead or the data coming from?","index":26,"end_time":124.96,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":119.92,"speaker_name":"David Willett"},{"text":"So we use Clay, which is able to pull in a bunch of different resources such as Apollo or Zoom info, LinkedIn audiences, everything like that.","index":27,"end_time":133.52,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":125.44,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Oh, interesting, interesting.","index":28,"end_time":135.68,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":133.84,"speaker_name":"David Willett"},{"text":"So yeah, Doug and I were talking last week and it''s kind of what prompted us to do a little bit of a shift in terms of the target audience on the institutional retail real estate owners.","index":29,"end_time":148.88,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":135.68,"speaker_name":"David Willett"},{"text":"At one point, I think we had been thinking about a subset of multifamily investors but wanted to maybe broaden the reach and see if it''s more applicable on a couple different fronts on the retail side.","index":30,"end_time":162.46,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":150.7,"speaker_name":"David Willett"},{"text":"But yeah, no, I''m really interested in how this works versus kind of other types of marketing campaigns and what the penetration and adoption rate is or what have you found kind of.","index":31,"end_time":181.36,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":164.14,"speaker_name":"David Willett"},{"text":"Well, one, have you done this type of work for other similarly focused, like real estate services companies targeting the investment community or the user community?","index":32,"end_time":195.04,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":182.24,"speaker_name":"David Willett"},{"text":"Absolutely.","index":33,"end_time":196.08,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":195.44,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":34,"end_time":196.48,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":196.08,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So with the real estate focus, but also.","index":35,"end_time":198.32,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":196.48,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Sorry, I''m getting a phone call with the real estate community, but also on the investing side.","index":36,"end_time":204.32,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":198.64,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So one of the numbers that we were alluding to with Doug last week was identifying the assets under management of these companies.","index":37,"end_time":210.48,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":204.32,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So that we have.","index":38,"end_time":211.35,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":210.56,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So that we know that we are really scoped in on who we''re talking to and making sure that one, that they are capable of doing the work that you guys are trying to reach out and get brought on board.","index":39,"end_time":220.46,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":212.22,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But two, that they are just the right fit in general.","index":40,"end_time":222.78,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":220.78,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Right.","index":41,"end_time":223.5,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":223.18,"speaker_name":"David Willett"},{"text":"Not too big and are just going to ignore us.","index":42,"end_time":226.46,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":223.5,"speaker_name":"David Willett"},{"text":"No, that''s great.","index":43,"end_time":227.42,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":226.7,"speaker_name":"David Willett"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":44,"end_time":228.14,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":227.74,"speaker_name":"David Willett"},{"text":"I think there are a lot of data providers out there that you can subscribe to and kind of glean that type of data, but converting that into targeted campaigns.","index":45,"end_time":239.34,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":228.14,"speaker_name":"David Willett"},{"text":"I''ve never used LinkedIn.","index":46,"end_time":242.27,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":240.83,"speaker_name":"David Willett"},{"text":"Is it LinkedIn marketer?","index":47,"end_time":243.75,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":242.51,"speaker_name":"David Willett"},{"text":"Is that what it''s called?","index":48,"end_time":244.51,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":243.75,"speaker_name":"David Willett"},{"text":"So, yeah, this is actually.","index":49,"end_time":246.19,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":245.07,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We use a tool called heyreach where we just connect directly to Doug''s profile and we send messages directly from his profile.","index":50,"end_time":252.83,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":246.19,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we configure it to have a limit so that his profile wouldn''t get flagged by LinkedIn for any way, but he would send probably about 15 to 18 messages a day to new contacts.","index":51,"end_time":260.91,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":252.83,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Oh, wow, that''s great.","index":52,"end_time":267,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":266.04,"speaker_name":"David Willett"},{"text":"Okay, that''s fantastic.","index":53,"end_time":268.16,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":267,"speaker_name":"David Willett"},{"text":"Account based.","index":54,"end_time":268.84,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":268.16,"speaker_name":"David Willett"},{"text":"I''m losing you a bit.","index":55,"end_time":286.6,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":285.4,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Doug, are you able to hear me?","index":56,"end_time":290.44,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":289.08,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I can hear you a little bit better now.","index":57,"end_time":292.2,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":290.76,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yes, I can hear you calling.","index":58,"end_time":294.8,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":293.64,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":59,"end_time":295.16,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":294.8,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"Okay.","index":60,"end_time":298.76,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":298.28,"speaker_name":"David Willett"},{"text":"Is that better now?","index":61,"end_time":299.64,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":298.76,"speaker_name":"David Willett"},{"text":"Yes.","index":62,"end_time":300.12,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":299.64,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right.","index":63,"end_time":301.32,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":300.76,"speaker_name":"David Willett"},{"text":"So is.","index":64,"end_time":302.56,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":302.04,"speaker_name":"David Willett"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":65,"end_time":302.76,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":302.56,"speaker_name":"David Willett"},{"text":"Is that, Is that being general?","index":66,"end_time":303.68,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":302.76,"speaker_name":"David Willett"},{"text":"Okay, cool.","index":67,"end_time":304.12,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":303.68,"speaker_name":"David Willett"},{"text":"That''s cool.","index":68,"end_time":304.48,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":304.12,"speaker_name":"David Willett"},{"text":"All right.","index":69,"end_time":304.72,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":304.48,"speaker_name":"David Willett"},{"text":"Very, very interesting.","index":70,"end_time":305.56,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":304.72,"speaker_name":"David Willett"},{"text":"Hey, Doug.","index":71,"end_time":306.52,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":305.8,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"Hey.","index":72,"end_time":307.56,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":307.16,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"What''s going on?","index":73,"end_time":308.28,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":307.56,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"Can you guys see me?","index":74,"end_time":311,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":309.56,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"Yes, we can.","index":75,"end_time":312.04,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":311.24,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, got it.","index":76,"end_time":314.52,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":312.52,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":77,"end_time":314.84,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":314.52,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"So Colin, just to kind of go off of the email I sent you, right.","index":78,"end_time":318.36,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":314.84,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"So I feel like we haven''t.","index":79,"end_time":322.72,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":319.76,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"Shouldn''t really matter too much because I don''t think we''ve gone too far in anything.","index":80,"end_time":326.16,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":323.36,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"But the focus we want to go for is institutional, retail oriented companies.","index":81,"end_time":332.32,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":326.56,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"Right.","index":82,"end_time":332.88,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":332.48,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"And what I was thinking is that it''d probably be best if David and I just kind of came up with A list of companies.","index":83,"end_time":338.64,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":333.44,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"Right.","index":84,"end_time":339.2,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":338.8,"speaker_name":"David Willett"},{"text":"Like, because we could probably look at each one in five seconds and determine if it''s a good lead or not.","index":85,"end_time":344.72,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":339.52,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"Just, like, the names of companies.","index":86,"end_time":347.14,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":345.7,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"Right, so.","index":87,"end_time":348.74,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":347.3,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"Yeah, but any thoughts or questions there?","index":88,"end_time":352.18,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":349.78,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"No, I mean, that would be great.","index":89,"end_time":353.46,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":352.34,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Typically, our clients don''t want to be like, they''d rather just review it and not.","index":90,"end_time":356.98,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":353.86,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Not do the work.","index":91,"end_time":357.58,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":356.98,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But if you guys, you know, have a handset of accounts, that would be great.","index":92,"end_time":360.98,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":357.58,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I already started going through clay and just putting in some filters.","index":93,"end_time":364.7,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":361.459,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I haven''t gotten all of them in there, but, you know, I''ve narrowed it down to about 13,000 companies, which we''re definitely going to need a smaller subset to start once we get all of the parameters in there with retail focus.","index":94,"end_time":374.9,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":364.7,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"A few more than we came up with.","index":95,"end_time":377.04,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":375.76,"speaker_name":"David Willett"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":96,"end_time":377.6,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":377.12,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":97,"end_time":378.88,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":378.4,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"Well, Colin, so how many, like.","index":98,"end_time":380.8,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":379.2,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"You.","index":99,"end_time":383,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":382.72,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Know, like, should we.","index":100,"end_time":384.72,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":383,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"How big should our list be for, like, what we have, you know?","index":101,"end_time":387.96,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":384.8,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"So typically for these campaigns to start out, I like to have about 500 to 1500.","index":102,"end_time":392.24,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":387.96,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"A thousand kind of being the sweet spot, right?","index":103,"end_time":395.28,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":392.24,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Not contacts, correct.","index":104,"end_time":396.72,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":395.28,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"Well, kind of averaging out to like 1500 contacts or a thousand contacts.","index":105,"end_time":400.8,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":396.88,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we could have multiple people at these companies that we''re speaking to with different messaging because they''re going to be dealing with different pain points.","index":106,"end_time":408.01,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":401.85,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we can have, you know, speaking to a few different job titles at each of those companies.","index":107,"end_time":412.57,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":409.21,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":108,"end_time":414.25,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":413.69,"speaker_name":"David Willett"},{"text":"And so, David, the one thing I would say about the list that you came up with, I think it was good, but the only thing I was questioning was, so some of those groups, right, they focus on, like, everything, right?","index":109,"end_time":424.65,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":414.25,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"Like, CBRE management, right?","index":110,"end_time":427.21,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":424.65,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"So it''s like, do we want to focus on, like, the pure retail people, do you think?","index":111,"end_time":431.57,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":427.73,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"Or so, like, and Colin, to give you some background, right, so like, when I say institutional retail, that means, like, people buying, like, shopping centers, right.","index":112,"end_time":439.65,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":431.57,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"Malls, things like that.","index":113,"end_time":441.81,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":440.37,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"Whereas some of the really large investment managers, like, probably most of them, I guess, but like, they.","index":114,"end_time":447.33,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":442.21,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"They do, like, retail, but they also probably buy, like, apartments and office buildings and, like, they do everything.","index":115,"end_time":452.21,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":447.33,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"Right.","index":116,"end_time":452.61,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":452.21,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"But there are.","index":117,"end_time":453.82,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":453.18,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"But there are groups that just do retail, right?","index":118,"end_time":456.3,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":453.9,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"Like, like an example would be like, you know, Federal Realty or like, Simon Property Group, right?","index":119,"end_time":460.62,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":456.3,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"Like, they just do retail.","index":120,"end_time":462.06,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":460.62,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"So it''s like.","index":121,"end_time":463.1,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":462.38,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"But you think that, like, it''s like you''re.","index":122,"end_time":466.06,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":463.5,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"You''re trying to tailor your.","index":123,"end_time":467.1,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":466.06,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"Your.","index":124,"end_time":467.74,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":467.34,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"Your, you know, emails and marketing, right?","index":125,"end_time":471.66,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":467.74,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"And if our focus is asset class, should we make a list just pure retail people, you know?","index":126,"end_time":476.78,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":471.82,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"Yeah, I mean, I think.","index":127,"end_time":478.46,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":477.42,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I don''t think it necessarily has to be purely retail.","index":128,"end_time":482.18,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":479.54,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So the, the cool thing that we''re able to do with these emails is have personalization fields.","index":129,"end_time":486.5,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":482.18,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we could say like, we could even have like the start of the email be the same for everyone and then like the bullet points or something that we''re talking about be different based on their industry or sub industry or job title even.","index":130,"end_time":496.82,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":486.5,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":131,"end_time":499.54,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":499.06,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"And.","index":132,"end_time":499.86,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":499.54,"speaker_name":"David Willett"},{"text":"Okay.","index":133,"end_time":500.38,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":499.94,"speaker_name":"David Willett"},{"text":"And then within, I mean, how granular can you get?","index":134,"end_time":503.38,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":500.38,"speaker_name":"David Willett"},{"text":"To the extent that it''s, that the information''s available, but like let pick, you know, Blackstone.","index":135,"end_time":510.91,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":503.46,"speaker_name":"David Willett"},{"text":"Right.","index":136,"end_time":511.19,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":510.91,"speaker_name":"David Willett"},{"text":"They''ve, they''re gigantic.","index":137,"end_time":512.95,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":511.19,"speaker_name":"David Willett"},{"text":"But they''re, as Doug said, diversified across property types.","index":138,"end_time":516.31,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":513.03,"speaker_name":"David Willett"},{"text":"Can you drill down into say, their, you know, their retail vertical and find contacts within that specific subgroup, if you will.","index":139,"end_time":529.11,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":517.75,"speaker_name":"David Willett"},{"text":"So it would take some research to find them specifically.","index":140,"end_time":532.63,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":529.59,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I feel confident that we could, but it would basically be tying in some manual LinkedIn research with the list builders that we have and making sure that those match up.","index":141,"end_time":541.01,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":532.95,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Got it.","index":142,"end_time":542.13,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":541.49,"speaker_name":"David Willett"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":143,"end_time":542.85,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":542.53,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"And it''s hard, David, like, because it''s like, I mean there, it''s like managing director.","index":144,"end_time":548.93,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":542.85,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"Right.","index":145,"end_time":549.41,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":549.09,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"And then like how do you like dig into like what they''re actually like focusing on?","index":146,"end_time":552.89,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":549.41,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"You know what I mean?","index":147,"end_time":553.49,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":552.89,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"They might have a title, but they don''t usually.","index":148,"end_time":557.25,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":553.49,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"Right?","index":149,"end_time":557.81,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":557.41,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":150,"end_time":558.53,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":558.13,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"So if they don''t have a title or one thing we can even do is scrape their LinkedIn posts.","index":151,"end_time":563.09,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":558.53,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But if they don''t talk about it on LinkedIn, then we sort of start to run out of options if they haven''t put that information out there anywhere.","index":152,"end_time":569.16,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":563.09,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, so I, I think I, I.","index":153,"end_time":571.32,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":569.64,"speaker_name":"David Willett"},{"text":"Agree with you, Doug.","index":154,"end_time":572.04,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":571.32,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"Like the Pure Play retailers or retail focused investors.","index":155,"end_time":576.92,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":572.04,"speaker_name":"David Willett"},{"text":"And if we''re looking for 1500 contacts, you know, that''s gonna, that, that''s gonna take that top 100 grouping that we came up with, Doug, and really kind of change the profile.","index":156,"end_time":593.13,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":579.56,"speaker_name":"David Willett"},{"text":"It''s going to be, it''s going to be, you know, I mean, I think we''d have to look at like kind of the top 3,000 to the extent that, that there are groups that are, you know, 3,000 of them that are pure play retail investors that have scale that, that, that, that, that kind of meet our criteria.","index":157,"end_time":612.57,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":593.13,"speaker_name":"David Willett"},{"text":"But I mean, I think that''s probably more fruitful than, than targeting the allocators and diversify, you know, managers.","index":158,"end_time":619.92,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":612.57,"speaker_name":"David Willett"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":159,"end_time":620.16,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":619.92,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"So, and, and yeah, so I just want us to come up with the, the, the, the companies.","index":160,"end_time":626.6,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":620.16,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"Right.","index":161,"end_time":626.88,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":626.6,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"And then you guys can come up with the context.","index":162,"end_time":628.44,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":626.88,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"Right.","index":163,"end_time":629.08,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":628.68,"speaker_name":"David Willett"},{"text":"And then.","index":164,"end_time":630.84,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":630.28,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"Yeah, so I guess the list.","index":165,"end_time":633.48,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":632.04,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"So you said 500 is kind of like the sweet spot.","index":166,"end_time":635.4,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":633.48,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"Right.","index":167,"end_time":635.639,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":635.4,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"Because then your times 3 equals 1500 is what that you''re thinking.","index":168,"end_time":638.84,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":635.639,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":169,"end_time":639.2,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":638.84,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So like if, if we had between 500 and a thousand companies, we''d be in a really good spot.","index":170,"end_time":643,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":639.2,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":171,"end_time":644.6,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":643.96,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"All right, sounds good.","index":172,"end_time":646.54,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":645.86,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"And then because, and then David, a question for you.","index":173,"end_time":649.86,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":646.54,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"Right.","index":174,"end_time":650.22,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":649.86,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"Is like, you know, I want to go after big companies.","index":175,"end_time":653.42,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":650.22,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"That''s like the reason I hire these, you know, groups.","index":176,"end_time":655.42,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":653.42,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"Right.","index":177,"end_time":655.7,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":655.42,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"This group, you know, I mean we can go over like the medium and all that.","index":178,"end_time":658.34,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":655.7,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"Like anyone, you know, wins a win.","index":179,"end_time":659.86,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":658.34,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"Right.","index":180,"end_time":660.26,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":659.86,"speaker_name":"David Willett"},{"text":"But the thing is that was kind of the goal and you know, for these really big companies.","index":181,"end_time":667.22,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":660.5,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"Right.","index":182,"end_time":667.7,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":667.3,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"Like even like Federal Realty, we''ve.","index":183,"end_time":670.42,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":667.7,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"Who I''ve actually spoken to a little bit.","index":184,"end_time":671.86,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":670.42,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"But it''s like.","index":185,"end_time":672.54,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":671.94,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"Or like Simon Property Group or something.","index":186,"end_time":674.66,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":672.54,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"What, what does like your intuition say, like who you would sell to right.","index":187,"end_time":677.63,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":675.07,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"Within the company?","index":188,"end_time":678.27,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":677.63,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"Because I have mixed, you know, I''ll just give you like two case studies.","index":189,"end_time":682.71,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":678.75,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"Right.","index":190,"end_time":682.99,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":682.71,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"Like we got hired by lasalle, the management fund.","index":191,"end_time":685.99,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":683.07,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"Right.","index":192,"end_time":686.27,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":685.99,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"At one point and that was just like I just email blessed.","index":193,"end_time":689.19,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":686.27,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"The CEO got super lucky and it led to it.","index":194,"end_time":691.27,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":689.19,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"Right, right.","index":195,"end_time":692.27,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":691.27,"speaker_name":"David Willett"},{"text":"That''s a Green Oak was like way more of like a. I don''t know, like somebody who handles vendors.","index":196,"end_time":698.71,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":692.27,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"I don''t even know like what the title would be.","index":197,"end_time":700.11,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":698.71,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"Right, yeah.","index":198,"end_time":700.71,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":700.11,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"Type of thing.","index":199,"end_time":701.31,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":700.71,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"And it kind of went through that chain.","index":200,"end_time":703.47,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":701.71,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"Right.","index":201,"end_time":703.87,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":703.47,"speaker_name":"David Willett"},{"text":"So what''s your thoughts?","index":202,"end_time":705.71,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":704.03,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"I mean, bad answer.","index":203,"end_time":709.79,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":706.35,"speaker_name":"David Willett"},{"text":"But it''s going to depend on each company''s individual structure.","index":204,"end_time":714.11,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":709.79,"speaker_name":"David Willett"},{"text":"The involvement level of.","index":205,"end_time":716.03,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":714.51,"speaker_name":"David Willett"},{"text":"Call it a CFO or coo.","index":206,"end_time":718.35,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":716.35,"speaker_name":"David Willett"},{"text":"There may be a group that''s focused on vendor procurement.","index":207,"end_time":721.87,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":719.15,"speaker_name":"David Willett"},{"text":"Procurement, yeah.","index":208,"end_time":723.71,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":722.67,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":209,"end_time":724.11,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":723.71,"speaker_name":"David Willett"},{"text":"I mean it could really vary from group to group.","index":210,"end_time":728.03,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":724.11,"speaker_name":"David Willett"},{"text":"I mean LaSalle and Benthol Green Oak are a perfect example.","index":211,"end_time":732.57,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":728.41,"speaker_name":"David Willett"},{"text":"And juxtaposing like a very different process in terms of who gets involved.","index":212,"end_time":738.81,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":732.57,"speaker_name":"David Willett"},{"text":"You do have some very in the weeds micromanaging senior execs at some of these firms.","index":213,"end_time":746.97,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":739.13,"speaker_name":"David Willett"},{"text":"And then you also have others that are built out with clear bureaucratic infrastructure where maybe not even asset management handle would handle that.","index":214,"end_time":756.85,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":747.21,"speaker_name":"David Willett"},{"text":"It would be under portfolio management or something of that nature.","index":215,"end_time":760.73,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":756.85,"speaker_name":"David Willett"},{"text":"So there''s no clear cut way other than, I mean at the, at the end of the day probably that the most effective or the highest likelihood is probably going to be a decision maker on the financial side.","index":216,"end_time":778.65,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":760.73,"speaker_name":"David Willett"},{"text":"Right.","index":217,"end_time":778.89,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":778.65,"speaker_name":"David Willett"},{"text":"To the spend dollars.","index":218,"end_time":780.21,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":778.89,"speaker_name":"David Willett"},{"text":"And that''s either going to be someone that''s going to be someone in the CFO chain, either someone who reports to the cfo, someone who''s the head of asset management, you know, from a.","index":219,"end_time":792.95,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":780.21,"speaker_name":"David Willett"},{"text":"Or I mean some, some groups qualify you know, characterize property management as, as, you know, maintaining leases as well.","index":220,"end_time":800.55,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":792.95,"speaker_name":"David Willett"},{"text":"So I think we''re going to have to kind of like, play around with.","index":221,"end_time":805.87,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":803.51,"speaker_name":"David Willett"},{"text":"It a little to figure out, but.","index":222,"end_time":807.71,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":805.87,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"We could probably take a few dozen test cases and, you know, of a certain mag, like certain scale and come up with a couple different routes.","index":223,"end_time":817.83,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":807.71,"speaker_name":"David Willett"},{"text":"Yeah, and there''s, there''s a few things to keep in mind there too.","index":224,"end_time":820.15,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":817.99,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So often what we find.","index":225,"end_time":821.63,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":820.23,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And Doug, you kind of even just alluded to it like you emailed this guy a bunch and kind of got lucky that you broke through.","index":226,"end_time":826.23,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":821.63,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"What we find is that C suite.","index":227,"end_time":828.55,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":827.029,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We want to be in their inbox.","index":228,"end_time":830.15,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":828.55,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"They''re often not checking, you know, as much as their, their staff.","index":229,"end_time":834.39,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":830.15,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So what we want to do is be able to give someone on their staff who is dealing with the pain point the information, maybe a downloadable piece of content or some sort of next step that they can take and really look good to their boss.","index":230,"end_time":845.86,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":834.63,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So the way that we kind of position this is almost making that person the hero at their company by saying, well, we should work with Gallagher Mohan.","index":231,"end_time":852.82,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":846.58,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, absolutely.","index":232,"end_time":854.1,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":852.98,"speaker_name":"David Willett"},{"text":"I couldn''t agree more.","index":233,"end_time":855.38,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":854.34,"speaker_name":"David Willett"},{"text":"That''s, that''s how you sell into, you know, corporations where you''re, you''re basically reducing their costs because you get a champion internally that can, that can be the hero in their, in their boss''s eyes.","index":234,"end_time":868.66,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":855.38,"speaker_name":"David Willett"},{"text":"Yeah, exactly.","index":235,"end_time":870.14,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":868.66,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"I did read a book one time called how to Sell to the Fortune 500 and it was all about like running through the procurement system.","index":236,"end_time":878.3,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":870.54,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"So, yeah, that''s about it.","index":237,"end_time":881.22,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":878.86,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"That''s all I picked up on it.","index":238,"end_time":882.46,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":881.22,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"And so, yeah, I mean, obviously you send us over any companies or anything even just running.","index":239,"end_time":888.38,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":883.9,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So one feature that we have access to is a lookalike audience as well.","index":240,"end_time":892.02,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":889.02,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So I just put in one of the brands that you mentioned was Federal Realty.","index":241,"end_time":896.1,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":892.02,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And so right now it''s scraped almost 2,000 companies that have similar characteristics to that and then we can filter down from there.","index":242,"end_time":903.7,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":896.18,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, the costar will be huge with this too, so we''ll dive into that later.","index":243,"end_time":908.82,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":904.82,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"But their database is really good.","index":244,"end_time":911.86,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":908.82,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"So.","index":245,"end_time":912.18,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":911.94,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"Yeah, Colin, it''s one thing we have a subscription to the super expensive private real estate focused database and they have a lot of lists that we could tie into as well.","index":246,"end_time":923.46,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":912.18,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"Perfect.","index":247,"end_time":924.04,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":923.8,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, that''s great.","index":248,"end_time":924.68,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":924.04,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":249,"end_time":925.08,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":924.68,"speaker_name":"David Willett"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":250,"end_time":928.16,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":927.64,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":251,"end_time":928.56,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":928.16,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"Wait.","index":252,"end_time":928.76,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":928.56,"speaker_name":"David Willett"},{"text":"Yeah, so, Colin, another thing too is like that, that list that you gave me.","index":253,"end_time":932.16,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":928.76,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"Right.","index":254,"end_time":932.44,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":932.16,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"I handed it off to somebody in my company.","index":255,"end_time":934.12,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":932.44,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"Did they fill out everything?","index":256,"end_time":935.72,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":934.52,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"Yeah, the, the questions that we needed, let me.","index":257,"end_time":939.24,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":937,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Or the asset intake.","index":258,"end_time":940.8,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":939.64,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I''ll check everything and send You.","index":259,"end_time":942.84,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":940.8,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I''ve just been out the last couple days, so I gotta check up on that.","index":260,"end_time":946.08,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":943.08,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But I''ll send you an email today to make sure we''re all set.","index":261,"end_time":948.04,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":946.08,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":262,"end_time":949.24,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":948.68,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"Cool.","index":263,"end_time":954.49,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":954.17,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then one thing I did want to talk through was we often have one or two like core offers in our communication.","index":264,"end_time":961.77,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":954.65,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You know, this could be like a cost analysis of things that they''re currently operating with or back office capacity assessments, something that feels kind of tangible or that gives these people a proof of value before they work with you.","index":265,"end_time":975.53,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":962.89,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"One thing that we found kind of across the market is people are much more protective of their time.","index":266,"end_time":980.65,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":976.01,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"They don''t even want to hop on like a 15 minute discovery call unless they''ve made up almost like 75% of their decision.","index":267,"end_time":986.55,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":980.65,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"The way that we can sort of push that along is by giving them something tangible or some, some sort of leave behind that they can even talk to their employers about.","index":268,"end_time":996.07,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":987.43,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So I wanted to have that kind of conversation and it may need to wait until you guys get back with this company list and we''re, we''re kind of set there.","index":269,"end_time":1002.79,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":996.47,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":270,"end_time":1004.27,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1003.75,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"I mean, David, that might be kind of like you talked about that one pager the other day.","index":271,"end_time":1007.43,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1004.27,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah, I think, I think a one pager.","index":272,"end_time":1009.46,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1007.74,"speaker_name":"David Willett"},{"text":"But I think instead of offering like a product or service that will, you know, make them better.","index":273,"end_time":1018.06,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1009.46,"speaker_name":"David Willett"},{"text":"I mean, yes, that''s what we''re, we''re pitching, but I think the proof can be in the pudding with respect to cost savings and because I, Colin, I agree, like it''s a show me business.","index":274,"end_time":1034.18,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1018.38,"speaker_name":"David Willett"},{"text":"Right.","index":275,"end_time":1034.66,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1034.26,"speaker_name":"David Willett"},{"text":"People want to, people want to see the results that they''re going to get before they actually sign up to do it.","index":276,"end_time":1039.54,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1034.82,"speaker_name":"David Willett"},{"text":"Yep.","index":277,"end_time":1040.1,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1039.54,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"However, I think there''s something about human nature that, that, that, that get, that resistance gets lowered a little when there''s proof of concept of an actual dollar or like percentage savings.","index":278,"end_time":1054.1,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1041.3,"speaker_name":"David Willett"},{"text":"Yep.","index":279,"end_time":1054.74,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1054.18,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"And so maybe we can tailor instead of, instead of a, a free look into our service that we would offer you or free analysis, it would be more of like, you know, this is, this is our average save rate on a, you know, what, whatever particular service we''re providing and offering to folks that could, that, that may have a little more weight.","index":280,"end_time":1079.35,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1055.06,"speaker_name":"David Willett"},{"text":"Yeah, that could be cool.","index":281,"end_time":1080.39,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1079.35,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And we could even build like a calculator where it could tie in like your averages and say like, you know, obviously this isn''t a guarantee, but this is know, anecdotal data to point to what the results could be.","index":282,"end_time":1091.56,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1080.39,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That''s a great idea.","index":283,"end_time":1093.04,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1092.12,"speaker_name":"David Willett"},{"text":"So, so if it''s a controller or someone on, you know, who''s running?","index":284,"end_time":1099.24,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1093.04,"speaker_name":"David Willett"},{"text":"If we''re saying lease admin, a lease admin team, and they''ve got five people, they know how much they pay them.","index":285,"end_time":1104.92,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1099.32,"speaker_name":"David Willett"},{"text":"And if we put in like our average cost of FTE they can do, they could quickly calculate the savings.","index":286,"end_time":1113,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1105.08,"speaker_name":"David Willett"},{"text":"Yeah, we could even get.","index":287,"end_time":1114.52,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1113.64,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"And we know the basic metrics.","index":288,"end_time":1116.25,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1114.81,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"Right.","index":289,"end_time":1116.53,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1116.25,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"Like how people think about it.","index":290,"end_time":1118.21,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1116.53,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"Like property counties.","index":291,"end_time":1119.13,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1118.21,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"They think about it per.","index":292,"end_time":1119.97,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1119.13,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"Count it.","index":293,"end_time":1120.37,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1119.97,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"Right.","index":294,"end_time":1120.57,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1120.37,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"Or sorry, per property.","index":295,"end_time":1121.57,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1120.57,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"Right.","index":296,"end_time":1121.93,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1121.57,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"Or per lease.","index":297,"end_time":1126.37,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1124.73,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"I don''t know, like how people think about that.","index":298,"end_time":1128.01,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1126.37,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"Per building, maybe.","index":299,"end_time":1130.37,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1129.13,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"I don''t know.","index":300,"end_time":1130.969,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1130.37,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"You can figure that out, but maybe even put a little bit more detail into the.","index":301,"end_time":1135.77,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1131.13,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"Rather than just like body for body.","index":302,"end_time":1137.93,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1135.77,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"But that''d be the easiest way, obviously.","index":303,"end_time":1139.69,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1137.93,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"But.","index":304,"end_time":1140.56,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1140.32,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"And so this calculator, where would it sit, like, would be like online, like.","index":305,"end_time":1144.96,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1141.92,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"Yeah, on the website.","index":306,"end_time":1146,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1144.96,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"On the website, yeah.","index":307,"end_time":1147.76,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1146.56,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"And it''s something that.","index":308,"end_time":1148.48,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1147.76,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So I know you have your own team, so if they wouldn''t be comfortable developing it, we could develop all the code and pass it over to them to publish on the site.","index":309,"end_time":1154.8,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1148.48,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":310,"end_time":1157.12,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1156.48,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"Yeah, I mean, we could.","index":311,"end_time":1160.08,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1158.88,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"That''s probably the best to save time, you know, like, type of thing.","index":312,"end_time":1163.36,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1160.88,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"David, we.","index":313,"end_time":1164.24,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1163.68,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"Like, that''d be kind of interesting, actually, if we made like a little like.","index":314,"end_time":1166.8,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1164.24,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"Like a cal.","index":315,"end_time":1167.72,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1167.12,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"Like a calculator.","index":316,"end_time":1168.44,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1167.72,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"That''s a little bit, you know, more, you know, it.","index":317,"end_time":1171.99,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1168.44,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"Let''s like.","index":318,"end_time":1172.51,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1171.99,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"I think we should try to think about how to put a little more thought into it beyond just like, you know, our first.","index":319,"end_time":1176.67,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1172.51,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"This is 40 hours.","index":320,"end_time":1177.55,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1176.67,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"Our person.","index":321,"end_time":1178.27,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1177.63,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"This is 40 hours.","index":322,"end_time":1178.99,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1178.27,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"Your person.","index":323,"end_time":1179.51,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1178.99,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"Like subtract the math, you know.","index":324,"end_time":1181.79,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1179.51,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"Yeah, but it.","index":325,"end_time":1182.67,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1181.95,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"But that, I mean, that is the number one calculation, I guess.","index":326,"end_time":1187.47,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1182.67,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"But it''s.","index":327,"end_time":1187.91,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1187.47,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"And maybe there''s multiple functions to it, you know.","index":328,"end_time":1189.71,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1187.91,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":329,"end_time":1191.07,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1190.59,"speaker_name":"David Willett"},{"text":"Do you have Khan.","index":330,"end_time":1193.15,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1191.95,"speaker_name":"David Willett"},{"text":"Do you have a.","index":331,"end_time":1194.43,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1193.39,"speaker_name":"David Willett"},{"text":"Maybe a set of best practices that other clients of yours have used or that.","index":332,"end_time":1205.36,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1196.56,"speaker_name":"David Willett"},{"text":"That you guys have found that are.","index":333,"end_time":1208,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1205.36,"speaker_name":"David Willett"},{"text":"That are quite effective in these types of campaigns that we may not even be thinking of that.","index":334,"end_time":1216.8,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1209.52,"speaker_name":"David Willett"},{"text":"Yeah, you brought up the calculator.","index":335,"end_time":1218.6,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1216.8,"speaker_name":"David Willett"},{"text":"Like, that''s not something I would have thought of off the top of my head.","index":336,"end_time":1221.2,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1218.6,"speaker_name":"David Willett"},{"text":"But are there other, you know, effective means that you''ve used in the past or seen successful that that might want to explore too?","index":337,"end_time":1230.72,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1221.68,"speaker_name":"David Willett"},{"text":"Yeah, it varies widely from.","index":338,"end_time":1232.52,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1230.88,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"From industry to injuries industry, as you can imagine.","index":339,"end_time":1234.92,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1232.52,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But one thing to kind of boil it down is it''s almost like a calculator with a PDF, downloadable.","index":340,"end_time":1241.68,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1234.92,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So someone goes in, they fill out a few questions about their company.","index":341,"end_time":1245.68,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1242.08,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And we have, you know, for.","index":342,"end_time":1248.69,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1247.21,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"For one example, one of my clients, they develop their Own like industry benchmark.","index":343,"end_time":1252.45,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1248.69,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So it''s like they work with a bunch of companies in a bunch of different industries.","index":344,"end_time":1255.21,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1252.45,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Here''s their anecdotal data and if you fill out a couple of questions, they''ll tell you whether you''re below average, average or above average and really push you towards a sales call.","index":345,"end_time":1263.77,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1255.61,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It automatically updates all the information in this PDF download, puts their company name in there, the answers to their questions, and where like all of the calculations landed, and then gives them a direct sales call to the sales rep that their territory is.","index":346,"end_time":1278.57,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1263.93,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So one thing that we have found is like something they can interact with and also almost like download or just have like an easy takeaway.","index":347,"end_time":1287.27,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1279.51,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, yeah, that''s helpful.","index":348,"end_time":1291.59,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1289.19,"speaker_name":"David Willett"},{"text":"I mean the calculator is kind of like an interactive tool.","index":349,"end_time":1294.23,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1291.59,"speaker_name":"David Willett"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":350,"end_time":1294.71,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1294.23,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And maybe it''s the calculator and like the results are just something they can easily download as a PDF and send to their boss, you know?","index":351,"end_time":1301.03,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1295.03,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah.","index":352,"end_time":1302.15,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1301.03,"speaker_name":"David Willett"},{"text":"And Doug, maybe we can actually.","index":353,"end_time":1304.15,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1302.63,"speaker_name":"David Willett"},{"text":"Think.","index":354,"end_time":1306.01,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1305.89,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"About it in a couple different metrics.","index":355,"end_time":1307.89,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1306.01,"speaker_name":"David Willett"},{"text":"Whether it''s number of property accountants or it''s number of properties, or it''s square footage.","index":356,"end_time":1313.89,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1307.89,"speaker_name":"David Willett"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":357,"end_time":1315.53,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1315.09,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"And they can, it''s a drop down menu and they can choose which metric they want to use.","index":358,"end_time":1319.17,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1315.53,"speaker_name":"David Willett"},{"text":"It actually does like do the baselines of report.","index":359,"end_time":1323.01,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1320.53,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"I mean that was kind of like my like idea.","index":360,"end_time":1327.17,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1324.53,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"Not like idea.","index":361,"end_time":1327.93,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1327.17,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"I mean like what I was thinking about when I was like growth team stuff.","index":362,"end_time":1331.25,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1327.93,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"It''s like, how do you calculate, like come up with a report?","index":363,"end_time":1333.09,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1331.25,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"It''s called a scalability report.","index":364,"end_time":1334.53,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1333.09,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"So that could be useful for us in general.","index":365,"end_time":1337.74,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1335.18,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"You know what I mean?","index":366,"end_time":1338.46,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1337.74,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"Yeah, we''re like, hey, listen, how are we going to approach Oregon companies?","index":367,"end_time":1342.86,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1338.46,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"Right?","index":368,"end_time":1343.58,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1343.18,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"Give them some sort of metric per person, blah, blah, blah, come with a report.","index":369,"end_time":1348.18,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1343.9,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"We''d have to tailor it up a little bit more, I''m sure, or whatever.","index":370,"end_time":1350.5,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1348.18,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"But anyways.","index":371,"end_time":1351.1,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1350.5,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":372,"end_time":1351.54,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1351.1,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"So I think it could be good.","index":373,"end_time":1352.94,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1351.54,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":374,"end_time":1354.3,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1353.82,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"The way to think about this too is it''s not only even like the people that were doing outreach to you directly, but if you find yourself on a phone call, be like, hey, yeah, go to our website and like hit this button real quick and start messing with the calculator.","index":375,"end_time":1365.13,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1354.38,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And you can see directly like how working with us would translate.","index":376,"end_time":1368.65,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1365.13,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, no, that''s.","index":377,"end_time":1372.13,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1371.05,"speaker_name":"David Willett"},{"text":"That, that could be very valuable.","index":378,"end_time":1373.61,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1372.13,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":379,"end_time":1375.69,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1375.05,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, so you guys will work on that list of companies then and send that over to us and then we''ll, we''ll build out the contact list from there.","index":380,"end_time":1384.33,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1376.97,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, awesome.","index":381,"end_time":1386.57,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1385.13,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"So we should try to give you that list this week.","index":382,"end_time":1388.17,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1386.57,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"I guess that would Be great because we are writing the ABM plan document that I''ll outline basically everything that''s going on in this, this week.","index":383,"end_time":1395.59,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1388.17,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right.","index":384,"end_time":1397.99,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1397.51,"speaker_name":"David Willett"},{"text":"Okay, awesome.","index":385,"end_time":1398.87,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1397.99,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"Great.","index":386,"end_time":1399.19,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1398.87,"speaker_name":"David Willett"},{"text":"And then, Doug, the only other thing I wanted to touch on, you were still kind of figuring out, but as far as setting up the, the content series for Gallagher and Mohan, there''s several different ways that we can approach it.","index":387,"end_time":1410.99,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1399.19,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We can just hold interviews and, and produce assets where we''re not on screen at all.","index":388,"end_time":1415.23,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1410.99,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You can be a host, you can rotate hosts, but it would just be something that we found to be a really strong source of content.","index":389,"end_time":1422.82,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1415.23,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So basically you have one 30 minute conversation.","index":390,"end_time":1425.02,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1422.9,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"From that we''re able to get four blog posts, 10 social media posts, a white paper, a video maybe, you know, all sorts of things.","index":391,"end_time":1433.14,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1425.02,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Have you put any more thought into who would run that or how that would go?","index":392,"end_time":1436.66,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1433.62,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"No, I haven''t thought about it at all, to be honest.","index":393,"end_time":1440.18,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1438.42,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"Yeah, no problem.","index":394,"end_time":1440.98,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1440.26,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I''m pretty like jam packed right now.","index":395,"end_time":1442.9,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1440.98,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"Like, I don''t know, it''s like really easy.","index":396,"end_time":1444.54,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1442.9,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"Like, it''s.","index":397,"end_time":1445.22,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1444.54,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"I don''t know, but we could think about that.","index":398,"end_time":1448.96,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1446.26,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"So do you believe in like, I mean, here''s like my point of view with like the LinkedIn, like people, you know, for the most part it''s like sometimes it''s good and sometimes they like piss me off too.","index":399,"end_time":1458,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1449.04,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"Like, if I''m being honest, you know.","index":400,"end_time":1460.64,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1458,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"It''S like I''m like, I share that sentiment, Doug.","index":401,"end_time":1464.2,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1460.72,"speaker_name":"David Willett"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah, yeah, it is.","index":402,"end_time":1466.48,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1464.2,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"It is certainly kind of a mixed bag as to how people respond to that.","index":403,"end_time":1470.64,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1466.64,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I think it''s actually even more about like how was their day going that.","index":404,"end_time":1474.04,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1470.88,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Day.","index":405,"end_time":1474.32,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1474.04,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"To how they react to it, but I''m thinking even more just on the content side.","index":406,"end_time":1480.12,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1476.52,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So this would be something we would syndicate across all social medias.","index":407,"end_time":1482.84,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1480.12,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Like a conversation that you had with a prospect or a current customer or even someone else on your, your sales team or your, your back end tools team that really just talks about why this is such a positive movement in the industry and how you''re able to really provide best results.","index":408,"end_time":1497,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1483.16,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So more like classic marketing kind of thing?","index":409,"end_time":1499.48,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1497.4,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah, it''s, it''s really just to.","index":410,"end_time":1501.56,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1499.64,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"The way that it''s easiest to understand is you have a 20 to 30 minute conversation that''s only taking 20 to 30 minutes of your time.","index":411,"end_time":1509.5,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1502.86,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Out of that, we are getting a month''s worth of blog posts, a month''s worth of social media, like all of this stuff that we can blast all over the Internet, point to in our emails, point to in our ads, things like that, okay.","index":412,"end_time":1522.06,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1509.66,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Certainly seems efficient from a leveraging the 30 minutes.","index":413,"end_time":1526.82,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1523.26,"speaker_name":"David Willett"},{"text":"But yeah.","index":414,"end_time":1527.5,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1526.82,"speaker_name":"David Willett"},{"text":"Yeah, I think it''s like, I mean, let me think about it more.","index":415,"end_time":1532.59,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1529.39,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"But I think if it was not like person centric, it''s kind of like, you know, like.","index":416,"end_time":1535.95,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1532.59,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"Or like we mix it up, right.","index":417,"end_time":1537.27,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1536.03,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"Like me, it could be David and they could be like, you know, one of our managers in India.","index":418,"end_time":1541.23,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1537.27,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"Right.","index":419,"end_time":1541.59,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1541.31,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"Or something like that and like, you know, kind of go from there then, you know, I mean if you guys think this, I think that.","index":420,"end_time":1548.31,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1541.59,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"Yeah, I think that''d be great.","index":421,"end_time":1549.39,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1548.31,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I think going into it with like too strict of rules is often a limiting factor that will lead to like, all right, by episode four you''re burnt out and you don''t want to do it anymore because you have way too other many things to focus on.","index":422,"end_time":1561.09,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1549.47,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But if we go in and we''re like we''re going to do this content series, it''s kind of, kind of rotate who''s leading it.","index":423,"end_time":1565.97,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1561.49,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But we always know like what we''d like to talk about.","index":424,"end_time":1568.77,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1566.37,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That''s the best way to set it up, in my opinion.","index":425,"end_time":1570.93,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1568.93,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, but how does it work with like, you know, like my like grainy computer, like video and you know, stuff like that?","index":426,"end_time":1579.81,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1572.37,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"Like how does that work?","index":427,"end_time":1580.57,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1579.81,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"So we do have like a recommended equipment list we set up.","index":428,"end_time":1583.69,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1580.57,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We''re partners with Riverside, which is a podcast recording platform.","index":429,"end_time":1587.17,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1583.69,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we get you guys set up on there for a heavy discount and it would basically work like this zoom call.","index":430,"end_time":1592.75,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1587.63,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So you wouldn''t even need to upgrade equipment if you wouldn''t, if you didn''t want to.","index":431,"end_time":1596.31,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1593.31,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We could send you recommendations but basically it''s a better zoom.","index":432,"end_time":1600.59,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1596.31,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So it would record, say you''re meeting with, with David right now.","index":433,"end_time":1603.469,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1600.59,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It would record you both separately.","index":434,"end_time":1604.71,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1603.469,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So there''s no lag and video feed or connection or anything.","index":435,"end_time":1607.95,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1604.71,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then we''re able to extract those files, develop a transcript, show notes and then we create multiple short form videos, things like that.","index":436,"end_time":1615.46,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1608.27,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Got it.","index":437,"end_time":1619.37,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1618.89,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"Okay.","index":438,"end_time":1620.01,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1619.37,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"Is that an add on service?","index":439,"end_time":1622.69,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1621.37,"speaker_name":"David Willett"},{"text":"Is that part of the package?","index":440,"end_time":1624.09,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1622.69,"speaker_name":"David Willett"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":441,"end_time":1625.33,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1624.97,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So everything we do is through points.","index":442,"end_time":1626.65,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1625.33,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So you guys pay a certain amount that leads to a certain amount of points that you get each month and we''re able to be flexible with those.","index":443,"end_time":1633.93,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1626.89,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That''s why we like the points model because it''s like a fixed cost.","index":444,"end_time":1637.13,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1633.93,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So essentially if you asked us to build a web page, we ran into like six hours of issues in the backend builder.","index":445,"end_time":1643.13,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1637.21,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We''re not charging you for those six hours of issues you ran into.","index":446,"end_time":1645.74,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1643.46,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It was the original price that you agreed to.","index":447,"end_time":1647.7,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1645.74,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, got it got it.","index":448,"end_time":1650.54,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1648.02,"speaker_name":"David Willett"},{"text":"Good to know.","index":449,"end_time":1651.14,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1650.54,"speaker_name":"David Willett"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":450,"end_time":1652.02,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1651.46,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right, so just with two minutes left, locking up.","index":451,"end_time":1654.94,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1652.34,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Next step.","index":452,"end_time":1655.3,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1654.94,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So you guys are going to send over a company list.","index":453,"end_time":1656.9,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1655.3,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Then we''re going to finalize the ABM plan and build a contact list from that.","index":454,"end_time":1660.26,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1656.9,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I''ll also check the asset intake and then we will start to move forward with some branding and design and name ideas for the content series.","index":455,"end_time":1668.18,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1661.22,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":456,"end_time":1670.11,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1669.71,"speaker_name":"David Willett"},{"text":"And I see that you guys use Fireflies.","index":457,"end_time":1672.75,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1670.83,"speaker_name":"David Willett"},{"text":"How do you like it?","index":458,"end_time":1673.55,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1672.75,"speaker_name":"David Willett"},{"text":"We use it a lot.","index":459,"end_time":1675.39,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1674.59,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we actually have this built to do a bunch of automation workflows.","index":460,"end_time":1678.19,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1675.39,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So when I leave this call, it''s going to go into a database, do a sentiment analysis and make sure that all next steps are understood.","index":461,"end_time":1685.11,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1678.19,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then even at a leadership level we''re able to say like, oh, this call was good, this call maybe needs a review or that call was bad, we need to hop in.","index":462,"end_time":1691.55,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1685.11,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We''re testing out different, different platforms.","index":463,"end_time":1695.57,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1692.99,"speaker_name":"David Willett"},{"text":"Does it, does it send you a transcript and like summary and next steps?","index":464,"end_time":1699.97,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1696.05,"speaker_name":"David Willett"},{"text":"It does, yeah.","index":465,"end_time":1701.09,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1699.97,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Would you be so kind as to.","index":466,"end_time":1703.13,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1701.41,"speaker_name":"David Willett"},{"text":"Share that with us so that.","index":467,"end_time":1704.09,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1703.13,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"Oh yeah, yeah.","index":468,"end_time":1704.81,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1704.09,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Take a look at it.","index":469,"end_time":1705.57,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1704.81,"speaker_name":"David Willett"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":470,"end_time":1706.13,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1705.65,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"Great.","index":471,"end_time":1706.53,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1706.13,"speaker_name":"David Willett"},{"text":"All right.","index":472,"end_time":1708.93,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1708.37,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Anything else from your guys end?","index":473,"end_time":1710.29,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1709.09,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Not really.","index":474,"end_time":1715.17,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1714.61,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"I mean the only thing I''d say is like when it comes to like the social media or the content campaign, I mean like how critical is that to everything we''re doing, do you think?","index":475,"end_time":1723.72,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1715.17,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"Like, because like if we could use our points elsewhere we might be interested too, you know, like, yeah, just like right now, you know, so it''s, it.","index":476,"end_time":1730.72,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1723.72,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"Really serves more of a brand awareness proponent.","index":477,"end_time":1733.68,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1730.72,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Also like whenever you get someone on the, you know, as a guest to interview or something like that, you are able to tap into their network because you''re sharing it with them on LinkedIn, they''re reposting it.","index":478,"end_time":1742.52,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1733.68,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"XYZ.","index":479,"end_time":1743.24,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1742.52,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we think of it as kind of like if you''re thinking about the marketing funnel, it is operating mainly at the top as an awareness based campaign and really just boosting the Galga and Mohan name versus the ABM is the complete opposite side of the funnel where we''re identifying exactly who we want to talk to and how we want to talk to them.","index":480,"end_time":1760.29,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1744.04,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, you may have already provided this to Doug, but for my benefit, do you have like a menu of services and like the points attached to each?","index":481,"end_time":1772.53,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1763.969,"speaker_name":"David Willett"},{"text":"Marketers in demand.","index":482,"end_time":1774.61,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1773.33,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Points.","index":483,"end_time":1777.22,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1776.98,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"Okay, awesome.","index":484,"end_time":1779.3,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1777.94,"speaker_name":"David Willett"},{"text":"Yeah, that''s our full menu of.","index":485,"end_time":1781.78,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1780.34,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And.","index":486,"end_time":1782.34,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1782.02,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And we can do custom work, you know, beyond that as well.","index":487,"end_time":1785.22,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1782.34,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Right.","index":488,"end_time":1786.34,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1785.94,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":489,"end_time":1788.82,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1788.34,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right, I do have to jump to another meeting.","index":490,"end_time":1790.34,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1788.82,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Great.","index":491,"end_time":1791.139,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1790.82,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Connected with you guys.","index":492,"end_time":1791.94,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1791.139,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"If anything else pops up, please do, Just send me an email.","index":493,"end_time":1794.02,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1791.94,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I''ll respond right away, but we''ll move forward with the.","index":494,"end_time":1796.54,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1794.02,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"The steps that we outlined.","index":495,"end_time":1797.62,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1796.54,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Sounds good.","index":496,"end_time":1799.5,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1798.98,"speaker_name":"David Willett"},{"text":"Sounds good.","index":497,"end_time":1800.1,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1799.5,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":498,"end_time":1800.66,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1800.18,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right, thanks.","index":499,"end_time":1801.3,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1800.66,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Thanks.","index":500,"end_time":1801.74,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1801.38,"speaker_name":"David Willett"},{"text":"Great to meet you, David.","index":501,"end_time":1802.74,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1801.74,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Likewise.","index":502,"end_time":1803.54,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1802.82,"speaker_name":"David Willett"},{"text":"Thanks.","index":503,"end_time":1804.09,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1803.7,"speaker_name":"David Willett"}],"dateString":"2026-01-12T18:00:00.000Z","host_email":"colin.costigan@marketersindemand.com","meeting_link":"https://us02web.zoom.us/j/83518678110?pwd=MiWMBPC8T7FkFpRVsa3mZByA9Y76FA.1","participants":["nathalie.mintjens@marketersindemand.com,colin.costigan@marketersindemand.com,dougg@gallaghermohan.com,dwillett@gallaghermohan.com","nathalie.mintjens@marketersindemand.com","dougg@gallaghermohan.com","dwillett@gallaghermohan.com"],"transcript_url":"https://app.fireflies.ai/view/01KE7TXRGCJPBZB1RBX6YR24GY","organizer_email":"colin.costigan@marketersindemand.com"}'::jsonb,
    '{"label":"positive","confidence":0.91,"bullets":["Defined campaign scope shift to institutional retail-focused firms; ABM list to be refined accordingly.","Agreed to deliver prioritized prospect company list this week to populate 1,500 contact ABM target.","Explored using cost calculator tool on website to quantify value proposition with real savings data.","Discussed multi-channel content series strategy; Doug suggested shared hosting to limit workload.","Fireflies.ai recorded meeting and will provide automated transcript, sentiment, and action summaries."],"highlights":[{"quote":"People want to see the results that they''re going to get before they actually sign up.","speaker":"David Willett"},{"quote":"One 30 minute conversation...we are getting a month''s worth of blog posts and content.","speaker":"Colin Costigan"},{"quote":"We should try to give you that list this week.","speaker":"Doug"}],"topics":["ABM","content","tools","targeting"],"model":"openai/gpt-4-1106-preview","version":1,"generated_at":"2026-01-12T00:00:00Z"}'::jsonb,
    '{"fireflies_summary":{"notes":"## **Account-Based Marketing (ABM) Strategy and Targeting**\n\nThe team is finalizing a detailed ABM plan focusing on institutional retail-oriented real estate companies to target precise contacts for personalized outreach.\n\n- **Colin Costigan confirmed** they are writing a **50-page ABM plan this week** detailing email sources, content types, channels, and user journeys to engage prospects for **Gallagher and Mohan** (01:50).  \n    - The ABM approach uses email, LinkedIn outreach, ads, and landing pages to control the full customer journey.  \n    - Data sourcing is from **Clay**, aggregating Apollo, ZoomInfo, LinkedIn, and other platforms to build targeted lists.  \n    - The campaign targets **1,000 to 1,500 contacts** across **500 to 1,000 companies**, emphasizing multiple job titles per company for tailored messaging.  \n    - This detailed segmentation aims to improve engagement by addressing specific pain points per role and industry segment.\n\n- **Doug and David Willett emphasized** focusing on **pure retail investors** (e.g., Simon Property Group, Federal Realty) rather than broad diversified asset managers to improve lead quality and message relevance (06:00).  \n    - Colin explained personalization fields allow emails to adapt content based on industry, sub-industry, or job title for flexibility.  \n    - They plan to manually refine lists using LinkedIn research to drill into specific retail vertical contacts within large diversified firms like Blackstone.  \n    - Recognizing challenges in job title clarity and contact specificity, they will blend automated lists with manual vetting to ensure accuracy.  \n    - The goal is a focused, high-value list to maximize outreach effectiveness against \"institutional retail\" buyers.\n\n## **Content and Outreach Execution**\n\nThe marketing team will leverage efficient 30-minute interview sessions to produce rich content assets that support brand awareness and nurture leads.\n\n- **Colin proposed** a **content series** based on short interviews generating multiple outputs: four blog posts, ten social media posts, white papers, and videos from a single 30-minute conversation (23:50).  \n    - Content can be rotated among hosts, including sales or back-office team members, to avoid burnout and diversify perspectives.  \n    - The team will use **Riverside**, a podcast recording platform, to capture high-quality audio/video remotely without the need for new equipment.  \n    - Content serves as branded assets to amplify ABM efforts via social media syndication and email campaigns, driving awareness at the top of the funnel.  \n    - This content strategy complements ABM’s precision targeting by building broader brand recognition.\n\n- Doug expressed mixed feelings about LinkedIn outreach but acknowledged its value when combined with content-driven campaigns to create engagement (24:15).  \n    - Colin highlighted that LinkedIn messaging volume is controlled (15-18 messages per day from Doug’s profile) to avoid flags and maintain authenticity.  \n    - Social media and content efforts mainly target brand awareness, while ABM focuses on direct, personalized outreach to decision makers and influencers.\n\n## **Lead List Development and Targeting Refinement**\n\nThe team agreed to provide a refined list of target companies this week to enable finalization of contacts and campaign parameters.\n\n- Doug and David will deliver a **company list by end of week** prioritizing institutional retail-focused firms (23:00).  \n    - Colin has pre-filtered about **13,000 companies** from Clay but needs a smaller, precise subset to start.  \n    - Focus will be on companies that fit the institutional retail asset class and have the right scale and fit for Gallagher and Mohan’s services.  \n    - The list will support building a contact list of **~1,000 to 1,500 individual contacts** to address multiple roles.  \n    - The subscription to additional data sources like **CoStar** and a private real estate database will supplement this effort.\n\n- They plan to use **lookalike audiences** based on key accounts like Federal Realty to expand the relevant pool while maintaining focus (14:50).  \n    - This data-driven approach ensures the outreach targets prospects with similar profiles and high potential fit.\n\n## **Value Proposition and Engagement Tools**\n\nTo reduce resistance and improve conversion, the team will develop interactive tools and tangible proof elements demonstrating cost savings.\n\n- Colin stressed prospects prefer concrete, quantifiable value before committing to calls, citing that **75% of the decision is made before a 15-minute discovery call** (16:00).  \n    - David and Doug agreed that highlighting **average cost savings or ROI** upfront is critical to lowering barriers.  \n    - They discussed building a **website calculator** where prospects input metrics (e.g., number of lease administrators, properties) to estimate potential savings (18:00).  \n    - The calculator would generate a downloadable PDF report with customized benchmarks and direct sales contact info to facilitate internal championing.  \n    - Colin shared examples of clients using interactive calculators paired with downloadable content to push prospects toward sales calls.\n\n- This tool aims to empower prospects to justify internal buy-in by quantifying benefits, turning contacts into internal champions.  \n    - The calculator will be developed by Colin’s team and then handed off for website integration to save time and resources.\n\n## **Process and Operational Coordination**\n\nClear next steps and process ownership were established to keep the campaign on track and ensure asset readiness.\n\n- Colin confirmed he will verify the **asset intake form** completed by Doug’s team and send a status update via email today (15:30).  \n    - After receiving the company list, they will finalize the ABM plan and build the detailed contact list.  \n    - They will simultaneously start branding, design, and naming concepts for the content series to align with campaign messaging.  \n    - Colin’s team uses **Fireflies** for call transcription, sentiment analysis, and tracking next steps automatically, improving follow-up and leadership visibility (27:40).  \n    - Doug requested a demo of Fireflies to evaluate its fit for their internal workflows.\n\n- The team emphasized flexibility in service usage, with Colin explaining the **points-based payment model** that fixes cost per deliverable regardless of back-end effort (27:00).  \n    - This model encourages efficient resource use and allows the client to prioritize high-impact activities within a fixed budget.\n\n## **Strategic Insights and Market Positioning**\n\nThe focus on institutional retail buyers reflects a deliberate strategy to engage decision makers who control significant budgets and are receptive to targeted, data-driven outreach.\n\n- David highlighted the variability in organizational structures across target firms, noting that financial decision makers (CFOs, heads of asset management) are typically the key contacts (12:00).  \n    - The team acknowledged the need for multiple outreach paths, including procurement and operational contacts, to navigate complex buying processes.  \n    - Doug shared prior success stories where direct CEO outreach or vendor managers led to conversions, underscoring the importance of tailored approaches.  \n    - Colin stressed empowering internal champions by targeting staff who can present Gallagher and Mohan as problem solvers to senior management.\n\n- The ABM and content strategies aim to differentiate Gallagher and Mohan by combining precise targeting with compelling proof of value and broad brand presence.  \n    - This dual approach addresses both the top and middle of the funnel, improving lead quality and accelerating decision timelines.","outline":null,"keywords":["Account Based Marketing","Institutional Retail Real Estate","Lead Generation","Interactive Calculator","Content Series","LinkedIn Outreach"],"overview":"- **ABM Plan Finalization:** A 50-page ABM plan targeting 1,000-1,500 contacts from 500-1,000 institutions is being drafted.  \n- **Campaign Focus:** Targeted outreach prioritizes pure retail investors to improve lead quality and messaging relevance.  \n- **Content Strategy:** Short interviews will create diverse content assets to support brand awareness and nurture leads effectively.  \n- **Lead List Refinement:** A precise company list targeting institutional retail firms will be provided this week for campaign setup.  \n- **Value Proposition Tools:** An interactive calculator will help prospects quantify benefits and justify internal support before calls.  \n- **Market Positioning Strategy:** Targeting key financial decision-makers within firms to streamline the buying process and improve outreach effectiveness.","action_items":"\n**Doug Gallagher**\nProvide a handpicked list of institutional retail-oriented companies (target 500-1000 companies) to Colin and David for campaign targeting (23:00)\nReview and respond to Colin’s email confirming asset intake details (15:35)\nConsider and decide on participation and hosts for content series production (25:30)\nReview and share feedback on Fireflies transcription and automation tool (28:20)\n\n**David Willett**\nCollaborate with Doug on curating a refined company list focused on pure retail investors for ABM targeting (23:00)\nShare feedback about toolkits and content offers such as one-pagers and calculator concepts (16:30)\nReview and help prioritize target decision-maker profiles within companies (12:00)\nReview Fireflies tool and collaborate with Doug on adoption (28:15)\n\n**Colin Costigan**\nFinalize ABM plan document integrating Doug and David’s company list and detailed campaign parameters (23:00)\nDevelop contact list from provided company list and build tailored outreach messaging (23:00)\nPropose branding, design, and naming concepts for content series production (23:30)\nShare Fireflies transcription and analysis sample with Doug and David (28:25)\nSupport development and transfer of interactive calculator web tool, including code handoff if needed (19:00)\n"},"migrated_from":"contract_meetings","original_id":"743a7731-8e48-429d-8fea-04bfa4383dee","master_marketer":{"status":"migrated"}}'::jsonb,
