INSERT INTO compass_notes (contract_id, meeting_id, note_type, title, content_raw, note_date, status, action_items, is_auto_generated)
SELECT
  new_meeting.contract_id,
  new_meeting.meeting_id,
  'meeting',
  'Meeting Notes: Gallagher & Mohan // MiD: Weekly Marketing Meeting',
  '## **Account-Based Marketing (ABM) Strategy and Targeting**

The team is finalizing a detailed ABM plan focusing on institutional retail-oriented real estate companies to target precise contacts for personalized outreach.

- **Colin Costigan confirmed** they are writing a **50-page ABM plan this week** detailing email sources, content types, channels, and user journeys to engage prospects for **Gallagher and Mohan** (01:50).  
    - The ABM approach uses email, LinkedIn outreach, ads, and landing pages to control the full customer journey.  
    - Data sourcing is from **Clay**, aggregating Apollo, ZoomInfo, LinkedIn, and other platforms to build targeted lists.  
    - The campaign targets **1,000 to 1,500 contacts** across **500 to 1,000 companies**, emphasizing multiple job titles per company for tailored messaging.  
    - This detailed segmentation aims to improve engagement by addressing specific pain points per role and industry segment.

- **Doug and David Willett emphasized** focusing on **pure retail investors** (e.g., Simon Property Group, Federal Realty) rather than broad diversified asset managers to improve lead quality and message relevance (06:00).  
    - Colin explained personalization fields allow emails to adapt content based on industry, sub-industry, or job title for flexibility.  
    - They plan to manually refine lists using LinkedIn research to drill into specific retail vertical contacts within large diversified firms like Blackstone.  
    - Recognizing challenges in job title clarity and contact specificity, they will blend automated lists with manual vetting to ensure accuracy.  
    - The goal is a focused, high-value list to maximize outreach effectiveness against "institutional retail" buyers.

## **Content and Outreach Execution**

The marketing team will leverage efficient 30-minute interview sessions to produce rich content assets that support brand awareness and nurture leads.

- **Colin proposed** a **content series** based on short interviews generating multiple outputs: four blog posts, ten social media posts, white papers, and videos from a single 30-minute conversation (23:50).  
    - Content can be rotated among hosts, including sales or back-office team members, to avoid burnout and diversify perspectives.  
    - The team will use **Riverside**, a podcast recording platform, to capture high-quality audio/video remotely without the need for new equipment.  
    - Content serves as branded assets to amplify ABM efforts via social media syndication and email campaigns, driving awareness at the top of the funnel.  
    - This content strategy complements ABM’s precision targeting by building broader brand recognition.

- Doug expressed mixed feelings about LinkedIn outreach but acknowledged its value when combined with content-driven campaigns to create engagement (24:15).  
    - Colin highlighted that LinkedIn messaging volume is controlled (15-18 messages per day from Doug’s profile) to avoid flags and maintain authenticity.  
    - Social media and content efforts mainly target brand awareness, while ABM focuses on direct, personalized outreach to decision makers and influencers.

## **Lead List Development and Targeting Refinement**

The team agreed to provide a refined list of target companies this week to enable finalization of contacts and campaign parameters.

- Doug and David will deliver a **company list by end of week** prioritizing institutional retail-focused firms (23:00).  
    - Colin has pre-filtered about **13,000 companies** from Clay but needs a smaller, precise subset to start.  
    - Focus will be on companies that fit the institutional retail asset class and have the right scale and fit for Gallagher and Mohan’s services.  
    - The list will support building a contact list of **~1,000 to 1,500 individual contacts** to address multiple roles.  
    - The subscription to additional data sources like **CoStar** and a private real estate database will supplement this effort.

- They plan to use **lookalike audiences** based on key accounts like Federal Realty to expand the relevant pool while maintaining focus (14:50).  
    - This data-driven approach ensures the outreach targets prospects with similar profiles and high potential fit.

## **Value Proposition and Engagement Tools**

To reduce resistance and improve conversion, the team will develop interactive tools and tangible proof elements demonstrating cost savings.

- Colin stressed prospects prefer concrete, quantifiable value before committing to calls, citing that **75% of the decision is made before a 15-minute discovery call** (16:00).  
    - David and Doug agreed that highlighting **average cost savings or ROI** upfront is critical to lowering barriers.  
    - They discussed building a **website calculator** where prospects input metrics (e.g., number of lease administrators, properties) to estimate potential savings (18:00).  
    - The calculator would generate a downloadable PDF report with customized benchmarks and direct sales contact info to facilitate internal championing.  
    - Colin shared examples of clients using interactive calculators paired with downloadable content to push prospects toward sales calls.

- This tool aims to empower prospects to justify internal buy-in by quantifying benefits, turning contacts into internal champions.  
    - The calculator will be developed by Colin’s team and then handed off for website integration to save time and resources.

## **Process and Operational Coordination**

Clear next steps and process ownership were established to keep the campaign on track and ensure asset readiness.

- Colin confirmed he will verify the **asset intake form** completed by Doug’s team and send a status update via email today (15:30).  
    - After receiving the company list, they will finalize the ABM plan and build the detailed contact list.  
    - They will simultaneously start branding, design, and naming concepts for the content series to align with campaign messaging.  
    - Colin’s team uses **Fireflies** for call transcription, sentiment analysis, and tracking next steps automatically, improving follow-up and leadership visibility (27:40).  
    - Doug requested a demo of Fireflies to evaluate its fit for their internal workflows.

- The team emphasized flexibility in service usage, with Colin explaining the **points-based payment model** that fixes cost per deliverable regardless of back-end effort (27:00).  
    - This model encourages efficient resource use and allows the client to prioritize high-impact activities within a fixed budget.

## **Strategic Insights and Market Positioning**

The focus on institutional retail buyers reflects a deliberate strategy to engage decision makers who control significant budgets and are receptive to targeted, data-driven outreach.

- David highlighted the variability in organizational structures across target firms, noting that financial decision makers (CFOs, heads of asset management) are typically the key contacts (12:00).  
    - The team acknowledged the need for multiple outreach paths, including procurement and operational contacts, to navigate complex buying processes.  
    - Doug shared prior success stories where direct CEO outreach or vendor managers led to conversions, underscoring the importance of tailored approaches.  
    - Colin stressed empowering internal champions by targeting staff who can present Gallagher and Mohan as problem solvers to senior management.

- The ABM and content strategies aim to differentiate Gallagher and Mohan by combining precise targeting with compelling proof of value and broad brand presence.  
    - This dual approach addresses both the top and middle of the funnel, improving lead quality and accelerating decision timelines.',
  '2026-01-12 18:00:00+00',
  'published',
  '[{"text":"Provide a handpicked list of institutional retail-oriented companies (target 500-1000 companies) to Colin and David for campaign targeting (23:00)","completed":false},{"text":"Review and respond to Colin’s email confirming asset intake details (15:35)","completed":false},{"text":"Consider and decide on participation and hosts for content series production (25:30)","completed":false},{"text":"Review and share feedback on Fireflies transcription and automation tool (28:20)","completed":false},{"text":"Collaborate with Doug on curating a refined company list focused on pure retail investors for ABM targeting (23:00)","completed":false},{"text":"Share feedback about toolkits and content offers such as one-pagers and calculator concepts (16:30)","completed":false},{"text":"Review and help prioritize target decision-maker profiles within companies (12:00)","completed":false},{"text":"Review Fireflies tool and collaborate with Doug on adoption (28:15)","completed":false},{"text":"Finalize ABM plan document integrating Doug and David’s company list and detailed campaign parameters (23:00)","completed":false},{"text":"Develop contact list from provided company list and build tailored outreach messaging (23:00)","completed":false},{"text":"Propose branding, design, and naming concepts for content series production (23:30)","completed":false},{"text":"Share Fireflies transcription and analysis sample with Doug and David (28:25)","completed":false},{"text":"Support development and transfer of interactive calculator web tool, including code handoff if needed (19:00)","completed":false}]'::jsonb,
