    '{"id":"01KE7GGYTJ3FARJ3MVYH8H3XYB","title":"Ponce Bank & MiD: Weekly Sync","summary":{"notes":"## **Project Timeline and Task Management**\n\nThe team agreed to tighten project tracking by breaking down high-level tasks into detailed subtasks to improve clarity and avoid delays (07:27).\n\n- **Christina Zanca** emphasized the need to actively reference and update the master Excel project plan, noting that some tasks due by **January 10th** were not marked as started, which risks slipping timelines.\n    - She highlighted critical overlooked tasks like domain transfers and email system migration that must be incorporated into the timeline.\n    - This detailed task tracking will reduce misunderstandings like those experienced with the data team’s work scope.\n    - She stressed that clearer task ownership, especially for Ponsse’s team, will help hold teams accountable and maintain schedule integrity.\n\n- **Colin Costigan** committed to creating a more granular timeline and task list based on last week’s conversations to ensure everyone knows who is responsible for what and when.\n    - He clarified that domain switching instructions will be sent to the IT team unless direct DNS access is provided, enabling a smooth transition expected to complete within **24 hours** of switching.\n    - He agreed to avoid confusion by explicitly detailing subtasks for items like email and domain transitions in the shared project documents.\n    - Colin confirmed ongoing efforts to ensure all teams work from the same understanding of project phases and deliverables (09:26).\n\n- **Victor Garcia** requested continuous updates on timelines and subtasks, using the example of sandbox setup where the high-level task exists but the detailed steps remain unclear.\n    - He emphasized breaking down tasks further to monitor progress and dependencies effectively.\n\n## **Website and Creative Review Process**\n\nThe team recognized the need to separate website discussions from broader marketing projects to allow focused, productive reviews and avoid rushed feedback (13:15).\n\n- **Guille Santana** presented homepage mockups and marketing collateral, proposing to share markup links for collaborative comments.\n    - Christina noted she has a hard stop at **11:30 AM** and suggested that in-depth website feedback might require additional meetings or offline review.\n    - Jane supported this by confirming that the **11:30 AM** meeting was dedicated to brand and art direction, making this initial session suitable for high-level updates only.\n    - Christina proposed sending website drafts ahead of meetings (ideally by the prior Friday noon) to allow pre-review by herself, Jane, and Victor for more focused discussions.\n\n- The group agreed to maintain a centralized library of drafts and versions for easy reference and progress tracking, aiding internal communication and leadership updates.\n    - Christina pointed out that previous feedback loops lacked accessible shared files, which limited visibility and slowed approvals.\n    - Guille committed to sending all materials in a single email and later compiling them into one Markup file for easier access.\n\n## **Marketing Collateral and Vendor Decisions**\n\nThe team progressed on printed marketing materials with specific vendor and format choices to optimize quality and flexibility (18:12).\n\n- Guille shared research recommending **SmartPress** for printing **6x9 postcards**, citing better space utilization and quality compared to other vendors.\n    - Christina deferred vendor choice to the design experts, prioritizing print quality based on positive past experiences.\n    - She requested copy layout revisions, specifically to better utilize front space with a clear callout (\"Now open in your neighborhood\") and more engaging back design using texture or color variation to avoid a bland look.\n    - Christina also noted that campaign operational readiness depends on sign-off from the new operations hire confirming reporting and management steps.\n\n## **Brand Color Alignment and Design Consistency**\n\nThe team agreed to standardize on the **royal blue** color from existing brand guidelines to avoid confusion and maintain consistency across digital and print assets (21:50).\n\n- **Jane** provided detailed brand context, explaining the use of **royal blue** and a very dark blue in different bank contexts, noting the shift away from lighter blues and teals due to poor reproduction and brand clarity.\n    - Jane and Christina both emphasized that the royal blue is bright, corporate, and visually distinct, making it the preferred choice for headlines and callouts.\n    - Christina explained that despite previous brand guidelines, some on-the-fly design adjustments are expected as real projects expose new needs.\n    - Jane sent the official color codes (CMYK, PMS, Hex) via email to ensure all designers have exact references.\n    - Guille confirmed the design team is currently updating all materials to align with the royal blue and correct fonts, including the newsletter template and website assets.\n\n- The group agreed to test color combinations across collateral to balance yellows, royal blue, and teal without diluting brand identity.\n    - Jane stressed the importance of readability, especially for disclaimers and legal text, which must not overpower the main messaging.\n    - Colin and Guille committed to creating color variations for review rather than exploring new palettes, focusing on refining existing brand colors.\n\n## **Project Communication and Documentation Practices**\n\nImproving communication protocols and document sharing was prioritized to support efficient reviews and stakeholder engagement (16:29).\n\n- Christina requested that draft materials be sent in advance of meetings to allow proper review and preparation, helping meetings be more productive and reducing last-minute changes.\n- Jane highlighted the importance of receiving PDFs and high-quality images rather than relying only on markup links or screenshots with poor resolution.\n    - This format enables easier sharing in board reports and internal presentations.\n- The team agreed to maintain consistent and accessible documentation libraries to keep leadership and stakeholders like **Betty** informed.\n- Victor and Christina underscored ongoing updates to timelines and task lists as essential for clear progress tracking and accountability.\n\n## **Website Technical and Launch Considerations**\n\nThe team discussed domain transfer timing and technical coordination to ensure a seamless website launch without downtime (04:44).\n\n- Victor confirmed desire for buffer time during domain transfer to avoid website outages.\n    - Colin clarified that domain management access is required or else clear switching instructions will be sent to the IT team.\n    - The domain switch will coincide with the **phase one website launch**, aligned with the readiness of initial site requirements.\n    - Subsequent pages and features will roll out progressively after the initial launch.\n- Colin committed to coordinating closely with Victor and IT to plan the domain switch with minimal risk.\n- Christina emphasized that domain and email migration tasks must be carefully integrated into the overall project timeline for transparency and coordination.","outline":null,"keywords":["Domain Transfer","Project Timeline","Website Mockups","Brand Colors","Marketing Collateral","Task Management"],"overview":"- **Project Tracking Enhancements:** Break high-level tasks into detailed subtasks for better clarity and avoid project delays.  \n- **Critical Task Updates:** Master Excel project plan needs updates; tasks due by January 10th must be marked to prevent timeline slips.  \n- **Website Review Process:** Separate website discussions from marketing projects; share drafts before meetings for focused feedback.  \n- **Vendor Print Materials:** SmartPress recommended for printing 6x9 postcards due to quality; layout revisions requested for better design engagement.  \n- **Brand Color Standardization:** Royal blue chosen for consistent brand identity, with exact color codes distributed for designers'' reference.  \n- **Communication Protocols:** Drafts should be sent in advance of meetings; maintain accessible documentation for stakeholder awareness and progress tracking.","action_items":"\n**Colin Costigan**\nProvide instructions or gain access for domain transfer and DNS changes, coordinating timing around phase one launch (05:06)\nUpdate project timeline with granular subtasks for clear ownership and deadlines, avoiding confusion (09:26)\nSend updated marketing collateral including web pages, brochures, and postcards for review by end of day (41:01)\nProvide design color variations for feedback, particularly regarding brand blue usage (35:03)\n\n**Guille Santana**\nShare homepage mockup and other design files via markup link for team feedback (13:15)\nSend all marketing materials and collateral in a single, easily accessible email/Marco file for review and internal sharing, including PDFs for reporting (39:35)\nEnsure design team updates all assets with the approved brand colors and fonts (35:53)\nImplement adjustments to postcard copy layout and back background texture per feedback (20:54)\nNotify team when meta image changes on the website take effect (37:37)\n\n**Christina Zanca**\nLead maintaining and actively referencing the Excel project timeline with detailed subtasks for task management and clarity (07:27)\nCoordinate feedback process by reviewing shared drafts ahead of meetings to optimize discussion time and clarity (16:29)\nCoordinate with Victor to schedule a team meeting for consolidated review and feedback of website materials (27:33)\n\n**Victor Garcia**\nMonitor domain transfer process and buffer timing requirements with IT team (05:06)\nMaintain updated timelines and ensure subtasks are detailed and tracked properly with vendors and internal teams (40:18)\nSchedule review meeting including Christina, Jane, and team for website feedback (27:33)\n\n**Jane Trachet**\nProvide official brand color values (CMYK, PMS, Hex) to team via email to ensure correct color application (24:40)\nParticipate in review and approval of design materials, emphasizing brand consistency and color fidelity (39:35)\n"},"duration":41.900001525878906,"speakers":[{"id":0,"name":"Guille Santana"},{"id":1,"name":"Colin Costigan"},{"id":2,"name":"christinazanca"},{"id":3,"name":"Jane"},{"id":4,"name":"victor garcia"}],"sentences":[{"text":"Hey, Colin.","index":0,"end_time":152.21,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":151.41,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"How are you doing?","index":1,"end_time":153.41,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":152.61,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"Good.","index":2,"end_time":154.13,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":153.93,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"How are you?","index":3,"end_time":154.73,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":154.13,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Good.","index":4,"end_time":155.85,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":155.45,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"How are you feeling?","index":5,"end_time":156.81,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":155.85,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"I am on medicine officially, so hopefully gonna start feeling better soon.","index":6,"end_time":163.77,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":157.69,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Oh, boy.","index":7,"end_time":165.21,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":164.41,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Sorry.","index":8,"end_time":166.41,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":165.93,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"But you know, it is what it is.","index":9,"end_time":168.81,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":166.41,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It''s winter time.","index":10,"end_time":169.77,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":168.81,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":11,"end_time":171.77,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":171.29,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"My daughter was sick, then my wife and I just couldn''t avoid it any longer.","index":12,"end_time":176.41,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":172.01,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Oh, no.","index":13,"end_time":178.33,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":177.61,"speaker_name":"Jane"},{"text":"Yeah, everyone''s sick around me too.","index":14,"end_time":181.3,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":179.46,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"Yeah, it''s crazy.","index":15,"end_time":184.82,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":181.7,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"How was your weekend?","index":16,"end_time":186.82,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":185.78,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Good.","index":17,"end_time":188.18,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":187.78,"speaker_name":"Jane"},{"text":"Good.","index":18,"end_time":189.62,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":189.22,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"All good.","index":19,"end_time":190.26,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":189.62,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"Nothing to complain.","index":20,"end_time":192.18,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":191.06,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"That''s good.","index":21,"end_time":193.38,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":192.74,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Do you want me to lead this meeting?","index":22,"end_time":199.22,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":197.46,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"Yeah, that would.","index":23,"end_time":200.34,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":199.62,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That way they don''t hear me cough like every five seconds.","index":24,"end_time":207.63,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":205.39,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, my husband had a cough for like three weeks.","index":25,"end_time":216.67,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":212.83,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"Yeah, it''s been.","index":26,"end_time":219.39,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":218.51,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It''s been annoying.","index":27,"end_time":220.67,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":219.71,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yep.","index":28,"end_time":222.91,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":222.35,"speaker_name":"Jane"},{"text":"Morning.","index":29,"end_time":224.99,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":224.59,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Morning, Victor.","index":30,"end_time":227.15,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":226.11,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"Good morning.","index":31,"end_time":228.75,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":228.19,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Good.","index":32,"end_time":229.87,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":229.47,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"How''s it going?","index":33,"end_time":230.67,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":230.03,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Oh.","index":34,"end_time":232.14,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":231.74,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"How am I?","index":35,"end_time":235.3,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":234.7,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"In an office and cold is beyond me.","index":36,"end_time":237.66,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":235.3,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Wow.","index":37,"end_time":239.58,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":239.02,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"How was your weekend?","index":38,"end_time":242.54,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":241.42,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"All good.","index":39,"end_time":244.54,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":243.9,"speaker_name":"Jane"},{"text":"It was good.","index":40,"end_time":247.059,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":246.38,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I finally got started on some medicine, so hopefully I''ll be feeling better soon.","index":41,"end_time":251.18,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":247.059,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Like absolute garbage, I''m sorry to say it.","index":42,"end_time":255.9,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":252.38,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Thank you, Victor.","index":43,"end_time":256.94,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":255.98,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Oh, man.","index":44,"end_time":258.02,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":257.38,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Don''t tell me your.","index":45,"end_time":260.1,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":259.22,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"The germs.","index":46,"end_time":261.14,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":260.42,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Your kids brought it to the house.","index":47,"end_time":262.42,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":261.14,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Is the reason that you''re sick.","index":48,"end_time":263.62,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":262.42,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Oh, it was my daughter, then my wife, now me.","index":49,"end_time":267.38,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":263.62,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Send them away.","index":50,"end_time":268.74,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":267.86,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"She''s.","index":51,"end_time":270.3,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":269.7,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"She''s not even one.","index":52,"end_time":271.22,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":270.3,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"She''s about to turn one this month.","index":53,"end_time":272.74,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":271.22,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Send her away.","index":54,"end_time":273.94,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":273.06,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"I know.","index":55,"end_time":277.86,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":277.3,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Christina told me she''s not able to join today.","index":56,"end_time":280.5,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":277.94,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Actually going to join in like two seconds.","index":57,"end_time":283.54,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":280.98,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Oh, she is?","index":58,"end_time":284.91,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":284.19,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":59,"end_time":285.27,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":284.91,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah.","index":60,"end_time":285.71,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":285.27,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Okay.","index":61,"end_time":286.19,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":285.71,"speaker_name":"Jane"},{"text":"I did have a quick question.","index":62,"end_time":288.19,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":286.99,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"You know what?","index":63,"end_time":289.63,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":288.99,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"I''ll wait for her because I want to make sure that we all hear this.","index":64,"end_time":294.11,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":289.63,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"The domains, when we''re ready to transfer them over, because I spoke with it briefly.","index":65,"end_time":301.23,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":296.43,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Is that something that you guys are going to be setting up or do we need to set that up?","index":66,"end_time":305.55,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":302.03,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"We would need access to your domain management system to be able to do that.","index":67,"end_time":311.27,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":306.43,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Or we can just share the records, like basically give them instructions on what to switch.","index":68,"end_time":315.63,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":311.27,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Got it.","index":69,"end_time":316.67,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":316.03,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":70,"end_time":317.23,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":316.67,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"And when should that be done?","index":71,"end_time":318.71,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":317.23,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Because obviously we don''t want our current website to go down in the.","index":72,"end_time":322.43,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":318.71,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Yeah, so that''ll be on like, when we agree upon that.","index":73,"end_time":325.03,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":322.51,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That phase one launch that Christina has alluded to of, like that kind of the requirements of the website that are ready to go live.","index":74,"end_time":332.83,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":325.03,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then we have like the.","index":75,"end_time":333.95,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":332.83,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, here''s other pages we can build as we keep going.","index":76,"end_time":336.59,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":333.95,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, got you.","index":77,"end_time":338.41,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":337.37,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Yeah, because the last thing I obviously want.","index":78,"end_time":340.57,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":338.41,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"No, I was just asking them, like our buffer room to make sure that the webflow website is obviously not active.","index":79,"end_time":348.57,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":341.45,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"But when we''re ready to do that transfer domain, because I got off the phone with Dean really quick just so that I can understand what he needed as a buffer room to make sure that that was up and running.","index":80,"end_time":359.45,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":348.65,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":81,"end_time":360.25,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":359.77,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And all that needs to be built into the project timeline.","index":82,"end_time":363.85,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":360.49,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So I guess that''s a good segue into just one thing that I wanted to mention.","index":83,"end_time":368.79,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":364.01,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Colin.","index":84,"end_time":369.27,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":368.79,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So we have the, you know, the overall Excel document that you set up with has what has all the stages and all that kind of stuff.","index":85,"end_time":377.31,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":369.75,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"I want to do a better job of like making sure that we refer to that in our, in our meetings and like keep that active.","index":86,"end_time":382.79,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":377.31,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Like there''s some things that, you know, there''s something that''s January 10th that''s past due, but it''s.","index":87,"end_time":386.99,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":382.79,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"I don''t think we''ve necessarily started it or maybe we did, but it''s not marked.","index":88,"end_time":390.63,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":386.99,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And then beyond kind of some of like the overarching tasks, I think that we need to start to make sure that we breaking out the subtasks, especially when it comes to the things that are going to be assigned to our team, like on the ponsse side, because then it helps me to understand kind of where we are in the delays, if there are any.","index":89,"end_time":412.67,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":391.19,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And we won''t have any kind of misunderstanding, I think in the, in the, in the tasks.","index":90,"end_time":420.27,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":413.79,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Because I think what happens is that like we saw with the data team there was a misunderstanding, understanding and the, I guess the amount of work that they needed to do.","index":91,"end_time":428.57,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":420.27,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And then also like how do, how are we building in the.","index":92,"end_time":433.73,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":429.29,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"The things that are not necessarily like part of the website HubSpot Project Plan, but like come as a, as a part of it, like the coming soon, you know, campaign.","index":93,"end_time":446.17,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":433.73,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"You know, the things like Victor just mentioned like the, the transfer of domains and stuff like that.","index":94,"end_time":452.41,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":447.53,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Like I don''t see those tasks like even for the email addresses, like once we get those system, like how can we start to transfer over the constant contact domain?","index":95,"end_time":462.31,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":452.41,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And like I know that there''s some things you have to do, but I don''t see those things captured.","index":96,"end_time":466.79,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":462.63,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So I just want to make sure that we are, we''re staying on, on course because it feels like time just flew by since like the August, September and you know, we made a lot of good progress but like it''s already mid January and I foresee like the content component and the approval process taken up, you know, a significant amount of time.","index":97,"end_time":490.45,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":466.79,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So I just want to make sure that, you know, we have all those things.","index":98,"end_time":493.17,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":490.45,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Yeah, I''m sorry, just, just for your reference and Guille, I sent both of those Excel documents in the Chat, just so you guys are aware.","index":99,"end_time":501.65,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":494.13,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":100,"end_time":503.01,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":502.61,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And it''s like, how does Ponce own the support of making sure that, you know, the.","index":101,"end_time":509.53,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":503.01,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"The teams get those things done?","index":102,"end_time":511.61,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":509.53,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"But, like, how do you guys own those actual project, you know, a little bit more tighter.","index":103,"end_time":518.27,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":511.61,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And then when we get into each stage, we''re going to have teams involved.","index":104,"end_time":523.95,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":519.63,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"You know, we''re going to start to have those working meetings and planning sessions and things like, similar to what we did with the last part.","index":105,"end_time":530.99,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":524.51,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Right now we''re only having meetings with the data team because it''s just one team.","index":106,"end_time":535.47,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":531.39,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"But I do foresee, like, bigger meetings.","index":107,"end_time":537.43,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":535.63,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And I want to make sure that we on those meetings bring up the project plan.","index":108,"end_time":540.67,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":537.43,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Like, have everybody buy into, like, what we need to do.","index":109,"end_time":544.77,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":540.67,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Because I think what''s going to happen is, is that the leadership of the.","index":110,"end_time":550.17,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":544.77,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"I guess the people that are overseeing the certain components are going to start to join these calls because they want to make sure that they''re pushing things along.","index":111,"end_time":558.25,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":550.81,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And so I just want to make sure that we''re not disjointed at all.","index":112,"end_time":562.01,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":558.97,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And then, you know, I think that''ll help a lot.","index":113,"end_time":565.53,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":563.61,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Yeah, absolutely.","index":114,"end_time":567.93,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":566.17,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we''ll get, based on Christina, our conversation last week, we''ll get much more grade and you learn that timeline.","index":115,"end_time":574.63,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":567.93,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Just so that everyone is crystal clear, there''s no room for any confusion of who''s doing what and what''s happening when.","index":116,"end_time":580.15,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":574.63,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So, yeah, we can do that.","index":117,"end_time":583.03,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":581.75,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I mean, like, the email stuff, all very easy to set up.","index":118,"end_time":585.59,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":583.03,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It''s going to be us sending to Victor''s question earlier, us sending instructions unless we have access to the DNS to make any switches.","index":119,"end_time":593.79,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":585.59,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But it would just be us sending instructions to the IT team.","index":120,"end_time":596.03,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":593.79,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then it''s like a.","index":121,"end_time":596.95,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":596.03,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Within 24 hours, it''s good to go type of thing.","index":122,"end_time":599.11,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":596.95,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So, yeah, we''ll get much more granular in the spreadsheet with all of those to avoid any possible confusion like Ashley had last week.","index":123,"end_time":605.83,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":599.11,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":124,"end_time":606.46,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":606.26,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And I think it''ll.","index":125,"end_time":607.22,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":606.46,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"It''s helpful because I think what.","index":126,"end_time":608.58,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":607.22,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"What''s happening is, is that.","index":127,"end_time":609.82,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":608.58,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And Ashley made a note.","index":128,"end_time":610.86,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":609.82,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"It''s like she was kind of like, going back to the process that she recalled in the.","index":129,"end_time":616.78,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":610.86,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"The Salesforce setup.","index":130,"end_time":617.9,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":616.78,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And at that time they set up.","index":131,"end_time":619.26,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":617.9,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"They set up the Salesforce marketing cloud.","index":132,"end_time":621.46,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":619.26,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So I think that there was some things.","index":133,"end_time":623.38,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":621.46,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"But I flagged to her, like, that''s probably because it was a project that was totally new.","index":134,"end_time":628.7,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":623.38,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Like, we are not necessarily looking at this point to reinvent the Salesforce wheel.","index":135,"end_time":634.58,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":628.7,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Um, so I think, like, everything that I outlined in my email to her is like where we stand.","index":136,"end_time":639.11,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":635.03,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So, like, what I would say is when we have that next data meeting, I think it.","index":137,"end_time":644.15,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":639.43,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"I think it is.","index":138,"end_time":645.19,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":644.39,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"I don''t know.","index":139,"end_time":646.03,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":645.51,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"We have one today.","index":140,"end_time":646.79,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":646.03,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":141,"end_time":647.59,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":647.11,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":142,"end_time":648.71,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":648.23,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"We should definitely make sure that we bring that up and just raise that as, hey, like what.","index":143,"end_time":654.95,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":649.19,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"What you guys aligned on last week is the be all, end all.","index":144,"end_time":659.55,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":655.19,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So there''s no confusion and we can.","index":145,"end_time":660.71,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":659.55,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Because I think she said that based off of that development, she feels comfortable with being able to do a.","index":146,"end_time":666.78,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":660.71,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Of like the next step stuff.","index":147,"end_time":668.45,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":666.93,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":148,"end_time":669.01,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":668.53,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then just.","index":149,"end_time":671.01,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":670.13,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"I know she had said that there wasn''t, like she didn''t get the APA doc documentation, but then I was like, I pretty much sure that it was sent.","index":150,"end_time":678.53,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":671.25,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So I think what, what we can do too is if there''s ever like documents being shared and it''s a lot of information or links or, or pages or whatever, if you guys could, um, just maybe flag like a starting point and then reference, like if you need additional contacts or other things.","index":151,"end_time":699.07,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":678.77,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Like this is what.","index":152,"end_time":699.95,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":699.07,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"The plethora of stuff that you could do your own research, I think.","index":153,"end_time":702.51,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":699.95,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Because what happens is that maybe they just got overwhelmed with all of the links that HubSpot has in their library and didn''t necessarily know where to start.","index":154,"end_time":711.99,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":702.51,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And so any place where we can kind of help avoid any of that confusion, I think is going to be helpful for us.","index":155,"end_time":717.91,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":711.99,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":156,"end_time":719.33,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":719.01,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Yeah, totally makes sense.","index":157,"end_time":721.17,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":719.89,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, sounds good.","index":158,"end_time":722.89,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":721.97,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All there.","index":159,"end_time":723.49,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":722.89,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And that I''m going to transfer it over to Guille to run so you guys don''t have to listen to me cough and sound.","index":160,"end_time":729.09,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":723.73,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I know you sound horrible.","index":161,"end_time":730.29,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":729.09,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Feel better.","index":162,"end_time":732.29,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":731.57,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"All right, let me share my screen.","index":163,"end_time":738.73,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":735.17,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"I know we have two meetings today.","index":164,"end_time":740.45,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":738.73,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"The first 30 minutes will be around or focused on just the website, specifically for the homepage mockups that we built so we can go over them.","index":165,"end_time":755.33,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":742.45,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"I''ll walk you through the homepage we designed and that we can maybe review it together.","index":166,"end_time":760.93,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":756.21,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"And we should like, review the overall structure, how everything''s like, prioritized and if you like the flow of it.","index":167,"end_time":768.37,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":761.65,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"So let''s go and let me know if you can see my screen.","index":168,"end_time":774.69,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":768.85,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"One thing I just want to flag is I do have a hard stop at 11:30, so potentially, like, this might not be something we get to cover or, or at least you won''t.","index":169,"end_time":786.09,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":777.41,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"You won''t probably walk away with full approvals at the end of this meeting.","index":170,"end_time":788.41,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":786.09,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"But, you know, if you share it with, with me, I can, I can take a bigger, you know, review.","index":171,"end_time":794.53,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":788.41,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"What I''ll do is I''ll share a markup link and you guys can leave your comments for copywriting.","index":172,"end_time":801.05,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":795.09,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"Images, structure, everything.","index":173,"end_time":803.72,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":801.05,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"Yes.","index":174,"end_time":804.44,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":803.96,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"I''m sorry, really quick G, before you continue, we do have an 11:30 meeting, Christina, with creative and brand in this discussion.","index":175,"end_time":811.08,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":804.44,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"So in that regard, where do we want to land with this then?","index":176,"end_time":815.16,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":811.24,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"I think.","index":177,"end_time":817.48,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":816.84,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Yeah, the plan, what?","index":178,"end_time":820.52,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":819.32,"speaker_name":"Jane"},{"text":"Just to backtrack and the plan that we set was that 11:30 was going to be brand, design, art direction, and that this first half was going to be.","index":179,"end_time":829.56,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":820.52,"speaker_name":"Jane"},{"text":"If this is the main agenda, this works for me.","index":180,"end_time":833.52,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":830.32,"speaker_name":"Jane"},{"text":"But yeah, that''s fine.","index":181,"end_time":835.2,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":833.52,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Okay.","index":182,"end_time":835.84,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":835.28,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So I''m happy to, you know, take a look at it, but if you need any kind of like, decisions or if you have any just like general updates across like all projects, then we can shift to that so you get what you need from, from me.","index":183,"end_time":848.48,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":836.64,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"But if not, then this is, this is cool to, you know, to walk through it.","index":184,"end_time":851.76,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":848.48,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":185,"end_time":853.84,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":853.36,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Do you want to maybe just go back to the slide deck and just show like all of the pieces that we have to cover between the two meetings?","index":186,"end_time":860,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":854.08,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":187,"end_time":860.64,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":860.24,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":188,"end_time":861.03,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":860.64,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"So it''s the website and brochure and rifles.","index":189,"end_time":864.3,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":861.34,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"We finish those.","index":190,"end_time":865.66,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":864.46,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"The postcard and what''s in progress.","index":191,"end_time":868.3,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":865.74,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"What I was.","index":192,"end_time":874.54,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":873.82,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Okay, so here, here''s what I''m going to suggest.","index":193,"end_time":876.86,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":874.94,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"I think that this meeting is great, but if we''re, if we''re going to take a lot of time because the website is so like, big, maybe we do need, just because it''s a separate project to separate like just regular marketing projects versus the we website.","index":194,"end_time":893.24,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":877.099,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"I hate to say like another meeting, but I don''t want to have to rush on like giving you guys good feedback because I''ll be honest, the first, like, just, just thing that you shared, I actually really like it.","index":195,"end_time":903.4,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":893.64,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So like, I want to be able to, you know, to give you guys, you know, good feedback and have you guys explain.","index":196,"end_time":908.6,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":903.4,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"But like, you could see we already went 11 minutes and just talking about like regular updates.","index":197,"end_time":913.56,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":908.6,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So maybe what we do is just give me a quick preview of the brochures, trifolds and I, I just want to take a glance at it and give high level thoughts.","index":198,"end_time":925.67,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":914.36,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And then on the 11:30 meeting, I think Jane, you know, with, from a creative lens could give some more granular feedback and then let''s maybe send the website components and mockups to, to me, Let me, let me take a little bit of time offline to just look at it, gather my thoughts and give you some overall feedback and then you could walk us through, you know, through it if we need to set up another, another meeting.","index":199,"end_time":952.67,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":925.67,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"But sorry to derail.","index":200,"end_time":953.95,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":952.67,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"I just I know, you know, we have a lot going on and I don''t know if 30 minutes is going to be enough time.","index":201,"end_time":957.91,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":953.95,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Yeah, all good.","index":202,"end_time":958.95,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":958.23,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And we have, we have four meetings this week alone.","index":203,"end_time":960.95,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":958.95,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So, you know, we need to restructure how those are set up.","index":204,"end_time":963.71,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":960.95,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We can, we can obviously adjust.","index":205,"end_time":965.19,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":963.71,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, cool.","index":206,"end_time":966.95,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":966.15,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":207,"end_time":971.55,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":971.19,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"So this is a sales sheet for the printed marketing materials.","index":208,"end_time":976.31,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":971.55,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"Like, we applied your feedback, implemented the tree structure.","index":209,"end_time":980.84,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":976.31,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"This is a commercial one.","index":210,"end_time":983.64,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":981.96,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"And we will also send you the consumer banking one.","index":211,"end_time":988.04,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":984.2,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"Okay.","index":212,"end_time":988.92,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":988.36,"speaker_name":"Jane"},{"text":"Yeah, no, I think this looks a little cleaner and visually, like, nicer than just like the, you know, the laundry list.","index":213,"end_time":996.84,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":989.64,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So the breakouts are better.","index":214,"end_time":998.32,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":996.84,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"What I would say is what, what also might be helpful to make these meetings a little bit more productive is if you feel free to, like, send me the, like, the drafts maybe the day before I could, you know, review them with Jane and Victor, you know, depending on what it is and like, at least come prepared to, like, give you some, some feedback.","index":215,"end_time":1019.31,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":998.32,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And then the last thing I would say is I would love to start to see a library of like, drafts.","index":216,"end_time":1026.91,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1020.11,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"I know, like, I raised like that when things go into, like you share things like, for example, on screen, right.","index":217,"end_time":1034.75,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1026.91,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And then I might give you feedback, but then it goes direct directly back to design team.","index":218,"end_time":1039.84,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1035.07,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Like, there''s no reference point for me to review back to that draft.","index":219,"end_time":1042.88,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1039.84,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"One of the biggest things that I like to do is I like to take Betty along on the process and share updates with her, but then I couldn''t access the files.","index":220,"end_time":1050.64,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1042.88,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So I think it would be really nice if we could, you know, maybe keep a library of some drafts.","index":221,"end_time":1055.88,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1050.64,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"You.","index":222,"end_time":1058.32,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1058.04,"speaker_name":"Jane"},{"text":"Know, just so I have as a reference point to show progress.","index":223,"end_time":1061.8,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1058.32,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So, yeah, I think let''s do that.","index":224,"end_time":1066.48,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1064.56,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Let''s start to have these documents sent at least maybe since we''re meeting Monday, the Friday, you know, by noon before and we''ll look at them and then, you know, at least have a good discussion on it.","index":225,"end_time":1079.4,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1066.48,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So.","index":226,"end_time":1079.76,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1079.4,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Got it.","index":227,"end_time":1081.72,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1081.28,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"Right.","index":228,"end_time":1081.92,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1081.72,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So that''s, that''s good.","index":229,"end_time":1082.88,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1081.92,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So glad to see those two things and moving along because I got some questions on those.","index":230,"end_time":1087.68,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1082.88,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"This is the postcard now.","index":231,"end_time":1090.08,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1088.8,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"All right, cool.","index":232,"end_time":1091.57,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1090.08,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Yeah, so we did some research on like, the alternative printing and mailing options and we suggest we go with SmartPress and using a 6 by 9 postcard.","index":233,"end_time":1104.61,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1092.37,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"This is the layout option that they''re giving us.","index":234,"end_time":1107.57,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1104.77,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"We also reviewed other vendors, but honestly they were thinking so much space on the postcard.","index":235,"end_time":1113.49,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1107.81,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"So at this one that we think, like, gives us more flexibility, but, like, let us know if you have like a preferred vendor or if you''re comfortable with like this decision?","index":236,"end_time":1123.42,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1113.49,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"Yeah, no, I mean, I''ll, I''ll defer to you guys to kind of, you know, be those experts and give us kind of the best approach.","index":237,"end_time":1134.94,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1124.78,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"As long as the quality of the postcard is going to be nice.","index":238,"end_time":1137.78,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1134.94,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Because I remember that the last postcard that you guys printed for us, the quality was really good and the team was happy with it.","index":239,"end_time":1143.42,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1137.78,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"What I would say now is now that you have, you know, the template kind of structure there, I do think that we need to rethink the, the copy layout because it, it''s just all over.","index":240,"end_time":1159.37,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1144.14,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"I think like now we maybe have the ability to go across farther into the right space.","index":241,"end_time":1164.81,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1159.45,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":242,"end_time":1165.29,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1164.81,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"You know, how do we maybe utilize the front space a little better?","index":243,"end_time":1172.93,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1166.01,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Like the now open in your neighborhood?","index":244,"end_time":1175.95,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1172.93,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Like, there''s really not a lot of copy on the, the, the front space and how maybe we take like that first section and have like the back be.","index":245,"end_time":1186.55,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1175.95,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Here''s all of the benefits, like a continuation.","index":246,"end_time":1189.11,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1186.63,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"You know, how like in a video they do like the lower thirds.","index":247,"end_time":1193.03,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1190.47,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"You know, we can have like a little call out bar like now open and you know, in your neighborhood, I think that might be nice.","index":248,"end_time":1200.55,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1193.35,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So if you guys could just tweak that a little bit and then, yeah, share that back.","index":249,"end_time":1210.82,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1201.78,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"We can then send that to the, to the team for review.","index":250,"end_time":1214.9,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1210.98,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"I expect a quick approval because the team, you know, provided the disclosures.","index":251,"end_time":1220.74,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1215.38,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So, you know, right now where we stand is just having the new person that''s working, you know, on the operations side, confirm some of the next steps for reporting and for actually like managing the campaign.","index":252,"end_time":1233.76,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1220.74,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And then we can, then we''re good to, to go.","index":253,"end_time":1235.68,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1233.76,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"My last piece of feedback is maybe we could kind of jazz up the back a little bit, the background that like yellowy color.","index":254,"end_time":1246.96,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1236.72,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Like maybe we just put like some other texture or something just to kind of like balance out the design.","index":255,"end_time":1252.88,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1246.96,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Because.","index":256,"end_time":1255.24,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1254.96,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"Like, the back is a little boring.","index":257,"end_time":1256.16,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1255.24,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"It''ll all look just like the text.","index":258,"end_time":1257.44,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1256.16,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"I have.","index":259,"end_time":1258.56,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1257.84,"speaker_name":"Jane"},{"text":"And I have a question comment with this overall brand, but it really applies here.","index":260,"end_time":1263.45,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1258.97,"speaker_name":"Jane"},{"text":"So in the initial color palette that you presented and we were moving forward with was a teal, a very, very dark navy blue, and I think white.","index":261,"end_time":1278.73,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1263.85,"speaker_name":"Jane"},{"text":"Right.","index":262,"end_time":1279.09,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1278.73,"speaker_name":"Jane"},{"text":"And maybe some use of gray here.","index":263,"end_time":1281.45,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1279.09,"speaker_name":"Jane"},{"text":"And on the website you just showed, I saw yellow, which I really like, and I''m not seeing, seeing the teal, but I''m seeing a baby blue.","index":264,"end_time":1289.97,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1281.61,"speaker_name":"Jane"},{"text":"And now on this logo I''m seeing a royal blue.","index":265,"end_time":1292.73,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1289.97,"speaker_name":"Jane"},{"text":"So I just wanted to provide some feedback, some thoughts which I shared a few times in Email and I did mention to Christina last week and seeing an execution really helped.","index":266,"end_time":1301.53,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1293.05,"speaker_name":"Jane"},{"text":"We have been using for the past year and a half really shifted towards our royal blue, which is what you see in our logo here.","index":267,"end_time":1309.77,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1302.33,"speaker_name":"Jane"},{"text":"I have heart for it because to me it''s bright, it''s, it''s happy.","index":268,"end_time":1315.74,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1311.13,"speaker_name":"Jane"},{"text":"It still looks corporate and important but it really pops off of the page.","index":269,"end_time":1319.86,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1315.74,"speaker_name":"Jane"},{"text":"Like if you look here, I, I don''t think this is the teal.","index":270,"end_time":1324.18,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1320.9,"speaker_name":"Jane"},{"text":"The headlines.","index":271,"end_time":1324.94,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1324.18,"speaker_name":"Jane"},{"text":"I think it''s a light blue.","index":272,"end_time":1326.58,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1324.94,"speaker_name":"Jane"},{"text":"I''m.","index":273,"end_time":1326.94,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1326.58,"speaker_name":"Jane"},{"text":"I''m not sure but it''s almost like the logos like the disclaimers and are the legal text has more visual weight than that blue.","index":274,"end_time":1336.1,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1326.94,"speaker_name":"Jane"},{"text":"Which is why everyone at Ponce kind of agreed to move away from a light blue.","index":275,"end_time":1340.1,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1336.1,"speaker_name":"Jane"},{"text":"And in seeing this, it''s really making me feel even more strongly that that royal blue is correct.","index":276,"end_time":1348.18,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1341.1,"speaker_name":"Jane"},{"text":"I''ll also add something because when we were talking about the budget, Betty was asking me, you know, for just some quick thoughts on how we would start to like make some brand changes and you know, to incorporate some of the new components in as like a phase two.","index":277,"end_time":1364.3,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1348.18,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And so what I would say is if like we''re not going to start to like make any color structure or anything changes to our logo or any of like the logo treatments on the, the.","index":278,"end_time":1376.92,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1364.78,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"The outside exterior of the bank.","index":279,"end_time":1378.44,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1376.92,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So like, I guess what, what we could just do is at this point just swap the, like keep the, the ponsse blue as it''s in our logo because it''s just going to be easier for us regardless of style.","index":280,"end_time":1393.4,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1378.52,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And you know, apologies that that kind of is a little bit of a.","index":281,"end_time":1396.92,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1394.12,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Of a change up from the approved brand guidelines.","index":282,"end_time":1400.66,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1397.34,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"I think what''s happening is now you''ll see sometimes like when you implement things, things come up.","index":283,"end_time":1406.46,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1400.66,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So if we could just do that, I think that that would be great.","index":284,"end_time":1409.22,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1406.7,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And what I''ll say is that when it comes to creative or anything of that nature, you know, I''m going to obviously, you know, provide you, you feedback but really the goal is for Jean to own that component.","index":285,"end_time":1422.94,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1409.22,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So what I would say is, you know, any, anything that she''s going to kind of give you direction on or suggestions on, just consider that we''re aligned and, and you guys can move that forward.","index":286,"end_time":1435.32,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1423.42,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Just so you know, there''s no confusion there and we can keep things moving.","index":287,"end_time":1438.8,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1435.32,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"That''s kind of the purpose of having the creative.","index":288,"end_time":1441.64,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1439.76,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And I just want to clarify because it''s not going to be clear in reviewing our assets.","index":289,"end_time":1445.52,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1441.64,"speaker_name":"Jane"},{"text":"It''s.","index":290,"end_time":1445.8,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1445.52,"speaker_name":"Jane"},{"text":"It''s a weird thing that we''ve done at Ponce, you will find two used colors in our logo.","index":291,"end_time":1450.88,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1445.8,"speaker_name":"Jane"},{"text":"One is the royal blue as you see it right now, and one is a dark, dark blue.","index":292,"end_time":1454.48,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1450.88,"speaker_name":"Jane"},{"text":"That''s because that''s what''s of our branches and in sort of like the corporate comms and like investor relations side of things.","index":293,"end_time":1463.74,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1454.8,"speaker_name":"Jane"},{"text":"And we haven''t wanted to invest the money to change all of our outside signage.","index":294,"end_time":1467.98,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1463.74,"speaker_name":"Jane"},{"text":"So we''ve remained that.","index":295,"end_time":1470.06,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1468.22,"speaker_name":"Jane"},{"text":"That''s why you will still see some of that dark blue.","index":296,"end_time":1473.1,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1470.14,"speaker_name":"Jane"},{"text":"But the royal blue is even in our.","index":297,"end_time":1475.54,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1473.1,"speaker_name":"Jane"},{"text":"All the new Inwood work we''ve done.","index":298,"end_time":1477.38,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1475.54,"speaker_name":"Jane"},{"text":"So, Jane, give them the CMYK PMS I have.","index":299,"end_time":1480.46,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1477.38,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"It''s in our brand guidelines.","index":300,"end_time":1481.9,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1480.46,"speaker_name":"Jane"},{"text":"Yeah, no, I know, but, but just if you, if you can pull it up.","index":301,"end_time":1485.47,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1482.31,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Sure, pull it up and, and just put it in an email and then it can just be clear on that.","index":302,"end_time":1491.15,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1485.47,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And then, you know, because I want to make sure that we align on that quickly because, you know, we''re obviously starting to do some other creative stuff and like to go back and forth and agree all those changes is going to be annoying.","index":303,"end_time":1502.95,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1491.15,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"All right, so I think, I think this is, I think this is really good.","index":304,"end_time":1508.27,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1504.31,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"I think we''re getting into a groove and I know it''s a little bit, you know, mishmash because we''re changing and making decisions on the, on the fly, but I think that definitely having the creative meeting is going to help move some of those things along.","index":305,"end_time":1522.01,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1508.27,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"I think definitely, like having a status update meeting that''s going to help us understand kind of all the projects and where they stand is great.","index":306,"end_time":1530.65,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1523.13,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"I think when it comes to the website and any bigger project where you want us to give you feedback, like, definitely making sure that you send us the files before.","index":307,"end_time":1540.41,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1530.89,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Because I was actually talking to Victor this morning and I think one of the site, one of the calls, the site map was brought up on and the, the wireframe, so it''s brought up on screen, but I don''t necessarily ever recall like getting like a, A P. Like a PDF or something like that.","index":308,"end_time":1559.95,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1540.65,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And maybe I missed it.","index":309,"end_time":1560.83,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1559.95,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So I want to make sure that I''m not missing things and I have like a good, you know, track record of, of it that I could refer back to in case I can''t attend a meeting.","index":310,"end_time":1570.87,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1560.83,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So I think that''ll help.","index":311,"end_time":1572.63,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1571.43,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So let''s go through with the rest of the website meetings this week and see how they pan out.","index":312,"end_time":1576.51,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1572.91,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"I want to use our time wisely.","index":313,"end_time":1580.27,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1576.51,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So I don''t necessarily want to have like 17 website meetings, but like we''re going to have to come To a point in time where it''s like okay, we have the website meeting for the data phase, then the website meeting where we maybe just talk about the project overall and then you know, down the line we''ll, we''ll bring other, other people in.","index":314,"end_time":1601.96,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1580.27,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"But yeah, I mean I think, I think Jane and I and Victor are going to have to do some, you know, quick review.","index":315,"end_time":1606.68,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1601.96,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"There was a couple things that I spotted that we''ll need to, to take into account.","index":316,"end_time":1611.8,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1606.84,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"The biggest one is the, the God awful regulation that says that the stupid logo, the member FTIC statement has to be at the top of the page to mess around with the design.","index":317,"end_time":1626,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1612.2,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So I didn''t see necessarily that there.","index":318,"end_time":1627.84,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1626.08,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So yeah, send me those, those things.","index":319,"end_time":1632.08,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1629.92,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"If you want to do them in mock up, I''m happy to kind of look at them.","index":320,"end_time":1636.48,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1633.68,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Maybe even Jane, what you could do or Victor''s just put some time on the calendar for us as a team tomorrow to go through it and start to think about, you know, feedback that we''re going to give.","index":321,"end_time":1649.6,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1637.2,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Cool.","index":322,"end_time":1652.99,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1652.67,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And I''ll send everything over in like a single email so you have it.","index":323,"end_time":1656.83,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1653.23,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"Yeah, no, I, I really, I really appreciate that.","index":324,"end_time":1660.51,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1657.31,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"But yeah, like even this, like this looks nice too.","index":325,"end_time":1663.27,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1660.99,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Like I, I think we''re, I think we''re making good.","index":326,"end_time":1665.87,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1663.27,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And just, just real quick, Jane, to clarify.","index":327,"end_time":1667.91,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1666.03,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So you wanted to switch the, the teal font.","index":328,"end_time":1669.95,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1667.91,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I know it wasn''t showing as teal like the monitors.","index":329,"end_time":1672.95,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1669.95,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Sometimes when you have a picture versus what you''re seeing of what it prints out.","index":330,"end_time":1675.91,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1672.95,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So that was the teal color on the postcard on the last slide.","index":331,"end_time":1678.88,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1675.91,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Ga.","index":332,"end_time":1679.24,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1678.88,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"If you can go back there real quick.","index":333,"end_time":1680.48,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1679.24,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I just want to confirm you wanted to switch that to the lighter blue, the royal blue for like now open in your neighborhood.","index":334,"end_time":1686.96,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1680.88,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I. Yeah.","index":335,"end_time":1690.24,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1688.72,"speaker_name":"Jane"},{"text":"Well let''s.","index":336,"end_time":1691.2,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1690.24,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Can we look at it?","index":337,"end_time":1692.16,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1691.2,"speaker_name":"Jane"},{"text":"I asked a while ago if we could look at a few things before we get into execution mode for this.","index":338,"end_time":1697.28,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1692.16,"speaker_name":"Jane"},{"text":"Yeah, no, we, they.","index":339,"end_time":1698.2,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1697.28,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"They did when Jay.","index":340,"end_time":1699.32,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1698.2,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"When you were on vacation.","index":341,"end_time":1700.32,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1699.32,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So I.","index":342,"end_time":1701.84,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1701.36,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"On my screen, this teal looks right.","index":343,"end_time":1705.01,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1701.84,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So it might be your resolution and that does happen sometimes.","index":344,"end_time":1708.57,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1705.01,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"But what I would say is.","index":345,"end_time":1710.41,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1708.57,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Let''S.","index":346,"end_time":1712.65,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1712.17,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"Give you both options.","index":347,"end_time":1713.61,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1712.65,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"The, you know, the, the blue for the logo for now.","index":348,"end_time":1718.57,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1713.93,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":349,"end_time":1719.89,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1719.45,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So I can even share.","index":350,"end_time":1720.81,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1719.89,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I just did a quick hop into Figma just to show like the two next to each other.","index":351,"end_time":1725.29,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1720.89,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah.","index":352,"end_time":1726.73,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1725.85,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"It might just be your screen because this teal does look like the teal that.","index":353,"end_time":1730.57,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1726.73,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Okay.","index":354,"end_time":1732.22,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1731.86,"speaker_name":"Jane"},{"text":"But then I, you know, but then there''s also that baby blue which we as.","index":355,"end_time":1736.5,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1732.22,"speaker_name":"Jane"},{"text":"Just so you know, we had like, bank wide killed that because it wasn''t reproducing and it really looked flat.","index":356,"end_time":1743.86,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1736.66,"speaker_name":"Jane"},{"text":"Like, if you look baby blue, if you look at our social, you''ll see that in like 2001 and then you''ll see that it died.","index":357,"end_time":1751.1,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1743.86,"speaker_name":"Jane"},{"text":"Okay.","index":358,"end_time":1751.54,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1751.1,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"Yeah, because I don''t see.","index":359,"end_time":1752.42,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1751.54,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"I don''t see any baby blue on here.","index":360,"end_time":1753.82,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1752.42,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So I don''t know, maybe on the.","index":361,"end_time":1755.46,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1753.82,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"A little bit on the front side or on the website site.","index":362,"end_time":1757.84,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1755.46,"speaker_name":"Jane"},{"text":"So I just want to align because if we move forward with one thing, I''d love to be.","index":363,"end_time":1762.16,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1757.84,"speaker_name":"Jane"},{"text":"All right, so why don''t you do that?","index":364,"end_time":1764.04,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1762.96,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Why don''t you look at some of the pieces?","index":365,"end_time":1765.36,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1764.04,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Not for, like a content review.","index":366,"end_time":1767.68,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1765.52,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Yeah, give, give some.","index":367,"end_time":1770.76,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1769.52,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Just, you know, stylistic or color feedback and then, you know, we can go from there.","index":368,"end_time":1776.56,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1770.76,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"I''m going to, I''m going to jump.","index":369,"end_time":1777.52,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1776.56,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So if you guys want to just move into that portion of it, just.","index":370,"end_time":1781.04,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1777.52,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"I''ll look out for your, your email and I''ll, I''ll make a good conscious effort later on to, to dive into it and get you guys some good feed and then team.","index":371,"end_time":1790.51,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1781.44,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"You know, Victor, if you could just put a meeting on the calendar, that would be great.","index":372,"end_time":1793.55,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1790.51,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Colin, feel better.","index":373,"end_time":1795.23,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1794.11,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"But, yeah, I, I''m, I think I''m like, psyching myself out because it''s just a lot and I want to be able to just push, like, things out of the way.","index":374,"end_time":1804.03,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1795.87,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So this is good.","index":375,"end_time":1805.15,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1804.19,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Thanks, guys.","index":376,"end_time":1806.59,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1805.87,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"I appreciate it.","index":377,"end_time":1807.39,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1806.59,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Thank you.","index":378,"end_time":1808.27,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1807.71,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Okay, bye.","index":379,"end_time":1809.39,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1808.51,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Okay, so I, I mean, you have them, but I''m gonna put in a screenshot for ease right into our chat.","index":380,"end_time":1818.89,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1811.07,"speaker_name":"Jane"},{"text":"If I can get my computer to work.","index":381,"end_time":1822.25,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1820.57,"speaker_name":"Jane"},{"text":"The Zoom chat might not allow screenshots.","index":382,"end_time":1829.93,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1827.53,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yes.","index":383,"end_time":1834.25,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1833.61,"speaker_name":"Jane"},{"text":"Sorry.","index":384,"end_time":1834.97,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1834.41,"speaker_name":"Jane"},{"text":"Do you have our brand guidelines?","index":385,"end_time":1842.53,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1840.33,"speaker_name":"Jane"},{"text":"Can I. Yeah, And I''m trying to get back into the SharePoint right now.","index":386,"end_time":1845.69,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1842.53,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It''s, it''s, it''s like one day it works and the next day it doesn''t.","index":387,"end_time":1849.4,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1845.69,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, I don''t know why.","index":388,"end_time":1850.84,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1849.72,"speaker_name":"Jane"},{"text":"Oh, you know what?","index":389,"end_time":1851.68,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1850.92,"speaker_name":"Jane"},{"text":"I think I can do this.","index":390,"end_time":1852.84,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1851.68,"speaker_name":"Jane"},{"text":"No, I can''t send a file in here.","index":391,"end_time":1857.64,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1855.32,"speaker_name":"Jane"},{"text":"I can.","index":392,"end_time":1861.16,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1860.52,"speaker_name":"Jane"},{"text":"Okay, give me one second and then I will just email it after.","index":393,"end_time":1865.72,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1861.48,"speaker_name":"Jane"},{"text":"No, I can''t.","index":394,"end_time":1866.68,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1865.88,"speaker_name":"Jane"},{"text":"It''s not letting me zoom.","index":395,"end_time":1867.96,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1866.68,"speaker_name":"Jane"},{"text":"Okay, I''m gonna email it over.","index":396,"end_time":1870.92,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1868.44,"speaker_name":"Jane"},{"text":"I just think we, you know, there might have been confusion.","index":397,"end_time":1879.81,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1875.81,"speaker_name":"Jane"},{"text":"Okay.","index":398,"end_time":1882.65,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1882.21,"speaker_name":"Jane"},{"text":"Sending it right now.","index":399,"end_time":1883.81,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1882.65,"speaker_name":"Jane"},{"text":"Computer is being bizarre.","index":400,"end_time":1894.29,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1892.69,"speaker_name":"Jane"},{"text":"Okay.","index":401,"end_time":1903.54,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1903.26,"speaker_name":"Jane"},{"text":"Hopefully that email goes through quickly.","index":402,"end_time":1905.82,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1903.54,"speaker_name":"Jane"},{"text":"I would just.","index":403,"end_time":1906.94,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1906.14,"speaker_name":"Jane"},{"text":"I didn''t even put a subject in the email.","index":404,"end_time":1909.7,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1907.82,"speaker_name":"Jane"},{"text":"Pardon me.","index":405,"end_time":1910.26,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1909.7,"speaker_name":"Jane"},{"text":"I just sent it through.","index":406,"end_time":1911.26,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1910.26,"speaker_name":"Jane"},{"text":"I''m just worried that we''re taking a step back to what everyone, including our executive leadership and Designers and everyone moved away from with that, that baby blue.","index":407,"end_time":1926.22,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1917.42,"speaker_name":"Jane"},{"text":"And I just want to see, because Christine and I looked at some things with our new royal blue, like what you used in our 207, and it just reads really well, both in positive and negative.","index":408,"end_time":1937.66,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1926.22,"speaker_name":"Jane"},{"text":"So white reads on top of it, but it also reads bright on top of white or on top of yellow, probably maybe even with a teal or something like that.","index":409,"end_time":1946.46,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1937.66,"speaker_name":"Jane"},{"text":"And what we don''t want to have happen is have the baby blue, the this royal blue, the navy blue, and a teal.","index":410,"end_time":1955.03,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1946.46,"speaker_name":"Jane"},{"text":"Because, like, the whole point of this was to streamline and let''s have, like, three colors, you know, and I want, we want to make sure they all work with each other.","index":411,"end_time":1963.67,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1955.03,"speaker_name":"Jane"},{"text":"And to date, I don''t think we''ve seen one material with all of them.","index":412,"end_time":1969.51,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1963.91,"speaker_name":"Jane"},{"text":"So, like, if you look at the new postcard and the 207, for me, the 207 feels more brand aligned in terms of color palette.","index":413,"end_time":1989.5,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1972.79,"speaker_name":"Jane"},{"text":"Like, so looks a little joyful, but it still looks corporate.","index":414,"end_time":1993.26,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1989.98,"speaker_name":"Jane"},{"text":"It all reads really well.","index":415,"end_time":1995.82,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1994.22,"speaker_name":"Jane"},{"text":"And that blue pops.","index":416,"end_time":2000.54,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1996.38,"speaker_name":"Jane"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":417,"end_time":2001.79,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2001.34,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"You know, I worry with lighter blue, like, if you like the disclaimer.","index":418,"end_time":2005.78,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2002.58,"speaker_name":"Jane"},{"text":"Right.","index":419,"end_time":2006.06,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2005.78,"speaker_name":"Jane"},{"text":"Like, on the back of the postcard right now, that disclaimer and the legal logos look more prominent to me than the rest of it.","index":420,"end_time":2014.34,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2006.06,"speaker_name":"Jane"},{"text":"Got it.","index":421,"end_time":2017.14,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2016.5,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"So I, I, I definitely still think there''s room for a third color, whether it''s.","index":422,"end_time":2026.86,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2019.54,"speaker_name":"Jane"},{"text":"Or maybe four, you know, like, whether it''s the yellow and this teal.","index":423,"end_time":2031.26,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2026.86,"speaker_name":"Jane"},{"text":"But it''s hard to say which one without seeing them together.","index":424,"end_time":2035.26,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2032.22,"speaker_name":"Jane"},{"text":"Like, do the check marks become the yellow or the teal?","index":425,"end_time":2038.46,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2035.58,"speaker_name":"Jane"},{"text":"And the headline, you know, like, can we see the front one more time of the card.","index":426,"end_time":2044.46,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2038.46,"speaker_name":"Jane"},{"text":"Here?","index":427,"end_time":2047.58,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2047.18,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"I got it.","index":428,"end_time":2054.42,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2053.82,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Q.","index":429,"end_time":2054.7,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2054.42,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":430,"end_time":2062.51,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2062.23,"speaker_name":"Jane"},{"text":"See, the other blue wouldn''t work on this yellow blue, like, it''s not dark enough or light enough, you know, and like on, on your website, front, like that quick splash, like that pops of yellow looks so nice.","index":431,"end_time":2075.19,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2062.51,"speaker_name":"Jane"},{"text":"Right.","index":432,"end_time":2075.91,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2075.51,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And I don''t think I had seen that in the last thing you guys designed.","index":433,"end_time":2080.31,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2076.31,"speaker_name":"Jane"},{"text":"So, like, I would, let''s, I just want to make sure before we press print on the next thing, like, we do a test of these things.","index":434,"end_time":2088.52,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2080.79,"speaker_name":"Jane"},{"text":"Both, like, putting a color on top of another color.","index":435,"end_time":2092.96,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2088.6,"speaker_name":"Jane"},{"text":"Like how the 150 is here.","index":436,"end_time":2094.92,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2092.96,"speaker_name":"Jane"},{"text":"Like, we learned the hard way a while ago with that light baby blue.","index":437,"end_time":2099.4,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2095.16,"speaker_name":"Jane"},{"text":"Yeah, I got you.","index":438,"end_time":2100.76,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2099.48,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":439,"end_time":2101.72,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2101.24,"speaker_name":"Jane"},{"text":"Okay.","index":440,"end_time":2103.8,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2103.32,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, we can, we can come up with a few more color variations.","index":441,"end_time":2106.92,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2103.8,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Oh, yeah.","index":442,"end_time":2107.64,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2107.08,"speaker_name":"Jane"},{"text":"So I don''t think we need to do a new color exploratory.","index":443,"end_time":2110.68,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2107.64,"speaker_name":"Jane"},{"text":"I just think we need to Test out everything that''s been floated around and narrow it down.","index":444,"end_time":2115.08,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2110.92,"speaker_name":"Jane"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":445,"end_time":2115.96,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2115.56,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, got it.","index":446,"end_time":2118.84,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2116.12,"speaker_name":"Jane"},{"text":"And I do really lean towards this new blue also.","index":447,"end_time":2122.48,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2119.08,"speaker_name":"Jane"},{"text":"It''s been really used in a lot of new stuff.","index":448,"end_time":2125,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2122.48,"speaker_name":"Jane"},{"text":"And like Christina and Betty said, I don''t think we can financially afford to switch everything right now, so.","index":449,"end_time":2132.28,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2125,"speaker_name":"Jane"},{"text":"Okay, got it.","index":450,"end_time":2137.08,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2134.36,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Okay.","index":451,"end_time":2138.12,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2137.56,"speaker_name":"Jane"},{"text":"So you should have the color I just emailed to you, which has the CMYK PMS hex code and all of that.","index":452,"end_time":2146.21,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2139.56,"speaker_name":"Jane"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":453,"end_time":2147.21,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2146.77,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And I''ll.","index":454,"end_time":2147.77,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2147.21,"speaker_name":"Jane"},{"text":"I''ll make sure the designers are aware of it.","index":455,"end_time":2152.53,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2147.77,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"Okay.","index":456,"end_time":2153.41,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2152.85,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Because they are right now, like, what''s in progress?","index":457,"end_time":2156.53,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2153.49,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"They are updating, like, the designs we Send over like 2 weeks ago to the old font because we''re reverting them.","index":458,"end_time":2164.69,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2157.01,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"All of them.","index":459,"end_time":2165.49,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2164.85,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"All of them.","index":460,"end_time":2166.01,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2165.49,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"Right.","index":461,"end_time":2166.37,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2166.01,"speaker_name":"Jane"},{"text":"This one, which is the newsletter.","index":462,"end_time":2168.65,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2166.69,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"I''m sorry, the newsletter template.","index":463,"end_time":2171.33,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2168.65,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"I''ll make sure they''re.","index":464,"end_time":2174.21,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2173.25,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"They''re all using like the color palette.","index":465,"end_time":2177.57,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2174.21,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":466,"end_time":2178.21,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2177.73,"speaker_name":"Jane"},{"text":"Because they''re working on it.","index":467,"end_time":2181.57,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2179.57,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"Shouldn''t be.","index":468,"end_time":2182.61,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2181.89,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"Okay.","index":469,"end_time":2183.09,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2182.61,"speaker_name":"Jane"},{"text":"So hard to.","index":470,"end_time":2183.85,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2183.09,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"Okay.","index":471,"end_time":2184.17,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2183.85,"speaker_name":"Jane"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":472,"end_time":2184.37,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2184.17,"speaker_name":"Jane"},{"text":"Like, I don''t see any yellow on this, you know, but you had it on the website, so, like, just knowing what''s intentional and certainly, like, as we present internally, like the first few things, it should look somewhat consistent.","index":473,"end_time":2197.81,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2184.37,"speaker_name":"Jane"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":474,"end_time":2198.85,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2198.57,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"If not purely.","index":475,"end_time":2199.77,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2198.85,"speaker_name":"Jane"},{"text":"Okay, got it.","index":476,"end_time":2202.17,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2200.65,"speaker_name":"Jane"},{"text":"And this is pretty much what''s in progress.","index":477,"end_time":2205.01,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2202.81,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"The designs are being built in HubSpot.","index":478,"end_time":2208.41,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2205.01,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"The assets that we send over, as I said, they''re being updated along with the white knockoff logo that you sent out last week.","index":479,"end_time":2220.81,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2209.93,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"Well.","index":480,"end_time":2221.85,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2221.45,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"And also you sent over an email on like an issue on a Bing in.","index":481,"end_time":2227.8,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2223.05,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"On a pink.","index":482,"end_time":2228.6,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2227.8,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"Yes.","index":483,"end_time":2228.92,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2228.6,"speaker_name":"Jane"},{"text":"Thank you so much for your quick response with that.","index":484,"end_time":2231.48,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2228.92,"speaker_name":"Jane"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":485,"end_time":2232.8,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2232.36,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"That you should see the change this week as well.","index":486,"end_time":2236.04,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2232.8,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"Okay.","index":487,"end_time":2237.72,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2237.16,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"But I think that''s everything that we wanted to cover for creative today.","index":488,"end_time":2244.52,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2238.04,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"Okay.","index":489,"end_time":2248,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2247.48,"speaker_name":"Jane"},{"text":"And just so I know, with the changing of the meta image.","index":490,"end_time":2251.4,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2248,"speaker_name":"Jane"},{"text":"When do.","index":491,"end_time":2254.17,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2253.89,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"We think that that''ll kick in?","index":492,"end_time":2256.13,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2254.17,"speaker_name":"Jane"},{"text":"Just in case someone asks?","index":493,"end_time":2257.49,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2256.13,"speaker_name":"Jane"},{"text":"Maybe tomorrow or Wednesday.","index":494,"end_time":2260.37,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2257.73,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"Okay.","index":495,"end_time":2261.41,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2260.85,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"Can you just send us an email when you notice that it has taken effect?","index":496,"end_time":2266.13,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2262.45,"speaker_name":"Jane"},{"text":"Yep.","index":497,"end_time":2267.17,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2266.53,"speaker_name":"Jane"},{"text":"Cool.","index":498,"end_time":2267.65,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2267.25,"speaker_name":"Jane"},{"text":"Thank you.","index":499,"end_time":2268.13,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2267.65,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Pretty much.","index":500,"end_time":2269.17,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2268.53,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"We just changed the SVG image to like the one that Victor sent, so should be updated soon.","index":501,"end_time":2277.33,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2270.53,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"Okay.","index":502,"end_time":2278.39,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2277.89,"speaker_name":"Jane"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":503,"end_time":2280.7,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2280.3,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"Okay.","index":504,"end_time":2282.54,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2281.98,"speaker_name":"Jane"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":505,"end_time":2284.94,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2284.38,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":506,"end_time":2285.74,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2285.26,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"So, yeah, we''ll.","index":507,"end_time":2286.98,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2286.06,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We''ll send over.","index":508,"end_time":2287.66,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2286.98,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we have the web pages, the postcards, the trifold brochure, and the, the two double sided brochures that we''ll send over for review as well.","index":509,"end_time":2296.14,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2287.66,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And, and we''re going through the.","index":510,"end_time":2298.94,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2297.58,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"The guidelines as Guille mentioned to update.","index":511,"end_time":2300.94,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2298.94,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And, and we''ll work on some just popping of more color and more color variation across those Designs as well.","index":512,"end_time":2308.87,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2302.3,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":513,"end_time":2310.14,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2309.82,"speaker_name":"Jane"},{"text":"And silly little thing, but it''s knockout logo.","index":514,"end_time":2313.5,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2310.14,"speaker_name":"Jane"},{"text":"I don''t want our board thinking we''re doing a knockoff.","index":515,"end_time":2316.14,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2313.5,"speaker_name":"Jane"},{"text":"Oh, knockout.","index":516,"end_time":2317.74,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2316.86,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"Yeah, Knockout.","index":517,"end_time":2318.82,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2317.98,"speaker_name":"Jane"},{"text":"Meaning, like, if you punch it out, it''s the negative.","index":518,"end_time":2321.1,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2318.82,"speaker_name":"Jane"},{"text":"Okay.","index":519,"end_time":2321.7,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2321.18,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"It''s okay.","index":520,"end_time":2322.38,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2321.7,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":521,"end_time":2322.9,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2322.46,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Right.","index":522,"end_time":2323.22,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2322.9,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Knockout.","index":523,"end_time":2323.9,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2323.22,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"Okay.","index":524,"end_time":2324.7,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2324.14,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"I did knock off.","index":525,"end_time":2326.3,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2325.02,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"All good.","index":526,"end_time":2327.1,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2326.54,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"All right.","index":527,"end_time":2329.98,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2329.42,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"No counterfeits.","index":528,"end_time":2331.26,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2330.14,"speaker_name":"Jane"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":529,"end_time":2332.78,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2332.22,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"Okay.","index":530,"end_time":2334.62,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2334.06,"speaker_name":"Jane"},{"text":"Is there anything you want to go over?","index":531,"end_time":2337.39,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2334.99,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"No.","index":532,"end_time":2339.23,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2338.83,"speaker_name":"Jane"},{"text":"So just to manage expectations, I.","index":533,"end_time":2342.11,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2339.23,"speaker_name":"Jane"},{"text":"What do you.","index":534,"end_time":2343.59,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2342.43,"speaker_name":"Jane"},{"text":"I think would be helpful, even if the text isn''t perfect, but just for, like, to just make some final decisions and move forward to see a few things, maybe even on one page, like a website home.","index":535,"end_time":2355.71,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2343.59,"speaker_name":"Jane"},{"text":"You know, a website homepage, front of a postcard, a flyer.","index":536,"end_time":2361.8,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2355.71,"speaker_name":"Jane"},{"text":"Just a few things, like a brand suite to make sure that the font, the colors, like the true branding works digitally print, simple corporate, you know, and then we just.","index":537,"end_time":2373.96,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2361.96,"speaker_name":"Jane"},{"text":"Done.","index":538,"end_time":2374.76,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2374.36,"speaker_name":"Jane"},{"text":"Once they''re all updated, I''ll send them over maybe in one single Marco file.","index":539,"end_time":2379.84,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2375.4,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"So you can.","index":540,"end_time":2380.28,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2379.84,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"I think that''s great.","index":541,"end_time":2381.08,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2380.28,"speaker_name":"Jane"},{"text":"But then, just a reminder.","index":542,"end_time":2382.68,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2381.32,"speaker_name":"Jane"},{"text":"Christina really does want to see things and be able to access them as PDFs, because we can''t.","index":543,"end_time":2388.3,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2382.84,"speaker_name":"Jane"},{"text":"We need to be able to quickly, like, import an image into a board report or show people, you know, the markup works for feedback, but it''s not how we can share things internally.","index":544,"end_time":2398.38,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2388.3,"speaker_name":"Jane"},{"text":"We need to be able to have some images to work with.","index":545,"end_time":2400.9,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2398.38,"speaker_name":"Jane"},{"text":"Got it.","index":546,"end_time":2402.42,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2401.86,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"So, like, the last time we did a report, we ended up screenshotting from the markup, but the resolution was terrible, and it didn''t do your design work justice.","index":547,"end_time":2412.1,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2404.02,"speaker_name":"Jane"},{"text":"Okay, got it.","index":548,"end_time":2413.47,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2412.1,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"Okay.","index":549,"end_time":2414.11,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2413.55,"speaker_name":"Jane"},{"text":"Got it, Got it.","index":550,"end_time":2417.23,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2416.27,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"And I think lastly, just for.","index":551,"end_time":2420.59,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2418.91,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Just.","index":552,"end_time":2422.15,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2421.79,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Just to bring this back up again, making sure that our timelines are constantly updated as well as the subtasks for those things.","index":553,"end_time":2429.31,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2422.15,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"So obviously, you know, just.","index":554,"end_time":2431.11,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2429.55,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Just for an example, you guys put in one of the Excel documents to set up the sandbox.","index":555,"end_time":2437.63,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2431.11,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Understanding that you guys are setting up the sandbox, but what are those steps to set up the sandbox?","index":556,"end_time":2442.83,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2438.99,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"So if we can break those things out in greater detail just so that we''re aware that those things are actually being done, that''ll help us with our timelines, just to make sure.","index":557,"end_time":2452.19,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2442.83,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Okay.","index":558,"end_time":2452.75,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2452.19,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Since they''re working on that, we need to work on this and these other subtasks that we need to complete just so that we can kind of stay on point.","index":559,"end_time":2459.39,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2452.75,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Got it.","index":560,"end_time":2461.79,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2461.15,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"Yep.","index":561,"end_time":2465.96,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2465.64,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Understood.","index":562,"end_time":2466.52,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2465.96,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Hey, what''s up, Mario?","index":563,"end_time":2470.12,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2468.92,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"So, yeah, that''s.","index":564,"end_time":2473.76,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2471.16,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"That''s it for me.","index":565,"end_time":2474.84,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2473.76,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Jane, is there anything else left for you besides us receiving the PDFs?","index":566,"end_time":2479.56,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2474.84,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"No, just an ETA of when you think you should expect those?","index":567,"end_time":2485.16,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2480.52,"speaker_name":"Jane"},{"text":"I think he said by the end of the day.","index":568,"end_time":2487.6,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2486.04,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Right.","index":569,"end_time":2487.88,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2487.6,"speaker_name":"Jane"},{"text":"The 5pM okay, great.","index":570,"end_time":2492.21,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2490.29,"speaker_name":"Jane"},{"text":"Okay.","index":571,"end_time":2493.17,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2492.53,"speaker_name":"Jane"},{"text":"All right.","index":572,"end_time":2494.53,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2494.05,"speaker_name":"Jane"},{"text":"We''Ll see you later if you''re.","index":573,"end_time":2500.09,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2496.45,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"1:30, I believe.","index":574,"end_time":2501.17,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2500.09,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"1:30.","index":575,"end_time":2502.25,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2501.65,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":576,"end_time":2502.69,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2502.25,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"All right.","index":577,"end_time":2503.09,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2502.69,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Thank you both.","index":578,"end_time":2503.69,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2503.09,"speaker_name":"Jane"},{"text":"Feel better.","index":579,"end_time":2504.29,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2503.69,"speaker_name":"Jane"},{"text":"Thank you.","index":580,"end_time":2505.57,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2505.01,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{